INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(26776, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You explain to Ghaliri what has happened up to this point.>$b$bIt would seem that Jin\'do has survived, and he is rallying his brothers to once again summon Hakkar into this world.  It was good of you to come to speak with me.$b$bThere is not much we can do now but to wait, and watch.  Jin\'do is weak, and prime for striking, but I must wait for word from Rastakhan before issuing orders.  Until then, you and your raptor will have to wait.', 25881), -- Ghaliri
(26775, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a shame, yes.$b$bThis is what the spirits wanted, yes.$b$bMaybe when you are stronger, you will go into Zul\'Gurub and take back your $n\'aka from Mandokir, yes.$b$bFor now, Priestess give you this.', 25881), -- Be Raptor
(26774, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hold on, next part is tough, yes.$b$bLots of chances to fail, yes.$b$bBut $n and $n\'aka going to be reunited... yes they will.', 25881), -- Mind Control
(26779, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As promised, your reward.  You do the troll nation proud.', 25881), -- Zul'Mamwe Mambo
(26780, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can see the difference already.  I can\'t wait until later tonight, when I get to perform my observations again!', 25881), -- Nighttime in the Jungle
(26773, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did Priestess tell you?$b$bThe raptor is daughter of Ohgan, heir to Mandokir\'s seat.$b$bHah!', 25881), -- See Raptor
(26782, 1, 462, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Wulfred peers into the box.>$b$bThis... this is not like what I expected.  I had thought it would be a... a...$b$b<His eyes glaze over.>$b$bAhem!  I\'m sorry.  I\'m not sure what came over me.  I\'ll be sending this south, to the Explorers\' League Digsite in the Cape.  Maybe they\'ll know what to do with it...', 25881), -- The Mosh'Ogg Bounty
(26772, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You bring feathers, yes.$b$bYou can follow directions, yes.', 25881), -- Mind Vision
(26781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You retrieved the eye!  Your might is the stuff of legends, $n!$B$BAnd to think my brother and sister said we wouldn\'t find anything of worth here in the Vale.  Hah!  And I\'m just getting started!', 25881), -- The Mind's Eye
(26749, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mandokir is alive, yes.$b$bYou are responsible, yes.$b$bYou may be able to stop him still, yes.', 25881), -- Priestess Thaalia
(26748, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad to see you\'ve come to your senses.$b$bCome and visit us in Zul\'Gurub sometime, $r.  I\'ll be watching...', 25881), -- Bloodlord Mandokir
(26747, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $r.  We have a head, a body, and some juju-voodoo-mojo nonsense.  Now, just a little shock of electricity to get things started, and...', 25881), -- A Physical Specimen
(26751, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Balance is restored - for now.  We may call on you again in the future, $n.', 25881), -- Population Con-Troll
(26746, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will provide a bit of... what\'s the troll word?  Voodoo?  Juju?  Tiklabang?$b$bIt doesn\'t matter.  If we\'re going to re-build a troll, we need troll magic, and these fetishes are full of it.', 25881), -- A Nose for This Sort of Thing
(26743, 1, 5, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'First you save me from the madman\'s jail cell, and now you bring me some keys to understanding trollish shamanism.$b$bThis is turning out to be a pretty good week!$b$bThank you again, $n.  I will see to it that you have the support of the Wildhammer clan as you continue on your journeys.', 25881), -- Sacred to the Bloodscalp
(26745, 71, 153, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What do we have here?  A young raptor, and her pet $r.  Hah!$b$bMore importantly, what is that skull you have there?  This was no ordinary troll.  He was big...$b$b<Osborn raps on the headcase.>$b$b... and strong, too.  You know, I\'ve been meaning to try my hand at some troll magic.  How hard could it be?  Let\'s use this strong fellow as a test subject, shall we?', 25881), -- Favored Skull
(26731, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My colleagues within the Kirin Tor will be happy to learn that the heart is ours.$b$bThank you for your assistance, $n.  I couldn\'t have done it without you.', 25881), -- The Altar of Naias
(26765, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s fixed!  This is great, now I can get dinner started!  Thanks so much, $n.$B$BI hope Krazek didn\'t give you too much trouble.', 25881), -- Return to Corporal Kaleb
(26744, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To be honest, I\'m sending this information home to Stormwind, for my wife and son.  They love to hear about what I\'ve been doing out here in the jungle, and I only get to visit so often.  Every little bit helps.$b$bThank you, $n.', 25881), -- Deep Roots
(26742, 432, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Berrin studies the inscriptions on the totem.>$b$bI think I can read this text... Fascinating!$b$bTsul\'kalu, Mahamba, Pogeyan... what are these names?', 25881), -- Bloodscalp Insight
(26730, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have what we need.  Are you ready to activate the Altar of Naias, $n?', 25881), -- You Can Take the Murloc Out of the Ocean...
(26729, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do for my purposes.  Though we can\'t activate the altar with bracers alone...', 25881), -- Water Elementals
(26763, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will work fine.  Just a moment please.$b$b<Krazek thrusts the stones into the cooking pot and wiggles them around a bit.>$b$bAll fixed!', 25881), -- Venture Company Mining
(26740, 5, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh I see, it\'s a Krazek\'s Crock Pot!  An ingenious piece of work, but it can break a spring or throw a gear now and then.  Let me see what\'s wrong with this one...$B$BAha!  Its steam charger is rusted out, it has a cracked knuckle-gasket and its fobulator is missing teeth.  I\'m surprised the pot could even boil a turnip in this state!$B$BCan I fix it?  Of course I can fix it!$B$BBut there\'s a price.  Oh yes, there is always a price...', 25881), -- Krazek's Cookery
(26737, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelously executed, $n.  My men and I can handle the rest.$b$bWith Kurzen out of the picture, we may be able to continue our original expedition here in Stranglethorn, which was... ahh...$b$bNo matter.  Please, feel free to peruse our armor stores.  You may find something that fits you well.', 25881), -- Stopping Kurzen's Legacy
(26734, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brother Nimetz opens up a pouch and lets you place the crystal inside.>$b$bI knew they\'d have some more of this substance.  I\'m going to send this to my contacts at Fort Livingston, to the south.  Hopefully they\'ll have some more luck with it.$b$bThank you for everything, $n.', 25881), -- The Source of the Madness
(26736, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  It looks like my suspicions were correct... the three prisoners seem to have escaped the affliction that gripped Kurzen and the rest of his men.$b$bBefore you arrived, Emerine teleported them over to Stormwind to get cleaned up after their ordeal.  They promised to return soon.', 25881), -- Spared from Madness
(26739, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She looks bigger already!  You can see, these raptors grow quickly.  You are lucky to have found such a strong companion.$b$bKeep her by your side as long as you can, $n.  I\'m sure she will prove to be an asset in the future.', 25881), -- I Think She's Hungry
(26733, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do.  Please hold on for a moment while I test this out.', 25881), -- Control Sample
(26735, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They KILLED him?  And all this time, I thought he had them underneath an iron bootheel...', 25881), -- The Fate of Kurzen
(26738, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, the little one seems to have taken a liking to you.  You\'re lucky... at this age, the raptors are calm, peaceful, and easily trained.  Keep her, $n... she may come in handy.$b$bIn fact...', 25881), -- Just Hatched
(26732, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.  Now, let\'s see what they\'ve got in this elixir of theirs...', 25881), -- Bad Medicine
(28699, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to our camp, $c, such as it is.', 25881), -- Hero's Call: Northern Stranglethorn Vale!
(26794, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Morgan Ladimore? Never heard of...$b$bOh, you mean Mor\'Ladim! I guess you haven\'t heard the story?$b$bWell, I\'ll give you the short version. A powerful undead calling itself Mor\'Ladim has been wandering Duskwood. From what we\'ve gathered, it appears to be the undead body of Morgan Ladimore, of whom you apparently know. He\'s been causing us all sorts of problems, attacking Watchmen on patrol and killing people.$b$b<She sizes you up.>$b$bYou seem to be capable enough, maybe you could lay him to rest.', 25881), -- Morgan Ladimore
(26683, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why yes, I used to own a looking glass.', 25881), -- Look To The Stars
(26726, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They will never be forgotten, $n. What you and the rest of Bravo Company sacrificed in order to save Redridge will be a tale told for ages to come.$B$BWhile I can in no way make up for the loss of your friends, I feel that you must be rewarded for such a heroic deed. These are Keeshan\'s possessions - the only things we found when we dredged the lake for his body. Troteman has informed me that Keeshan would have wanted you to take something as the lone surviving member of Bravo Company. Remember them, $n!', 25881), -- Triumphant Return
(26714, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<A single tear rolls down Troteman\'s left cheek.>$B$BThey died in defense of the Alliance. In defense of our kingdom! Heroes, all of them, and they will be laid to rest as such.', 25881), -- Darkblaze, Brood of the Worldbreaker
(26713, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Bravo Company field kit beeps loudly.>$B$BCome in, $n. Are you there? If you can hear me: Blackrock has the upper hand. I repeat. Blackrock has the upper hand. GET BRAVO COMPANY OUT OF TH...$B$B<Troteman cuts out.>', 25881), -- Showdown at Stonewatch
(26708, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The only thing left to deal with now are the orcs holding out at Stonewatch Keep.', 25881), -- AHHHHHHHHHHHH! AHHHHHHHHH!!!
(26694, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He teleported away? Mentioned Darkblaze? What the hell is going on here.$B$BLooks like it\'s time to strap in and finish this nonsense.', 25881), -- The Grand Magus Doane
(26693, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keeshan comes in over the Bravo Company field kit.>$B$BNow that the easy part is over, it\'s time for phase two.', 25881), -- The Dark Tower
(26692, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Danforth\'s voice comes in over the Bravo Company field kit.>$B$BHello? Is this thing on?$B$B<You hear Keeshan\'s voice in the background, and some muffled scrapes as they adjust the signal.>$B$BThere we go. Good work, $n. We\'re closing in on the Blackrock high command. There\'s nowhere left for those dogs to run.', 25881), -- Shadowhide Extinction
(26668, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you see those orcs explode? THAT\'S HOW WE DO IT IN BRAVO COMPANY! Now to clean up the rest of these jackasses.', 25881), -- Detonation
(26651, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And now, we blow the whole damned thing up.', 25881), -- To Win a War, You Gotta Become War
(26646, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The radio on the Bravo Company field kit crackles.>$B$BLooks like the P.O.W.s are free. Time to initiate Operation: End All.', 25881), -- Prisoners of War
(26640, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keeshan reads the report.>$B$BDAMN IT! This just got complicated. We\'ve got prisoners of war to rescue before we can blow up the valley. Not to mention the orcs have black dragons on their side.$B$BAre you ready, $n?', 25881), -- Unspeakable Atrocities
(26636, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice job, rookie. I\'m gonna go ahead and put the camo in the box. We should be ready soon.', 25881), -- Bravo Company Field Kit: Camouflage
(26638, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work, $n. We need to move quickly before they send for reinforcements.', 25881), -- Hunting the Hunters
(26639, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brubaker is dead. It looks like the orcs are attempting to send a message with this grisly display. Upon closer examination you notice something in Brubaker\'s pouch.', 25881), -- Point of Contact: Brubaker
(26637, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Those orcs won\'t know what hit \'em - literally. I\'ll need a few minutes to get these in working order and then I\'ll put them in the Bravo Company field kit.', 25881), -- Bravo Company Field Kit: Chloroform
(26616, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s orc killin\' time.', 25881), -- It's Never Over
(26607, 1, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keeshan takes the bundle from you and opens it.>$B$BMy bow... and knife! Where did you...$B$BJade\'s amulet... My darling Jade.$B$B<Keeshan picks up his red headband.>$B$BWe got orcs to kill.', 25881), -- They Drew First Blood
(26563, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Colonel Troteman salutes.>$B$BUnbelievable work, $n. You\'ve managed to rescue the entire Bravo Company from the clutches of the Blackrock orcs? With Keeshan\'s team rescued and Keeshan\'s belongings returned, there\'s no way Keeshan could refuse us.', 25881), -- Return of the Bravo Company
(26573, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope with these items and with his crew all rescued he\'ll have a change of heart. We can\'t do this without Keeshan.  ', 25881), -- His Heart Must Be In It
(26569, 4, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic work, $n! These will come in handy for our next project, the Lakeshire SUPER BRIDGE, meant to traverse the length of Lake Everstill. It should be done in 20 or so years. Give or take a decade or two.', 25881), -- Surveying Equipment
(26570, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve probably bought us another day, maybe two. Nice work, $n.', 25881), -- Render's Army
(26562, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'About damn time you sissies showed up. My arms were gettin\' tired.\n', 25881), -- And Last But Not Least... Danforth
(26561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wha... Where am I? What happened? Messner? Jorgensen?$B$BOH MY GOSH! We have to get to Danforth! It might already be too late!\n', 25881), -- Krakauer
(26560, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know where they\'re holding Krakauer and Danforth. We gotta hurry. They were prepping those two for a sacrifice!', 25881), -- Jorgensen
(26587, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'IT\'S PAYBACK TIME!', 25881), -- Breaking Out is Hard to Do
(26586, 6, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keeshan? You mean JOHNNY\'S ALIVE? You bet your sweet behind I\'ll help, but first you gotta get me out of this damned cage.', 25881), -- In Search of Bravo Company
(26571, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gnomecorder buzzes with energy.>$B$BCome in, $n. Do you copy? Troteman here! Great job on getting Keeshan\'s weapons back! Now there\'s one final mission you have to run. Are you up to the challenge?', 25881), -- Weapons of War
(26568, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Troteman sighs.>$B$BI\'m not giving up on him, $n, and I\'m not giving up on Redridge. We need to boost his spirits... Rouse the slumbering monster within him!', 25881), -- This Ain't My War
(26567, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Help you? Help these people? These people that would rather spit on me than crack a smile?', 25881), -- John J. Keeshan
(26520, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You used an ettin to remove the boulder that was crushing Foreman Oslow? Incredible work, $n! Oslow will be grateful once he regains his composure.', 25881), -- Saving Foreman Oslow
(26545, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Magistrate Solomon takes the plans from you and begins reading.>$B$BShadowhide army!? Damn those orcs to hell! These invasion plans speak of a massive build up of orcish and gnoll forces in the east. Looks like Gath\'Ilzogg, the Blackrock general, is preparing to march his armies across Lakeshire and attack Stormwind directly!', 25881), -- Yowler Must Die!
(26513, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, citizen. Without you, we would have starved or worse, been forced to go out and get food for ourselves.', 25881), -- Like a Fart in the Wind
(26544, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gnomecorder buzzes and whirs.>$B$BJust put the missive in the little compartment and I\'ll read it. I am fluent in orcish.$B$B<You hear a distraught yell in the background.>$B$BIt looks like these orcs are here under the direct command of Yowler. That means Yowler must have the orc invasion plan.', 25881), -- They've Wised Up...
(26514, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gnomecorder crackles and pops.>$B$BGood work, $n. I\'ve just been handed some important information. It would appear that our most hated enemy, the Blackrock orcs, have wised up...$B$B<The gnomecorder whirs as a compartment opens up.>$B$BI\'ve transferred a few silver over to you for the gnome, erm, gnoll kills.', 25881), -- Canyon Romp
(26519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The orb hisses as you touch it.>', 25881), -- He Who Controls the Ettins
(26512, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The gnomecorder crackles and pops.>$B$BCan you hear me, $n? Is this thing on? Ah, yes, I see you there now.$B$BLet\'s get to work!', 25881), -- Tuning the Gnomecorder
(26510, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! Let me make a few adjustments here and we should be good to go.', 25881), -- We Must Prepare!
(26511, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That ought to teach those murlocs a lesson. Hopefully the next time they decide to raid our town they\'ll think twice.$B$BWe both know that won\'t happen.', 25881), -- Lake Everstill Clean Up
(26508, 4, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for finding my necklace $G mister : miss; $c... you are very kind!  My kitty thanks you too - isn\'t that right Effsee?', 25881), -- Nida's Necklace
(26509, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally the menace is laid to rest!  Thank you, $n, you have done me a great service.  The garden shall be in full bloom this season!', 25881), -- An Unwelcome Guest
(26761, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I heard about the Defias making a return. Terrible news. I wish I had better news, but it would appear that Lakeshire is under attack! We are losing citizens left and right. Our own guards are spread far too thin to handle the situation. We need a hero to step up!', 25881), -- Threat to the Kingdom
(26505, 1, 1, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Magistrate Solomon puts on his monocle.>$B$BOh, you\'re not Conacher. What have you got there?$B$B<Magistrate Solomon takes Parker\'s report from you.>$B$BOh for pity\'s sake. Yowler? AGAIN?', 25881), -- Parker's Report
(26504, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done deserves a reward, wouldn\'t you say?$B$BDon\'t spend this all in one place, $c. Better to spread it around, if you catch my drift.', 25881), -- Wanted: Redridge Gnolls
(26503, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew it! Looks like Yowler is behind this uprising - which is incredible, because we keep killing gnolls named Yowler. I don\'t know how many sons the original Yowler had, but it\'s got to be close to a hundred.$B$BWell, looks like we got ourselves another Yowler to kill.$B$BMagistrate Solomon must be notified.', 25881), -- Still Assessing the Threat
(26506, 4, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'PERFECT! I\'ll put these in the pot right away. Dinner should be ready in a few hours.$B$BThank you, darling!', 25881), -- Franks and Beans
(26365, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Heard Westfall was in some deep doody.$B$B<Parker doesn\'t even turn to face you.>$B$BWell, we got our own set of problems here. See them gnolls out there? Looks like they\'re actin\' up again. I don\'t like it. Don\'t like it one bit.', 25881), -- Hero's Call: Redridge Mountains!
(26370, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Five years of work burned to the ground in five minutes. Damn the Defias!$B$BAnd this is only the beginning, $n! We have a long, hard road ahead of us.', 25881), -- Return to Sentinel Hill
(26322, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will deploy a battalion of soldiers to Westfall at once! With the Defias Brotherhood reborn, an old threat to the kingdom is renewed.', 25881), -- Rise of the Brotherhood
(26230, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just smellin\' you comin\' got my stomach rumblin\'! We\'re gonna eat like kings tonight!', 25881), -- Feast or Famine
(26378, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Murder, rookie. That\'s what you\'re looking at on the ground in front of us.', 25881), -- Hero's Call: Westfall!
(26152, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And justice is served!', 25881), -- Wanted: James Clark
(26396, 4, 2, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Great, you brought the armor!  We\'ll get this divvied to those who need it immediately.$B$BThank you, $n.  Your efforts have been a great help to us.  And now that you\'re no stranger to gryphons, I hope you\'ll come and lend your aid to Goldshire often!', 25881), -- Return to Argus
(26395, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A crate for Goldshire, eh?  People sure are getting lazy. Have you been to Goldshire before?  If so, then it\'s no problem, my friend.  I have plenty of gryphons trained to fly that route!', 25881), -- Dungar Longdrink
(31592, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now those look like some healthy pets, $n.  Remember, you can heal and revive your entire collection of pets at any time by visiting a stable master.', 25881), -- On The Mend
(37112, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rest and relaxation for the tired and cold -- that\'s our motto! Please, take a seat by the fire and rest your weary bones.$B$BWould you like to try a sampling of some of our fine food and drink?', 25881); -- Rest and Relaxation
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(28579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You must be here to help Fuselight! Let\'s get you to the Badlands right away.', 25928), -- Hero's Call: Badlands!
(27683, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes?', 25928), -- Into the Woods
(32618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t forget to buy your mount while you are here!  Katie Hunter can be found here in camp.', 25928), -- Learn To Ride
(27206, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lost?  No... next, they\'ll be coming for Chillwind, I suppose.  This was a major strategic blow to the Alliance\'s plans for Lordaeron.$b$bVery well.  I will report the results of this battle to King Wrynn.  I don\'t expect him to be happy.', 25928), -- Alas, Andorhal
(27204, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I watched your victory from below.  Well-fought, but ultimately, it was for naught.$b$bThe val\'kyr and the Forsaken press on; soon, they will overtake us.  We have lost Andorhal.', 25928), -- Aradne
(27201, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For every val\'kyr you slay, you save dozens of our men... and prevent the Forsaken forces from growing.$b$bStill, they press on.  We may not win this battle after all.', 25928), -- Val'kyr Incursion
(27202, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You fought valiantly, but we\'re getting nowhere.  Every body that falls just fuels their forces.', 25928), -- Brother Against Brother
(27205, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Val\'kyr?  Koltira brought val\'kyr to this fight?  Has he gone mad?$b$bNo, this is not Koltira\'s work.  This was Sylvanas.', 25928), -- The Depravity of the Forsaken
(27199, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done.  With them out of the way, I have no more excuses.$b$bSoon, I must battle Koltira, for honor and for Andorhal.', 25928), -- Ashes to Ashes
(27198, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You fight well, $n.  I wish I had your ability... and your bravery.', 25928), -- Supporting the Troops
(27197, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Word has it that you helped those farmers arm themselves.  Well, now they\'ve initiated the attack without my order!  They\'ve forced my hand.$b$bThe battle has resumed.  This time, we fight the Forsaken... and I fight Koltira, my old brother of the Ebon Blade.', 25928), -- The Battle Resumes!
(27174, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can handle things from here.  I thank you for your help, $n.$b$bI assume that when we next meet, it will be in battle.  Take care of yourself until then.  We\'ll need all the help we can get.', 25928), -- Combat Training
(27173, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You fight well, $r.  My men could stand to learn a few moves from an experienced $c like you.', 25928), -- This Is Our Army
(27172, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, now that you\'re here, we\'ll gladly take that armor off your hands.$b$bYou can keep the weapons, though.  These men wouldn\'t know which end to hold.', 25928), -- The Writhing Haunt
(27175, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $c.  As you can see, our camp is a joint expedition between Argent Crusade members and Cenarion Circle druids, but we welcome all who wish to help heal the land.', 25928), -- The Menders' Stead
(27171, 274, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Attacked by ghosts?  Strange.  I suppose that crypt wasn\'t fully healed after all.$b$bYou just missed Thurman Grant... you remember, that oaf of a farmer that was here earlier.  He took his men with him and traveled to the nearest farm... against my orders.', 25928), -- Ambushed!
(27168, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully most of them passed on peacefully.  I thank you, $n.', 25928), -- Those That Couldn't Let Go
(27170, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Scattered all over the bottom level of the crypt, you find shattered crates that once held weapons and armor.$b$bIt appears that somebody got here before you did.', 25928), -- The Abandoned Crypt
(27169, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You and the humans at Chillwind Camp wish to re-take Andorhal?  I wish you luck.', 25928), -- Uther's Blessing
(27167, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You hunt like a true $c.  Even if we can\'t set up our homesteads... at least we can still eat.', 25928), -- A Mighty Hunger
(27166, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will have my fletchers get to work on these.$b$bI\'m glad to see you being so useful right away, $n.  Perhaps later I will have some more exciting tasks for you.', 25928), -- Go Fletch!
(27165, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Word arrived shortly before you did, $n.  With the Scourge ejected from Andorhal, we are one step closer to retaking Lordaeron.', 25928), -- Victory, For Now
(27163, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellently done, $n.', 25928), -- Brute Strength
(27164, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Araj dead... this is good.  That gnome has done his part in winning this war.  As have you, $n.', 25928), -- Araj the Summoner
(27162, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellently done, $n.  And now, with the leader of the Scourge forces eliminated from Andorhal, we bide our time.', 25928), -- Scholomancer
(27160, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Abominations... strong.$b$b$n... stronger.', 25928), -- War Machines
(27159, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You may not act quickly, but at least you do not fail me.$b$bVery well.  I will have a more important task for you, $n, when the time is right.', 25928), -- Scourge First... Horde Later
(27161, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These grenades are all explosives, nothing more.  I may not be a goblin engineer... but I still understand the value of being able to just explode things every once in a while.', 25928), -- The Endless Flow
(26821, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating!$b$bI\'ll need some time to study this.  Why don\'t you have a look around Booty Bay and come back later?', 25928), -- Airwyn Bantamflax
(26814, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I ask you to slay Zanzil the Outcast, a lowly, hermetic exile of the Gurubashi, and what do you do?  You dash headfirst into the Gurubashi capital and eliminate one of their High Priests!  Very nearly two!  Only one word suffices to explain such a rash and foolhardy endeavor:$b$bHeroism.$b$bJin\'do the Hexxer still walks within Zul\'Gurub\'s walls, but he lost one of his legs when you crushed Jeklik.  Today\'s battle is ours.', 25928), -- High Priest Venoxis
(26813, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You find yourself deeper within Zul\'Gurub.  The snake statues indicate that you have reached the terrace of High Priest Venoxis - follower of Hethiss, the snake god.', 25928), -- Plunging Into Zul'Gurub
(26812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have succeeded in preventing Zanzil from resurrecting High Priestess Jeklik.  Without one of his priests, Jin\'do will certainly have a difficult time summoning Hakkar.', 25928), -- High Priestess Jeklik
(26811, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have arrived safely within Zul\'Gurub, the ruined capital of the once-mighty Gurubashi Empire.', 25928), -- Through the Troll Hole
(26810, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You appear to be too late.  Zanzil has left Aboraz.', 25928), -- Eliminate the Outcast
(26809, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is as I suspected.  Zanzil is too haughty to interfere with the squabbles between the Bloodscalps and the Skullsplitters.  No, he is playing a part in a grander scheme... Jin\'do the Hexxer is using him to help bring Hakkar back to Zul\'Gurub.$b$bIt\'s good that we found this out now, because it offers us a simple solution.', 25928), -- Backdoor Dealings
(26816, 1, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is fascinating!  Just think of all the applications!$b$bThanks again, $n.  Remember, if you ever need anything mixed for you... and I mean ANYTHING... you can always ask The Flask.', 25928), -- Recipe for Disaster
(26824, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew that alchemist was all talk.  Well, thanks for your help, $n.  I know you tried.', 25928), -- Results: Inconclusive
(26815, 463, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Dask carefully analyzes the strange compound.>$b$bThis mixture is... PERFECT!  Let\'s see what it does to your potentially-titan artifact here!', 25928), -- Zanzil's Secret
(26808, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The troll looks into the package.>$b$bYou have my thanks.  You may tell your young dwarven $g friend: girlfriend; that I am not sad.  I am waiting.  For you.$b$bI have identified you as the most promising $r here in this strange town.  I have a task for you, if you would be willing to take it.', 25928), -- Maywiki
(26817, 7, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Do you know how hard it is to get fresh water in Stranglethorn?  It\'s no wonder that the nagas guard their shrine so ferociously!$b$bAlright, let\'s get this mix started!', 25928), -- Perfectly Pure
(26820, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These statues are beautiful...$b$bWow, I had no idea the naga were so talented.  Thanks, $n!', 25928), -- If They're Just Going to Leave Them Lying Around...
(26819, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hooray!  It\'s been days and days since we last had Akiris reeds!', 25928), -- Akiris by the Bundle
(26818, 273, 1, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Linzi feels the hides and smiles to herself.>$b$bThese are so nice and cushy!  I think my customers are going to LOVE them!', 25928), -- Plush Pelts
(26823, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright!  Step one - getting ingredients - is all done.  Time for the next step: getting more ingredients.', 25928), -- Too Big For His Britches
(26822, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahem!  Ahhh... right...$b$bWell done!  And, congratulations, on killing them, I mean.$b$bHere you go.', 25928), -- Good-Fer-Nothin' Slither-Dogs
(26825, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So once again, it falls upon tiny Dask to get the Explorers\' League work done!  Alright... let\'s see what you\'ve got in there.', 25928), -- Dask "The Flask" Gobfizzle
(26805, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wulfred has a good eye.  I think you\'ll do just fine here at my camp.', 25928), -- To the Cape!
(26451, 396, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r!  Did you feel it?  The rush of the melee?  The true risk of free-for-all combat?$b$bAs today is your first day here, I\'ll let you perform in one more competition for another reward.  If you return in the future, you may compete again, once a day.  Your rewards will, of course, improve as you become stronger.', 25928); -- Gurubashi Challenge: Free-For-All Arena Combat
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(27561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You notice a small heap of stones within the caravan.$b$bThey do not appear out-of-the-ordinary, yet one of them attracts your attention.  You sense a warmth coming from within it.', 25944), -- Rimblat's Stone
(27562, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It looks like Beezil has already made himself comfortable, and has stuffed several peculiar gizmos into the caravan.$b$bMost of them seem too impractical or dangerous to take with you.  One small cogwheel, however, looks to be fairly well-crafted.', 25944); -- Beezil's Cog
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(28582, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We, too, are suspicious of the Dark Irons.', 25946), -- Hero's Call: Searing Gorge!
(27825, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I imagine those ogres weren\'t too much trouble for you.  Here - some coin for your troubles.', 25946), -- Survival of the Fattest
(27833, 21, 21, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r.  However, I\'m afraid I don\'t have much to give you, other than this passionate round of applause.$b$b<Terrance looks down into his bags.>$b$bOh, I do have these.  Here, take your pick.', 25946), -- Half-Ton Holdouts
(27858, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thankfully, you have avoided Deathwing\'s notice.  Rhea and the black dragon egg, however, may not have been so lucky...', 25946), -- Rheastrasza's Gift
(27832, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The egg must always be moving.  We are not safe anywhere.$b$bDeathwing, even in his madness, knows all the hidden places in this world.  The egg must not rest.', 25946), -- The Hidden Clutch
(27831, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just think... Nyxondra may end up being the mother of the new black dragonflight.  In death, she has given a gift to the future generations of Azeroth.', 25946), -- The Sorrow and the Fury
(27830, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Two more dangerous black dragons have been removed from this egg hunt.  Your greatest task, however, still awaits.', 25946), -- Their Hunt Continues
(27829, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One less dragon to worry about, one step closer to redemption.  Onward, my soldiers!', 25946), -- The Wrath of a Dragonflight
(27834, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think you\'re ready, $n.  You\'re getting the hang of this.', 25946), -- Baelog, the Glass Cannon
(27828, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m not what you\'d call \"very strong\" or \"battle-hardened\", but I get the job done my own way.$b$bLookin\' forward to fightin\' with you.  I never fought with a fancy-lookin\' $c before.', 25946), -- Eric, the Utility Dwarf
(27835, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See?  No need to worry when Olaf is around.  Just let me know, and I\'ll protect you from the monsters.', 25946), -- Olaf, the Big Fella'
(27827, 1, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re the $r we\'ve been waiting for?  It\'s about time you got here.  My legs could use a stretch.$b$bCome on boys!  Let\'s go kill us some black dragons!', 25946), -- The Swift, the Fierce, and the Stout
(27826, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll take that egg out of your hands now.  We need to get this egg incubated... and hidden, quickly.  There are lots of angry dragons looking for this.$b$bIt\'s good to see you again, by the way.', 25946), -- Into the Dragon's Mouth
(27794, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just one tiny little device?$b$bI never did understand those titans.$b$bVery well!  Let\'s see what this peeper can do.', 25946), -- Return to Blam
(27912, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You peer into the chest...', 25946), -- The Titans' Trove
(27824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now here\'s some treasure!  I was beginning to worry that these weren\'t titan ruins at all!$b$bI\'ll show these to Durdin.  Thanks again, $n.', 25946), -- The Good Stuff
(27823, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sigrun instantly downs a dusty mug of shadowstout.>$b$bWow, this stuff is strong!  I knew they had beer, but I never expected them to have shadowstout!  That\'s my favorite shadowbeer!', 25946); -- A Dwarf's Got Needs
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(26192, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These sacks look like just enough, $n.  Can\'t wait to see the smiles on the orphans\' faces.', 25950), -- Orphans Like Cookies Too!
(28322, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You peer inside, and find...', 25950), -- The Spoils of War
(28321, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Colonel Troteman is beaming.>$b$bWelcome home, $g boys: you two;.', 25950), -- Glory Amidst Chaos
(28320, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you see them run?  They didn\'t know what was happening!  Beautiful!$b$bOur job\'s almost done, $n.  It\'s time to deliver the deathblow.', 25950), -- Assault on Dreadmaul Rock
(28327, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n\'s here!  We can get started.$b$bThis is our big moment, $n.  I hope you brought your A game.', 25950), -- Locked and Loaded
(28318, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What are these?  Oh, are these imps?$b$bI\'m pretty sure that imps don\'t just fall asleep in boxes!$b$bI\'ll take your word for it, though.  I don\'t understand any of this warlock crap.  Leave them in the corner.', 25950), -- A Delivery for Neeralak
(28317, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well would you look at that!  My favorite soldier comes through in the clutch!$b$bI\'ll make sure to get this distributed among the ogres.$b$bI\'ll see you in Redridge, soldier.  For the glory of the Blackrock!', 25950), -- A Delivery for Thorg'izog
(28319, 1, 6, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pff!  You\'re late!  Do you know how long I\'ve been waiting for Ner\'gosh to deliver this orb?$b$b<Xi\'lun looks down at the orb, then up at you.>$b$bThere\'s something strange about this orb... it\'s too...$b$b<Xi\'lun trails off.>$b$bNever mind, it must be my nerves talking.  Thank you for the delivery.  For blood and honor!', 25950), -- A Delivery for Xi'lun
(28326, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you\'re back.$b$bI hope you\'ve still got that disguise.  You\'re going back undercover, $n.', 25950), -- Placing the Pawns
(28314, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keeshan is covered in blood and sweat.>$b$bThat was exactly what I needed.', 25950), -- Blood Tour
(28316, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, the whelplings.  I will take care of them.$b$bAs for the agreement I made with your Colonel Troteman earlier, tell him that I will hold up my end of the bargain.  You will have your dragon for the battle against the orcs.$b$bWe hold no particular love for the Redridge Mountains, but we do share your grudge against the Blackrock clan.', 25950), -- A Deal With a Dragon
(28315, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your kill count is adding up, $n.  We\'re chipping away at them.$b$bAnd we are going to win.  Redridge will NOT fall to these cowards.', 25950), -- Draconic Vanguard
(28415, 5, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ll never guess what happened!  Winky came back!  No flameflies needed.$b$bCan a dwarf get a celebratory belly rub?  Come on now!  RUBBA MAH BELLY!', 25950), -- SEVEN! YUP!
(28313, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This meat looks good... but I think it needs a little \"seasoning\".  I\'ll make sure that gets taken care of.$b$bThank you, $n.', 25950), -- A Heap of Delicious Worg
(28312, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To the untrained eye, these will look exactly like imps.$b$bWe just need to get them to that untrained eye.  I\'ll work on preparing them for delivery.', 25950), -- Latent Demons of the Land
(28311, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, these will do.  I will get this packed up for you.', 25950), -- Blackened Ashes
(28310, 5, 482, 22, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve arrived!  And just in time for the friendship ceremony!$b$b<Oralius looks wistfully over his shoulder at the ogre head, and quickly becomes panicked.>$b$bCaptain Winky!  Where\'d Captain Winky go?$b$bNo, don\'t tell me he got cold feet!', 25950), -- Morgan's Vigil
(28286, 6, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You alright?$b$bGood.  You did a fine job out there, $n.  Now pack up your things.  We\'re moving out of here.', 25950), -- Enough Damage For One Day
(28278, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have a feeling we\'ll be hearing about you and your exploits for a long time, soldier.  I look forward to fighting by your side in Redridge.$b$bYou are dismissed.', 25950), -- I Am the Law and I Am the Lash
(28279, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Without those sergeants, Thorg\'izog will be hard-pressed getting his troops ready for battle.$b$bAlready the dominoes are beginning to fall, $n.', 25950), -- Abuse of Power
(28266, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had a feeling you\'d be the one returning to me.  I like your style, soldier.', 25950), -- Trial by Magma
(28265, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More outsiders?  What do you want?', 25950), -- General Thorg'izog
(28253, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I didn\'t count on obtaining an item like this.  I will change our plans accordingly.', 25950), -- Taking the Horn For Ourselves
(28252, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your job is complete.  You take a look at the horn that they gave you, and decide to hang onto it for a while longer.', 25950), -- The Kodocaller's Horn
(28245, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmph.  Good work, grunt.', 25950), -- Grunt Work
(28246, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not only did you pull off the executions, you made them all look like accidents!$b$bYou were the right $r for this undercover work.  Good job, soldier.', 25950), -- Strategic Cuts
(28239, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where have you been, grunt?  You\'re late!  Give me one reason why I shouldn\'t kill you on the spot!', 25950), -- Into the Black Tooth Hovel
(28202, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s it?  That\'s your disguise?$b$bI\'m feeling less confident about our chances.  It was nice knowing you, kid.', 25950), -- A Perfect Costume
(28254, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You need a disguise?  Well, you came to the right place, $g honey: sister;.$b$bLet me take a look... mm-hmm.  I know exactly what we\'ll do.', 25950), -- A Needle in a Hellhole
(28184, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ll have to excuse me, but we\'re not taking visitors right now.  I\'ll ask you to leave Chiselgrip out the same door you came in.$b$bOh, Keeshan... is that you?', 25950), -- Chiselgrip, the Heart of the Steppes
(28183, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keeshan looks through the crate.>$b$bGood, good, good.  We can move on.  Our war takes us east, away from Blackrock Mountain... for now.', 25950), -- Return to Keeshan
(28182, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Knowing the way those orcs operate, there\'ll be another one to take his place soon.  I\'ll see if I can\'t sneak back into the altar before that happens.$b$bThanks, $g buddy: my dear;.', 25950), -- Shadow Boxing
(28181, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope that\'s what Keeshan was looking for.  It\'s not doing me much good right now, anyhow.', 25950), -- Warlocks Have the Neatest Stuff
(28180, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gah!  Who are you?$b$bOh, so Keeshan sent you?  Good.  Would ya mind sticking around for a while?  It\'s nothing big... I just need you to kill some warlocks for me.', 25950), -- The Sand, the Cider, and the Orb
(28179, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is exactly what we need.$b$bDon\'t worry, $n... the orc-killing will come soon enough.', 25950), -- Mud Hunter
(28178, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Believe me, $n... I\'m just as anxious to get to the killing as you are.  We\'ve got to keep to the plan.  The armageddon will come soon enough.$b$bI\'ll keep these hides here.', 25950), -- A Future Project
(28177, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those scorpids are easy to underestimate.  You\'re lucky you didn\'t end up on the end of one of these barbs.  Or maybe you\'re just good.$b$bI\'ll add these to the stockpile.  We\'re not done yet, $r.', 25950), -- Stocking Up
(28172, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see to it that these dragons are taken care of.', 25950), -- Done Nothing Wrong
(28416, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad to have you on my side, $n.  Bravo Company reunited, right?$b$bOh, did I mention that Troteman\'s here, too?', 25950), -- Burning Vengeance
(28514, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, Oilfist sent you?  Hah!$b$bDid he ever tell you how he got the name Oilfist?  You\'ll have to ask him about that one sometime.', 25950), -- Mouton Flamestar
(28666, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s time for the Blackrock orcs to feel the full wrath of the Alliance. They will pay for what they\'ve done.', 25950); -- Hero's Call: Burning Steppes!
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(26049, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As the eldritch shackles are placed around the Shards, an unhuman wail is heard from far below.  The scream is followed by a roar.$B$BThe Shards of Myzrael no longer invoke feelings of warmth and security as they once did.  Now they pulse with an open menace... as if the thing beneath them holds ill will toward the surface.', 25961), -- The Princess Unleashed
(26346, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Say no more, $n. I followed up with an... \"old friend\" while you were gone. I should\'ve known better than to send you to those shards.$B$BWe\'ve both made a grave mistake in involving ourselves in this. Luckily, I \"persuaded\" my boy Gerrig to tell me what to do if this happened.', 25961), -- Myzrael's Tale
(26038, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Malin couldn\'t\'ve asked a worthier person to come here an\' aid us, $n. You\'ve done a grand job!$B$BHe\'ll be pleased to see what an overwhelming success our mission\'s been.', 25961), -- Attack on the Tower
(26095, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  We will inform the families of these fallen soldiers that they were killed in battle.$B$BIt will be grim news to bear, but it is better than the uncertainty of a missing loved one.', 25961), -- Stromgarde Badges
(26037, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You amaze me, $n. Well done again.$B$BGive me a moment to cast the proper spell an\' you\'ll be ready.', 25961), -- Trelane's Defenses
(26942, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'d love for you to come aboard as a full G-Team Commando, but you have other adventures to pursue.$B$BI\'m sure we\'ll meet again, and I hope you\'ll have considered joining by then. Here\'s something for your trouble.', 25961), -- The G-Team
(26941, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Took you long enough. Get behind the pillar with me before you blow our cover!', 25961), -- The G-Team
(26939, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope that wasn\'t too much for you. The mission is far from over!', 25961), -- The G-Team
(26943, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Never thought I\'d see a $r like you down here. Any particular reason you\'re risking life and limb?', 25961), -- Home Sweet Gnome
(26036, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant, $n. One item down an\' three more to go, based on my list. The other three items are all in Stromgarde.$B$BTake a rest an\' get your strength back--the next phase of my plan\'ll require a little more time an\' effort. Come back to me after you\'ve gotten a warm meal an\' some rest.', 25961), -- Wand over Fist
(26035, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad. Since it\'s clear you\'ve got your head on straight, I was hoping you could help us with a more pressing job.', 25961), -- Worth Its Weight in Gold
(26117, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I admit I\'m impressed, $c. It\'s a small comfort amidst all that\'s happened here.$B$BYou have fought the undead, struck back against the Horde, and honored the memory of the victims of Southshore. On behalf of the kingdom of Stromgarde, I present you with an official commendation, and this reward.', 25961), -- For Southshore
(26116, 2, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done a great service for us, $n. Thank you.$B$BI hope Kin wasn\'t too much of a handful down there. She\'s very friendly, but can be just as deadly when you\'re her enemy.', 25961), -- Kinelory Strikes
(26114, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The plague took our friends and family, but it was the Forsaken that took Phin. They\'re just as bad as the Scourge. I\'ll destroy every one of them with my own hands if I have to.$B$BWhen you\'re prepared, come let me know. We\'ll get started right away.', 25961), -- Quae Trusts You
(26110, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Apothecaries yet again. You think they\'d get the message. Let\'s see what it is this time...', 25961), -- Just Like Old Times
(26113, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Refuge Pointe sent you? Good to know they\'re still there.$B$BWe\'ve got some interesting things to check into here, $c.', 25961), -- Quae and Kinelory
(26341, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The shards pulse softly, and a whisper slowly echoes through your head.>$B$BHelp...', 25961), -- The Stone Shards
(26079, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Falconcrest and Otto?  Wonderful!$B$BHere is your reward, $n.  I am happy to pay it.', 25961), -- Wanted!  Otto and Falconcrest
(26024, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You took down Marez Cowl?  Well done, $n.  Well done indeed!$B$BMarez menaced our Stromgarde defenders, and it is rumored she was an emissary between the Syndicate and some other, darker power.  We are glad to see that she\'ll no longer ply her powers against us.', 25961), -- Wanted!  Marez Cowl
(26093, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good, $n.  The last thing we need with the undead looming is a gang of common thieves distracting us.', 25961), -- Northfold Manor
(26336, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahoy, $c. Any friend of Skuerto is a friend of mine.$B$BYou\'ll find plenty of work needs doin\' around here. We\'re not sittin\' in this cove twiddlin\' our thumbs by choice.', 25961), -- Shakes O'Breen
(28573, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Would that you were a company, but we\'ll have to make do with with what we have.', 25961), -- Hero's Call: Arathi Highlands!
(27354, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, I have been expecting you, $n. Maginor Dumas has spoken highly of you and the royal commission only confirms his words. It is an honor to be able to craft a staff for you.', 25961), -- Mastering the Arcane
(24611, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My thanks for this Lovely Charm Bracelet.', 25961), -- A Gift for the Prophet
(24610, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My thanks for this Lovely Charm Bracelet.', 25961), -- A Gift for the High Priestess of Elune
(24609, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My thanks for this Lovely Charm Bracelet.', 25961), -- A Gift for a Lord of Ironforge
(26128, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And good riddance!$B$BThandol Span\'s safe thanks to you, $n, and hopefully Calamoth is down for good this time.', 25961), -- The Battle of Thandol Span
(26127, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good show, $glad:lass;, but we\'ve no time to celebrate. Thandol Span\'s in danger!', 25961), -- The Twilight's Hammer Revealed
(26327, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met! If you\'ve got a weapon on you, I\'ll take any help I can get clearing out these crazed fools!', 25961), -- Anvilmar the Hero
(26196, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Supplies from Ferilon? Bless his heart.$B$BWe\'re good on food, but we\'re runnin\' out of bullets!', 25961), -- Longbraid the Grim
(25927, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... the flames die. There is peace now. Peace for the land.', 25961), -- The Threat of Flame
(25939, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In sparing the land further suffering, you\'ve also helped us soothe the greenwarden.$B$BMany thanks, $n.', 25961), -- For Peat's Sake
(25926, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahhh... yes. The swamp suffers less now.$B$BMore threats, though. More lurk. I can see them!', 25961), -- Mired in Hatred
(26120, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The orcs will know better than to press further west now. Well done.', 25961), -- The Crazed Dragonmaw
(26195, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Greenwarden\'s Grove, $c. I am glad Whelgar has told you of us.$B$BIf you are able to lend us your assistance, I will be most grateful.', 25961), -- Who Wards The Greenwarden
(26189, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you back in one piece, $n! You\'re quite a piece of work.$B$BI\'ll be tellin\' Captain Stoutfist how you took care of those orcs!', 25961), -- The Angerfang Menace
(25849, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See? Not bad, eh? Why, I almost wish all my finds decided to dig themselves up for me. It\'d make my job a lot easier!$B$BOf course, you made it easier too, $n. Much obliged.', 25961), -- When Archaeology Attacks
(25853, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a relief! Maybe we can dig our way out of the hole we\'re still in, eh?$B$BNo, nevermind, just a bad joke.', 25961), -- Tooling Around
(25850, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s showin\' em what for! Good on you.', 25961), -- Strike the Earth!
(26981, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met, $c. We\'ve got raptor problems for sure... sort of.$B$BMore like the entire dig site deciding to attack us. I\'ve never seen rocks and fossils get so upset!', 25961), -- Whelgar's Retreat
(25868, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done! You\'ve brought one of Ironforge\'s most wanted to justice today, $n. I\'d say you\'ve earned a mighty fine reward.', 25961), -- Yorla Darksnare
(25867, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should do it! The more gnolls those fools have to chase after, the easier it\'ll be to keep them in line.', 25961), -- Gnoll Escape
(25866, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t suppose they agreed to come along quietly? Didn\'t think so.', 25961), -- Dark Iron Trappers
(25855, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wonderful! I\'ll be able to start reassembling these right away. Thank you so much!', 25961), -- Gizmos and Gadgets
(25865, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! The Ironforge Guard appreciates this, $n. You\'ve done our city a fine favor.$B$BBut something new has come up...', 25961), -- The Mosshide Job
(25854, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! These should be ready to hatch within the day...$B$BNow I just need to cobble up a raptor pen before they all hatch nigh-simultaneously. What could go wrong?', 25961), -- I'll Call Him Bitey
(25857, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Amazing! You\'re a true hero, $n. I\'ll never forget what you\'ve done for me and my family.$B$BI know it\'s not much, but please, take this with my blessing.', 25961), -- Hunting Horrorjaw
(25864, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done. Consider this reward not from me, but from Ironforge; the preservation of Khaz Modan is a matter that concerns every dwarf.', 25961), -- Dinosaur Crisis
(25856, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m much obliged, $c. This\'ll go a ways towards getting my family back on their feet.', 25961), -- Crocolisk Hides
(26980, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stoutfist sent you, eh? He\'s a good captain, runs his men well. Just wish he\'d stop starin\' at my midriff.$B$BDon\'t let me catch you doin\' it either. We\'ve work to take care of here!', 25961), -- Swiftgear Station
(25819, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Eye of Paleth? You say Fitzsimmons sent you out?$B$BBy the light...not again. Fitzsimmons is dead, $glad:lass;. You\'ve not the first to come to me like this, either.', 25961), -- The Eye of Paleth
(25818, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The key is rusted but it fits the lock neatly.', 25961), -- Lifting the Curse
(25817, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The cries of anguish have been stifled...but the source of the curse still lurks.', 25961), -- The Cursed Crew
(25816, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fitzsimmons sent you, didn\'t he? It\'s been so long...', 25961), -- Cursed to Roam
(33514, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done, $n. With Amnennar\'s phylactery now protected by the Red dragonflight we can now rest at ease.', 25961), -- The Ritual
(33513, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, but this is only half of the battle. With his support structure in disarray it is time to strike at Death Speaker Blackthorn.', 25961), -- Blackthorn's Lieutenants
(30995, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s all that survived?$b$bThe Horde is going to pay for this in blood.', 25961), -- No Man Left Behind
(30996, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that the dark shaman experiments drove Gordoth insane.$b$bHopefully we\'ve seen the last of this, $n.', 25961), -- The Dark Shaman
(30998, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n. Now we can figure out what it is they were trying to achieve down here.', 25961), -- A New Enemy
(34672, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was incredible, $n! The Old Gods will think twice before trying to crawl out of their pit again.', 25961), -- The Rise of Aku'mai
(31493, 273, 274, 0, 0, 0, 3000, 0, 0, 'Ah yes!$B$B<The Hooded Crusader rubs her hands together gleefully at the sight of the codex.>$B$BAnd now, I have a checklist with the name of every Scarlet Crusader on it!$B$BYou know... just in case any of them are unaccounted for. I don\'t like loose ends.', 25961), -- Just for Safekeeping, Of Course
(31490, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great start, $p!$B$BIt won\'t be long now before the Scarlet Crusade is nothing more than an ugly footnote in the annals of history.', 25961), -- Rank and File
(25770, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! Nice to see those addlebrained mountaineers knew to hand the ale off to a real $Gman:woman; to get the job done.$B$BWelcome to my survey. If you\'re of the mind to help Ironforge by takin\' over the intended jobs of some useless, lazy sods that call themselves dwarves, you\'re in the right place!', 25961), -- Keg Run
(25395, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the Makers! It\'s downright pristine. Those orcs couldn\'t figure out the tap-lock, it seems...and couldn\'t hack through the mastercraft work of Ironforge\'s keg-crafters with their crude weapons!', 25961), -- The Stolen Keg
(25211, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll show \'em!  Nice work!', 25961), -- Cleaning Hovel
(28565, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We haven\'t gotten much in the way of reinforcements lately. We can use every pair of hands we can get.', 25961), -- Hero's Call: Wetlands!
(26118, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The ambassador will trouble us no more. He is not the only Dark Iron dwarf whose heart still belongs to Twilight\'s Hammer. We must remember that and remain vigilant against their schemes, else my son will inherit only ruins and ashes.', 25961), -- Seize the Ambassador
(26112, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And just what is this?$B$B<Moira takes the report and the color drains from her face as she reads.>$B$BThis is impossible!', 25961), -- Demanding Answers
(29352, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, that\'s exactly what I needed. Ye have me thanks, $n, and me apologies fer bein\' so brusque earlier. I just cannae stand the thought of not gettin\' a meal finished on time.', 25961), -- A Fowl Shortage
(26102, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done it! Without your help, Ironforge Airfield would surely be occupied by the enemy and the Dark Irons would have a clear road to Ironforge itself.$B$BThe Council of Three Hammers must be informed of what happened here.', 25961), -- Grimaxe's Demise
(26094, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The momentum is starting to shift, $n, largely due to your efforts. Now, it is time to strike at the Dark Iron leadership.', 25961), -- Striking Back
(26085, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The men are finding hidden reserves of strength and courage to deal with the Dark Iron onslaught. The airfield will not fall on our watch!', 25961), -- Rallying the Defenders
(26078, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! My men are working hard on getting our flying machines and steam tanks back into the fight.', 25961), -- Extinguish the Fires
(25998, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness you\'re here, $n. The airfield\'s been attacked by the Dark Irons and I don\'t think we can hold out much longer.', 25961), -- Get to the Airfield
(27915, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am pleased to see you once again, $n. You are truly noble to assist me further.', 25961), -- The Heart of the Temple
(26187, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  I, and the people of Surwich, are in your debt.$b$bFeel free to take one of these.  While we haven\'t got much, we\'re happy to reward those that protect us.', 25961), -- The Downfall of Marl Wormthorn
(26186, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mayor Charlton Connisport looks warily at the device you\'ve assembled.>$b$bVery well, $n.  We have what we need to break Marl\'s trance and put an end to both him and his experiment.', 25961), -- Demoniac Vessel
(26185, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While I\'m surprised that Connisport is willing to go forward with his plan, I\'m also relieved.  I\'ve seen the demons rallying around Maldraz, and I share his fears.', 25961), -- Advice from the Cenarion Circle
(26184, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You say the demons were all worshipping the tree?$b$b<The mayor sighs.>$b$bIt is as I feared, then.', 25961), -- Wormthorn's Dream
(26175, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Surwich, $r.  Please, have a look around.', 25961), -- Surwich
(26171, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Loramus, resurrected!?  And then he trapped the demon inside his own body... by the Light...$b$bI see.  So this was Kasim\'s plan all along.  I suspected correctly, but I suppose I refused to believe it.$b$bAh, one last thing!  Kasim left one more instruction for me within his rune.  I did not understand it at first, but given the events that have taken place today, it now makes much more sense:$b$bHe asked me to let you choose from one of these.', 25961), -- You Are Rakh'likh, Demon
(26170, 397, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that we are prepared to face our demon, $n.  We have the amulet\'s blessing, we have the stone knife, and I alone know the demon\'s true name: Rakh\'likh.  Together, this may be enough to defeat the Defiler.', 25961), -- The Final Ritual
(26162, 53, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... you fool!  What have you done?', 25961), -- The Altar of Storms
(26161, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see... yes, I can work with this.$b$b<Kasim looks at the night elf\'s head.>$b$bLoramus Thalipedes, demon hunter.  I look forward to our reunion.', 25961), -- Not Just Any Body
(26166, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is sufficient.  If you see Grimeo again, you may tell him that he performed satisfactorily, but no... his debt is not yet cleared.  I will get to work on fashioning the stone knife of sealing.  There is no need for questions now.  All will be revealed in time.$b$bWhile I work, I have another task for you to complete.$b$bDon\'t look so upset!  This task will be fun... it involves collecting body parts.', 25961), -- Enhancing the Stone
(26174, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re certain nobody saw you?  Good.$b$b<Netherwane listens to your recount of the information you saw.>$b$bHmph... fairly harmless stuff.  Either the Horde are foolish enough to NOT be planning something against us... or they\'re hiding their information better than I expected.  Either way, well done, soldier.', 25961), -- Watching Our Back
(26173, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your work is appreciated, soldier.$b$b<The commander leans in close, and whispers:>$b$b$R... if you\'re still interested, I have one more small task for you...', 25961), -- Protecting Our Rear
(26165, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is no doubt about it, you have found demon blood.$b$bKasim\'s requests aside, I am sure that my Watch Commander is thankful for your efforts.  They have been struggling to deal with these demon distractions for some time now.', 25961), -- The Vile Blood of Demons
(26164, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope this is what the gnome wanted.', 25961), -- The Charred Granite of the Dark Portal
(26163, 5, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No, no, no... not Kasim again!  This is madness!$b$bPlease, remain quiet.  If my commander learns that I still work for the short one, do you know how quickly I will be removed from the watch?$b$b<Grimeo takes the rune from you, presses it to his chest, closes his eyes, and sighs.>$b$bI see you speak the truth.  Let us begin our business quickly, so that it may end even quicker.', 25961), -- Time is Short
(26169, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kasim clutches the third amulet.>$b$bHe was a powerful warrior, this one.  I will keep the amulet until we are ready to proceed.', 25961), -- The Amulet of Grol
(26168, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kasim hefts the amulet.>$b$bA warlock... and a powerful one at that.  I will hold onto this until the time is right.', 25961), -- The Amulet of Sevine
(26167, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kasim examines the amulet.>$b$bHe was an archmage, I can feel it.  I will hold the amulet for you while you collect the rest.', 25961), -- The Amulet of Allistarj
(26160, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The blood ritual was a success; I can clearly see where we are going next.$b$bI\'m sorry, I misspoke.  What I meant to say is, I can see where YOU are going next...', 25961), -- Blood Ritual
(26172, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfect, $n.  I will eat well for the next several days.', 25961), -- A Bloodmage's Gotta Eat Too
(26159, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kasim eyes the blood hungrily.>$b$bMore than enough, and still warm!  Now, let\'s get this ritual started, shall we?', 25961), -- The First Step
(26158, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  You\'ve managed to complete the simplest of tasks without dying.  Now that that\'s out of the way...', 25961), -- Attune the Bloodstone
(26157, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah!  You Nethergarde nincompoops are always two steps behind me, and I\'m nowhere near as fast as I used to be.$b$bI don\'t need Mahar\'s note to know what\'s going on.  Why do you think I\'m cooped up in the back of this cave?  What I do need, however, is a strong $r like you.', 25961), -- Kasim Sharim
(25716, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ably done, $n.  Now we see if my suspicions are correct.$b$b<The watcher selects a spell focus and focuses intently on its shadows.  After a moment, he turns back to you with a look of horror on his face.>', 25961), -- Cultists at our Doorstep
(25714, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My associates were correct to send you to me.  I have a problem which may threaten the sanctity of Nethergarde, and I need someone more capable than most.', 25961), -- Watcher Mahar Ba
(25713, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, the sound of things going boom makes my heart pitter-pat.  You\'ve made this gnome\'s day, $n.', 25961), -- Remove Their Arms
(25712, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  Thanks to your efforts, I am confident that with time, we will take back the Nethergarde Mine.', 25961), -- Nethergarde Reigns
(25711, 1, 14, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re an excellent asset to the Alliance and the Kirin Tor, $n.  Well done.$b$bWith time, our forces will retake the mine and press these Horde dogs out of the Blasted Lands.', 25961), -- Eliminate the Okril'lon
(25709, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a tragedy, what happened on the Shattershore.  They weren\'t even soldiers... just people looking for a new home.$b$bI think we\'ve done all we can, $n.', 25961), -- Curtail the Darktail
(25708, 92, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Enohar takes a sip off of a freshly-refilled mug.>$b$bAye, you\'ve done well, $g lad: lassie;.  You do the Alliance proud.', 25961), -- Our Fallen Friends
(25710, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... not bad.  You\'re quicker than many of my men.  Stick around, $n... I may have use of you yet.', 25961), -- Minor Distractions
(25715, 274, 274, 1, 0, 0, 777, 777, 0, 'You saw worgen?  That\'s bad.$b$bWorgen ghosts?  That\'s even worse.$b$bThose weren\'t Horde ships... they were Gilnean.  And they must have been headed down to Surwich, at the bottom of the Tainted Forest.  That makes a lot more sense.$b$bWe\'ve got to try to help them, $n!  The worgen are our allies!', 25961), -- A Closer Look
(27919, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, has Avuun sent ye? Good, good...', 25961), -- Onward to the Blasted Lands
(28673, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For decades has the garrison at Nethergarde held firm against the threat of the Horde and we do not intend to surrender now.', 25961), -- Hero's Call: Blasted Lands!
(24913, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am moved, $n. Prophet Velen has been in closely guarded seclusion. He has dared not waste his energy on anything save preparing for the final confrontation he has foretold.$B$BAnd yet, he came here, in person, to comfort a single dying soul.$B$BI must thank you as well, for helping me make my last effort to comfort my friend. My research will continue... and I hope that Magtoor will continue to watch over me.', 25961), -- Remember the Light
(27904, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can only hope this will lead to a cure, $n. Thank you for bringing it to me.', 25961), -- Breath of Mist
(27902, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Such clarity... let us hope this will aid poor Magtoor.', 25961), -- The Purespring
(27876, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It will have to be purified, but this will be most helpful. Thank you.', 25961), -- Secrets of the Mire
(27875, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Prayerblossom has been used by the Broken as a remedy since they settled in this swamp. If it soothes the physical form, it might be used for more powerful healing...', 25961), -- Prayerblossom
(27918, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. I am afraid it may be too late... but I refuse to give up, even if the Exodar itself does not hear my cries.', 25961), -- The Harborage
(27851, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n. With this, it\'s only a matter of time until the orcs are fleeing for the portal or begging for surrender.', 25961), -- Cutting Supply
(27849, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve followed orders well, $n. On behalf of the crown, I\'m rewarding you for your bravery on the battlefield.', 25961), -- Assault on Stonard
(27845, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. Those soldiers deserve better than to be left face down in the mud.', 25961), -- Marking the Fallen
(27843, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once again, well done. With a few more pushes the battle will be ours.', 25961), -- Reinforcements Denied
(27795, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Going toe to toe with ogres is impressive, $n. I\'m glad I\'ve got soldiers like you out here.', 25961), -- Tides of Darkness
(27840, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  We, are in your debt.', 25961), -- Draenethyst Crystals
(27860, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'It still pains my heart to have asked you to do this, though I know there is no other way. You have saved those of us still holding on from a terrible menace.', 25961), -- The Lost Ones
(27822, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve had strikes on our own lumber line while you\'ve been gone. This should at least put us on equal footing for gathering rates.$B$BGood work, $n.', 25961), -- Lumbering Oafs
(27821, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More black on you than red... that\'s what I like to see. Looks like you\'ve got what it takes, $n.', 25961), -- Orcs and Humans
(27870, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Trouble within the temple... I wish we could spare forces to deal with it. The war with Stonard is already raging, and we need every man we can get.', 25961), -- To Marshtide Watch
(27116, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What in blazes WAS that? A flying mechanostrider?$B$BYou know what, I don\'t want to know. I\'m just going to pretend that didn\'t happen, and we\'ll be all nice and businesslike.', 25961), -- The Winds of Loch Modan
(27115, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s working! My father brought it!', 25961), -- Ando's Call
(27078, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it! We may not have stopped the cult dead, but we\'ve shown them we\'re not easy pickings and given them a welt to prove it.$B$BTake this with my gratitude, and try not to blush if anyone in Thelsamar calls you \"hero\"!', 25961), -- Gor'kresh
(27077, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shame that these half-formed things are too brittle and warped to be used for some weapons of our own. But it\'s thanks to you that we had the chance to get them out before they set. I\'m not about to complain.', 25961), -- Clutching at Chaos
(27075, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It may look grim, but we\'ll win with your help, $n. They won\'t keep the dwarves down.', 25961), -- Servants of Cho'gall
(27074, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You hit the twilight camp at the center of the lake? Not bad, $glad:lass;!$B$BIf you\'re ready to take the fight right to their doorstep, I\'ve got your chance.', 25961), -- Fight the Hammer
(27035, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it? You did! You fought them and won!$B$BThere\'s hope after all...', 25961), -- Standing Up
(27034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t care about my father and his silly inventions! It\'s all just nonsense!', 25961), -- He's That Age
(27037, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for helping me out with my little plan, $n. I\'ve been itching for months to get back at that snooty, stuck-up boy, and I\'d say we did a pretty good job! Here, have this, you\'ve earned it.', 25961), -- Vyrin's Revenge
(27036, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Er... what\'s this? A bear\'s head, by the looks of it.$b$b<He runs a finger along his scar unconsciously.>$b$bWell, that\'s quite an interesting kill you have yourself there. Couldn\'t be that bear from back then...$b$b<He trails off then starts to visibly shake.>$b$bOh, take that away take it away! Get that grisly thing out of here!', 25961), -- Vyrin's Revenge
(27033, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! Now that I\'ve perfected the wing balance and have all the parts I need, all we need is a pilot.', 25961), -- Skystrider's Heart
(27026, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Okay, yes, I have already been informed that bobcats are much smaller than I was assuming. But that\'s still pretty dangerous for gnomes!$B$BYou\'ve done a good thing for the safety of this lodge, $n!', 25961), -- Defcon: Bobcat
(27032, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Skystrider sits silent, its chance to fly gone. An obvious hatch on the front is marked \"SRW\".>', 25961), -- Bird is the Word
(13661, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You located all of our documents! We can\'t thank you enough for the help... we\'d all but given up hope. It seemed sure that the Dark Irons would be able to act upon all of this information soon. It\'s good to know that they\'ll be left blind in their attacks for quite a while yet.$B$BTo thank you for all of your efforts on our behalf, we would like to offer you a gift. An artifact really... something we recovered from one of our digs. You have the appreciation of all of the Explorers\' League.', 25961), -- Heartfelt Appreciation
(13657, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our historical records! The thought of Dark Iron vermin delving into our past just made me sick to my stomach.$B$BWe appreciate you bringing this back to us. We\'d like to offer you some coin as a reward.', 25961), -- Explorers' League Document (3 of 6)
(27028, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lovely specimens you\'ve got there! Here\'s my wager, $glad:lass;.', 25961), -- Hornet Hunting
(13659, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! Think they got a kick out of seeing how low they were on our list of threat assessments? This document was admittedly a bit out of date, but none the less amusing.$B$BOf course, we\'ll offer you some money as a reward for returning this anyway - your efforts are appreciated!', 25961), -- Explorers' League Document (6 of 6)
(13658, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ug, I can\'t believe they got their hands on our transport routes - that was just asking for trouble!!$B$BThank you for getting this back to us before they were able to do much with it! You probably saved us a lot of heartache. Please accept some coin as a reward for your efforts.', 25961), -- Explorers' League Document (4 of 6)
(13660, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our artifact records! I was pretty well worried what the Dark Irons might try to steal with this information at their disposal.$B$BThank you for bringing this back to us. We\'ll gladly part with some coin to express our gratitude.', 25961), -- Explorers' League Document (5 of 6)
(13636, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Orders! Let\'s see what we have here... hah! He wants me to deal with the infestation of rat men. We\'re already in the middle of that, so no real deviation there.$B$BCare to lend a hand?', 25961), -- Stormpike's Orders
(26176, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad to hear you\'ve been clearing out the troggs. Let\'s have a look at this report, and...$B$B...Is that a beer stain?', 25961), -- Onward to Thelsamar
(26147, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew the second I laid eyes on you, $n, that you would make Ironforge proud.  You have served our people well. I salute you, $n.', 25961), -- Bigger and Uglier
(26148, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most excellent, $n! You have brought hope to Loch Modan. With Grawmug dead, we stand a better chance of seeing the Troggs eliminated from the land.', 25961), -- A Decisive Strike
(26146, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n!  You demonstrated uncanny courage on the battlefield.  Our war against the Troggs will be won with efforts such as yours.  You have served King Magni well.', 25961), -- In Defense of the King's Lands
(26145, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am quite impressed, $n.  You have done the Dwarven race a great favor by defending our lands.  King Magni Bronzebeard himself would be proud!', 25961), -- The Trogg Threat
(13635, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The South Gate status report? Excellent. I\'ve been awaiting news from them for a while.$B$BWith the increasing number of troggs in the hills on all sides, I fear the outposts will be the first to feel any aggressive action.', 25961), -- South Gate Status Report
(26855, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is grim news, for Hildelve was a good friend.  And I wish I could have been there with you when you found the beast, Mangeclaw!$B$BThank you, $n. Your deed will be remembered by the pilots of the Ironforge Siege Brigade.', 25961), -- A Pilot's Revenge
(26854, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here is the corpse of a dwarf -- mauled, frozen, and picked clean by mountain scavengers.  Clutched in its hand is a book containing the roughly scribbled notes of Mori Hildelve.  And around its frame, still in superior condition, is a Brigadier\'s Vest.$B$BThis grisly scene must have been where the Siege Engine pilot met his end.', 25961), -- The Lost Pilot
(28567, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have our leaders finally heard my pleas? We\'re down to just a handful of pilots and mountaineers to defend Loch Modan.', 25961), -- Hero's Call: Loch Modan!
(28675, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Bogpaddle, $c. I fully expect you will enjoy all our facility has to offer.', 25961); -- Hero's Call: Swamp of Sorrows!
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(29037, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your cub looks satisfied for now.', 25996), -- 'Borrowing' From the Winterfall
(29032, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These cubs are just the right age to begin their training. A few of them even have the proper traits to be trained as mounts. As promised, I\'ll select one of these cubs for you to train. This fellow here seems to have an affinity for you.$B$BI\'ll train the more common, docile cubs for the market in Darnassus.', 25996), -- Get Them While They're Young
(28524, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, how nice of those dear furbolg. I feel so bad for them, cooped up in that hold, afraid of the world.$B$BBut can you blame them? These Winterfall furbolg are turning just as vicious as any in Felwood. I\'d like to put a stop to it... if only for the sake of my own research, let alone the dear Timbermaw.', 25996), -- Delivery for Donova
(13510, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some sort of shield you say? We might have a way around that. Balthule had an idea for breaking whatever protective enchantments their shaman had, so it might work on this too. Thank you for saving Aynasha and bringing me this information - it may well make the difference in our battle.', 25996), -- Timely Arrival
(13511, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alanndarian is dead then. That saddens me greatly, but it is not entirely unexpected. I expect no mercy from these savages, and will show them none.', 25996), -- One Bitter Wish
(13508, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Alanndarian looks very pale, though shallow breaths betray the life that remains in her.>$B$BYou\'re here...  to save me? A bit later... than I hoped.', 25996), -- Swift Response
(13506, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '\"Another?\" They have more than one. I will not leave any of my people to be tortured, we must act quickly.', 25996), -- Reason to Worry
(13898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.  The naga seek the destruction and subjugation of all surface-dwellers -- do not hesitate to drive them out of our lands and back into the shadowy ocean depths where they belong.', 25996), -- The Tides Turn Against Us
(13897, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can finally rest here now, $n.  It appears Darkshore has been saved -- and we have you to thank for it.', 25996), -- The Battle for Darkshore
(13900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $n.  Unfortunately the battle is far from over.', 25996), -- The Offering to Azshara
(13899, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The warlord doesn\'t seem to have the horn on him.  Perhaps he was telling the truth.', 25996), -- The Darkscale Warlord
(13891, 4, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 0, 'Love of Elune, look at you. That must\'ve been some fight! You\'re covered in what looks like... chowder.$B$BIf a mere minion could cause so much agony here in Darkshore, I can\'t even imagine the suffering that a true Old One could bring about.$B$BWell, at least the animals are safe for now. I will plant the sapling you created to help rebuild this shattered land. Thank you, $n! I\'d give you a hug but, you know. Chowder. ', 25996), -- The Devourer of Darkshore
(13885, 6, 274, 0, 0, 200, 900, 0, 0, 'So the animals are safe, then. Thank you, thank you!$B$BBut now it\'s time to turn our attention to the source. ', 25996), -- In Defense of Darkshore
(13925, 21, 1, 0, 0, 0, 600, 0, 0, 'Interesting... It sounds like our cure will keep the wildlife safe, but you say you saw something else? Some kind of angry presence?$B$BThis is a good sign, $n. Whatever is behind this isn\'t happy, and that means we\'re on to something.  ', 25996), -- An Ounce of Prevention
(13953, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The naga are in league with the Twilight\'s Hammer?  Just what we needed.', 25996), -- Naga In Our Midst
(13895, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aros\'s body appears to be lifeless yet still warm.  Perhaps his killers are nearby.', 25996), -- The Slumbering Ancients
(13882, 4, 1, 0, 0, 100, 1200, 0, 0, 'Perfect, this is everything. Did you have fun collecting the wisp? I used to chase the wisps around Ashenvale when I was just a girl.$B$B<Lost in memories for a moment, Kathrena suddenly grows somber.>$B$BI\'m afraid I\'ve found out what we\'re dealing with.', 25996), -- The Seeds of Life
(13893, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The dwarf\'s story is unsettling... yet informative.  It seems we have few options left.', 25996), -- Soggoth and Kronn
(13896, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, we know a thing or two about this Soggoth.  The question is... do you really want to know?', 25996), -- Unearthed Knowledge
(13881, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, '<Kathrena recoils at your description of the ravaged animals and the cruel device at the bottom of the lake.>$B$B$n, this is terrible. What is that thing, and how did it get there? Something is devouring these animals, physically and spiritually. I had suspected the satyrs or some sort of disease was the culprit, but this is shaping up to be something... unnatural.', 25996), -- Consumed
(13948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is dire news, $n.  If you are correct, then we\'d best act swiftly and decisively.$B$BWe cannot allow this \"Soggoth\" to be brought back to life.', 25996), -- Stepping Up Surveillance
(13546, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. You are a hero to my people. Without you, we would be doomed to madness and death. May the bear spirit always watch over you.', 25996), -- The Defiler
(13572, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. With your efforts, we might be able to save the Blackwood who remain.', 25996), -- Jadefire Braziers
(13545, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. My people have begun to emerge from their madness, but they will fall back into it if we do not deal with the source of the corruption.', 25996), -- Cleansing the Afflicted
(13544, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Elder Brolg accepts the blessed bundle from you and looks over it.>$B$BThis is exactly what we needed. The bear\'s spirit favors us and there may be hope for my brothers after all.', 25996), -- The Bear's Blessing
(13526, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are poor, weak stalks, but they are all we have. The corruption spreads quickly, even among the plants of the forest.', 25996), -- The Bear's Paw
(13892, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is dire news, $n.  If you are correct, then we\'d best act swiftly and decisively.$B$BWe cannot allow this \"Soggoth\" to be brought back to life.', 25996), -- Leave No Tracks
(13910, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 1500, 0, 0, 'Har har, that sounds like quite a heap you built there. Did they take to it? Good, good! Let\'s see if my plan comes to fruition.$B$B<Archaeologist Groff watches as scores of murlocs stream down the beach, pouring into the hovel from all corners of the compass. Gradually his brows knit together.>$B$BWhat have I done?', 25996), -- A New Home
(13909, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 800, 0, 0, '<Archaeologist Groff picks through the wreckage.>$B$BWell, not much here that don\'t look stepped on, sat on, or soaked in a toilet. But toss some thatch on top and it\'ll do.$B$BTell me, $n, do you consider yourself an architect?', 25996), -- Got Some Flotsam?
(13918, 4, 5, 0, 0, 200, 800, 0, 0, 'Why yes, yes, this is it! See here, the slot is the exact dimensions of the ancient disc, just as I\'d surmised. Here\'s your reward, $n - you\'ve earned it.$B$B<Jr. Archaeologist Ferd upends the device and pours mud and garbage from the slot.>$B$BAre you ready to meet history face to face? Let\'s see what the ancients have to say! ', 25996), -- The Titans' Terminal
(13912, 21, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Spectacular! Good work, $n. I\'m sure Remtravel would thank you himself if he could remember your name.$B$BLook at the surface of the disc - these microscopic etchings - this is amazing. I\'m certain this strange wheel holds information, if only we could read it...', 25996), -- Swamped Secrets
(13907, 1, 15, 0, 0, 0, 800, 0, 0, 'Bravo, $n! Now let\'s take a look-see at our new situation.$B$BWhat? MORE murlocs? I swear on my stones, the more murlocs you kill, the more murlocs appear. Is it just me? We\'re going to need a new approach.', 25996), -- Sweeping Clean the Ruins
(13911, 1, 5, 0, 0, 200, 500, 0, 0, 'Ah, you\'ve helped the Prospector find his missing journal! To think it was here all along.$B$BSomeday you\'ll have to show me this other set of ruins he\'s always going on about.', 25996), -- The Absent-Minded Prospector
(13525, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why have you come here, outsider?$B$B<You tell the elder that you were sent by Foriel Broadleaf at the Grove of the Ancients. He seems to relax slightly.>$B$BThe elf is right. The forces of Felwood have seeped into Darkshore and sickened my people.', 25996), -- What's Happening to the Blackwood Furbolg?
(13582, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Aroom lets out a long low-pitched hoot.>$B$BFinally kin may rest.', 25996), -- Elune's Fire
(13578, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $r.  Soon my kin will rest.', 25996), -- Aroom's Farewell
(13601, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you for coming to our assistance.  As you can see, the refugees\' situation is dire.', 25996), -- In Aid of the Refugees
(13596, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $n.  Now give me a moment to examine the plans you\'ve brought me.', 25996), -- Twilight Plans
(13519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $n.  The Twilight\'s Hammer is a dangerous cult.  It would be foolish to underestimate the danger they represent.', 25996), -- The Twilight's Hammer
(13570, 1, 1, 1, 2, 0, 60, 60, 60, 'I just want to offer my sincerest thanks for all that you\'ve done for us. In my grief, I\'m afraid that I didn\'t extend the gratitude that you truly deserve. We may not have made it here without you.$B$BKnow that you will always have friends here.$B$BAnd you needn\'t worry about my loneliness. Grimclaw has taken to keeping me company, and I have to say he\'s a more comforting companion than I would have expected.$B$BTake this, and go with all our blessings. Until we meet again, $n.', 25996), -- Remembrance of Auberdine
(13591, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, this news is disturbing indeed. I will start dispatching messengers to Ashenvale immediately and see if we can\'t get some reinforcements prepared for them.$B$BI cannot thank you enough for all the help you\'ve lent us in these trying times. Such heroic deeds deserve reward. I think I might have something that will serve you perfectly.', 25996), -- Disturbing Connections
(13514, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You performed excellently up there! We are fortunate to have you with us.$B$BI haven\'t yet received word regarding their leader. If you haven\'t spoken with Sandrya at the cave in the back of the vale, be sure to do so before you depart.', 25996), -- The Ancients' Ire
(13515, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We owe a great debt to you for all that you\'ve done to see this battle through.$B$BNot often can we claim victories so decisively, but it seems there\'s far more to this plot than just the Shatterspear. If you haven\'t already checked his body for information, make sure to do so before you leave.', 25996), -- Ending the Threat
(13590, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to meet you. Word has been sent to me of the efforts you have made to aid us against the trolls, and I must admit I am a bit impressed. The final fight is upon us now, I hope you are prepared.', 25996), -- The Front Line
(13512, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve shown a great deal of talent for one so young. Good work. It seems the final battle is before us.', 25996), -- Strategic Strikes
(13513, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do perfectly. I will prepare them for Sandrya - you are sure to be dispatched to meet with her shortly.', 25996), -- On the Brink
(13844, 273, 1, 0, 0, 200, 400, 0, 0, 'Let\'s see what we\'ve got here.... By Elune, his notes are scrawled in a half dozen languages. What is this, blood? This archive makes my flesh seethe, but at least it\'s secure. It will take us some time to decipher these notes.$b$bOh - your reward? Yes, here. Nice work with those undead scavengers. Now get back to the fight.', 25996), -- The Looting of Althalaxx
(13507, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. One more threat we can worry a bit less about. We\'ll continue the offensive while they are still off-guard.', 25996), -- Denying Manpower
(13509, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. That should slow them down a bit.', 25996), -- War Supplies
(13504, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. Thank you, $c.', 25996), -- Shatterspear Laborers
(13505, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! Thank you so much. I would hate to lose more records of our culture to war - far too much has been sacrificed already.', 25996), -- Remnants of the Highborne
(13589, 6, 0, 0, 0, 20, 0, 0, 0, 'Glynda sent you to lend a hand, did she? I\'m glad she did - I could certainly use the help.$B$BI\'m working on our initial plans to start whittling away at their ranks. Please feel free to help Tysha and Balthule in the meantime.', 25996), -- The Shatterspear Invaders
(13560, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The decoys worked then? Great to hear it! Don\'t you worry yourself one bit about the treasures. Me and Gary will take care of the rest this time around.$B$BTruth be told, if something went wrong again and I lost any more of you adventurer types, I\'m pretty sure they\'d kick me out of town. ', 25996), -- An Ocean Not So Deep
(13563, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. Perhaps it would have been better... if I had done it myself. But even after these thousands of years, I could not bear to raise my hand against my beloved.$b$bPlease, I would be alone with my grief...', 25996), -- A Love Eternal
(13599, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve returned! It is good to see you again. I suppose we have you to thank for Grimclaw\'s return?$B$BI\'m afraid... I have some bad news. I\'ve been unable to purge the toxin... their conditions worsen. Gershalla died shortly after you left, and Volcor... Volcor passed just before you came back.$B$BHe lived long enough to see Grimclaw come back safely, so he died with a smile on his face. I\'m just sorry that I couldn\'t do more.$B$BFor now, I\'m doing everything I can to save Shaldyn, so please excuse me.', 25996), -- Grimclaw's Return
(13562, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have our thanks. It is time that we leave the past behind us, and start looking to our future.', 25996), -- The Final Flame of Bashal'Aran
(13523, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve succeeded... it hasn\'t all been in vain...$B$BMy time approaches.  Go now, $n, and may Elune protect you.', 25996), -- Power Over the Tides
(13569, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it is done. You have received the blessing of a great animal spirit, and I shall now complete the ritual for you. Please stand still.', 25996), -- The Ritual Bond
(13597, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For countless ages I have walked these forests and lived in these mountains. Through snow and fire, I have watched civilizations crumble and nature press on. Now, the very earth turns against us, and it becomes very apparent that we must fight if our legacy is to continue.$B$BYour heart is true, and I would choose you as our champion. If you value the thick hide and resilience of my kind, then accept my boon. Know that the other spirits will not accept you once this choice is made, so choose wisely.', 25996), -- Spirit of the Thistle Bear
(13568, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I share these forests willingly, accepting night elf kind into my home, and on occasion calling them friend. Though they have been tainted greatly in recent memory, I can see in you the same strength, honor, and spirit that first endeared them to me.$B$BIf you place value in the ferocity necessary to overcome all odds, then I am willing to call you my champion. Know now that if you side with my kind, the other spirits will not accept you, so consider your choice carefully.', 25996), -- Spirit of the Moonstalker
(13567, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am the caretaker for my kind, leading not through force, but through wisdom and swift action. Wisdom is what carries us into the deeper forest when danger beckons and swiftness is what leaves our enemies basking in our absence.$B$BIn this wisdom, I see through to your true intentions, and I know that you are deserving of my blessing, the blessing of my swiftness. It can be yours, but know that the other spirits will not welcome you once you proceed - consider this carefully before accepting my boon.', 25996), -- Spirit of the Stag
(13566, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do perfectly. These are the final ingredients for an incense I\'ve been working on. I will explain in just a moment, let me mix these in first.', 25996), -- Ritual Materials
(13598, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks, young one. We should be able to speed Grimclaw\'s recovery dramatically with this salve.', 25996), -- Unsavory Remedies
(13565, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, ally. We shall keep a more vigilant eye should they return.', 25996), -- Twice Removed
(13564, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, traveler. You seem to have an interest in my friend here. You\'re here on behalf of his friend Volcor then I imagine? If Volcor didn\'t come himself, he must be injured as well. I hope he recovers quickly.$B$BGrimclaw is too injured to be moved far and he\'s going to need some immediate treatment. I\'m afraid I can\'t let you take him back just yet, but perhaps you can help me while I tend to him. ', 25996), -- A Lost Companion
(13561, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks. Though they may not be able to show it, you have the thanks of the Highborne spirits as well.$B$BFare safely, traveler.', 25996), -- Solace for the Highborne
(13554, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should be plenty! Thanks so much! I\'ll get working on a cure for this nastiness immediately.', 25996), -- A Cure In The Dark
(13831, 273, 1, 0, 0, 200, 800, 0, 0, '<Tharnariun Treetender pages through the notes as you relate your story, the lines in his face deepening with concern.>$b$bSo the Forsaken have been studying Foulhoof\'s work? My gut crawls at the thought of what they might have done were they able to weaponize his corruption. You\'ve done well to destroy their work, but this raises deeper concerns. What brought the Forsaken to our doorstep? Are they working with the Shatterspear trolls to our north? Sorrows are heaping upon sorrows, $c. I\'m glad you\'re here.', 25996), -- A Troubling Prescription
(13557, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am pleased to hear that you were able to free some of the remaining wildlife. With a bit of good fortune, we will find the cure for the corruption that the others have faced before any more of them die.', 25996), -- Bearer of Good Fortune
(13529, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done then. Thank you. I only hope that the wildlife here will see more peace with his passing.', 25996), -- The Corruption's Source
(13528, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Static precedes Wizbang\'s distorted voice.>$B$BThe results are coming in now. We should have some information on how the bears contracted this in just a moment.', 25996), -- Buzzbox 723
(13527, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This definitely looks like the stuff they were eating. Let me take a closer peek...', 25996), -- No Accounting for Taste
(13521, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The machine crackles loudly, and then Wizbang\'s static-ridden voice becomes audible.>$B$BLovely! I hope you didn\'t kill too many of them. We\'re not trying to wipe out the population, we just need to get to the source of this corruption quickly! I\'m proceeding with the analysis now.', 25996), -- Buzzbox 413
(13520, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do perfectly. Thank you so much!$B$BI suspect they will want to thank you personally should they recover, so perhaps you can stop by later on.', 25996), -- The Boon of the Seas
(13522, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts are very much appreciated. Since the Cataclysm, the elementals have been out of control. We have little hope of taking back Auberdine without extinguishing their presence first.', 25996), -- Threat from the Water
(28529, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where did you find these?! You haven\'t shown them to anyone else, have you?$B$BI apologize. You took me off guard. Telarius was a very powerful Demon Hunter, but he was slain during a confrontation with the warden, Maiev, many years ago. You are fortunate that his ghost was only a shade of his former power. I wonder how many have found their way to him in those ruins.$B$BI will see to it that these scrolls make their way to the high priestess immediately. Thank you, $n.', 25996), -- Writings of the Void
(25451, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Incredible!  You may have found the granddaddy of all yeti hides with this!$B$BYou better believe I\'ll pay you for it.  I normally don\'t pay that much for a single hide, but I\'m pretty sure I can make something special from it.  Thanks for thinking of me on this, $n!', 25996), -- Pristine Yeti Hide
(26401, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How horrible... for someone so young and full of promise to fall to demons!$B$BI beg your forgiveness for sending you into danger as well, $n. I hope you don\'t cross paths with that demoness again...', 25996), -- Return to Vestia
(25350, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The apprentice\'s body is cold. He has been dead for a while.>', 25996), -- The Lost Apprentice
(26687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What now, soldier?$B$BReinforcements? For the Barrens? We\'ve been bleeding supplies and men there for months!$B$BDoes someone need to remind Twinbraid of the attack on Northwatch? Our losses at Honor\'s Stand? What happened to the men I sent to Fort Triumph? We\'ve nothing to spare!$B$BListen $n, if you want to help out our cause, you\'ll focus your efforts here in Dustwallow. Between the deserters and the Horde encroachment... we could use a hand.', 25996), -- Reinforcements From Theramore
(24934, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You make a hell of a marine, $n.$B$BWe\'ll mop up the others. But it looks like the Horde fleet is disengaging - maybe to land more troops ashore?$B$BAdmiral Aubrey will know what to do. Talk to me when you\'re ready to fly back!', 25996), -- Repel Boarders!
(25197, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve ventured all the way here from Honor\'s Stand? Excellent, we could use your experience here.$B$BThey may have breached the walls, but Northwatch isn\'t going down without a fight.', 25996), -- The Admiral Won't Back Down
(25191, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What, what!? Can\'t you see we\'re under attack here!$B$B<Gimbleheart snatches the readouts from the survey craft, then stuffs them haphazardly into a duffel bag.>$B$BYes sure of course I\'ll give Nibb\'s findings careful study. Later. From the safety of the Eastern Kingdoms, if I have any say about it! ', 25996), -- Survey the Destruction
(25852, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You say the Grimtotem are no longer a threat? That\'s great, but we\'ve got Horde all up our keesters!', 25996), -- All's Clear
(28511, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Elune has favored us with your arrival, $c. There is much to do.', 25996), -- Hero's Call: Feralas!
(25479, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thyssiana sent you? Good! We need your help, now!', 25996), -- To New Thalanaar
(28160, 6, 25, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, she\'s evil! But, what does it mean, $n? Is Magatha going to destroy us? Is she in charge of the Twilight\'s Hammer now?$B$BWhatever happens, you\'ve delivered us from our enemies. Please allow me to show you our gratitude.', 25996), -- Spread the Word
(27329, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, she\'s been taken prisoner by the Twilight\'s Hammer. I can\'t say that I feel sorry for her, but she might prove even more dangerous in their hands.', 25996), -- Invoking the Serpent
(27357, 2, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is embarrassing to have been kidnapped by Arnak again. I heard the fighting outside. Did you kill him?$B$B<The shaman looks sad for just a moment.>$B$BI am happy to be free once more. Now, how can I help you, $r?', 25996), -- The Captive Bride
(27327, 6, 25, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For some reason they all think that you\'ve been sent by Magatha Grimtotem. I know it must have something to do with that wind serpent that\'s been hanging around.$B$BDoesn\'t matter. Their leader is dead. It\'s only a matter of time before the tauren of Freewind Post regain their home.$B$BIf I were them, I\'d push back a little to teach the Grimtotem a lesson, but they probably won\'t. They\'re tauren.', 25996), -- Grimtotem Chiefs: The Chief of Chiefs
(27325, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Surely that was the voice of the Elder Crone!$B$BWe must be very careful, $n. Great danger lies ahead if Magatha Grimtotem has taken notice of you.', 25996), -- The Drums of War
(27310, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s see them wage their war now!', 25996), -- No Weapons For You!
(27323, 6, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The sentinel gives you an appraising look.>$B$BWhat is it with you? Why do they all seem spooked by you being here?', 25996), -- Grimtotem Chiefs: Grundig Darkcloud
(27312, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That put a dent in their numbers! Can\'t say that they didn\'t deserve it.', 25996), -- Darkcloud Grimtotem
(27318, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s two of them. Two more to go.$B$BI wonder what he meant about being \"chosen\"?', 25996), -- Grimtotem Chiefs: Elder Stormhoof
(27314, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She was tougher than I thought. We worked well together, but we\'re going to have to make sure not to underestimate the other Grimtotem chiefs.', 25996), -- Grimtotem Chiefs: Isha Gloomaxe
(27320, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m fairly certain that\'s it. This is very intriguing, $n. What are they doing here? Are they being used as a weapon?$B$BThe wind serpent flew northwest to that next bluff. Maybe that\'s where the drums are?', 25996), -- The Writ of History
(27316, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s true then! What is it doing here, though? And if it\'s here, that must mean that the writ and the drums are also nearby!$B$BMaybe there\'s some link between it and the wind serpent that just appeared? I think that I\'ve an idea what that creature is as well.', 25996), -- The Rattle of Bones
(27275, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $n. Let us put the fear of the Goddess into the Grimtotem.', 25996), -- Together Again
(25873, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A traitor amongst the tauren?$B$BI\'ve never heard of such a thing. Clan rivalries and warfare are one thing, but killing your own in cold blood.$B$B<Quentin shakes his head in disbelief.>', 25996), -- Horn of the Traitor
(25869, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Grim business, that.<Quentin coughs.>$B$BNo pun intended.', 25996), -- Grimtotem in the Post
(25871, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for freeing her, $n. Those Grimtotem monsters would have killed her in cold blood.', 25996), -- Save the Sentinel
(25835, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad that Fizzle finally sent you here. We\'re helping the tauren to retake Freewind Post and push back the Grimtotem.', 25996), -- Free Freewind Post
(25825, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is oil! You\'re really proving yourself to be invaluable, $n!$B$BToo bad I\'m going to have to send you off now.', 25996), -- Deliver the Goods
(25585, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re still shooting, but not nearly as much! Yeeeeeeeeeaaaaaaaaaaah!', 25996), -- Quiet the Cannons
(25588, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll teach those scurvy dogs! You have my thanks, $n.', 25996), -- A Little Payback
(28031, 4, 1, 6, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'That must be the new I-Scream Cryocannon! Ain\'t she a beauty?!$B$B<Brivelthwerp eyes you shrewdly.>$B$BI\'m going to let you in on a secret, my good $g friend : lady;: the groundwork for a vast mercantile empire is being laid right here!$B$BTell me... how do you feel about ice cream?', 25996), -- Special Delivery for Brivelthwerp
(25627, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, yeah, yeah... I\'m sure that your little adventure into the cave was very interesting.$B$BHow about we talk about it over drinks back on the Speedbarge once you get me out of this cage?', 25996), -- Two-Tusk Takedown
(25609, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yeah! Look at all that booty.$B$BWait a minute... bring it closer!', 25996), -- Sunken Treasure
(25590, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey! Get me out of here!', 25996), -- Where's Wizzle?
(25813, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well then, let\'s see them get any kind of magical hocus pocus air support now when we take over!', 25996), -- Go Blow that Horn
(25798, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oil! Black gold! Tanaris Tea!$B$BWe\'re rich! We just have to clear out the remaining pesky centaur. I\'m sure with all the money we\'re going to make, we can relocate them to some other bluff.', 25996), -- Defend the Drill
(25796, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll teach them. You\'ve softened the Splithoof up enough that we should be able to govern them now with a minimal guard presence from the Speedbarge.$B$BThat is, once we\'ve dealt with their supposed air elemental leader.', 25996), -- Eminent Domain
(25790, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'THEY WHAT?!', 25996), -- Back to Crazzle
(25778, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just put it down on the ground, $r.', 25996), -- Fake Gold for Black Gold
(25774, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Genius! Now, where\'s that gold paint? I know it\'s around here somewhere.', 25996), -- Fool's Gold
(25756, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What?! How\'d they get that much gold to offer?$B$BWe don\'t have that kind of money!', 25996), -- Get Zherin!
(25744, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Crazzle gets a gleam in his eye.>$B$BI\'ve got Kravel Koalbeard up there talking to one of their chiefs, but now that you\'re here, we\'ll have the rights to pump up their oil in no time!', 25996), -- Negotiations
(25542, 4, 17, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! You did it!$B$B<Jinky grabs you and gives you a big smooch on the cheek! She then regains her dignity and smooths her clothes.>$B$BThanks for saving my Speedbarge, Captain $n.', 25996), -- Circle the Wagons... er, Boats
(25532, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One problem down. Now to deal with the greater threat!', 25996), -- Pirate Accuracy Increasing
(25515, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This\'ll do for a start.', 25996), -- Down in the Deeps
(25524, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness! Now, just a little shove....', 25996), -- In the Outhouse
(25517, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the spirit! You\'re a real credit to the Alliance!$B$BYou know, you can go back in there and do that anytime you feel like it. I highly encourage you to do so!', 25996), -- Bar Fight!
(25504, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, '<Jinky eyes the list of parts and spits!>$B$BI don\'t have even half of that stuff!', 25996), -- Do Me a Favor?
(25488, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'YES?! Do you see me interrupting your fascinating argument?$B$BNo... no, please, go ahead. I\'m sure that your interruption is about something very important. More important than dealing with the survival of everyone here, in fact.$B$B<Fizzle taps his foot impatiently.>', 25996), -- Two If By Boat
(28395, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n!  I will make sure that your deeds are known amongst my kind.$B$BRemember to bring any of the feathers you find to me.  I will continue to accept them as long as necessary.', 25996), -- Feathers for Nafien
(28392, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The druids of Talonbranch Glade have assisted us before. We are still unused to \"friendly\" worgen in these woods, but our people are also familiar with the sorrows of curses and corruption...$B$BSorrows that I hope you can aid us in, $c.', 25996), -- The Timbermaw Tribe
(28389, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let the goblins and all the Horde know we will not have offers of peace and sanctuary abused... most of all not in our new home.$B$BI am grateful my people have found allies as bold as you, $n. This reward will represent your bond with our pack. You will always be welcome here.', 25996), -- Report to the Denmother
(28388, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Serves every last one of them right. Let\'s hope those in charge send the rest of their greedy scavengers somewhere else.', 25996), -- Bloody Wages
(28387, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at them run... the live ones, that is. Glorious.', 25996), -- Burnout
(28396, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n!  I will make sure that your deeds are known amongst my kind.$B$BRemember to bring any of the feathers you find to me.  I will continue to accept them as long as necessary.', 25996), -- Feathers for Grazle
(27291, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Captain Vimes smiles slightly as you relate the events you witnessed at the Hyal family grave.>$B$BIt\'s good to know that they understand. You didn\'t tell them about James, did you?$B$BI\'ll deliver his wife\'s message to him, but I doubt he\'ll understand.', 25996), -- Peace at Last
(27430, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The captain listens to your report intently.>$B$BWe have avenged James and his family, but not even that can restore what was destroyed.', 25996), -- Justice for the Hyals
(27429, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope the Grimtotems got the message. Any attempt to return will be met with far worse than a mere torch. My apprentices and I will see to that.', 25996), -- Raze Direhorn Post!
(27428, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you want me to scry for Grimtotems, eh? And what will you say when I tell you there\'s no need?', 25996), -- Tabetha's Assistance
(27245, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The freed captives have already begun returning from Blackhoof Village. The information the captain is receiving from the prisoners will give us an advantage in our next battle against the Grimtotems.$B$BYou have my thanks and that of the men. ', 25996), -- Prisoners of the Grimtotems
(27243, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The sergeant doesn\'t bother to hide his grin.>$B$BGood. That ought to forestall a raid or two.', 25996), -- Unleash the Raptors
(27242, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look a little scratched up, but nothing major. You\'re certainly in a lot better shape than the Grimtotems will be when our new raptor friends get done with them.', 25996), -- Raptor Captor
(27427, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Captain Darill inspects the armaments you\'ve brought from Blackhoof Village.>$B$BThere\'s no doubt about it. These match the description exactly, but there\'s just one problem -- these have never been used in battle. Blackhoof Village must not be the only Grimtotem post in the marsh.', 25996), -- Arms of the Grimtotems
(27426, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Captain Darill glances at the battle plan.>$B$BI\'d say it doesn\'t get any clearer than this. They\'ve taken it upon themselves to fight back against human settlements in the area and I have little doubt Theramore is next on their list.', 25996), -- Confirming the Suspicion
(27425, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Captain Vimes thinks the Grimtotems are behind the destruction of the Shady Rest Inn? They wouldn\'t have been first on my list of suspects, but if Captain Vimes sent you here to follow up on a lead, he must have his reasons. Regardless, the Grimtotems have been a thorn in our side for some time and we\'re always glad to have the extra help.', 25996), -- A Grim Connection
(27288, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will send Lieutenant Caldwell to deal with the deserters at Lost Point. In addition, I will instruct him to find Reethe. The marsh is not so big and trackless that he should be unable to find him.', 25996), -- The Deserters
(27287, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did Vimes send you? Couldn\'t do his dirty work himself, could he...', 25996), -- The Deserters
(27285, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s not much information to work on, but we\'ll have to keep it in mind. Hopefully some of the other pieces of this mystery will fall into place, and paint a more helpful picture of what happened.', 25996), -- The Black Shield
(27284, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hm... interesting piece of iron you have here. Definitely not made by any of the blacksmiths I know over on this side of the sea, and it\'s certainly not my work.', 25996), -- The Black Shield
(27286, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Missing? That would be Tesoran\'s kind way of saying traitor.$b$bNo doubt he\'s one of those fools so blindly loyal to Admiral Daelin that he turned traitor.  Isn\'t that a delicious irony? The deserters accuse us of betraying the Alliance.', 25996), -- Daelin's Men
(27264, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, $n. You\'d like information about a specific member of the Theramore guard? Reethe, was it?$b$bJust give me a moment to find the right book.', 25996), -- Lieutenant Paval Reethe
(27263, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s never good news when a guard\'s badge is brought to me.$b$bSometimes it\'s a man or woman who\'s fallen in battle, and I\'m left to bring the news to the grieving family. Other times we never find out what happened to them. And other times it\'s even worse than that.', 25996), -- Lieutenant Paval Reethe
(27252, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hm, I\'m no expert with the construction of arms and armor. Their use, yes, but not their making.$b$bThis shield seems as ordinary as any, excepting the damage from the fire that engulfed the inn.', 25996), -- The Black Shield
(27262, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hoofprints, eh? It is true that there is an extraordinary amount of centaur activity in the lands near the Dustwallow Marsh. In brief excursions into the Barrens, we found their camps and holdings dotting the area.$b$bI\'ll send out Falgran Hastil, one of our trackers, to see if he can find where the tracks lead.', 25996), -- Suspicious Hoofprints
(27249, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see that Captain Vimes is finally assigning others to this investigation.$B$BI\'ve used a reflective powder to dust the area. It will reveal suspicious objects and markings, helping you to focus your efforts. Look over anything the dust illuminates.', 25996), -- Inspecting the Ruins
(27248, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Theramore is interested in doing business? Well, that\'s not an offer I\'d turn down. Supplies are pretty scarce here right now, so we need all the business contacts we can get!', 25996), -- Mission to Mudsprocket
(27247, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A report from an orc spy!  How did you find this?  No matter -- let\'s see what it says...', 25996), -- Captain Vimes
(27246, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hm... I can\'t read orcish very well, but this looks like a report... written by an orc spy!', 25996), -- The Orc Report
(27215, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Get off my lawn... unless, that is, you want to help old \"Swamp Eye\" with a little bit of cooking. Whad\'ya say?', 25996), -- The Hermit of Swamplight Manor
(27241, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have no doubt that the king meant every word when he told you he plans to destroy the Defias once and for all. He does not make promises lightly, and the enemies of Stormwind should know it.', 25996), -- Return to Jaina
(27240, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it was the Defias who served as the hands of Onyxia in this plot?$B$B<The king\'s face grows red with anger and his hands clench into fists.>$B$BYou and Lady Jaina have done Stormwind a great service this day. The traitors will not live long enough to regret their crimes.', 25996), -- Proof of Treachery
(27239, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lady Jaina listens intently as you report the results of your aerial survey.>$B$BA rune circle, dragonkin? The Defias have allied themselves with HER? The traitor?$B$B<Lady Jaina composes herself and prepares to explain.>', 25996), -- Survey Alcaz Island
(27238, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You and Renn have done excellent work in bringing this information to light and reporting it immediately. Now, we must confirm your findings. The implications are too great if we are wrong.', 25996), -- Jaina Must Know
(27237, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Renn rifles through the contents of the strongboxes you recovered.>$B$BGood work. Now, let\'s see if our \'precious cargo\' is in here....', 25996), -- Recover the Cargo!
(27236, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, this is in worse shape than I\'d thought, and these tools...$B$BWell, I said I\'d get this back into working condition for you, so I\'d better get to work.', 25996), -- Secondhand Diving Gear
(27235, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Renn looks over the orders.>$B$BSo there was valuable cargo on board! We have to locate it before the Defias recover it. These guys are no divers, but we\'re going to need some of their gear if you\'re to help me find the cargo.', 25996), -- Renn McGill
(27234, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Captain Wymor accepts the orders from you and reads over them.>$B$BWhat in the world could \'precious cargo\' refer to? The Defias have done some small time smuggling back in Stormwind, but this seems out of their league. The language of these orders suggests a wealthy or noble patron.', 25996), -- Defias in Dustwallow?
(27214, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The captain makes no effort to hide that he\'s assessing your abilities.>$B$BSo you\'ve heard about the recent shipwreck off the coast? Good, I could use some help confirming my suspicions about the survivors. Welcome aboard, $n.', 25996), -- A Disturbing Development
(27213, 2, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gavis\' request isn\'t as outlandish as it might sound. With the proper handling, Lady Jaina can return the deserters to the fold, but that is her decision, of course.$B$BIt\'s been a pleasure working with you, $n. Without your help, I doubt the operation would\'ve gone so smoothly. When I make my report in Stormwind, it will name you as the $c who ended the deserter threat.', 25996), -- The End of the Deserters
(27212, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Calia chuckles as you describe the guards\' reactions to the propaganda.>$B$BJust as I\'d hoped! I think it\'s safe to say any deserter agents who try to infiltrate Theramore will be laughed right out of town!', 25996), -- Discrediting the Deserters
(27222, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n! I\'ll admit, when I caught my first glimpse of that beast, I had doubts about our ability to defend the docks, but you held together the defenders brilliantly!', 25996), -- Take Down Tethyr!
(27221, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You recount your experiences with Nat Pagle, carefully omitting the portion about the \'bait test.\'>$B$BWell, it sounds like we\'ve got our work cut out for us. I\'ll make the preparations.', 25996), -- Oh, It's Real
(27220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad at all, but you know, I think I\'d get a bath in as soon as possible, if I was you.$B$BNow, about your sea monster...$B$BHelp yourself to a brew or two in the meantime.', 25996), -- Nat's Bargain
(27219, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you want to know about sea monsters? Hmm... well, I\'ll make you a deal, but it\'s going to involve a lot of alcohol and some embarrassment on your part.', 25996), -- Is it Real?
(27211, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The SI:7 agent nods in approval.>$B$BExcellent. All that remains is to discredit the deserters so that they\'ll never gain a foothold in Theramore again, and I have just the plan to do it.', 25996), -- Propaganda War
(27218, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, now, that was thoughtful o\' Babs to send that over. I don\'t know if you\'ve leafed through it or not, but there\'s a lot of truth to the tales in that book. Sailors didn\'t just make it all up, you know.', 25996), -- Dastardly Denizens of the Deep
(27217, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, I have my doubts, but this is the only solution available right now. Once we have it up and running, I\'m sure there will be time to look at other ways to fuel the lamp.', 25996), -- Thresher Oil
(27216, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. I can use all the help you can offer. My first priority is to get that lamp re-lit.', 25996), -- This Old Lighthouse
(27210, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. I think we managed to catch them off guard. Their agents probably thought themselves safe within the city walls.$B$BGiven time, the agitators will return and spread their lies again. We\'ll use the time you\'ve bought to shut out the deserters further.', 25996), -- Traitors Among Us
(28552, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Deserters from the city guards are spreading discontent in the ranks. We have to get to the bottom of this before it undermines our defenses.', 25996), -- Hero's Call: Dustwallow Marsh!
(44560, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aha! With this we can start on an antidote for this awful mixture. Thank you for bringing this to me.', 25996), -- Follow the Recipe
(44558, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job, kid. You deserve a little somethin\'. And hey, come back tomorrow if you get the time; I might have a job for ya.', 25996), -- Crushing the Crown
(28756, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your deeds do honor to those who fell in battle defending this hallowed ground.', 25996), -- Aberrations of Bone
(32675, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, good to see you. You look like you are ready to take to the skies!\n\nRemember, you can buy a flying mount from Tannec Stonebeak over there.', 25996), -- I Believe You Can Fly
(24597, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My thanks for this Lovely Charm Bracelet.', 25996), -- A Gift for the King of Stormwind
(31447, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Behold my true form.$B$BI owe you a debt, one which I can never repay. But, I thank you for lifting the curse off of my family.$B$BKel\'Thuzad, the Lich King, and now Darkmaster Gandling -- all are dead.$B$BPerhaps now I too can find some semblance of peace.', 25996), -- An End to the Suffering
(31440, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.$B$BWith the destruction of the tomes I\'ll go to my final rest knowing that those books will never again haunt a living soul.', 25996), -- The Four Tomes
(27125, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes! I can see that you were indeed successful. You have received your tribute, the Gordok advance will exist no longer, and the Gordok are blissfully ignorant! This is a true winner\'s scenario, $n.', 25996), -- King of the Gordok
(27118, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A large, broken trap lies before you.  From the looks of it, the ogres have tried to repair the trap but to no avail.$B$BA hastily written note lies next to the trap, and strangely enough it details exactly how to repair it: just a few simple adjustments ought to do it.  Were the trap repaired, an ogre passing near it might get trapped, and could be avoided.$B$BClearly, it would seem fortuitous that very few ogres know how to read.$B$BClearly.', 25996), -- A Broken Trap
(27105, 1, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is very troublesome that a water elemental was here, let alone one that powerful. Take this as my thanks for your efforts. I must examine this essence for any knowledge it may contain.', 25996), -- An Unwelcome Guest
(27104, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, very well done indeed. You\'ve made an old spirit very happy this day. You deserve proper thanks for the risks you\'ve taken.', 25996), -- Alzzin the Wildshaper
(27107, 1, 1, 2, 0, 500, 1000, 1500, 0, 'Now you watch Master use book to kill stupid trees and stupid goat men! YAR!', 25996); -- Pusillin The Thief
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(39199, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming. We could use more able bodies.', 26124), -- Hero's Call: Blade's Edge Mountains
(39181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Cenarion Refuge, $n.  I hope you\'ve come to aid us in our mission.  We\'ve much work ahead of us.', 26124), -- Hero's Call: Zangarmarsh
(39197, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are welcome here in Telaar.', 26124), -- Hero's Call: Nagrand
(39188, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad that Stonebreaker Hold sent you.  The druids of the thicket have been slain!  Only myself and one other have survived, and he\'s insane.$B$BI don\'t know what happened, but I intend to get to the bottom of it.  Whatever it was, it happened quickly and feels unnatural.$B$BWill you help me?', 26124), -- Hero's Call: Terokkar Forest
(27446, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings and salutations, friend. Welcome to Tanaris!', 26124), -- Tanaris is Calling
(13429, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Xi\'ri pulses with energy as you feel an object materialize in your hands.  It is the medallion you gave to A\'dal on Akama\'s behalf, its power augmented by the naaru\'s magic.  The Sha\'tar have entrusted you with the Medallion of Karabor, and with it access to the Black Temple.>', 26124), -- A Distraction for Akama
(29644, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'I cringe to think what would have happened had Murmur escaped to the outside world.$B$BThank you, brave hero.', 26124), -- Into the Heart of the Labyrinth
(29645, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It won\'t bring anyone back, but at least justice has been done.', 26124), -- Ambassador Hellmaw
(29641, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, these are the soul devices that the Shadow Council were using to enhance their summoning power?  Intriguing.', 26124), -- The Soul Devices
(29643, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Opening the magically-suspended tome, a sense of dread overwhelms you.$B$BSomething is most definitely wrong here!', 26124), -- The Codex of Blood
(29640, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you think you could help me get out of this cage?  It\'s a bit cramped.', 26124), -- Find Spy To'gun
(29659, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. Any advantage we can take away from Kael\'thas\' forces is to our benefit.', 26124), -- Lost Treasure
(29681, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. Your actions this day have prevented countless tragedies.', 26124), -- Maximum Security Breakout
(29675, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Legion seeks only to consume. They hold no regard for the balance.', 26124), -- Hey There Dalliah
(29674, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Creatures of the void are naturally chaotic. They are a necessary part of the universe, but they must be kept in check by the Light.', 26124), -- Unbound Darkness
(29658, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my gratitude, $n.', 26124), -- The Calculator
(29657, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $n. But more work remains to be done.', 26124), -- With Great Power, Comes Great Responsibility
(49550, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re gettin\' hammered out here, $Glad:lass;.$B$BI hope you\'re here to help.', 26124), -- Hero's Call: Shadowmoon Valley!
(28263, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see you again, $n. Stormwind has need of your skills.', 26124), -- Meet with Maginor Dumas
(37445, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me take a look at those.$B$BYes, I think that these will do nicely; good job, $n. The emitter is rather complex so it may take some time to finish the repairs. I\'ll let you know when it\'s ready.$b$bIn the meantime, you might see if Vindicator Aldar has anything he could use you for.', 26124), -- Spare Parts
(37444, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With many of the owlkin now inoculated, we can focus on getting out of here and not have to worry about wiping out the owlkin population in the area.$B$BHere, choose from these.  You\'ve done good work, and you deserve to be rewarded!', 26124), -- Inoculation
(24911, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Hey Hol\'anyee, look at the getup on this one!$b$b<Williden turns to face you.>$b$bAhem.  Our recruiter sent you?  Good.  Let\'s start out with a bit of honesty: Un\'Goro isn\'t the perfect nirvana that you may have been promised.  You\'ve probably figured that out on the way over here, though.$b$bShall we get to work?', 26124), -- Tropical Paradise Beckons
(25513, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic. I might challenge you to a duel myself someday.', 26124), -- Thunderdrome: Grudge Match!
(25421, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is amazing. These hieroglyphs are undoubtedly titan, but the markings below it...$B$BIf I had to hope, this is the same passage written over and over again in an entire assortment of ancient languages. We might be able to use this to decipher the hieroglyphs! If the antechamber was covered in them as you say, who knows what else we\'ll learn.$B$BI\'d like to grant you a fine reward, $n. We\'ve made the find of the century!', 26124), -- The Grand Tablet
(25566, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This chest lies undisturbed, sealed for thousands of years.', 26124), -- The Secrets of Uldum
(25565, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Would you take a look at these...not troll, not qiraji, just pure mystery waiting to be unlocked.$B$BThese aren\'t going anywhere now that they\'re safely in our hands. It\'s time to make our way into the ruins!', 26124), -- Fragments of Language
(25559, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll teach the Horde twofold! Don\'t mess with dwarven history, and don\'t send a bunch of frail couch-dwellers to do your fighting!', 26124), -- Laying Claim
(25420, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $c. We\'re that much closer to the secrets of Uldum.', 26124), -- Ancient Obstacles
(28881, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What, you here to help?', 26124), -- Prospector Gunstan
(25065, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. The contents of this chest are sure to advance Gnomeregan\'s knowledge base significantly. I believe you\'ve earned a reward.', 26124), -- You Too, Brute?
(25063, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, gosh, this day just keeps getting better and better! I may actually smile.$B$BWhen you\'re not looking. You\'ve seen enough of that already.', 26124), -- Terrapination
(25062, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kelsey takes the journal and gingerly flips through it.>$B$BI\'m trying not to laugh. This is classic. They have no idea they\'re even on Kalimdor!$B$BThese later pages though...something more significant may be occuring here.', 26124), -- What We Came For
(25060, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your reports of their behavior are truly disturbing...but also slightly amusing.$B$BIf only that Dreadshredder wench had escaped on these vessels instead...', 26124), -- Define "Crazy"
(29669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He was a noble guardian in life. His presence will be missed.', 26124), -- A Most Somber Task
(29667, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well thus far, $n. However, there is still one more task I must ask that you complete.', 26124), -- Culling the Herd
(29660, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They were going to die to the creatures contained here soon even without our interference. It is for the greater good.', 26124), -- Saving the Botanica
(39202, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey there. Looking for work? Perfect!', 26124), -- Hero's Call: Netherstorm
(49864, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Having made your decision, you can now set off in search of bigger adventures in far-off lands.>', 26124); -- Wars on Two Fronts
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(39204, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been expecting you, $c. We have much work to do, you and I.', 26365), -- Hero's Call: Dragonblight
(28709, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The expedition needs your help, $c.', 26365), -- Hero's Call: Northrend!
(29654, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have struck a major blow against the enemy with your help.$B$BHonor Hold is far safer than it\'s been in years.', 26365), -- Turning the Tide
(29656, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My superiors will be very pleased to see this. Thank you.', 26365), -- O'mrogg's Warcloth
(29649, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He was a good soldier.', 26365), -- How to Save a Life
(29652, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If only we could have saved him.', 26365), -- One Last Favor
(49551, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is it?!\n\nCan\'t you see I\'m already busy trying to get this port ready, $r?', 26365); -- Hero's Call: Howling Fjord!
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(49554, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yo! Do I have an explosive proposition for you, pal....', 26822), -- Hero's Call: Storm Peaks!
(49555, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Valiance Expedition is ready to strike at the heart of the Scourge, $c. Are you up to the challenge?', 26822), -- Hero's Call: Icecrown!
(49553, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad you\'re here, $r. Hemet has not been heard from for quite some time, and I could really use your help finding him.', 26822), -- Hero's Call: Sholazar Basin!
(49552, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Death and acts of sacrilege pervert this land.\n\n<Lantinga lets out a drawn-out sigh.>\n\nThankfully, we\'re here to stop it.', 26822), -- Hero's Call: Zul'Drak!
(39207, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Savage monsters - those Horde.$B$BPayback will come for what they\'ve done. You can count on at least that much, $c.$B$BNow, it\'s time to put you to work.', 26822); -- Hero's Call: Grizzly Hills
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(49865, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n. Thank you for responding to my request.', 26899); -- Cataclysm First Responder
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(28558, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are wonders just waiting to be discovered beyond this valley. And they will be ours!', 26972), -- Hero's Call: Uldum!
(27398, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your aid is most timely, $n.', 26972), -- The Battle Is Won, The War Goes On
(28870, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hail, $n.  Nadun spoke highly of you.$B$BAre you here to aid us?', 26972), -- Return to the Lost City
(28845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You actually came here looking for me?', 26972), -- The Vortex Pinnacle
(29201, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well done, $c. We\'ve managed to take a foothold in our enemy\'s realm without their notice. Our armies are moving through to establish a front as we speak.$B$BWe have a long, brutal war ahead of us. It is my hope that you\'ll be around to help us see it through.', 26972), -- Through the Gates of Hell
(29202, 1, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, Hamuul lives. You can visit him in the tent behind me, but please, be careful. He is in a fragile condition, and we are doing everything in our power just to keep him alive and comfortable.$b$bWhoever did this to the Arch Druid showed no mercy. I hope that you are someday able to return the favor.', 26972), -- The Fate of Runetotem
(29437, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alysra has been brought to justice, but from her mangled remains emerged something else. A creature of living flame, twisted to serve the will of the Firelord.$B$BYou suspect your paths may someday cross again.', 26972), -- The Fallen Guardian
(29200, 273, 5, 6, 0, 500, 500, 0, 0, '<Matoclaw listens intently as you explain what happened.>$b$b<She is visibly distressed.>$b$bYou deviated from our plan, $n. Our attack was supposed to happen today! All this preparation... how will we succeed without the aid of Hamuul?', 26972), -- Leyara
(29199, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. I will send for our reinforcements right away.', 26972); -- Calling for Reinforcements
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(25558, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Earthen Ring has received my distress message and sent help - just in time it would seem.$b$bHopefully more can be sent soon. We are but few against a great many.', 27101), -- All or Nothing
(25547, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No time to address the troops now.$b$bJust as well. They know what must be done.', 27101), -- On Our Own Terms
(25564, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Everything here seems to be in working order.', 27101), -- Stormwind Elite Aquatic and Land Forces
(25545, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c!$b$bThanks to you, my men will be ready to confront the enemy when they attack.', 27101), -- To Arms!
(25357, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s hope your efforts prove to be enough of a diversion...', 27101), -- Buy Us Some Time
(25546, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should help relieve our exhaustion.$b$bAgain, we thank you.', 27101), -- Traveling on Our Stomachs
(27724, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All of our war ships are off fighting the Horde. You\'ll have to take the mercenary ship.', 27101), -- Hero's Call: Vashj'ir!
(27940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve made the Cradle of the Ancients a somewhat less despicable place to travel through.', 27101); -- Dirty Birds
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(25888, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us hope for the safety of those released prisoners.$b$bIn return for your noble efforts, please accept this gift.', 27178), -- Decompression
(25885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes. This is the stuff.$b$bMaybe I can gradually eat less of it and avoid that side-effect.$b$bThank you, $n.', 27178), -- What? What? In My Gut...?
(25824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s not encouraging, but it\'s something...', 27178), -- Debriefing
(25812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A... a $r? Here?$b$bI must be mad...', 27178); -- Spelunking
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(26193, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, there you are. Erunak has gone ahead to speak with Neptulon. We must hurry!', 27219), -- Defending the Rift
(26181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello again, $c.$B$BI felt L\'ghorek die. A shame that such a magnificent being is gone.$B$BIf we do not assist Neptulon, we will all meet the same fate.', 27219), -- Back to Darkbreak Cove
(26144, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A job well done. Now you don\'t need to worry about what would have happened to them if you hadn\'t been around.$B$BThe last one was even appreciative enough to give you a reward they\'d kept hidden on their person.', 27219), -- Prisoners
(26132, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The last thing we needed was a bunch of summoned creatures swarming our forces during the final assault.', 27219), -- Fiends from the Netherworld
(26070, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good enough for me.$B$BDon\'t get too complacent, $n. The hard part\'s about to come.', 27219), -- Clearing the Defiled
(25983, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s very disturbing news, but I believe our Earthen Ring friends here have a plan.$B$BAnd now that you\'re here....', 27219), -- Promontory Point
(25987, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What happened? That thing wasn\'t completely dead! Maybe I should stick to mechanical stuff.$B$BIt gave you a vision? Of killing all of us?! That doesn\'t sound good.$B$BWell, in any case, that Earthen Ring fellow, Erunak Stonespeaker, wants these specimens all taken out to him. I\'ll make sure he gets them. I don\'t want them anywhere near me.', 27219), -- Put It On
(25981, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, they\'re ugly, but they mostly look harmless. Smelly though.$B$BHere, let me clean the gilblin stuff out of these. I\'ve got an idea....', 27219), -- Those Aren't Masks
(25975, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should be enough for now. We know where there\'s more should the need arise.', 27219), -- Treasure Reclamation
(25977, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice Uncle Bob of pokin\' their general.$B$B<The lieutenant shakes her head and grins.>', 27219), -- A Standard Day for Azrajar
(25950, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chicken and rice, $n! That will show those sorry and sad snakes who\'s the ol\' pitch and toss!$B$BNow it\'s bird lime for that tiddlywink. Finger and thumb or plink plonk?', 27219), -- Sira'kess Slaying
(26080, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see.  Yes, I am rememberink now... Humphrey and Oskar vere not the strongest svimmers.$b$bThe reconnaissance is helpful, and the extra fish look very tasty.  If you are seeink Mister Digsong before he returns, please send him my thanks.', 27219), -- One Last Favor
(26021, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oskar\'s alive?  Wait... what did ya say?  Ya let him FLOAT AWAY AGAIN?!$b$bWell... ya held up your end of the bargain, and I appreciate everything ya\'ve done, $n.$b$bHere... take this.  I\'ve only been hanging onto it as ballast, but it doesn\'t seem to be doing much good.', 27219), -- The Brothers Digsong 2: Eel-Egg-Trick Boogaloo
(26017, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya did good, $n!  Ya did real good!', 27219), -- A Lure
(26018, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Humphrey listens as you recount your fights with the Coldlight murlocs.>$b$bHmm... they sound like regular ol\' murlocs... just underwater.  That\'ll make Cap\'n Glovaal happy.', 27219), -- Coldlights Out
(26019, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whaaa... an egg?  An EEL egg?$b$b<Even upside-down, you can see the gears in Humphrey\'s head turning.>$b$bWe can definitely do something with this!  Get ready kid, \'cause it\'s time for some good ol\'-fashioned Digsong revenge!', 27219), -- Enormous Eel Egg
(26015, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Humphrey grabs the phosphora from you and attaches it to an unusual device.>$b$bThere ya go.  It\'s beautiful!  Oskar would be proud.', 27219), -- Phosphora Hunting
(26014, 18, 18, 18, 0, 0, 3000, 5000, 0, 'Of course we haven\'t returned yet!  We\'ve had our fair share of setbacks... not the least of which was the passing of my dear brother Oskar.$b$b<Humphrey sniffles loudly.>$b$bHe lost his grip and floated away, the poor lad!  He thought he\'d grab some fish to bring back to the captain, but he floated off, and was eaten by one o\' those... those great-eels!  Bwaaaah ha ha haaaah!', 27219), -- The Brothers Digsong
(26106, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you considered a career in science, $n?  If you ever get tired of this $c nonsense, come see me!  I could use an assistant with your devotion to experimentation and the scientific method.', 27219), -- Fuel-ology 101
(26103, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Engineer Hexascrub sticks a finger into each sample and sniffs it.>$b$bYes, I think this will do.', 27219), -- Bio-Fuel
(26105, 273, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did well, $n.  We need to be especially wary of Horde attacks right now.  The Pincer X2 has plenty of firepower at sea, but in the back of this cave, she is exceptionally vulnerable.', 27219), -- Claim Korthun's End
(26219, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vell done, Private $n.$B$BThe cavern is ours, but the beast escaped. Should it raise its ugly head again, ve vill make with blastink it out of the vater.', 27219), -- Full Circle
(26005, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it out! Good to see you, $n.$B$BIt\'s good to be out of the water for a bit, and to have some resources at our disposal again. I\'m sure many of the boys would give anything to turn around and head home after what we\'ve been through, but we still have a grim task ahead.$B$BWhat about you? Want to stick it through to the end with us? I wouldn\'t blame you if you\'ve had your fill.', 27219), -- A Breath of Fresh Air
(25626, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Minions of the Old God? Two very potent foes have joined forces then. Their hope to defeat the Tidehunter may not be so foolish after all.$B$B$n, we can\'t let that happen. If Azshara defeats the Tidehunter and takes his power for herself, I\'m not sure any number of us could ever hope to oppose her on the seas.$B$BThe first step is clear at least - we need to hunt down the fiend that destroyed our ships. The navy was confident enough to bring in a new fleet, perhaps they have a plan.', 27219), -- Visions of the Past: Rise from the Deep
(25911, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That is the best news I\'ve heard in what seems like an eternity. We\'ll get the survivors moving over there to the surface as soon as possible. Perhaps we can forget that this whole nightmare ever happened.$B$BThank you, $n. I\'m not sure there\'s anything I can do to repay you for everything you\'ve managed to accomplish in this ocean, but I will try to find a way.$B$BYou should consider meeting us at the ships later, when you finish saying your goodbyes to the naga.', 27219), -- Welcome News
(25898, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! There\'s no way they missed that, fighting or not.', 27219), -- Honor and Privilege
(25894, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Less gill goblins is good!$B$BI\'m glad that they\'re so primitive. I don\'t think I\'d want to be dealing with a race of aquatic tech-freaks right now. Not at all.', 27219), -- Hostile Waters
(25897, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is great! I love it. It should work per... ewww! Is this stuff braided with hair?$B$BDoesn\'t matter. Almost done. This thing will be ready in the twist of a rope.', 27219), -- Unfurling Plan
(25895, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me see, let me see... flare gun... balloon... no rope. Never any rope. Terribly impractical if you do ask me. Rope should be mandatory.', 27219), -- Come Prepared
(25893, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impeccable timing. Like clockwork! Trouble comes. You come. Save the day.  Clockwork!$B$BWe\'ve devised our brilliant plan. Gloriously simple, barring the hostility of local life. Simpler yet with a you available! ', 27219), -- Desperate Plan
(25892, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it! After the attack at the forward post, I thought we might be the only ones left. I\'m very glad to see you.', 27219), -- Losing Ground
(25755, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re finished! Just in time. I don\'t think we could have held them much longer.$B$BAn artifact? Could this be something we can use against the naga? I suppose that would require finding it.$B$BWe may have to attend to more pressing matters first, until an opportunity to pursue this further presents itself.', 27219), -- Visions of the Past: The Slaughter of Biel'aran Ridge
(25754, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Still so many? They must want something very important here to come in such numbers.$B$BI will be honest with you, $n, because you deserve at least that: I don\'t know how much hope there is. We will retreat shortly, but we won\'t be able to defend ourselves when they strike back. We don\'t have anywhere to run... we\'re running out of options.$B$BI\'m sorry, I should keep such thoughts to myself. Do me a favor and don\'t mention any of that to the men. I\'ll figure something out.', 27219), -- Gauging Success
(25753, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. Truly.$B$BWe need to get these men moving as soon as possible. I\'ll meet you back at the forward post soon, I\'m sure.', 27219), -- Fallen But Not Forgotten
(25752, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did great up there! You devastated their ranks, but there were far more than we accounted for, and most of our men went down out there in the masses of naga.$B$BWe\'ll need to hold this position as long as possible to buy them time. Hopefully some of them will still make it to the rendezvous.', 27219), -- Swift Action
(25751, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are brave indeed! I\'ve seen you battling all manner of murloc, naga, and pointy-toothed fish, but that was nothing! The way you just sling those kelp bulbs under your arm like that is a whole new kind of fearless. BOOM! You could blow up at any second.$B$BYou\'re my kind of $r.', 27219), -- Properly Inspired
(25749, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are perhaps the most dependable person I\'ve ever met. I wish I could have more men half as thorough as you.', 27219), -- Not Entirely Unprepared
(25748, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More naga are amassing to the south than reported too it seems. We shall have to move quickly then.', 27219), -- Clear Goals
(25747, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $c. I almost thought we\'d lost you to the Wavespeaker\'s fool errand.$B$BDid anything come of it?', 27219), -- Looking Forward
(25760, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A Battlemaiden? I never heard of such a thing.$B$BThe way you explain it, it sounds like the naga forces are far greater in scope than the Admiral could possibly have realized. We might be able to learn more through the blade if we can find other locations where this Battlemaiden was present, but the information you gave me makes me fear for the admiral and his soldiers. We must warn them.', 27219), -- Visions of the Past: The Invasion of Vashj'ir
(27716, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant! It will take me a while to translate, but this is precisely the kind of find I was hoping for.$B$BThere\'s no knowing if we will make it out of this place, but if it comes down to it, I will find a way to float this to the surface in hopes that it will one day be found.$B$BThank you again, $n. Here... perhaps I have something that may be of use to you.', 27219), -- Piece of the Past
(25581, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much for taking this seriously.$B$BThis is some of the first definitive proof of other members of the Vashj family. Very interesting. And I\'d never even heard of either of the other two figures you mentioned until now.$B$BSo much of our history was lost during the sundering - it\'s exciting to have a chance at reclaiming some of it.', 27219), -- An Occupation of Time
(25583, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Interesting indeed.$B$BThe remains you describe sound much like the sea vrykul we encountered in Northrend. I highly doubt we will be striking any alliances with their sort, no matter the cause. Still, this information may prove useful in the future.$B$BI will think on it further if time permits. Thank you for bringing it to my attention.', 27219), -- Upon the Scene of Battle
(25579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $c.$B$BI will get some of our own patrols out to make sure that no more naga get within sight of this cave. We should have the area secured within the hour.', 27219), -- Caught Off-Guard
(25582, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is good intel. You have a sharp eye, $c.$B$BIt sounds like the building tucked under the terrace at the far end of the ruins will make a suitable forward post. I will send some men immediately to start defensive preparations and we will reposition there as soon as possible.', 27219), -- A Better Vantage
(25580, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n, and just in time too. The Admiral just started sending more men out. Strong sword arms to be sure, but I doubt they possess quite the same awareness and finesse that you do.$B$BWe were lucky to have you here when things went south. I suspect you will have a large role to play in things to come as well.', 27219), -- Swift Approach
(25540, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is wonderful. I will begin cooking them immediately. It is good to know that of our many fears, starvation shall no longer need to be one of them.$B$BI imagine the Admiral will have much work for you. Let me trouble you no further for a while.', 27219), -- Bellies Await
(25536, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for stepping up to take care of this, $c. I know there are a lot of concerns swarming us right now, but maintaining the safety of the survivors is paramount.', 27219), -- Cold Welcome
(25538, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done my odorific associate. You are both swift and assiduous, if I do say so myself. May your future travels be rampant with inspiration and opulence.', 27219), -- Odor Coater
(25539, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, indeed. This is an entirely unshameful amount of clams to have gathered. The survivors back at the cave will surely be grateful.', 27219), -- Clamming Up
(25537, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Superb! Chemicals abound!$B$BMy instantaneous chemical synthesizer is already pre-tested and prepared. Your deployment compound shall be ready in the blink of an eye!', 27219), -- Art of Attraction
(25535, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More help! Superb! We can certainly use it, I\'ll tell you that much.', 27219), -- A Powerful Need To Eat
(25922, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It appears that I owe you my life, yet again.  Thank the Light that you found me before you and your shaman activated those bio-defenses.', 27219), -- Waking the Beast
(25921, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'No need to bring me up to speed... Nespirah has been narrating your adventures as they happened, and Captain Taylor filled me in on the rest.$b$b<Duarn closes his eyes and nods.>$b$bNespirah says that she is quite grateful, and that she has a small surprise ready for the naga.', 27219), -- Overseer Idra'kess
(25919, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully we made some progress.  I\'m not sure how we\'ll know when the creature wakes up, but something tells me that it will be pretty obvious when it does.', 27219), -- Body Blows
(25918, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, '<Admiral Dvorek admires the polearms you present him.>$b$bOh, I\'m sorry.  I was just imagining what these will look like with little bits of naga stuck to the ends of them.  Thank you, $n.  We\'ll put these to good use.', 27219), -- Hopelessly Gearless
(25920, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant work!$b$b<Valoren tucks the pearls away beneath her armor.>$b$bNow I just need you and Captain Taylor to get me safely out of here.  I can handle the studies from there on.', 27219), -- Still Valuable
(25917, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n... is that you?', 27219), -- We Are Not Alone
(25916, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had assumed that the naga were only here for those pearls.  No, this makes much more sense.  If they had Nespirah\'s power under their control, the amount of damage the naga could do would be catastrophic!$b$bSomething must be done.', 27219), -- Breaking Through
(25909, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Duarn looks at the crab and disguises a frown.>$b$bIt doesn\'t look very impressive, does it?', 27219), -- Capture the Crab
(27687, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s not much, but it\'s all I\'ve got down here.$b$bYou\'re more than welcome to it, $c.', 27219); -- An Opened Can of Whoop Gnash
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(49557, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You seem like someone who needs some excitement in their life. Excitement... and beer!', 27326), -- Hero's Call: Valley of the Four Winds!
(30142, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Congratulations! It\'s a beautiful hatchling of your own.$B$BPlease take care of it, $n.', 27326), -- It's A...
(30140, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah yes, Elder Anli mentioned that a new student had joined our ranks. I see you have already chosen your cloud serpent egg.$B$BI will instruct you on its care. Let me see it for a moment.', 27326), -- The Rider's Journey
(30138, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You may choose only one egg to take with you.$B$BChoose carefully. There is no going back.', 27326), -- Choosing the One
(30137, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wonderful!$B$BThese eggs look...well...they look a little on the small side. Are you sure you couldn\'t find any better ones?$B$BOh well, I suppose with the current situation, we can\'t be so picky.', 27326), -- Egg Collection
(30136, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t worry. The hatchlings will be safe inside their nests.$B$BI can\'t thank you enough for arriving when you did.', 27326), -- Empty Nests
(30135, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r.$B$BI tried to stop the Slitherscale where I could, but I was no match for their numbers.$B$BYour work today will help preserve an entire generation of cloud serpents.', 27326), -- Beating the Odds
(30134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness, they finally sent someone!$B$BThings have gotten out of control!', 27326), -- Wild Things
(29755, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This age must be one of great strife to breed heroes such as you. I can only imagine what adventures must lie ahead.$B$BIt has been my great honor to have met you, $p.$B$BI will remain here to usher out the last of the spirits before crossing the tan-chao myself.$B$BStill, I am disturbed by the spirit waker\'s dying curse...$B$B\"You will not stop the thunder.\"$B$BWhat could he have meant?', 27326), -- Pei-Back
(29754, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<A simulacrum imbued with the ancient and powerful spirit of Pei-Zhi would make a horrifying weapon for the mogu. Shan Jitong must be stopped!>', 27326), -- To Bridge Earth and Sky
(29756, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. These mushrooms may not seem like much of an offering, but the sentiment alone will be enough to draw the spirits to us.$B$BAlso, they make a pretty fine stir-fry.', 27326), -- A Humble Offering
(29753, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their bodies had long since returned to the land - their spirits can now follow.', 27326), -- Back to Nature
(29752, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. I will take them with me into the nether.', 27326), -- The Wayward Dead
(29750, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c.$B$BI can already sense the spirits within these bottles - they cry out with fear, confusion... rage.', 27326), -- Vessels of the Spirit
(29751, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. With these, I can complete the ritual to send all of the spirits here--including myself--back where they belong.', 27326), -- Ritual Artifacts
(29749, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Allow me to introduce myself: I am Pei-Zhi, Master Spiritsage under the last pandaren emperor Shaohao.$B$BAt least... I was.', 27326), -- An Urgent Plea
(29748, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The statues topple and shatter with ease; a testament to the immense weight of the spirit.>', 27326), -- Simulacrumble
(49559, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Traveling to Kun-Lai? Right this way, wanderer, right this way!', 27326), -- Hero's Call: Kun-Lai Summit!
(29922, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your deeds have sparked a long forgotten memory I have of an ancient prophecy. This deserves investigation.$b$bIn order to investigate, I need jade though. I have instructed Toya to gather as much as he can find and give it to you when he is done. Bring it to me and we will see about deciphering the ancient \"Emperor\'s Omen.\"$b$bWhile he gathers the jade, feel free to explore. You may find the people of this town are in need of a person of your caliber. ', 27326), -- In Search of Wisdom
(29901, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He did WHAT?!?!?$B$BHe\'s lucky that I haven\'t found him yet, because when I do, I just might kill him myself!$B$BWhatever he thinks he\'s doing... chasing after this Vale... it is not behavior fit for a prince!$B$BIf we didn\'t have more pressing matters at hand, I would send our entire fleet chasing after his heels!', 27326), -- Anduin's Decision
(29898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The healing waters should abate Ren\'s fever for a short while, but alas, I fear it is no permanent cure.$B$BThank you, $c. We have granted him a little more time, at least.', 27326), -- Sacred Waters
(29899, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you... friend. I am... happy... knowing... the spirits... are at peace.', 27326), -- Rest in Peace
(29900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh... it is the poem! Did you... read it? What did you learn about the Vale?', 27326), -- An Ancient Legend
(29890, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How did you find me?$B$B<Anduin listens to you describe the vision from the Dream Brew.>$B$BRemarkable! That\'s exactly what happened several days ago. We\'ve been laying low since then.', 27326), -- Finding Your Center
(29893, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful color, rare transparency, shimmer but not sparkle...these will do quite well.$B$BI am beginning to see great potential in you, strange one.', 27326), -- Hue
(29892, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you have crocolisks where you are from?', 27326), -- Body
(29891, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is an amazing specimen! I am quite shocked that you have succeeded, actually.', 27326), -- Potency
(49556, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our role is of utmost importance, $n.\n\nAdmiral Taylor and his flagship have gone missing.... More importantly, the young Prince was with him, and it is our primary objective to bring him back home safely.', 27326), -- Hero's Call: Jade Forest!
(27787, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $g lad : lass;! You beat that damned gronn and sent Cho\'gall packing into the Twilight Bastion.$B$BDon\'t you worry. With your help and that of your friends, we\'ll get in there and we\'ll kill Cho\'gall once and for all!', 27326), -- Skullcrusher the Mountain
(27784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Hammer of Twilight floats in the middle of the altar, unprotected....', 27326), -- The Hammer of Twilight
(27782, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you\'re back. We know where Cho\'gall\'s ultimate weapon is located!', 27326), -- Mathias Needs You
(27720, 5, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh no! My weapons and totems!$B$BThey\'re destroyed!!!', 27326), -- Mr. Goldmine's Wild Ride
(27711, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, glad you\'re back! Have I got something fun for us to do!', 27326), -- Back to the Elementium Depths
(27719, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Hammer of Twilight? And you say you got this information out of a drowned Wildhammer dwarf?$B$BYou\'re kidding, right?', 27326), -- Water of Life
(27702, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our efforts to improve relations with the red dragons has really paid off, $n.', 27326), -- Coup de Grace
(27700, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Isn\'t she a beauty?$B$BLet\'s see what she does now that she\'s free.', 27326), -- Dragon, Unchained
(27695, 273, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That thing looks sharp. Sharp enough to do the deed, at least.$B$BBut if I\'m a judge of weaponry, that\'s not what Cho\'gall\'s after.', 27326), -- The Elementium Axe
(27688, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That takes care of most of their leaders outside of the Bastion of Twilight.$B$BWe work well together, $n.', 27326), -- Distract Them for Me
(27657, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n! I\'m glad you\'re here.$B$BOf course, I\'m more than happy to lend you whatever assistance that I can.', 27326), -- Help from the Earthcaller
(27654, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'None of us are too good to get our hands a little dirty. Or bloody, in this case.', 27326), -- Bring the Hammer Down
(27652, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m not sure what I\'m going to do with all of these. I\'ll probably fence them and donate the proceeds to the Stormwind orphanage.$B$BNow to find someone sick enough to buy such a thing. It\'ll probably be a goblin. Or, a gnome warlock.', 27326), -- Dark Assassins
(27636, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where are the rest of my people?', 27326), -- Just You and Mathias
(27502, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh no!', 27326), -- Up to the Citadel
(27500, 1, 273, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The paladin frowns.>$B$BThat\'s quite a gruesome trophy collection you have there. I would have believed you if you had simply said they were dead. Regardless, thank you for having the foresight to take care of them.$B$BThe Twilight Gate will soon be ours. Time to move up to the Twilight Citadel.', 27326), -- Four Heads are Better than None
(27498, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The horns have been sounded. Victor\'s Point should launch their attack at any moment.$B$BNow there\'s only one thing left to take care of.', 27326), -- Signal the Attack
(27494, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Success!', 27326), -- Move the Mountain
(27490, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That must have been deadly.$B$BWhile I don\'t approve of their methods, no one can question the effectiveness of Master Mathias Shaw and his SI:7. Not to mention that you\'re here. Our victory is all but assured.', 27326), -- SI:7 Drop
(27496, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, our cannoneers hit their marks. Tell me about the situation within the Twilight Gate.', 27326), -- Call in the Artillery
(27492, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the spirit, $g lad : lass;! Today\'s already shaping up to be a good one.', 27326), -- Ogres & Ettins
(28248, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $n. We\'re in the process of preparing the attack now.', 27326), -- Victors' Point
(28109, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The gate is clear. Once your people finish clearing the canyon, we will speak to your leaders about the next move.', 27326), -- Pressing Forward
(28107, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We make it look easy.', 27326), -- Paving the Way
(28108, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Like a well-oiled machine.', 27326), -- If The Key Fits
(28104, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good going.$B$BDoesn\'t look like much, does it?', 27326), -- Precious Goods
(28103, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Now we can start pushing our ground forces up towards Grim Batol.', 27326), -- Easy Pickings
(28101, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The red dragons have agreed to help! No small feat, I\'m sure. You have the thanks of the Alliance.$B$BWe\'d already laid out plans for our ambush on a Twilight caravan by the time the dragons contacted us. They\'re helping by cutting off their retreat.$B$BThe battle still rages. You can definitely be of aid.', 27326), -- Mathias' Command
(27485, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad Lira didn\'t scare you off. I won\'t say her concerns aren\'t warranted, but we have a common enemy. She is perhaps a bit overzealous.', 27326), -- Warm Welcome
(27374, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $Gbrotha:sista;. You\'ve chosen a harsh time to be joinin\' us, but that is to our fortune. We could use ya help.', 27326), -- The Maw of Madness
(28655, 4, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $n! Fighting that ... thing side-by-side really brought all the Wildhammers together. The heads of the families are more united than I\'ve ever seen them. Drink up, $n, and celebrate!!$B$BOf course, our work is only beginning. I\'ll rally our new Wildhammer reinforcements with the rest of the Alliance and prepare to storm the Twilight Bastion.$B$BI\'m sure we\'ll meet again soon. ', 27326), -- Wild, Wild, Wildhammer Wedding
(28411, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lookat that! You\'re practically bent double under the weight of all that meat. I\'d better get my people cooking.', 27326), -- Something Stewed
(28410, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, aye! Kilts for the gents, gowns for the bridesmaids.$B$BJust don\'t tell the ladies they\'re wearing clothes fit for a blimp.', 27326), -- Something Stolen
(28409, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, Russell the Bard is always raving about Thundermar Lager. I guess it doesn\'t have the kick of a good Wildhammer brew, but he goes on and on about the \"body\" or \"flavor.\" I guess we\'ll find out, eh?', 27326), -- Something Brewed
(28408, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you work fast. Bold feathers for a bold woman. Well done!', 27326), -- Something Bold
(28413, 6, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s catchy, that\'s for sure.$B$BBut is it a classic?', 27326), -- Words and Music By...
(28407, 15, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Fanny throws her arms up, exasperated.>$B$BYou, Kurdran, Firebeard, and now my brother - everyone\'s got wedding fever!$B$BFine, fine, I\'ll marry Keegan Firebeard. But only \'cuz he\'s strong and handsome, with a jaw that can cut gravel and an arse like an anvil. Not for any political reasons.$B$BWe\'re going to need your help, though. We got a whole lotta wedding to put together, and not a lot of time to do it.', 27326), -- The Bachelorette
(28379, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Har! My men could learn a lot by watching you work. Well done.', 27326), -- Ogre Bashin'
(28378, 4, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fanny is safe! I hear Firebeard was in there with you? Nice to hear he\'s finally pulling his weight.$B$BWait, why are you looking at me like that, $n? Do you know something I don\'t? ', 27326), -- Find Fanny
(28377, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to have you fighting at my side again, $n!$B$BAnd I see the Firebeards have come as well. I suppose they\'ll provide a distraction while me and my boys do the heavy lifting.', 27326), -- Rescue at Glopgut's Hollow
(28346, 6, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? Kurdran\'s talkin\' marriage!? Didn\'t he just see me an\' ol\' Thunderface tearing each other new ones?$B$BThe only eligible Thundermar is Fanny. Now, I\'ll give you this, she\'s got the looks allright. All lumpy in the right places, if you hear me. But she\'s not got that somethun\' somethun\' a Firebeard looks for in a woman, right?', 27326), -- The Bachelor
(28294, 3, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, $c! Keegan Firebeard here has told me all about your heroics down south. Thank you for all of your efforts on behalf of the Wildhammer.$B$BI see Colin Thundermar is right behind you. The summit is ready to begin! Please stay and let\'s see how things unfold...', 27326), -- The Kirthaven Summit
(28282, 4, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $n! Narkrall Rakeclaw lies dead at my feet, and Thundermar has weathered a storm of drakes!$B$BThis wouldn\'t have been possible if it weren\'t for the help of the Alliance. I owe you a debt that I don\'t think can ever be repaid.', 27326), -- Narkrall, The Drake-Tamer
(28244, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did you see, $n? Cho\'gall? Wait - he saw YOU!?$B$BOh aye, that wee sneaky eye! It looks both ways. That cheeky looker! Where\'s me hammer!?', 27326), -- Eye Spy
(28281, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You sure know your way around a battlefield, $c. It looks like they\'re about to fall back.$B$BAll we need is one decisive blow...', 27326), -- Last Stand at Thundermar
(28280, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $n! Alliance ingenuity to the rescue.$B$BOf course, I don\'t have anything to help you fight the dismounted riders now that they\'re on the ground. You\'re a $c; improvise!', 27326), -- Tear Them From the Sky!
(28243, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found one? A gen-u-ine Eye of Twilight? Lemme see.$B$BOh Gods. It\'s lookin\' at me. It\'s lookin\' right back!$B$BI need a drink. Can you face that thing toward the wall or somethin\'?', 27326), -- The Eyes Have It
(28215, 4, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Terrific! These coils will decompress with the force of a thousand suns!$B$BThat\'s just a rough approximation of course, don\'t hold me accountable for those numbers.', 27326), -- Potential Energy
(28212, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelous! I\'ll smelt this down into a delicious soup. An angry soup. Of molten metal.', 27326), -- Hot Stuff
(28211, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at that - OW! Pointy! Hot!$B$BThese spears should cut through that dragonhide like an electric cheese-slicing apparatus through butter.', 27326), -- Tempered in Elemental Flame
(28216, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, that\'s him. Can you believe this thing was human once?$B$BThat\'s the Twilight\'s Hammer for you. What they don\'t destroy, they corrupt.$B$BThank you, $c.', 27326), -- Magmalord Falthazar
(28242, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Eye glimmers darkly, colors swirling about its dusky surface.>$B$BAh, the succulent thrill of life extinguished. Do you feel it, $c? Do you relish it as I do?$B$BNo, I see not. You fight to protect the lives of others. Pity.', 27326), -- We All Must Sacrifice
(28241, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Eye sits before you, humming ominously with dark energies.>$B$B<Without warning, the orb rotates, as if to look at you. You sense a malevolent presence, as though the orb is alive.>', 27326), -- A Vision of Twilight
(27753, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good - hardly a worm or weevil to be found!$B$BThis is a lifesaver to the folk who fled here for survival.', 27326), -- Never Leave a Dinner Behind
(27752, 273, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh aye ... we get a few of these kegs out to the boys on the front and we\'re gonna see some fireworks. Thank you, $n!', 27326), -- Fight Like a Wildhammer
(27754, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at that! That\'s quite a collection of trophies you have there.$B$BI\'ll spread the word. If a single Alliance $c can do this, imagine what the rest of your lot can accomplish!', 27326), -- Dragonmaw Takedown
(28369, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Me brother sent you? Good! I could use a $c. Can ya hold yer own in a fight?', 27326), -- My Sister, Fanny
(28001, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here here, WOT!? He calls ME a COWARD!?$B$BJust like a Firebeard, all hot air and not a lick of sense. I\'ve been bearing the brunt of a Dragonmaw invasion from the south, much of Thundermar is in ruins, and do any of the other clans stick up to help? NO! Ol\' Thundermar is on his own he is, and you\'d better believe I\'m usin\' everything in my arsenal just to stem the tide.', 27326), -- A Coward's Due
(27651, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for your help. You\'ve got a warrior\'s spirit in ya - you coulda fooled me for a Wildhammer if it weren\'t for your... well.. you know.$B$BI know Firebeard sent you to unite us. My love for that dwarf runs shallow, but you know now we\'ve got plenty of reasons to make enemies of Twilight. If you see him, tell him that when the battle starts, the Dunwald family will be there.', 27326), -- Doing It Like a Dunwald
(27649, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Woooooh! That\'s exactly what my belly needs!$B$BYou get me all the nice things.', 27326), -- A Steady Supply
(27650, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for bandin\' my brothers back together. I know they\'re tough, but they\'re even tougher when they\'re side by side, and there\'s a lot of Twilight out there.$B$BYou\'re good to put a gal\'s heart at ease.', 27326), -- Home Again
(27647, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Donnelly\'s belly! That\'s more like it. Good to not be dyin\' of the thirst again.$B$BHere, have some. Good ol\' Eoin\'s never so impolite as ta not share!', 27326), -- Anything But Water
(27642, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That many dead, eh? Not seemin\' likely that anyone outside of me brothers fought through it then. I guess I already expected as much.$B$BThanks for takin\' the time to look for me.', 27326), -- Sifting Through The Wreckage
(27641, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s what I\'m talkin\' about $glad:lass;. My kinda $r.', 27326), -- While Meeting The Family
(27646, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found\'m! You found Beak! I like you, new friend!$B$BI\'m gonna go show Keely. Keely like Beak too.', 27326), -- Finding Beak
(27643, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hi friend! I don\'t think I know you... I\'m Donnelly Dunwald.$B$BWhat\'s your name? I don\'t think I know you... Do I know you?', 27326), -- Donnelly Dunwald
(27644, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of all the buildings in all the towns to collapse, why\'d it have to be this one?!', 27326), -- Eoin Dunwald
(27648, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A thing of beauty, isn\'t it? An\' they keep comin\' back for more. Love it!$B$BI\'ll go find Keely and settle her nerves in a bit. Just one more go through the row.', 27326), -- Once More Into The Fire
(27645, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well look at ya, all geared and fancy. Keely send you to keep an eye on old Cayden, eh? Won\'t be needin\' it. I got these louts handled.$B$BHahah! They chose the wrong dwarf to be ambushin\' today! Ahahahahah!', 27326), -- Cayden Dunwald
(27640, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If it\'s Dunwalds you be lookin\' for, it\'s Dunwalds you\'ve found. A couple of\'m anyway. I can\'t find me other brothers for the life of me.', 27326), -- Dunwalds Don't Die
(27817, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s how it\'s done, $g lad:lass;!$B$BWith a real gryphon wing back together, we can take the fight to the rest of the Twilight. You\'re welcome to fly with us anytime.', 27326), -- Dropping the Hammer
(27816, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems you had some luck bringin\' riders back. Well timed too - we just pushed the elementals back, so we should have the arm room to lead an attack right away.$B$BThank you, $n. You\'re a good $r.', 27326), -- Personal Request
(27812, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya got the Mullans. Good news! They\'re worth more than their weight in a fight, and they ain\'t exactly skinny.', 27326), -- The Loyalty of Clan Mullan
(27811, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good on you. I always feel like a part of me is missing when my gryphon isn\'t nearby. I can\'t speak for Duglas or the rest of the clan, but I\'ll be ready to ride at Firebeard\'s call.', 27326), -- The Scent of Battle
(27810, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the stuff! Not half bad. You\'ve got a bit of fight in ya after all.', 27326), -- The Fighting Spirit
(27807, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Iain sent ya?$B$BYou don\'t look like a Firebeard to me. Why exactly should I be listenin\' to anything you say?', 27326), -- Clan Mullan
(27999, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a right shame. Stubborn as they were to speak to, they were just as stubborn in a fight. Would have been good to have \'em.$B$BOnce this is done, we\'ll have to send some boys out to bring them back for a proper send off.', 27326), -- The Fate of the Doyles
(27808, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems the Doyles suffered the worst of the attacking Twilight drakes.$B$BIt\'s clear that they fought to the end: not a single rider\'s footprint more than a few yards from his gryphon. It\'s doubtful there were any survivors.', 27326), -- Stubborn as a Doyle
(27815, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! Looks like their raid went mighty well then. I\'ll have to buy ol\' Forgehammer a round once we finish with this mess.', 27326), -- Somethin' for the Boys
(28234, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you!  Now turn around so I can put\'em on.', 27326), -- They Took Me Pants!
(28233, 6, 396, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Don\'t be looking!  I\'m not wearin\' me pants!', 27326), -- The Lost Brother
(27814, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yer a good $glad:lass;.  Have me thanks and a little gold for yer troubles.', 27326), -- Anything We Can Get
(27813, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s more like it. Let\'s finish gatherin\' up supplies and get back to Keegan.', 27326), -- Death Worthy of a Dragonmaw
(27809, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '\'Bout that time, eh? Help us wrap things up then.', 27326), -- Firebeard Bellows
(27806, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $r. Sent by Keegan?', 27326), -- Honorable Bearing
(27805, 275, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are very generous. Thank you.$B$BThere\'s a lot of darkness in our world these days. We appreciate the light that you\'ve brought here.', 27326), -- Small Comforts
(27804, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for your help. Every little bit makes a difference.$B$BWe\'ll keep the water going until we can push the Twilight back.', 27326), -- The Only Homes We Have
(27803, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $gboy:girl;. Good to have another capable set of hands about.', 27326), -- Welcome Relief
(27621, 6, 396, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Come to join the patrol, $glad:lass;? Glad to have ya.$B$BI need some bodies helpin\' to get our defenses under control here. Help me out and I\'ll see if I can\'t find some more prestigious work for ya.', 27326), -- Firebeard's Patrol
(27545, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ho! I knew you were a $c I could count on, $n. Use that portal anytime you need to get from Stormwind back to the Highlands.$B$BNow then, time to get to business. We need to locate and unite the lost Wildhammer clans scattered around the Highlands. Talking with Thordun here is a good start!', 27326), -- The Way is Open
(27538, 6, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh... mud. You brought me mud?$B$BWow - this stuff oozes with power! I see what Thordun was saying, now. I\'ll distribute this to all of the healers. Our wounded will be on their feet in no time!', 27326), -- The Perfect Poultice
(27537, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My word, $n. These elemental energies are so powerful, so chaotic - no wonder the Twilight\'s Hammer has chosen to build their stronghold here!$B$BI should be able to channel these energies into something more benign and productive though. Let\'s give it a try...', 27326), -- Any Portal in a Storm
(27516, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n! Aiding that downed gryphon-rider has given us our first contact with the old Wildhammer clans. We\'ll be able to find out who\'s still left, and in what numbers.$B$BOur campaign is looking up!', 27326), -- Wings Over Highbank
(27515, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, that\'s the stuff all right! Hope ya didn\'t eat any. Gives you the cramps something awful but it does wonders for birds.', 27326), -- Roots'll Do 'Er
(27514, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aw dang crap it all. You\'re just an Alliance $c. I was hoping for a rescue.', 27326), -- Bird Down! Bird Down!
(27468, 274, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yep, one more tank limpin\' back home for repairs.$B$BAll these trees an\' stumps an\' mud an\' rock - you couldnae drive a golfball into this turf, much less a tank.$B$BWe\'re gonna need a new approach.', 27326), -- Siege Tank Rescue
(27433, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh aye, tha\'s the stuff! A good engineer can make anything outta just about anything.$B$BThis here doo-jicker could recouple a busted cylinder casing... Oh! And who doesn\'t want a dongle? ...And you can fashion this jobby into a ... thing.$B$B<Flintlocke sticks one of the grease-smeared engine parts into his mouth.>$B$BYep, perfect.', 27326), -- Shredderectomy
(27366, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dead? By the dozen?$B$BIt\'s a start, $c. It\'s a start.', 27326), -- Landgrab
(27341, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the lay of the land, soldier. If you\'re having trouble fighting here on the coast, you might consider pitching in and helping us take and hold that hill.', 27326), -- Scouting the Shore
(27338, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep your head down \'fore you lose it, $c!$B$BThis is MY beach.$B$BThe Horde WANTS my beach.$B$BThey will NOT have my beach.$B$BIs the beach situation clear?', 27326), -- Our Boys on the Shore
(27177, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at all this! You were able to recover more than I thought. We can outfit a whole squad of marines with this stuff.$B$BWe have the gear. If we only had some way to bolster our numbers here in the Highlands...', 27326), -- Salvage Operation
(27178, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll send \'em packing, $n! Cho\'gall won\'t be able to count on the naga to back him up in this fight. From here on out, it\'s just us versus the Twilight\'s Hammer.$B$B<Simon pauses, his jaw tightening.>$B$B...And the Horde.', 27326), -- Naga Reinforcements
(27200, 274, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She had me under her spell, $n. I wouldn\'t have made it out of there alive if it weren\'t for you. Thank you!$B$BMaybe the rest of the Alliance fleet can finally anchor here in peace...', 27326), -- Siren's Song
(28599, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The King himself sent you? Good to hear that Stormwind is secure.$B$BI was expecting more in the way of troops, but word is that the Alliance fleet was ambushed by the Horde on the way here. They gave as good as they got, but the fleet is in shambles.$B$BIf we\'re to make any forward progress here in the Highlands, we\'re going to need the help of heroes like you.', 27326), -- Kurdran's Waitin'
(28598, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Flintlocke wipes tears from his eyes.>$B$BOh, $n. $n!$B$BThat ... were beautiful.', 27326), -- Aiming High
(28597, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aye, that\'ll do \'er.$B$B<Flintlocke stuffs some of the powder in his mouth.>$B$BOhhh, fresh. Heady. Redridge fine grain with a hint of Westfall sulphur and a mild aftertaste. Highbank gets the good stuff. ', 27326), -- Burnin' at Both Ends
(28596, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s more like it. We should be able to mop this up from here.', 27326), -- Welcome to Highbank!
(28832, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You two are the last thing I expected to see fall from the sky. Highbank is under attack!', 27326), -- Twilight Shores
(28238, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A ride to the Highlands, then? I\'ve just the thing!$B$BI\'ll make room for yeh in me seaplane. I\'ll have to ditch the cat-food I was packing, yeh know, in case we crash in the mountains and ain\'t rescued fer weeks.$B$BOn second thought, jes\' keep the cat food on yer lap, aye. ', 27326), -- Twilight Shores
(28716, 403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am pleased that you have answered my summons, $c.', 27326); -- Hero's Call: Twilight Highlands!
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(29758, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My MY now look at THIS! What a beautiful shell!$B$BYou were wise to bring this to me, my friend. It will make a fantastic serving platter.$B$BPlease, take this for your troubles.', 27356), -- Guess Whose Back
(31287, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The deed is done and a debt must be paid. Here is your reward. You have our gratitude.', 27356), -- Educating Saurok
(31286, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, our merchandise. Madam Goya will be pleased. You have the gratitude of her ladyship. ', 27356); -- Robbing Robbers of Robbers
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(30628, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Peering inside, you find...', 27366), -- The Gratitude of Stoneplow
(30627, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe it! You - a foreign-born $r - have succeeded where the Shado-Pan have failed. You\'ve succeeded where the WALL has failed.$b$bWe may hold this farming village after all.', 27366), -- The Savior of Stoneplow
(30626, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see.$b$bWell, we gave it our all. It\'s time to evacuate, save lives, and reassess our strategy, before these mantid take over the entire valley.', 27366), -- Retreat!
(30625, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They can\'t keep fighting like this forever. Those kids are downright heroic, but I don\'t want them to die as heroes.$b$bIt\'s time to throw in the towel.', 27366), -- Students No More
(30622, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My wall... I spent my life atop that wall...', 27366), -- The Swarm Begins
(30623, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It looks like the mantid are definitely under the sway of the sha... the sha of fear.$b$bPerhaps they\'re not attacking after all - perhaps they are running away from something. What could possibly be on the other side of that wall?', 27366), -- The Mantidote
(30624, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nothing makes a pandaren happier than an untapped keg. Chen\'s beer may not have improved anyone\'s fighting skills today, but it certainly improved their morale.', 27366), -- It Does You No Good In The Keg
(30360, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mantid from the south? This is not a good day.', 27366), -- Warn Stoneplow
(30672, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jay listens to your account of the day\'s events.>$b$bI see. We\'ll keep an eye on the Ungas from here. And we\'ll do our best not to fish these waters too heavily, either. No doubt we\'re part of the problem, too.$b$bUntil next time, $n.', 27366), -- Balance
(30675, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With some effort, the box creaks open. This must be what the hozen were hiding...', 27366), -- Buried Hozen Treasure
(30674, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The grateful fish swim happily toward the safety of the middle of the lagoon.$b$bWith any luck, they will be eaten by crocolisks.', 27366), -- Balance Without Violence
(30691, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nahassa\'s fevered suffering has come to an end.', 27366), -- Misery
(30671, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve brought me more meat than I could ever hope to eat.$b$bNow, I suppose I owe you a story...', 27366), -- Wisdom Has A Price
(30669, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You appear troubled, child.$b$bHow can this Lorewalker serve you? What is it that you seek?', 27366), -- The Lorewalker on the Lake
(30668, 432, 432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jay deftly weaves the planks together into a surprisingly seaworthy-looking vessel, then tosses them down into water below.>', 27366), -- Build Your Own Raft
(30667, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks, $n. You\'ve made my day. I always hate to see such a prime feather-gathering opportunity go to waste.', 27366), -- Particular Plumage
(30666, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yesterday, we were fishing happily. Today, the crocs just started... tryin\' to eat us.$b$bStrange.', 27366), -- Sudden, Unexpected Crocolisk Aggression
(30445, 18, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He... he shouldn\'t have done that! He shouldn\'t have paid for my mistake!', 27366), -- The Waters of Youth
(30359, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for avenging my daughter. I am not willing to let her stay dead however.$b$bI still have the waters of youth.', 27366), -- The Lord Reclaimer
(30357, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It has been a long time since I rolled up my sleeves and helped the needy. In my lust for immortality I forgot why I became a priest.$b$bThank you for reminding me there is good in this world worth fighting for, $p.', 27366), -- The Stoneplow Convoy
(30361, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your help, $c! I\'ve never seen anybody stand up to the mantid like that before.$b$bWell, other than the Shado-Pan, of course...', 27366), -- The Mantid
(30355, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done $p. You have removed the sword from the child\'s hands.', 27366), -- Re-Reclaim
(30356, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have bought us some much needed breathing room to lick our wounds and prepare a counter-attack.', 27366), -- Sever Their Supply Line
(30354, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are so few of us, it is a great relief to see such help.', 27366), -- No Sister Left Behind
(30363, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$p, well timed as usual. It turns out the mogu know how to use portals as well.', 27366), -- Going on the Offensive
(30169, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done us a great service today. On behalf of my people I thank you.$b$bPlease, accept this token of our gratitude.', 27366), -- Raid Leader Slovan
(30168, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not many would stop to help a village in need... especially so deep in the wilds.$b$bYou are a champion to our people, $p.', 27366), -- Thieving Raiders
(30273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have vanquished the Sha of Despair. My order can handle the remaining cleanup from here.$B$BIt seems the time has finally come to face the consequences of Shaohao\'s actions.$B$BThis conflict has been a long time coming - the arrival of your people was merely a catalyst. Now, your help will be necessary if Pandaria is to survive.', 27366), -- In the House of the Red Crane
(30271, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Honestly, I\'m a little surprised that worked.$B$BPandaria is proving to be a land where the lines between metaphor and reality are blurred.', 27366), -- Sha Can Awe
(30272, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You know something, $p? We make a pretty good team!', 27366), -- Striking the Rain
(30695, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Koro\'s metaphors can get a little tiring, but there\'s always true wisdom behind them.', 27366), -- Ahead on the Way
(30268, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. I knew you\'d be hardy enough to handle it.$B$BJudging by the sounds coming out of these refugees, I would not wish the murksweats on my worst enemy.', 27366), -- The Murksweats
(30694, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Every trap you sprang is a life saved, be it pandaren, beast, or otherwise. Nobody deserves an honorless death like that.', 27366), -- Tread Lightly
(30270, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. I only wish I could have accompanied you...$B$BThe blood on these hand-wraps is not my own, you know.', 27366), -- Blinding the Riverblades
(30269, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. We would not have made it without your help.', 27366), -- Unsafe Passage
(30178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see... And the sha have seeped out as far as the province already, have they?$B$BWell, I hate to break it to you, but the temple is also overrun with sha. Those of us who haven\'t been killed or... possessed, or whatever, are fleeing for our very lives.$B$BIf you defeated the sha at Zhu\'s Watch, I have to implore you to help us deal with them here.\n', 27366), -- Into the Wilds
(30348, 25, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wha... what happened? The water... it... it only transfers life. It will not make new life.', 27366), -- Immortality?
(30351, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s it! You pick, I punch!', 27366), -- Lotus Tea
(30347, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... you found the pools! The waters do exist!$b$bSomething is wrong though. I feel equal parts shadow and light swirling in this vial.', 27366), -- The Pools of Youth
(30349, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $p. Another few missions like that and we might have to make you an honorary sentinel.', 27366), -- Threat from Dojan
(30346, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $p. Hmm, it looks like the mogu are here to collect ancient relics and weapons from their forgotten dynasty. That is a problem we can face later though.$b$bAh! Here is a reference to the Pools of Youth.', 27366), -- Where are the Pools
(30344, 2, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh! Fabulous! Fabulous!$b$BYour one trip has advanced my research more than ten years of reading dusty tomes and decaying scrolls...$b$bAnd those \"mogu\" you saw. I have been doing some research as well as speaking to Kang on the subject.$b$bI suspect now that they were the race of the lost dynasties that my research is derived from.$b$bOf course, that also means that they are the ones who used to control the Pools of Youth.', 27366), -- The Lost Dynasty
(30384, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sunwalkers are not to be trusted. They are the most militant branch of the tauren armies within the horde.$b$BThank you for your help in this, $p. Please accept this token as a reward.', 27366), -- Blind Them!
(30350, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! With this I can make a stew potent enough to knock these waifish elves on their feet.', 27366), -- Squirmy Delight
(30274, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fabulous! Your timing was impeccable. Another day in there and I think we would have wasted away to nothing.$b$bNow we can continue our search for the Pools of Youth!', 27366), -- The Arcanic Oubliette
(29874, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pretty sure this settlement wasn\'t here a few weeks ago. Where did these people come from?', 27366), -- Kang Bramblestaff
(31262, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Now THAT is a trophy. Looks intimidating. Wait... is this your blood on it?', 27366), -- Crane Mastery: Needlebeak
(31260, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive! Can you smell the money? Here\'s your end.', 27366), -- Profit Mastery: Chasheen
(30353, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! This stuff is gonna make me a mint back in Kalimdor. Here\'s your cut.', 27366), -- Profit Mastery
(30352, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic. Only thing that would make this hunting trip more entertaining is a chair. Here is the reward I promised you.', 27366), -- Crane Mastery
(30090, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did some good work here today, $p.$B$BMonastery always tell us to leave a place better than we find it.', 27366), -- Zhu's Despair
(30089, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We saving pandaren, but the land still sad... Look, rain\'s not stopping at all!$B$B<Ken-Ken shakes his tiny fists at the sky.>$B$BHow many more butts we gotta punch before we fix this town?!$B$B<The sky darkens in response.>', 27366), -- Apply Directly to the Forehead
(30083, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. That should teach those savages to know their boundaries.', 27366), -- Securing the Province
(30084, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.$B$BZhu Province serves as a corridor from the upper tier of the valley down to the sea.$B$BKeeping the province safe requires daily efforts to maintain a border against the savage Krasarang Wilds.', 27366), -- Borderlands
(30088, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just in time! All done... look!$B$B<Ken-Ken holds up a carved wooden mask with a ridiculous face.>$B$BNow we put on finishing touches and we gots a guaranteed FUN MACHINE!', 27366), -- Why So Serious?
(30081, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pandaren got a case of the spooky-dooks!$B$BDooks get scared sometimes, don\'t wanna come out. Poor, fluffy mopey-dopes must be ready to explode by now!$B$BThis just the thing to bring \'em out. That make pandaren happy for sure!$B$BJust like ol\' gramma used to say: can\'t THROW if can\'t GO!', 27366), -- Materia Medica
(30091, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c.$B$BIt\'s time we take back our land from this curse.', 27366), -- Tears of Pandaria
(30082, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe he was actually going to do that... This despair is worse than I had even imagined.$B$BI cannot thank you enough for bringing him back.', 27366), -- Cheer Up, Yi-Mo
(30080, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me guess: my aunt sent you?', 27366), -- Finding Yi-Mo
(30079, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only one lady-panda who\'s not crazy? This worse than Ken-Ken thought...', 27366), -- What's Eating Zhu's Watch?
(49558, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What the dook is going on here, $r?!\n\nWhy are pandaren so sad?!', 27366), -- Hero's Call: Krasarang Wilds!
(30117, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally! Emmi\'s come through.$b$bI hope all is well at the Stormstout Brewery. My men don\'t do well without beer.', 27366), -- Stoneplow Thirsts
(30078, 25, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Take a look around - it\'s a lot calmer outside. All the brewery needed was somebody strong to take care of it.$b$bIt\'s going to take some time to clean this place up, but I don\'t really mind that so much.$b$bThis is, after all... my home.', 27366), -- Cleaning House
(30077, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is it with monkeys and barrels, anyway?', 27366), -- Barrels, Man
(30075, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve had just about enough of this brewery. I\'m starting to think that you and I should just bust down the wall and clean house.', 27366), -- Clear the Way
(30076, 1, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like plain ol\' water to me. It\'s hard to believe it\'s actually the corpse of a real, honest-to-goodness walkin\'-around living thing.$b$bCan\'t wait to turn it into beer and drink it.', 27366), -- The Fanciest Water
(31945, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, I\'ll be! I\'ve certainly seen larger scallions, but this will do quite nicely. You\'ve just saved our hides, $n!', 27366); -- Learn and Grow VI: Gina's Vote
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(32109, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Blue sails are barely visible on the horizon - the full might of the Alliance fleet, awaiting one final signal.>', 27377), -- Lion's Landing
(32247, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m satisfied with this site, it\'s time to bring in our fleet.', 27377), -- A King Among Men
(32246, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have impeccable timing, $c. King Wrynn is just about to land, and the full might of our fleet will follow soon after.', 27377), -- Meet the Scout
(31384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Grim times, $c. We welcome any help you have to offer.', 27377), -- The Golden Lotus
(31015, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah! Now that that is done we can start to place your collected research here. I look forward to seeing what you find.', 27377), -- Your Private Collection
(31512, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Shrine of Seven Stars.$B$BI wish I could bring you better tidings, $c, but the situation here in the Vale is quite dire.$B$BThere is much to do, but first, rest and explore the city.$B$BWelcome to the Vale.', 27377), -- A Witness to History
(31606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at you! Many parts and pieces... yes... and all of them so good at killing. Fascinating.$B$BI must pick your brain some time. Muhahah.', 27377), -- The Dissector Wakens
(31605, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<From the looks of it, this mantid was just recently broken out of his chamber. He lets out a hacking cough.>$B$B...Diss-ec...tor... has... returned...', 27377), -- The Zan'thik Dig
(31782, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are... undone, wakener.$b$bYour efforts appear to have become imperative to our cause.$b$bOn behalf of the remaining council, I implore you to continue in your assistance.', 27377), -- Overthrone
(32030, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your arrival is timely, wakener.$b$bOur ritual is underway.', 27377), -- Once in a Hundred Lifetimes
(31354, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey there!$B$BOh, I\'m fine. I\'ve had worse spills than that after a night at the Chum Bucket.$B$BBut would you look at this thing? I spotted it peeking out of the sea floor when I went under - Jiao must have dredged it up while he was thrashing around.$B$BNot really sure what to do with it, but it looks valuable. Seeing as how you pretty much saved all our hides, I think we owe you this catch.', 27377), -- Mazu's Bounty
(31190, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice shooting out there!$B$BI knew we could do it. Never met anything that can\'t be killed with enough harpoons.', 27377), -- The Mariner's Revenge
(31189, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What happened out there?! I heard a scream and next thing I know these nasty things come rolling in on the next wave!', 27377), -- Reeltime Strategy
(31184, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the charter tube, alright. I guess you\'d like to know what all the fuss is about, eh?$B$B<Soggy lets out a long sigh as he un-caps the tube.>$B$BMight as well get it over with.', 27377), -- Old Age and Treachery
(31185, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How did it go? I hope he didn\'t cause too much trouble!', 27377), -- Walking Dog
(31188, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those are perfect, just put them down over there. I\'d rather not touch them myself. Creeps me out.', 27377), -- Shark Week
(31187, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work out there!', 27377), -- On the Crab
(31186, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Dog licks his chops happily, looking satisfied.>', 27377), -- Dog Food
(31183, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'New deckhand, eh? We\'ll see about that.$B$BI run a tight ship - even if she IS at the bottom of the sea.', 27377), -- Meet the Cap'n
(31182, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should keep their little whiskers out of our traps for awhile.', 27377), -- You Otter Know
(31181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, green, not bad.', 27377), -- Fresh Pots
(31265, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ll thank me later.', 27377), -- Mazu's Breath
(31727, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 3, 0, 0, 'So the bugs have taken an interest in us have they? Well if they want somethin\' from us they\'ll have to come and earn it themselves!$b$bYou work for what you get here. That means you too!', 27377), -- Gambling Problem
(31179, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have succeeded once again. Well done, Wakener.', 27377), -- The Scent of Blood
(31178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this will do.', 27377), -- A Bloody Delight
(31177, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. This shall give me the strength to vanquish my foes.', 27377), -- Fine Dining
(31176, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, give it here! Well done, Wakener.', 27377), -- A Strange Appetite
(31175, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The hunger... they said it would be fierce, but I did not expect anything like this.$B$BIt is strange to feel so... weak.', 27377), -- Skeer the Bloodseeker
(31086, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should do it! Recipe... complete.$b$bNow let\'s see how this beer tastes.', 27377), -- Blood of Ancients
(31085, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There was a... a mantid inside that amber? I never would have thought that the solution to our war on the mantid would be... another mantid.$b$bThere are still many things that I have left to learn, but I do know this: that CERTAINLY wasn\'t a beer recipe.', 27377), -- Fires and Fears of Old
(31084, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The blade is prepared.$b$bNow, only one task remains: you must use it.', 27377), -- Bind the Glamour
(31079, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to have someone of your colossal size in our village.$b$bYou have many uses.', 27377), -- The Horror Comes A-Rising
(31080, 15, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'YEAH!!! FLITTERLING DUST!!!$b$b<Olon throws the powder into the pot.>$b$bThis brew is turning out... strange, and pretty smelly. I\'m starting to think maybe Lya was right.', 27377), -- Fiery Wings
(31081, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work. I\'ve heard the sprites talking about us.$b$bWe\'re getting their attention.', 27377), -- Incantations Fae and Primal
(31082, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, good. The motherseeds are taken care of.$b$bNow, we may speak of your enchantment.', 27377), -- Great Vessel of Salvation
(31075, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s been a while since I brewed on the road.', 27377), -- Sunset Kings
(31078, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'First Evie, now Han.$b$bI was too late again.', 27377), -- Han Stormstout
(31077, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Chen is, for the moment, silent.>', 27377), -- Evie Stormstout
(31073, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll get these pieces prepared.$b$bWe\'ve already gathered quite a few of these ingredients! I\'ll have to get a pot boiling soon.', 27377), -- Bound With Wood
(31074, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, look! The daggers - they\'ve bound together, into a forked blade.$b$bWe are on the right track. I knew this wasn\'t a beer recipe.', 27377), -- Wood and Shade
(31133, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve got the makings of a fine brewgarden guard, $r. Let me know if you ever get tired of the whole \"$c\" thing.', 27377), -- Kor'thik Aggression
(31129, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Chen listens intently.>$b$bBig Dan, Han, Evie, and Mama. I understand.$b$bIt seems like Dan will be safe here. I will go look for Evie, Han, and Mama Stormstout.$b$bTake care, $n.', 27377), -- Fate of the Stormstouts
(31072, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These daggers, look!$b$b<Lya holds the blades hilt-to-hilt.>$b$bThey were built to fit together! But how to join them...?', 27377), -- Rending Daggers
(31069, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful. This will make a fine addition to our brew.$b$bThe most dangerous ingredients are quite often the most delicious.', 27377), -- Bound With Shade
(31071, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have brought me joy, traveler.', 27377), -- I Bring Us Great Shame
(31070, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never thought of putting mushan teeth in a brew before.$b$bThat scroll\'s got some wacky ideas.', 27377), -- Daggers of the Great Ones
(31067, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re not here to hurt anybody. We just want to make a little bit of brew out of this tree sap. Is that too much to ask?', 27377), -- The Heavens Hum With War
(31068, 483, 1, 0, 0, 0, 5, 0, 0, '<Lya reads the entirety of the message.>$b$bThis scroll, this... this prophecy...$b$bIt\'s terrifying!', 27377), -- Sacred Recipe
(31730, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So they want us to leave do they? What a selfish request! We\'re only taking amber from one tree.$b$bWell, I\'m not going anywhere! I have brew to make.$b$bIf you help us maybe we can all come to a mutually beneficial agreement. I give them some brew, they stop trying to kill us.', 27377), -- A Not So Friendly Request
(31023, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These relics describe the history of Kypari Vos and the nearby amber trees.$B$BI would like to study these.$B$BThank you, $c.', 27377), -- Relics of the Swarm
(31026, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, Wakener. Kypari Zar can now dream in peace.$B$BHowever, the beast was merely a vessel for the corruption.$B$BNo... the true corruption lies much deeper.', 27377), -- The Root of the Problem
(31022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once, great rivers of amber coursed through this tree\'s veins. Now, it is but a dried husk.', 27377), -- Kypari Zar
(31021, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, Wakener. That is enough for now.', 27377), -- Living Amber
(31020, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I feel the strength returning to my body.', 27377), -- Feeding the Beast
(31019, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The whispers seem to be emanating from within this amber.$B$BCould there be another paragon sleeping within?', 27377), -- Amber Is Life
(31398, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were wise to bring this to us. This is a piece of another paragon\'s encasing amber.$b$bThe damage suggests the paragon may be in trouble.$b$bI will speak with the council to decide what should be done next.', 27377), -- Falling to Pieces
(31092, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good! I had half expected Kovok to just eat you. What a pleasant surprise to see you both in one piece.$b$bPerhaps Kunchong raising is in your blood.', 27377), -- Feed or Be Eaten
(31359, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am most impressed with your progress, Wakener. Kovok\'s training is coming along nicely and he seems to be fond of you.$b$bI have no doubt that you are the best choice to assist me in training him.', 27377), -- The Kunchong Whisperer
(31091, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kovok is just as impressive as the last time I saw him. He will ensure great victories for the Klaxxi.', 27377), -- Reunited
(31089, 64, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What... what sort of creature are you?$b$bHow have you awoken me?', 27377), -- By the Sea, Nevermore
(31090, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even this raw amber will be of use. We can\'t afford to be picky in times like these.$b$bThe Klaxxi\'va will be glad I thought of this. I will tell them you helped!', 27377), -- Better With Age
(31088, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Klaxxi are pleased with our work, outsider. You have proven to be more resourceful than we thought.', 27377), -- Crime and Punishment
(31087, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good you showed up when you did.$b$bPerhaps you are not as useless as I thought...$b$bThe Klaxxi\'va sing to the paragon now. Soon they will know where to send you. For now there are other tasks.', 27377), -- Extending Our Coverage
(31108, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What would happen, I wonder, if you ate one? What would it do to your soft, pink insides?', 27377), -- Concentrated Fear
(31689, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In disciplined hands, the spear is the perfect weapon. Only the weak would augment it with sorcery.$B$BAnd we have no need for the weak.', 27377), -- The Dreadsworn
(31107, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They are large. They will hatch soon.$B$BGood. We may need them.', 27377), -- Citizens of a New Empire
(31066, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What?! How did you...$B$BThe Deathcaller was a legendary hero. He must not have been fully wakened.$B$BYou are fortunate.', 27377), -- A Cry From Darkness
(31660, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their eggs should have basked in the warmth of the sun and the song of a million wings for ten more years.$B$BThe Empress will pay for her crimes.', 27377), -- Not Fit to Swarm
(31007, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A few less traitors for us to feed to the kunchong when the dust settles.', 27377), -- The Dread Clutches
(31010, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My slumber was interrupted by sudden dreams. Unspeakable nightmares.$B$BThen I awoke.$B$BThe Klaxxi have spoken to me. I have my orders. There is much to be done.', 27377), -- In Her Clutch
(31661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you have any idea what this is? It\'s amber!$B$BBut it is polluted with fear.$B$BI would not expect an outsider like you to understand the consequences of this.', 27377), -- A Source of Terrifying Power
(31008, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If all goes as planned, the Klaxxi will stop the Empress without your help. Still, it is my role to be prepared.', 27377), -- Amber Arms
(31009, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As the crystal buzzes to life, a harsh mantid voice permeates your mind.>', 27377), -- Dead Zone
(31006, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a sacred meeting place for the Klaxxi.$B$BIt would be wise of you to let me do the talking.', 27377), -- The Klaxxi Council
(31005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do.', 27377), -- Wakening Sickness
(31676, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have a common enemy in the mogu. And perhaps others.$B$BWe shall see.', 27377), -- Ancient Vengeance
(31004, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Klaxxi... call to me.', 27377), -- Preserved in Amber
(31003, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<This mantid is severely wounded. He barely manages to choke forth his words between wheezing gasps for breath.>$B$BHold, $r...$B$BWe are... not your enemy.', 27377), -- Psycho Mantid
(31002, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work with that dragon gun. I did what I could down here, but arrows are only so useful against these things.', 27377), -- Nope
(31001, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fall wasn\'t that bad, actually. I\'ve always had a knack for soft landings.$B$BThat I landed on a pile of spider corpses probably helped, too.', 27377), -- Falling Down
(49561, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A volunteer for Dread Wastes duty? I think you might be the first.\n\nPleased to meet you.', 27377), -- Hero's Call: Dread Wastes!
(31110, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! Excellent!$B$BThis is just the stuff, $n.$B$BWe\'ll get to work right away. I have no doubt we\'ll be done very soon.', 27377), -- Through the Portal
(30927, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c.$b$b<Qipan sighs.>$b$bI should have been among them.', 27377), -- Give Them Peace
(30928, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We already have mantid, mogu, and yaungol to worry about. This sha problem needs to be nipped in the bud before even we are overrun.', 27377), -- A Trail of Fear
(30926, 1, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me make this clear... that creature was NOT the Sha of Fear. Simply a shadow... a fraction of the sha\'s true power.$b$bNo, the Sha of Fear is with the mantid now. The elders of my order need to be informed of this immediately.$b$bI will handle the rest from here. Thank you for your assistance, $r. Once again, your kind proves to be an asset to Pandaria.', 27377), -- The Terrible Truth
(30925, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Niuzao will be pleased.$b$bDespite his size, our patron is a beast of grace and compassion. He treasured this icon... just as he treasures each of his followers.', 27377), -- Niuzao's Price
(30930, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, well! A good yak!$b$bTell you what, $n. I take this GOOD yak, and you can do whatever you want with this bad, bad one.', 27377), -- Pick a Yak
(30932, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No shield, no crossbow, no yak... something bad has happened to dad.', 27377), -- Father's Footsteps
(30931, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, this is dad\'s.$b$bLet\'s head on over to the temple. They\'ll know what...$b$b<Ku-Mo\'s voice catches.>$b$b...what happened to him.', 27377), -- My Father's Crossbow
(30929, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think we made a pretty convincing argument. They\'ll HAVE to replace my yak now.', 27377), -- Bad Yak
(30924, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your Shado-Pan associate has spoken with me. Yes, Niuzao knows why the mantid are attacking. But he is not ready to tell you.$b$bNot yet.', 27377), -- The Wisdom of Niuzao
(30964, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do.$b$bThe Shado-Pan appreciates your work, $n.', 27377), -- A Proper Poultice
(30963, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. I\'ll get to repairing the armor tonight, once most everyone\'s returned.', 27377), -- The Field Armorer
(30922, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your messy work may have saved a few lives today, $r.', 27377), -- Natural Antiseptic
(30923, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are in your debt, $r.', 27377), -- Set the Mantid Back
(30921, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The abundance of yak hair on that mantid\'s body suggests one thing... it came from Niuzao Temple. Our journey continues westward, $c.', 27377), -- The Motives of the Mantid
(32681, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have arrived just in time, $n. This land needs to be controlled by the Kirin Tor for everyone\'s safety. This will not be an easy task.', 27377), -- The Storm Gathers
(31809, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you present the Claw to Ban, his eyes grow wide with the realization of what you have done.>\n\nI see now what about you has changed.\n\nYou have done the impossible. The Shado-Pan shall record your name, and honor it as long as we stand watch over this land.', 27377), -- Remnants of Anger
(30968, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Defeating a Sha... is not an easy thing. It is a miracle that we came out of this unscathed.$B$BTaran still blames himself for letting his hatred get the best of him and setting this beast loose upon the land. It may take some time for him to come to terms with this, but it is important that he does, lest he be vulnerable again.$B$BWe accomplished a great thing this day, a thing that will not soon be forgotten.$B$BAnd neither shall you for your hand in this.  Thank you.', 27377), -- The Sha of Hatred
(31064, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The final crystal is ours. We are on the doorstep of our final confrontation.', 27377), -- Nurong and Rothek
(31063, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have the second crystal then. Good.', 27377), -- Lao-Chin and Serevex
(30981, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The first crystal is ours...', 27377), -- Taoshi and Korvexxis
(31688, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Leng told me of your heroics. He is in your debt, as am I.', 27377), -- The Search for Restless Leng
(31687, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The mantid are relentless. Fortunately for us, you have a dedication that surpasses even theirs.$B$BIt is good to have you walk these roads, $c.', 27377), -- Thinning the Sik'thik
(31065, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our tasks lay before us.', 27377), -- Buried Beneath
(30980, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I like that I can always depend on you. You have the spirit of a true Shado-Pan.', 27377), -- Heroes of the Shado-Pan
(30977, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts are appreciated, $c. Even a few more moment\'s breath between attacks are a relief these days.', 27377), -- Grounded Welcome
(30979, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where have you been all my life?!  That was amazing!$B$BI\'d be proud to fight beside you any day.', 27377), -- Devastation Below
(30978, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent shooting!$B$BI\'m pretty sure that big bug survived the fall though...', 27377), -- Hostile Skies
(30899, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s a lot of movement on the other side of the chasm... something big is coming.', 27377), -- In Skilled Hands
(31032, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your help is appreciated, stranger.', 27377), -- Choking the Skies
(30976, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are close. I can feel the unnatural hatred surging.$B$BIt\'s a testament to the training of the Shado-Pan that the forces here have not been consumed by its influence.', 27377), -- Joining the Hunt
(30975, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The mantid aren\'t likely to return soon after a beating like that... and now Lao-Chin is free to join us in the hunt.', 27377), -- The Taking of Dusklight Bridge
(30973, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have the added benefit that the mantid will leave with broken morale after watching their brethren burn to death.  Grim, but many lives will be spared if they simply stop pressing our lines.', 27377), -- Up In Flames
(30972, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Taran Zhu told me what became of my camp. I would have stopped it if I could, but the attacks from the bridge have not let up.$B$BThank you for bringing these arrows - my archers will make good use of them.', 27377), -- Joining the Fight
(30970, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. What\'s left of the camp will be a bit safer.', 27377), -- Enraged By Hatred
(30971, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I... you... er, thank you. You didn\'t have to help, but you did. Thank you.', 27377), -- Taking Stock
(30901, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s get this taken care of so we can get down to the bridge.', 27377), -- Along the Southern Front
(30900, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You. You\'re coming with me.$B$BI\'ve never seen someone handle themselves on the battlefield like that. I need a strong $c like you with me when we face the Sha of Hatred.', 27377), -- Terror of the Dread Wastes
(30898, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re not done yet...', 27377), -- Cutting the Swarm
(30895, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to have a $c that I can count on.', 27377), -- Improvised Ammunition
(30896, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I guess you\'re a bit faster than me. Well, thanks.$B$BI\'ll try to finish collecting some orbs and get them back to camp while there\'s still some face to save.', 27377), -- Thieves and Troublemakers
(30897, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... you are a lifesaver! Seriously.$B$BThank you so much!', 27377), -- In the Wrong Hands
(30893, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The men of the battlefront are growing to respect you. You clearly know how to fight.', 27377), -- The Endless Swarm
(30894, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are in great condition! Thank you, $n!$B$BYou know, I\'ve managed to distil some of their poison into a form that we can apply readily. I\'ve even come up with some methods for weaving it into spell-casting, if you believe it. Would you like to give some a try?', 27377), -- Rummaging Through the Remains
(30892, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are several warriors that owe their lives to you. You have my deepest appreciation, $c.', 27377), -- Back on Their Feet
(30891, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelous. And in good condition too!$B$BThank you, kind $c.', 27377), -- Treatment for the Troops
(30960, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back. I heard about the breaches in the eastern pass. It sounds like I put the right people on the job.', 27377), -- Returning from the Pass
(30889, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We could use a few more capable $gmen:women; like you around the camp. Thank you for your help, $c.', 27377), -- Trap Setting
(30890, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. I\'ll have the new scouts at their posts shortly.', 27377), -- The Restless Watch
(30888, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are more getting through than I thought. I may need to stay here and clean up a while.$B$BYou\'ve done more than your part though, $c. Thank you.', 27377), -- Breach in the Defenses
(30887, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is where they\'re getting through, the eastern pass.', 27377), -- Unwelcome Intruders
(30884, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look capable. Taran knows to send me the best. I like that.', 27377), -- Behind the Battlefront
(30785, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did the northern expedition go well, then? What news do you have to report?', 27377), -- Gao-Ran Battlefront
(30793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My name will be forgotten, but my actions will not.$b$bNor will yours, $n.', 27377), -- Mists' Opportunity
(30792, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I told you earlier, this wound would be my death. While you have bought me a bit more time, it is not long now.', 27377), -- Orbiss Fades
(30791, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yet another step closer to completing my mission.', 27377), -- Arconiss Thirsts
(30790, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are one step closer to my goal.', 27377), -- Golgoss Hungers
(30815, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By removing this spear, I have truly guaranteed my own death.$b$bThis does not frighten me.$b$bI would sooner die than live carrying the weapon of my enemy.', 27377), -- The Death of Me
(30789, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It will be difficult to lose with Arconiss by my side.', 27377), -- Arconiss
(30788, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Golgoss does not speak your language, other than a few words. I suppose I am unique in this regard.$b$bHe thanks you for summoning him.', 27377), -- Golgoss
(30787, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This torch... the yaungol once used these to communicate with me, with my people.$b$bNow, they use them to undo us.', 27377), -- The Torches
(30786, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am freed.$b$bThe yaungol must be stopped.', 27377), -- A Spear Through My Side, A Chain Through My Soul
(31894, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orbiss groans at you in agony.>$b$bSo, the shado-pan have sent you to see what the yaungol are doing? Well, do you see?', 27377), -- A Delicate Balance
(30784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? She was possessed by the Sha of Hatred?$B$BNo. NO!$B$BDespite our differences, she was one of us. Today, the Shado-Pan has lost a dear sister.$B$BHer death will not be in vain. I will not rest until I have defeated the Sha of Hatred!$B$BSuna, I swear this to you!', 27377), -- The Point of No Return
(30782, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. We cannot bring them retribution, but at least we can end their rage.', 27377), -- Spiteful Spirits
(30783, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.$B$BThe sha preys upon the weak and the vulnerable.$B$BIf we are not vigilant, even the strongest of us can succumb to the sha\'s dark influence.', 27377), -- Hatred Becomes Us
(30827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We look upon the true face of hatred!$B$BNow it all makes sense. This is the work of the sha.', 27377), -- What Lies Beneath
(30780, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was right! These totems were once used to store and conduct immense magical energies.$B$BI do believe I can use them once again to do the same.', 27377), -- Totemic Research
(30781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your help, $n.$B$BWe cannot know exactly what happened here, but it\'s clear that something caused the yaungol to turn on one another.$B$BWhat kind of power could do this?', 27377), -- Last Toll of the Yaungol
(30779, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. It was an unpleasant task, but it had to be done.', 27377), -- Slaying the Scavengers
(30778, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n.$B$BHopefully, their spirits are in a better place.', 27377), -- Dust to Dust
(30777, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, we made it.', 27377), -- In Search of Suna
(30776, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Jung Duk is dead at last.$B$BHundreds, perhaps thousands, lost their lives due to his violent aggression.$B$BThough they are not here to witness his demise, they owe deep gratitude to your bravery today.', 27377), -- Jung Duk
(30775, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It pleases me to know those cowards died at your hands.$B$BPerhaps now, this burning tide in my heart will ebb.', 27377), -- The Exile
(30774, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am truly sorry to hear that Lin did not make it.$B$BSuna is taking the news quite hard. She will forgive me in time.$B$BAs for the rest of the Shado-Pan that you saved, well, I am very grateful to see them returned safe and sound.', 27377), -- Ranger Rescue
(30773, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, $c.$B$BNow that they cannot hide behind their siege weapons, they have no choice but to face us.', 27377), -- Pitching In
(30772, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should put a serious dent in their numbers.$B$BI doubt they will be able to recover from such losses.', 27377), -- Seeing Red
(30769, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. I hope you showed those cretins no mercy.', 27377), -- First Assault
(30771, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It still smells fresh.$B$BGood job, $n.', 27377), -- Perfect Pitch
(30770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ohohoho! I saw those animals trailing dust from up here.$B$BThose yaungol are probably still wondering what happened.', 27377), -- Running Rampant
(30814, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. I can see that you are capable.$B$BI hope to rely on your talents for what is to come.', 27377), -- A Foot in the Door
(49560, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Townlong Steppes, outsider.\n\nIf you insist on wandering in to the darkest places of Pandaria then far be it from me to not put you to good use.', 27377), -- Hero's Call: Townlong Steppes!
(30768, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Looks like the rest of the Shado-Pan decided it was a good time to catch up.', 27377), -- My Husband...
(31394, 5, 396, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'You did it, $n!$b$bThe White Tiger has agreed to allow us to accompany the Pandaren into the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. An Alliance outpost is already set up within. Now, the hard work of cleaning up the damage can begin!', 27377), -- A Celestial Experience
(31392, 396, 5, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, '$C, I\'m glad you\'re here! The \"Vale of Eternal Blossoms\" is legendary among the Pandaren. It\'s a place of great healing, if the locals are to be believed.$b$bBut the Horde Warchief has done something to the Vale - something terrible.$b$bWe need to get in there!', 27377), -- Temple of the White Tiger
(30820, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Let us begin the funeral.', 27377), -- A Funeral
(31228, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These events should be learned from, $n.$b$bIt is important that we learn from our history. Had we paid attention to the histories, we may have been able to head this off before it got this far.$b$bEverything that has happened was already foretold, we just didn\'t know how to read it.', 27377), -- Prophet Khar'zul
(30819, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see... it is tragic what has happened there. We will meet you at the graveyard to honor them.', 27377), -- Preparing the Remains
(30807, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Thank you. After this, I cannot imagine leaving my fellows to less than a proper burial.', 27377), -- By the Falls, For the Fallen
(30806, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful, beautiful. Better to not need to bury our friends, but if we must, it is good they will have a fitting ceremony.', 27377), -- The Scent of Life
(30805, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh.. they are dead. Already, I can feel my spirits lifting. Soon I will have the strength to return to the village.', 27377), -- Justice
(30794, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. I suppose... I\'ll need to ask you to do a bit more before I can return to the village. I cannot leave the bodies of my friends and family here.', 27377), -- Emergency Care
(30816, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh... My cousin is wise to be worried... I am not well...', 27377), -- Checking In
(30946, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We cannot dwell on this setback, $n. Prophet Khar\'zul must be dealt with.$b$bEvery member of the Thunder King\'s forces we are able to destroy brings us one step closer to victory.', 27377), -- Revelations
(31011, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Zandalari have started to retreat, $n. This victory will mean a great deal to the villagers.$b$bIn the chaos I was able to capture one of the fighters. Perhaps we can get information from him.', 27377), -- Enemies At Our Door
(30945, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, these are better than I had anticipated! I can make four spears for every one of their blades.$b$bDon\'t you worry, I\'ll make sure the villagers are armed when the time comes.', 27377), -- What's Yours Is Mine
(30943, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfect! Now, I would go wash your hands a few times $c.$b$bI would also continue to avoid open flames for a few days...', 27377), -- Handle With Care
(30942, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I told you I was a fast learner! I will head back to the village to start training others. Thank you, $n.', 27377), -- Make A Fighter Out of Me
(30944, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good, $c! With the villagers rested we may yet stand a chance against the Zandalari.', 27377), -- It Takes A Village
(30935, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The elders have agreed to help us figure out where the Zandalari have hidden the Thunder King\'s remains.$b$bThey have a few conditions though...', 27377), -- Fisherman's Tale
(30802, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is dark Zandalari blood magic. Once we\'re done with the map it should be burned.$b$bThe map indicates they have headed for the coast just outside of a tiny fishing village called Zouchin. The villagers there may be able to help us find the Zandalari. We just have to hope the village is still standing...', 27377), -- Chasing the Storm
(30801, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They will need to move the remains to a secure location. We must go after them!', 27377), -- Lessons from History
(30800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are fortunate they haven\'t gotten to Lei Shen\'s remains... yet.$b$bThe Zandalari will not give up until they have what they want. ', 27377), -- Stealing Their Thunder King
(30798, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Mogu and the Zandalari intend to resurrect the Thunder King?!$b$bWe cannot let this happen, $n! The Thunder King will rain destruction on this land with his return. ', 27377), -- Breaking the Emperor's Shield
(30799, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These tablets recount the history of the Mogu and Zandalari alliance dating back to the time of the first Mogu emperor.$b$bBy the looks of things they have rekindled their alliance. But why now?', 27377), -- The Tomb of Shadows
(30797, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This text is curious indeed, $n...$b$bIt appears to have been written in the Meng dynasty, but some of the symbols are wrong. I don\'t think the Mogu wrote this, although it is oddly close.$b$bIt will take me some time to translate. Keep moving and see if you can find anything else.', 27377), -- It Was Almost Alive
(30796, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done them a great service, $n.$b$bIt is a cruel fate to be stuck between the living world and the afterlife.', 27377), -- An End to Everything
(30795, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good! The relic works!$b$bIt appears there is more going on in the Valley of Emperors than I had anticipated. It is crucial we figure out why the Mogu are opening the tombs.', 27377), -- Staying Connected
(30829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This must be a very powerful relic for Zuan to want it back so badly.$b$bIt frightens me to think of what else they may find in the tombs...', 27377), -- The Tongue of Ba-Shon
(30684, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you made it, and you honored the shrines.$B$BI knew you could handle it.', 27377), -- Seeker's Folly
(30683, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were attacked by a mogu? That sounds terrible!$b$bI hate to ask, but did you manage to pick up any supplies while you were fighting for your life?$b$bNo?! This is very bad luck.', 27377), -- One Traveler's Misfortune
(31030, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have come. Good. This is a calamitous situation.', 27377), -- Into the Monastery
(30752, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No... this is worse than I could have possibly imagined. The monastery itself has been compromised...', 27377), -- Unbelievable!
(30993, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here we are, and now you know why we cannot let our brothers sit idly by.', 27377), -- Where are My Reinforcements?
(30992, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, their lieutenant is dead. I think we have finally pushed them out of Kun-Lai. \n\nBut at what cost? So many dead, Lin captured... I will not allow Taran Zhu to continue to ignore his charge.', 27377), -- Finish This!
(30991, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whoo, that was an explosion! Several, in fact.\n\nSad my beer had to go, but at least we\'re safe, for now.', 27377), -- Do a Barrel Roll!
(30994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you made it back in one piece. Thanks to your help with the barrels, I\'ve managed to brew up a good surprise for our yaungol friends at the front.', 27377), -- Lao-Chin's Gambit
(30750, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! I could see them flying. Good work.', 27377), -- Off the Wall!
(30751, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright. I am off to prepare our next move. Good luck, friend.', 27377), -- A Terrible Sacrifice
(30724, 5, 2, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Wow, that was quite a bit of kite-flying there. Good job getting up here and not dying.\n\nIt\'s good you\'re here, too. Lao-chen\'s got an idea he\'s working on, but in the meantime we\'ve got yaungol to deal with.', 27377), -- To the Wall!
(30715, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. I will see to it that the armor is returned to their pupils.', 27377), -- A Line Unbroken
(30723, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. After what they have done, I would not show the Yaungol kindness in life. But neither will I allow their bodies to be eaten by the birds.', 27377), -- Honor, Even in Death
(30699, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shado-Master Chong sent you, hmm?\n\nYes, we received his request for reinforcements.\n\nWe are in no position to grant it, however. We\'ve just concluded a battle of our own, and the monastery\'s been locked up tight. \n\nWe can\'t even get reinforcements here, and we\'re just down the hill!', 27377), -- To Winter's Blossom
(30682, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We didn\'t know that there were any survivors out there.$B$BThank you for bringing them to safety, $n.', 27377), -- Holed Up
(30690, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I should feel shame at the loss of the village. I should feel great pride in your success. \n\nI should feel many things, but must not allow myself to. Until our struggle with the sha is complete, we must maintain total control of our emotions.', 27377), -- Unmasking the Yaungol
(30665, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have bought us some time to breathe. We must not despair - instead, we must act.', 27377), -- The Defense of Shado-Pan Fallback
(30670, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Now you will see how to defeat unbridled rage.\n\nI will craft these into a trap for Kobai, the leader of the yaungol. Though he will be snared, and we will defeat him, he is not our ultimate target...', 27377), -- Turnabout
(31455, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who are you? Can you fight? If so, we can use your help.', 27377), -- The Shado-Pan
(30747, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow! That was VIOLENT.$B$BNot sure what I was expecting...$B$BThanks to you, I think we may have just formed a mutually beneficial relationship with the Terror of Kota Peak.', 27377), -- The Burlap Grind
(30743, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great, I\'ll get up there and... harvest them soon.$B$B<Cousin Gootfur begins wrapping long strips of linen around his hands.>$B$BCan\'t believe I thought this was a good idea.', 27377), -- Gourmet Kafa
(30742, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, friend. Let this be a lesson to you: never feed the goots.', 27377), -- Shut it Down
(30745, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it!$B$BYeti\'s are tough enough on their own - can\'t imagine what a cranky kafa-addict yeti must be like. You brave. Or lucky. Or dumb.$B$BMaybe all three.', 27377), -- Trouble Brewing
(30746, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You brought kafa?!$B$BYou...$B$BMagnificent...$B$BLuckydo...$B$BHurry, let\'s give it to her! Maybe she won\'t have us both for snack...', 27377), -- A Fair Trade
(30744, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you bundle the berries together, you hear a mighty roar echo across the mountain, followed by the squeal of a terrified grummle.>', 27377), -- Kota Blend
(30692, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha ha! Hero of grummles! Welcome to Kota Basecamp. Enjoy good fortune for most happy grummle delivery.', 27377), -- The Burlap Trail: To Kota Basecamp
(30612, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Ook of Dook is dead! Hurray!', 27377), -- The Leader Hozen
(30611, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ready for the yeti?', 27377), -- Unleash The Yeti!
(30610, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that hozen king is going to learn why it is bad fortune to cheat grummles.', 27377), -- Grummle! Grummle! Grummle!
(30608, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Today is a day of many good and bad fortunes. Bad fortune that hozen stole my grummles. Good fortune that my $r saves my grummles. Bad fortune that so many hozen must die to learn lesson. Good fortune that $rs are luckydos and know how to fight.$b$bGrummles are not fighters. We carry, we explore, and we are content.', 27377), -- The Snackrifice
(30607, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh wow that looked like one wild ride!', 27377), -- Hozen Love Their Keys
(30606, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a true luckydo.', 27377), -- Thumping Knucklethump
(30605, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good fortune for me to be saved by a luckydo like you.$b$bAnd Brother Rabbitsfoot always say I not have good fortune. Bah!', 27377), -- Bros Before Hozen
(30604, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p! Hopefully that will slow the Broketooth ravage.', 27377), -- Breaking Broketooth
(30600, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are good fortune for grummles.$b$bWhen we are back at a proper camp I must buy you the smelliest, luckiest incense I can find.', 27377), -- No Pack Left Behind
(30599, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A confident hozen is a dangerous hozen.$b$bThank you for your help, friend of grummles.', 27377), -- A Monkey Idol
(30603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My luckydo! Oh happy day of good fortune! Many thanks!', 27377), -- The Broketooth Ravage
(30602, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look what Broketooths and Knucklethumps did to grummle waystation. Hardly a luckydo to be found.$b$bGrummles had a deal with the hozen. We give them food, and they don\'t ravage. Whenever they think to ravage, Shado-Pan remind them not to ravage.$b$bBut all of Shado-Pan are away defending the wall now. And the hozen want more food than the grummles have.', 27377), -- The Rabbitsfoot
(30487, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve arrived just in time, $c! I was starting to think I would die up here!', 27377), -- Comin' Round the Mountain
(30618, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh thank you, $n! If I just cut off the nibbled pieces and repair the minor damage, I may still be able to sell these.$b$bOnce your cart is ready to go I\'ll have the supplies I promised loaded up!', 27377), -- Resupplying One Keg
(30601, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Incense works like a charm! Effects will not last long, so you must hurry!', 27377), -- Instant Courage
(30621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you! It appears my trinkets were lucky for you too, $c. While you were gone I did not gamble and lose my cart.$b$bI would be happy to lend it to you for your journey. Besides, I have some goods to win back from this shady grummle!', 27377), -- They Stole My Luck!
(30592, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many thanks and fortune to you, friend of grummles. But the journey to the Serpent\'s Spine is not safe yet.', 27377), -- The Burlap Trail: To Burlap Waystation
(30999, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Travel to Seeker\'s Point will require much good fortune, $c. Hopefully you have many lucky trinkets!', 27377), -- Path Less Traveled
(31460, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, hello. Nice to see you again.', 27377), -- Cho's Missive
(30617, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to One Keg! Gateway to Burlap Trail and Mount Neverest.', 27377), -- Roadside Assistance
(30616, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good fortune that a $r comes to help grummles. Good fortune to friend of grummles.', 27377), -- Traffic Issues
(30614, 15, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Happy day! Your reward. May these coins bring you good fortune.', 27377), -- Oil Stop
(30808, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hurray! Our Luckydos. Many thanks and fortune to friend of grummles!', 27377), -- A Grummle's Luck
(30492, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah! I can smell the luck from here. The Muskpaws always have good yaks for sale.', 27377), -- Back in Yak
(30804, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yee haw! I knew you $rs might be good for somethin\'. He must of made a very satisfying \"thump\" when he hit the ground.', 27377), -- The Fearmaster
(30587, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well then, I am mighty grateful for you culling some of those yaungols for us.$b$bHopefully your little display of authority will be enough to discourage them from coming over here.', 27377), -- Yakity Yak
(30582, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya never know how much you can lose until you\'ve lost it. My wife passed a few seasons ago, but I can tell you this is a day when I could use her smile the most.$b$bAt least she doesn\'t have to see what these yaungol did to her beloved ranch.', 27377), -- The Late Mrs. Muskpaw
(30491, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, stranger! Hopefully we\'ll be able to cash these in and recoup some of the damages the yaungol inflicted.', 27377), -- At the Yak Wash
(30489, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You just earned me a handsome bonus. Getting those needles is a pain in the paw but worth it when we take our yaks to market. Here, for your troubles.', 27377), -- Fresh Needle Scent
(30488, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for the save, stranger!', 27377), -- The Missing Muskpaw
(31456, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wha? Who the heck are you? What are you doin\' here?\n\nOh, you wanna help?', 27377), -- Muskpaw Ranch
(30651, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ho ho, that were a fine sight to see. I knew I should have gone up there with ya, $n!', 27377), -- Barrels of Fun
(30650, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, if it isn\'t our hero, $n.\n\nI really wasn\'t sure we stood a fighting chance out here, you know?\n\nThese guys may be a little rough around the edges, but we\'ll be able to whip \'em into shape. And when we do, we\'ll have a real fighting chance at holding our own here in Kun-Lai.\n\nGood work.', 27377), -- Pandaren Prisoners
(30660, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it, $n! I\'m in your debt!$B$BAgain!', 27377); -- The Ordo Warbringer
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(30652, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Ordo lieutenants are dead. The shield is down.>$B$B<Time to take out the Ordo leader!>', 27377), -- In Tents Channeling
(30575, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These yaks will do the trick nicely. Good work, $p. I\'m feeling better about this whole situation already.', 27377), -- Round 'Em Up
(30593, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright! Looks like we won\'t have a bunch of statues to worry about any more. Good work, $p!', 27377), -- Deanimate the Reanimated
(31252, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did good, bringing these guys back. We\'ll have \'em farming you up some food in no time!', 27377), -- Back to Westwind Rest
(30583, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work! I\'m telliin\' ye, these Kun-Lai meaty bits are grade A goodness!', 27377), -- Blue Dwarf Needs Food Badly
(30619, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, thank goodness! You\'ve saved all of our skins, believe me.\n\nYou have no idea how much trouble those guys can stir up.\n\nErr, or, I guess you do, now. Kind of. Almost.\n\nImagine that, but a lot worse, and for a couple thousand years.', 27377), -- Mogu?! Oh No-gu!
(30571, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now ain\'t you just the thing?$B$BThough, I guess it\'s not fair to force these here workers to stay with us, now that we don\'t have much work for \'em...', 27377), -- Farmhand Freedom
(30581, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well there you go. We should be plenty good, now.', 27377), -- ... and the Pot, Too!
(30569, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a sight for sore eyes, $c.$B$BI\'ll be glad to help you Alliance fellas out. First though, you need to help me get my farm back.', 27377), -- Trouble on the Farmstead
(30595, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow! I mean, wow! Thank you, $n!$B$B<Bao Jian\'s eyes widen with anticipation of the proceeds from the relics.>$B$BNow that you\'ve softened them up, I\'m thinking that I might head in. Just a few more relics from around the outskirts. Nothing dangerous.', 27377), -- Profiting off of the Past
(30514, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! At the very least, we have justice, and safety, though in the process we have lost so much.\n\nRegardless, it has been decided. We will join the Alliance, and with your help, rebuild this village.', 27377), -- Challenge Accepted
(30512, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well... we are alive, and that is better than we could have hoped for without your help.\n\nBut, if this is truly to become a base of operations for you, and if we are to join your Alliance, there is one more thing you must do to guarantee our security.', 27377), -- Westwind Rest
(30855, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. You have assured that this corruption will not spread, and that my people - those who have not been corrupted - will be able to live on and found a new village. \n\nOur history will live on. You have done more for us than we could have ever hoped.\n\nThank you, friend.', 27377), -- The Fall of Shai Hu
(30828, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Mere... I can feel the corruption clearing. At least now, this corruption will not spread.\n\nBut, there is one more thing we must do.', 27377), -- Cleansing the Mere
(30480, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see now that this ritual rips whatever was controlling the minds of these creatures from them. I now know what we must do.', 27377), -- The Ritual
(30468, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is satisfying to hear that our enemies are dead. Perhaps you can use one of my bodyguard\'s weapons.', 27377), -- Enraged Vengeance
(30834, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found him! This is all I have to give, but in finding my son, you have more than earned it.', 27377), -- Father and Child Reunion
(30469, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you... we will eat now, at least.', 27377), -- Repossession
(30967, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though we may not seem like much, from these inauspicious beginnings I know we will rebuild. Thank you, friend.', 27377), -- Free the Dissenters
(30496, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Now we have some hope of redeeming this situation.', 27377), -- The Waterspeaker's Staff
(30467, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So horrible... When I saw the killing, I just ran. My father, Mei... are they alive?', 27377), -- My Son...
(30508, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, is that you? I can\'t believe we survived the destruction of the Jade Serpent.$B$BSome of us anyway.', 27377), -- Admiral Taylor has Awakened
(30460, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks, $n. You have shown great honor through your actions.$B$BI hope that my family\'s dit da jow was of some use to you.', 27377), -- Hit Medicine
(30457, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are delivered! I was right about you, $c.', 27377), -- Call Out Their Leader
(30459, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. You\'ve saved our defensive line here.$B$BThis next attack wouldn\'t have been possible without you.', 27377), -- All of the Arrows
(31254, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Oh, you are a friend of Cho\'s? Welcome! Welcome!$b$bI would serve you a banquet but as you can see we are in dire straights at the moment.$b$bSay, would you be willing to lend us a hand?', 27377), -- The Road to Kun-Lai
(31285, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Wheh, we made it. Welcome to Binan Village.', 27377); -- The Spring Drifter
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(36269, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is perfect! The cloth and magic are perfectly balanced and stable.\n\nI am happy to say that you have learned the basics of my tailoring methods. I respect your skill and your eagerness to learn new techniques.\n\nLet me give you some other patterns and materials that I hope you find useful during your journey.', 27547), -- Hexcloth
(36266, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Again, you show me great kindness.$b$bNow, let us begin.', 27547), -- The Clothes on Their Backs
(36315, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... This is it, after so many years. Soon, I will have all of the Armaments of Oru\'kai.\n\nReturn my ring as well and I will fulfill the promise I made to that squeamish draenei. \n\nTake this book. If you have any skill, you can use it to decipher and learn Draenor\'s enchantments. \n\nOf course, you will need a proper workplace as well. Here are plans; hopefully you can follow them.\n\nNow, be gone, and steer clear of the other armaments, for they are mine.', 27547), -- Oru'kai's Staff
(36313, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. I thought I was going to be stuck here forever.', 27547), -- Failed Apprentice
(36310, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do I also detect that you have in your possession an artifact of our land? \n\nCan I see it?\n\nOne of Oru\'kai\'s bracers... Thank you!', 27547), -- The Arakkoan Enchanter
(34897, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for the report, $n. We must keep a close eye on these southern wilds.', 27547), -- Rangari Roundup
(36643, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me unpack that for you.$b$bI should let you know - while we managed to expedite this one, future work orders will take longer.', 27547), -- Your First Tailoring Work Order
(36645, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me unpack that for you.$b$bI should let you know - while we managed to expedite this one, future work orders will take longer.', 27547), -- Your First Enchanting Work Order
(36192, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s how it\'s done, commander!$B$BWe\'re now fully operational. Any time you have enough timber to place a work order, come on back to me and we\'ll get started.$B$BThis garrison ain\'t gonna build itself!', 27547), -- Turning Timber into Profit
(36189, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re going to make a fine overseer, $g sir:ma\'am;! Keep those lumberjacks in line!$B$BNow you know the basics of logging and finding timber. Time to put them to good use for the good of your garrison.', 27547), -- Easing into Lumberjacking
(36262, 470, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is that my tailoring tome? It is! I\'m so glad it is safe! How can I ever repay you?', 27547), -- Ameeka, Master Tailor
(36308, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Interesting, an Arakkoa recently visited the garrison looking for an armor piece with a powerful enchantment like this. His name was Delath.\n\nThe enchantment on this bracer is beyond my skill, but perhaps this Delath can give you the necessary insight to replicate it.', 27547), -- Enchanted Highmaul Bracer
(36236, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems that you have found a very special tailoring book.$b$bIt belongs to Ameeka, a tailor of great renown from Embaari Village.', 27547); -- The Cryptic Tome of Tailoring
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(39665, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Equipment can really make a difference out there!', 27602), -- A True Naval Commander
(39666, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Equipment can really make a difference out there, let\'s see what I can do to help ya out.', 27602), -- Equipping Our Fleet
(39655, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was an amazing turn around commander!  Great work.', 27602), -- If At First You Fail, Try Again!
(39404, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They lured us into a trap, commander.  I want revenge!', 27602), -- Destroying the Competition
(39056, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work Commander!  You are going to make a great captain one day.', 27602), -- Naval Commander
(39422, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have been waiting for you, Commander.', 27602), -- Shipyard Report
(38603, 603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Welcome back!$b$bWe\'re getting a strong feed from those sensors! The crew locked the navigation system on to the signal and everything should be good to go!$b$bWe set the machine up next to Skyguard Thann.', 27602), -- Setting the Signal
(39432, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As your archmage told me, the power that has warped these crystals comes from far beyond this world. I will need more help in discovering how to turn back the darkness inside my people.', 27602), -- Unknowable Power
(38581, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you see what we face here. We will keep as much pressure here as we can so your base can remain free to attack all over the jungle.', 27602), -- The Battle for the West
(38445, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The easy part is done, now comes the hard part.', 27602), -- The Assault Base
(39313, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! I\'m always here if ye\' ever want to change your mind!', 27602), -- Bring the Reinforcements
(38444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t worry, I have a taskforce coming in a bit to clean the rest up. We should move before their runners get back to Gul\'dan.', 27602), -- In, Through, and Beyond!
(38436, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our forces can finish driving off the remaining lurkers. But there\'s another problem up ahead.', 27602), -- Obstacle Course
(38435, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The landing was easier than I expected but there is trouble ahead.', 27602), -- The Invasion of Tanaan
(36289, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll need to keep an eye on this Azuka Bladefury character. Sounds dangerous.', 27602), -- Out of the Shadows
(38356, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the best Draenor has to offer? Lucky for you I went to engineering school. One Tune-O-Tron 5000 coming up!', 27602), -- Bringing the Bass
(35169, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s over. The Warsong are broken. Garrosh Hellscream is finally dead.$B$BSomehow, I sense it\'s only a matter of time before Grommash seeks vengeance.', 27602), -- And Justice for Thrall
(35141, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wait a minute, $n... let\'s be reasonable. I can hear what\'s in that carrier.$B$BIt was just a harmless prank.$B$BDon\'t do it, please!$B$BStop!$B$BDon\'t open that carrier!', 27602), -- Carrier Has Arrived
(35062, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you hadn\'t gone to Lok-rath, our forces would have been decimated.$B$BI\'m sorry to hear they laid a trap for you. I guess you have a reputation now.', 27602), -- Lok-rath is Secured
(36220, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you kill Lug\'dol, you definitely belong in da proving grounds.$B$BI don\'t even care that you tiny not ogre!', 27602), -- How Tough Are You?
(36219, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I won\'t waste your time, champ. I\'ve got a once in a lifetime opportunity for you.', 27602), -- Garrison Campaign: The Ring of Blood
(35140, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding.$B$B<Vindicator Yrel beckons you closer so that the two of you can conspire.>', 27602), -- THAELIN!
(35061, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Unfortunate, but I\'m glad you made it out of that trap alive.', 27602), -- The Pride of Lok-rath
(35069, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the beast\'s collar? I heard its howls all the way over here!', 27602), -- Terror of Nagrand
(35068, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Regrettable, but I understand the pride of the Warsong. I would never surrender.', 27602), -- If They Won't Surrender...
(35067, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, commander. I thought we were done for sure.', 27602), -- Silence the War Machines
(35060, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Commander $n.$B$B<Uruk Foecleaver looks at you and grins.>$B$BTerms of surrender? Hmm... let me think.', 27602), -- Terms of Surrender
(34747, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am without a clan. The Burning Blade are dead to me. Perhaps someday I will create a clan of my own.$B$BIn the meantime, it would be an honor to fight at your side. You freed me and fought well.$B$BThere is much we could learn from each other. What do you say?', 27602), -- The Honor of a Blademaster
(34957, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A great victory over the Burning Blade!$B$BThis new Warlord Azuka Bladefury sounds formidable. We\'ll have to keep an eye on her and her blademasters.', 27602), -- Challenge of the Masters
(34952, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You done us a solid with them Burning Blade, $g lad:lass;, and we\'re not the forgettin\' kind.$B$BLet\'s celebrate o\'er a pint in an hour. Drinks are on me.', 27602), -- The Friend o' My Enemy
(34956, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it. Good.$B$BGetting in here was nothing compared to what\'s to come.', 27602), -- Meet Me in the Cavern
(34955, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t expect you to understand the importance of what you\'ve done.$B$BPerhaps one day you will.', 27602), -- Not Without My Honor
(34954, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you can defeat Luhk, then perhaps there\'s some hope for you after all.', 27602), -- The Blade Itself
(34951, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who are you?$B$BDon\'t you know death by sight, $c?', 27602), -- They Call Him Lantresor of the Blade
(34572, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect, they will have to concentrate more on base defense now.  Hopefully things will get back to normal out there.', 27602), -- Obliterating Ogres
(35350, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Magnificent kill, commander. You\'ve done us all proud.', 27602), -- Queen of the Clefthoof
(35357, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. You succeeded where I did not.$B$BPerhaps you outsiders aren\'t such bad hunters after all.', 27602), -- King of the Breezestriders
(35337, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Twelve pairs, huh? That\'s pretty good, commander.$B$BUm, no, I think that\'s about how many I managed to bag. Yeah... about a dozen pairs of ears. Yep....', 27602), -- That Pounding Sound
(35356, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s MY arrow! Where\'d you get it?', 27602), -- Someone's Missing Arrow
(35338, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Twenty-four, huh? That\'s fine work.$B$BI brought back fifty.$B$BI\'ll send someone out for the meat. Waste not, want not.', 27602), -- Shooting the Breeze
(49567, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They came at us... from... nowhere.\n\n<The lieutenant nearly passes out.>', 27602), -- Hero's Call: Nagrand!
(34448, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A wise elder of my order once told me, \"True power is the strength to act and the wisdom to know when not to act.\" May those words and the memory of Kaelynara stay with you on your journey, $n.', 27602), -- Kaelynara Sunchaser
(34415, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is sad to see such a mighty creature fall, but An\'dure was a danger to all within the mine. The heart of the crystal giant will aid us in restoring peace to the Jorune Mine.', 27602), -- An'dure The Giant
(34406, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for getting the workers our of the mine safely, $n.', 27602), -- Caught In The Chaos
(34403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. The arcane essence you\'ve collected will do nicely. All we need now is a suitable crystal to attune...', 27602), -- Arcane Essence
(33944, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh thank you, $gmister:ma\'am;! I can\'t believe Sher\'khaan got Ricky!$b$bYou\'re my hero!', 27602), -- And the Elekk Too?!
(33884, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re so brave! I could never have taken Sher\'khaan out on my own!$b$bNow I only have to worry about the scary orcs, giant birds, hippos, big bird men, spiders, everything being on fire...$b$bYa\'know maybe I shouldn\'t be out here all by myself...', 27602), -- Sher'KHAAAAAAANNNN!
(33882, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh thank you! Now these little peachicks can be moved to safety.', 27602), -- Just Peachicky
(36848, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts will be well rewarded, $n.  The ancient waygates now serve you.', 27602), -- Ogre Waygates
(36495, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back, $n.', 27602), -- News from Talador
(34279, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Blook never beat before.$b$bBlook follow tiny person now, so Blook learn how to beat more people.', 27602), -- I Am Blook
(35828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah perfect. I\'ll get this up an\' runnin\' in no time.', 27602), -- I Drew Aggro...culture
(39055, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have our first ship!  Great work $n.  I will get to work preparing her for travel to Tanaan right away.', 27602), -- Ship Shape
(39276, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Interested in shipbuilding, I see?  I will do everything I can to help out, commander.', 27602), -- Strange Tools
(39054, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah, we\'ll make you a sea-dog yet. Let\'s get started on our first ship!', 27602), -- Shipbuilding
(39082, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I love the smell of fresh-cut wood and tar! Are you ready to start construction?', 27602), -- Let's Get To Work
(38259, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Roark scans the horizon.>$b$bYes, here. A good natural bay. The remains of that old warship can be gutted and turned into your first transport.$b$bI see you\'ve gathered all the materials we need. Are you ready?', 27602), -- All Hands on Deck
(38258, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found us a shipwright then? Good! Some of your followers are eager to take to the open seas.', 27602), -- Nothing Remains
(38256, 25, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Solog Roark takes in the view of his harbor one final time.>$b$bWe built it all for nothing, $c. Gul\'dan will claim whatever your troops do not destroy.$b$bNext time, I will build something that will last.', 27602), -- Hook, Line, and... Sink Him!
(38255, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lower your weapon, stranger. Blackhand is dead and our new \"Warchief\" just signed my death sentence. It looks like I\'m going mercenary.$b$bYou want to build a shipyard? Then you want me.', 27602), -- The Train Gang
(38254, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Roark is definitely in this prisoner train but it\'s locked tight. We\'ll have to - oh - you brought explosives? Naielle thinks of everything! Let\'s crack this car open and see if we can convince that engineer to defect...', 27602), -- Derailment
(38257, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Commander! I was told to expect you. The situation here is chaos.$b$bMy Rangari have had this place under surveillance since your original assault. It\'s come back to life in recent weeks as the remnants of the Iron Horde flee to Tanaan under Gul\'dan\'s orders.$b$bMy scouts have learned something that might interest you...', 27602), -- We Need a Shipwright
(34802, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, a thousand times thank you.', 27602), -- A Pilgrimage Gone Awry
(34465, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now THAT is a hat. See how it flickers in and out of time as if someone were temporally jiggling it?$b$bI\'d try putting it on if I weren\'t afraid it would wipe me from the timeline.', 27602), -- Mysterious Hat
(49565, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see you, Commander $n. I require your advisement.', 27602), -- Hero's Call: Talador!
(38354, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you found Apprentice Var\'nath.  Now, keep him supplied with waystones and we will be well on our way to defeating the iron horde.', 27602), -- Portable Portals
(36601, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Commander. Good to have you back.\n\nWe\'ve got some movement in Nagrand. The board can fill you in on the details.', 27602), -- News from Nagrand
(37141, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My purpose as a Talonpriest has been fulfilled, though Iskar and Zellek must think me a fool for altering the sacred rites.$B$BI care not for their approval, and I am done hiding in the shadows.$B$BLet me fight for you. I should like to improve this world before I fade away from it.', 27602), -- Talonpriest Ishaal
(35704, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Percy and I want to give you something as a token of our thanks. It\'s not much but please, take your reward.', 27602), -- When All Is Aligned
(36085, 5, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work!$B$BNow, it is time for the next phase of our plan.', 27602), -- On Ebon Wings
(35009, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done much to help my little nest of forgotten ones. The poor creatures are not quite sane but with their own kin hunting them I pity their plight.$b$bTheir flying kin, the Adherents you call them, would see the forgotten ones destroyed and my children made into slaves.$b$bThis I must not allow!', 27602), -- Call of the Raven Mother
(36790, 2, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The lives of all the flock are precious.\nI\'m glad to know that his murderers have been brought to justice.\n\nThank you, $n, you have done us a great honor.', 27602), -- The Initiate's Revenge
(34924, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These poor ravens have avoided a horrible future in the Bloodclaw lands.$b$bWe will take far better care of them.$b$bThank you!', 27602), -- The Egg Thieves
(34939, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, these will do nicely as an offering to the Raven Mother! May she feast upon our enemies!', 27602), -- Declawing The Bloodmane
(34938, 4, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let it be known that on this day the stranger has returned victorious from slaying the feared foe of the Flock!$b$bPraise the Raven Mother!', 27602), -- Ralshiara's Demise
(34923, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your strength has given us time to rest and continue our rituals.$b$bMay the Raven Mother ever keep you in her shadow.', 27602), -- The Bloodmane
(49566, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Azik looks you up and down.>\n\nAzik is betting you are someone of importance to your people.\n\nCome closer, friend. Azik could use your help.', 27602), -- Hero's Call: Spires of Arak!
(38408, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you find something you like!', 27602), -- New Goods
(36861, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, you\'re from that Alliance base right?$b$bGlad you made the trip because we really could use your help!', 27602), -- Pinchwhistle Gearworks
(34455, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The controller breaks in your hands.$b$bExposing this weakness will definitely make the Iron Horde rethink their tactics for controlling the Rylak.', 27602), -- Free their Minds
(36448, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Weldon holds Alexi\'s head up to his face and begins speaking.>$B$BYou no-good, backstabbing son-of-a-goat! Your greed is only surpassed by my own!$B$BAs for you my peasant friend, you have served me well. Here are your just rewards!', 27602), -- Reduction in Force
(36429, 603, 5, 603, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, '\"The brothers united once more,\" he said.$B$B\"A world full of untold riches to plunder,\" he said.$B$B\"Wealth beyond imaging,\" he said!$B$BAnd then he proceeded to drop a log on top of me.$B$B\"There can only be one CEO of Barov Industries,\" he said.$B$BAt least we can agree on that...', 27602), -- The Rise and Fall of Barov Industries: Weldon Barov
(37322, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The shrine has dozens of niches where the Prophet\'s followers have placed their own memory crystals, mourning the great leader\'s sacrifice. You slide the crystal into an empty socket and the memorial comes to life...', 27602), -- The Prophet's Final Message
(36194, 1, 23, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We haven\'t even scratched the surface when it comes to overkill.$B$BIt looks like this group will serve you well, $g sir:ma\'am;. Medium sized trees across Draenor are now at your mercy. That means more timber per tree!', 27602); -- Sharper Blades; Bigger Timber
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(39365, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a blueprint for some high tech naval equipment.  I should be able to reverse engineer the plans and have this equipment available for you shortly!', 27791), -- Equipment Blueprint: Ghostly Spyglass
(34466, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm. This staff looks familiar. I wonder...$b$bYou did the right thing bringing it to me. I will investigate further!', 27791), -- Mysterious Staff
(38446, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will be a difficult campaign to be sure.', 27791), -- Commander in the Field!
(39581, 6, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice! You\'re quite the slayer, $n. Gimmie a low-five!', 27791), -- Demonslayer of Tanaan
(39433, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will continue to need your help until this world is free of whatever terrible presence Gul\'dan has invited to destroy us.', 27791), -- Unseen Influence
(38578, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will speak more of this later, but thank you.', 27791), -- A Message of Terrible Import
(39601, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I look forward to seeing your impressive fleet of battleships, commander.', 27791); -- I Sunk Your Battleship
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(44240, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our hearts and minds are with you, $n.', 27843), -- Orange is the New Purple
(38945, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a shame. Without the ability to do any stitching, we can hardly do anything with this fabric.$b$b<Tanithria pouts.>$b$bStill, there ARE patterns we know that don\'t require stitching. Shoulderpads are easy, and belts should be a cinch.', 27843), -- This Should Be Simple... Right?
(38944, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now this... this I can work with!$b$bReminds me of some old night elven festival cloth I\'ve seen.', 27843), -- Sew It Begins
(42213, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Archmage Khadgar has set aside a space here for the Tidestone of Golganneth, as well as the rest of the Pillars of Creation.>', 27843), -- The Tidestone of Golganneth
(38203, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, outsider! Thank you very much.$b$BYou have done more for me than my own people ever have.$b$bLady Challiane would never take the word of a lowly cellarman over her vintners.$b$bNow I can use this recipe to earn her favor, and then the favor of our beloved queen Azshara...', 27843), -- Challiane Vineyards
(38286, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Tidestone of Golganneth stands whole and unprotected.>', 27843), -- Wrath of Azshara
(42696, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n! I can see that the Hall of the Guardian is in good hands.', 27843), -- Tech It Up A Notch
(42687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was very lucky that we found Chronicler Elrianne among the survivors. A well-respected archivist from the Kirin Tor, she also spent several months studying with the pandaren in their library in Tian Monastery.$B$BHer knowledge of ancient magic will be invaluable to our order.', 27843), -- Troops in the Field
(44547, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You are well-prepared to hunt down the next Pillar of Creation.>', 27843), -- Isle Hopping
(38656, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am impressed that you were able to defeat such a powerful demon. We are fortunate that you have lent us your aid.', 27843), -- Mark of the Demon
(38323, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thaon will be dearly missed. We may not have always seen eye to eye, but he was a great druid and a true protector of the vale.$b$bXavius will pay for his death...', 27843), -- Return to the Grove
(39354, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh thank you traveler! You have truly helped the forest today.', 27843), -- Wisp in the Willows
(42751, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My wounds are great, and my magic has been severely drained. I must recover from this enervation and return to the Dreamgrove.\n\nThe owlkin here are beyond saving by mortal hands, but perhaps Elune will one day shine her light upon them again.\n\nThank you, $n. May your path be blessed.', 27843), -- Moon Reaver
(42786, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These remains... this is horrible! They are turning dryads into mindless piles of ooze!', 27843), -- Grotesque Remains
(42750, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew Leirana... she was one of Remulos\' favored, and kindhearted soul. If he has been captured as she believes, we have no time to mourn her passing.', 27843), -- Dreamcatcher
(42747, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wish it did not have to come to this, truly.', 27843), -- Where the Wildkin Are
(42748, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The owlbeasts are... melting the dryads down and using their bones to create minions?! How... how could this even be?', 27843), -- Emerald Sisters
(38862, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Until I can discover what is vexing the Thistleleaf, I\'ll have to look after the Lunarwing eggs. At least I know they will be safe.', 27843), -- Thieving Thistleleaf
(40221, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'On behalf of the Lunarwings, thank you.', 27843), -- Spread Your Lunarwings and Fly
(40220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should set those vexing Thorndancers on their way.', 27843), -- Thorny Dancing
(42423, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm. This appears to be Archmage Vargoth\'s notes on the Nightborne Soulstone. Supposedly the energy of captured souls stored within it can be channeled directly from the stone! If that\'s true, it is very powerful, indeed!', 27843), -- Archmage Vargoth's Retreat
(42416, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If it is true that Archmage Vargoth is exploring fel magic, I will be shocked! Still, we owe you our thanks in bringing this matter to our attention.', 27843), -- The Council is in Session
(50432, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Spectacular! Marvelous! At last, I understand fully, and the titans themselves speak to me! They have shown me how to use the essences to craft the finest armors the world has ever seen, though I think the results may be... somewhat unpredictable.$b$b<Vridiel beams with pride.>$b$bWell, what are you waiting for? Bring me as many Wakening Essence as you can find!', 27843), -- Titanic Innovation
(42954, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Books on magical illnesses? I might know where such a thing exists...', 27843), -- A Small Favor
(42705, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'I have been Archmage Vargoth\'s apprentice for far too long. Perhaps it is time for me to serve a new master. I would be honored if you would accept me as your champion, $n.', 27843), -- Champion: Ravandwyr
(42706, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'You and I have proven to be quite successful together. I\'d be happy to lend you my swords and spells against the Burning Legion anytime, $n.', 27843), -- Champion: Esara Verrinde
(42222, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ravandwyr speaks very highly of how you dealt with the Empyrean Society, $n.', 27843), -- Empyrean Society Report
(44098, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you, $n. My apprentices are learning rapidly and are ready to serve you.', 27843), -- Recruiting Apprentices
(42171, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for uncovering the truth about the Empyrean Society, $n!', 27843), -- Final Exit
(42206, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I like you, $n. You don\'t hesitate to take action when necessary!', 27843), -- The Next Level Has Arrived
(42149, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'d better take those back to the Hall of the Guardian for safekeeping, $n.', 27843), -- Some Knowledge Shouldn't Be Shared
(42166, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re using fel magic. I knew there was something off about them, but I never suspected this!', 27843), -- What Is Going On Here?
(42435, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Now we should be able to enter the Empyrean Society enclave and have a look around.', 27843), -- Prepare To Be Assimilated
(42434, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good; you found me, $n.', 27843), -- A Covert Operation
(42418, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have we met before? Your face seems a bit familiar.', 27843), -- An Unexpected Visitor
(42433, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your champion has discovered some very powerful artifacts, $n!', 27843), -- Ancient Magic
(42429, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, your eyes gleam with newfound knowledge, $n.$b$bThat staff of yours has seen the passing of many mortal lifetimes. <Cough> It can teach you a great many things, if you\'re willing to listen.$b$bAs for its memories... they may be unreliable. You may find a different reflection haunts the streets of Dalaran each day. I leave it to you to find them all.', 27843), -- Memories of Ebonchill
(42479, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your ability continues to astound me! Balaadur lies dead in his own realm, and you now wield Ebonchill. I look forward to seeing what you will do next.', 27843), -- The Mage Hunter
(42477, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our order suffered a great loss that day. It is a shame we chose to hide it instead of study it.$b$bYou have another critical element to the ritual, and we are one step closer.', 27843), -- Daio the Decrepit
(42476, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is better than I hoped. A working ward prototype and the ritual notes as well!$b$bI\'m beginning to believe this is possible!', 27843), -- The Deadwind Site
(42455, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! Honestly, I\'m surprised you mages no longer use Mana Gems. I found them terribly useful.$b$bAt any rate, these will make up for the lack of additional mages.', 27843), -- Alodi's Gems
(42452, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'From the texts you found, it is clear that Ebonchill is in the hands of Balaadur. There is no way he would not claim such a powerful staff.$b$bThat is a problem, but not an impossible one. All we need to do is get access to Balaadur.', 27843), -- Finding Ebonchill
(44310, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it shall be done.', 27843), -- Thrice the Power
(42127, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. These troops will be invaluable in our fight against the Burning Legion. Deploy them on missions, just as you would with our champions.', 27843), -- Building Our Troops
(42126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your champion did well! Archmage Omniara agreed to join us and is getting situated as we speak.', 27843), -- Archmage Omniara
(42703, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $n. The fires of Azeroth give us the power to see beyond ourselves.', 27843), -- Technical Wizardry
(11997, 603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Felo\'melorn... I can barely believe that such great power is locked within a blade as beautiful as this!$b$bWith this weapon in your hands, the Legion will surely fall!', 27843), -- The Frozen Flame
(40270, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our next journey will be to Icecrown, $n.$b$bThere, in the heart of the Scourge, we will find Felo\'melorn.', 27843), -- The Path of Atonement
(40267, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, I\'m glad you came.$b$bI\'ve found information on just the thing we need to turn this war in our favor.', 27843), -- An Unexpected Message
(43441, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is decided then.', 27843), -- A Second Weapon
(42663, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Archmage Kalec and Archmage Modera are two of the greatest mages in Azeroth\'s present and past. They will be exemplary representatives of our order.', 27843), -- Rise, Champions
(42662, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'The blue dragonflight has always represented magic on Azeroth, and it is fitting that we work together against the Burning Legion now more than ever. I would be honored to fight for you as your champion in these dark times.', 27843), -- Champion: Archmage Kalec
(42685, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'It is good to see the Tirisgarde rise again, $n. While not everyone on the Council of Six agrees with me, I believe it is imperative for us to work together and defeat the Burning Legion once and for all!', 27843), -- Champion: Archmage Modera
(42175, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you here, $n. There is much to be done!', 27843), -- Growing Power
(41141, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright, then! I can get started recruiting, and you can get to taking the fight to the demons!$B$BYeah, I know I\'m letting you take the easy job, but hey, what are friends for?', 27843), -- A Conjuror's Duty
(41124, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re a Conjuror now, huh? Fan-cy!$B$BWe\'ve got a good start with this Tirisgarde thing here, but I think we should keep up the recruiting if we actually plan on invading demon-town.$B$BFortunately for you, nobody negotiates contracts like a goblin!', 27843), -- The Tirisgarde Reborn
(41113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I understand he may be unconventional, but I think this goblin is exactly what we\'ll need to quickly get this new Tirisgarde up to snuff for the task at hand.$B$BI\'ve already sent word to many talented mages who can help. They await transportation to the Hall, where they can begin their new purpose.$B$BShall we?', 27843), -- The Only Way to Travel
(41112, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You could say you\'ve got my attention, pal!$B$BSo you\'re looking to hire me on full-time, eh? Well if the future payoffs are anything like this, I\'d say you\'ve got yourself a deal.', 27843), -- The Great Akazamzarak
(41114, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You learn quickly, $n. $B$BI think Kathra\'natir will rue the day he made you his enemy.', 27843), -- The Champion's Return
(42011, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my gratitude for saving Azuregos, $n. I can rest easy knowing that the Nexus is under his care.$B$BAs for you, I can see you\'re full of surprises. Never in my time have I seen a mage who can control the chaotic energies of Aluneth. $B$BThank you for what you have done for me and my kind today. You are truly the hero we need to face the Legion.', 27843), -- The Nexus Vault
(42010, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Azuregos!$B$BHe must have returned to the Nexus to secure the vault. Malygos always trusted him to watch over the magical artifacts in the care of the flight.$B$BI\'m afraid I must ask another favor of you, $n.', 27843), -- Arcane Unleashed
(42009, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you are able to harness the energies of Aluneth. It has been a long time since there was a $c that could control it.\n\nNow, are you prepared to unleash it?', 27843), -- Harnessing the Arcane
(42008, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems that the Ethereum has gleaned how to use Malygos\'s surge needles to bore deeper into the Twisting Nether.$B$BI believe we might be able to use these devices against them.', 27843), -- Eyes of the Dragon
(42007, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the Ethereum has taken the Nexus... and yet, that seems the least of our worries.$B$BTheir plan to widen the breach into the Twisting Nether poses a threat to all of Azeroth. It seems fate has set you on this path for a reason, $n. Not only must you recover the weapon you seek, but you must put a stop to the Ethereum as well!$B$BI regret that I cannot assist you more directly, but I will guide you as I can.', 27843), -- A Forgotten Enemy
(42006, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This appears to be a communication device commonly utilized by the ethereals.$B$BPerhaps it could be the key to finding out who is behind the happenings at the Dragonshrine.', 27843), -- A New Threat
(42001, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you seek Aluneth? A dangerous weapon, to be sure.\n\nLong ago the Kirin Tor entrusted the blue dragonflight with its safekeeping. It was locked away in the only place that could contain its rampant power  - the Nexus Vault.\n\nI have not been there in some time, however. After the blue dragonflight was dissolved, the Nexus was all but abandoned. There is no knowing whether the Nexus Vault is still intact - or what may be waiting in the Nexus itself.', 27843), -- Aluneth, Greatstaff of the Magna
(41085, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a wise choice. $B$BIt should serve you well in our hunt for Kathra\'natir.', 27843), -- A Mage's Weapon
(41036, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In times past, the Council of Tirisfal called upon the Tirisgarde, the protectors of Dalaran, to do battle in the Guardian\'s absence.$B$BIt is clear now that the hall of the Tirisgarde must be rebuilt to face this new threat.$B$BI need your help to accomplish this. First of all, you\'ll need to know how to get to this hall. I will show you.', 27843), -- The Dreadlord's Prize
(41035, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was a fool. I thought that I could banish Kathra\'natir once and for all, but instead the dreadlord broke free.$B$BIn the years he spent trapped within my body, he must have been privy to my secrets... such as those of the Council of Tirisfal.$b$bThe damage he could do with this knowledge is unthinkable. He must be stopped.', 27843), -- Felstorm's Plea
(39874, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m relieved you\'ve come, $n. We could certainly use another enchanter in the shop at a time like this.', 27843), -- Some Enchanted Evening
(44663, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n, it\'s good to see you on your feet! The members of the Council of Six are recuperating from their ordeal.$b$bThe intensity of the teleportation spell can be disorienting. It seems you lost consciousness for a time, but at least you didn\'t awaken to find yourself stuck in a wall!$b$bDalaran has been relocated to the Broken Isles. From here, we will spearhead the effort to acquire the Pillars of Creation and drive the Legion from Azeroth once and for all!', 27843); -- In the Blink of an Eye
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(51140, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some people would have just run off with this, but you didn\'t! We\'ll split this up into two hundred and fourteen shares. Here\'s your cut.', 27980), -- Share the Wealth
(50691, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I almost trust you $r.', 27980), -- Not On Our Payroll
(50704, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll make good money off these. No one will know they are used parts.', 27980), -- Anchors Aweigh Too Much
(50696, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got the coins, and only mild radiation poisoning.', 27980), -- Fun With Magnets
(50697, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Boom!  Problem solved.', 27980), -- Bomb Beats Rock
(50675, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw you killing those Irontide, you want in on our action?', 27980), -- Treasure Hunting
(50674, 21, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'You\'ve got skills we could use. You want join us and find the treasure before the Irontide?', 27980), -- Two Faced Pirate Scum
(50802, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No one\'s gonna cry about a few less pirates.  I may even dance about it!', 27980), -- Iron Low Tide
(50810, 21, 396, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'With everyone free, we can get back to finding the treasure!', 27980), -- Break 'Em Out
(51554, 21, 396, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Lea Martin?  She\'s a tough one!  I\'ll try to help her, but we gotta save our people first.', 27980), -- Reloading
(52876, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One less threat to safety of Stormsong', 27980), -- WANTED: War Gore
(51712, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe you actually pulled that off. We may actually stand a fighting chance now!', 27980), -- Eye for an Eye
(49887, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At least not all of the tidesages have turned on us.$B$BNot yet.', 27980), -- Forced Labor
(49704, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! Here, let me take a closer look.', 27980), -- Haywire Harvesters
(49706, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Independence?!$B$BThis is too far. A shattered Kul Tiras will never stand!', 27980), -- Proclamation Investigation
(49705, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is much work to be done, but not at the cost of our own people\'s lives.', 27980), -- Unnecessary Duress
(49703, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What has become of our people...', 27980), -- House Stormsong
(49725, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, Brother Alen sent you. Good.', 27980), -- A Risky Ploy
(51401, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like more trouble.', 27980), -- Carry On
(51490, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work! Now these fine people can go about their lives.', 27980), -- Border Issues
(51489, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s going on here?!', 27980), -- Time to Leave
(46268, 403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As the king examines the compass, his expression turns from recognition to sorrow.>$b$bWhen I went through my father\'s things and didn\'t find this compass, I assumed it was with him on the Broken Shore when Gul\'dan...$b$b<The king\'s voice breaks.>', 27980), -- A Found Memento
(44176, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The heavy chest offers plenty of room to carry all of your belongings.', 27980), -- The Conveniences of Home
(47182, 603, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a true hero, $n. Even though the demons freed Raalgar and thought him immortal, he was no match for you! Perhaps the Fel Heart will be of use to you. It is now available in the Matrix Core.', 27980), -- Long Overdue
(48280, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our answer lies in the Legion\'s own portal network in the heart of Antorus.', 27980), -- Visions of Another
(48277, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ye came just in the nick of time.', 27980), -- The Speaker Seeks
(47134, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did your best, $n, but the demons won this round.$b$bIt won\'t take Raalgar long to gather his power to attack us. But I have learned the source of his immortality while you were gone!', 27980), -- Foiling the Legion's Jailbreak
(47104, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'High Inquisitor Raalgar? A fearsome creature but he has been held securely in the Arcatraz at Tempest Keep for a very long time. $b$bIf the Legion plans to free him then they must know that he is particularly dangerous to us.', 27980), -- Imprisoned Inquisitor
(47554, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Skara and Brae gave their lives to get us this information and the codebook. Their sacrifice will not be forgotten.$b$bNow, let us decipher the orders and see what the Legion is up to.', 27980), -- Intercepting the Legion's Plans
(47102, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve found one of our scouting reports? It was overdue, and I feared it had been intercepted by the enemy.$b$b<The captain looks over the letter.>$b$bYes, this is what I\'ve been expecting. The Legion is planning something and this is the breakthrough we\'ve been looking for!', 27980), -- The Mysterious Missive
(46510, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s... Wet. This thing is most likely worthless now.$B$BIs there a good piece of treasure on this cursed island? I may not be the brightest tool in the bag, but I\'m starting to think this place doesn\'t really fit my \"chance of death versus treasure\" ratio.', 27980), -- Ship Graveyard
(46509, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you bother to read the label on this potion? I\'m going to assume, no. You may find some sucker who will pay you for it.$B$BBetter luck next time kid.', 27980), -- Tomb Raidering
(46501, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found a key in a chest? Nothing else?$B$BI\'m guessing the last guy took all the goods, then accidentally locked the key in the chest. So, you just found a key to a chest that you\'ve already looted. Fantastic work... And people say I suck at this job.', 27980), -- Grave Robbin'
(46935, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Legion uses these beacons to communicate with their fleet up above. If we were to find more of these...', 27980), -- The Shadow of the Sentinax
(46251, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It has been pointed out to me that I can, on occasion, get a bit carried away.$b$bThis... <clears throat> might possibly have been one of those times.$b$bA single Nethershard will suffice for my purposes. I\'m certain you can put the rest to good use.$b$bLet\'s not speak of this again.', 27980), -- Shard Times
(47137, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another powerful ally recruited to our cause!$b$bYou have bolstered our strength against the Legion once more, $n.', 27980), -- Champions of Legionfall
(46782, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our power grows.', 27980), -- Further Advancement
(46043, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Archmage, the events of the past have long weighed heavily upon me. While I do not regret my actions, I do regret what happened. If I could go back and change things...$b$bI hope in time the Kirin Tor - indeed, all of Azeroth - will better understand my loyalties. Thanks to you, crisis has been averted. Please accept my enduring gratitude.', 27980), -- Champion: Aethas Sunreaver
(46290, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must not forget that this is a temporary measure. I cannot overstate the devastation that will ensue if Kathra\'natir escapes... $b$bStill, thanks to you, Dalaran\'s teeth are sharpened once more. Well done, Archmage $n!', 27980), -- Return of the Archmage
(46000, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, Archmage $n! Dalaran can defend herself once again.$b$bFor all of our sakes, let us hope that the shields keeping Kathra\'natir imprisoned do not fail before we are able to find a safer solution.', 27980), -- Arming Dalaran
(45586, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. The Soulstone\'s shields should be sufficiently strengthened now.', 27980), -- Shield Amplification
(45614, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Felborne will respect the Tirisgarde now, do you not agree?', 27980), -- Lady Remor'za
(45251, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us get to work, shall we?', 27980), -- Redundancy
(46351, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this?$b$bThis is not just any old shield generator - it is almost... a sentient entity...$b$bAnd it is very eager for a job to do. Yes, I think it will be quite content to work with us.', 27980), -- Keep it Secret, Keep it Safe
(44770, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Few texts written by the ancient shal\'dorei remain. I am sure the Tirisgarde\'s librarians will be thrilled with these!', 27980), -- Secrets of the Shal'dorei
(44768, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That is one less Legion supporter we need to worry about. Oh, and you found a shield generator too? Wonderful!', 27980), -- Nyell's Workshop
(46345, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think we have stumbled upon their headquarters. Be careful in here!', 27980), -- Into the Hornet's Nest
(46339, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This appears to be some sort of attunement crystal. Perfect.', 27980), -- Keymaster Orlis
(46705, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Revenge is so sweet. Thank you.', 27980), -- Retaliation
(45207, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve heard so much about you, Archmage $n. It is a pleasure to finally meet you!', 27980), -- The Nightborne Apprentice
(46338, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So word has gotten out about Ryanna already? Ha!', 27980), -- A Creative Solution
(46335, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s quite the eclectic collection if I ever saw one!$b$bThese are all powerful in their own way to be sure, but none are useable for our needs. At least not in their current form.$b$bI wonder...', 27980), -- The Vault of the Tirisgarde
(44766, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm. An interesting challenge!', 27980), -- Backup Plan
(45437, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have been unfairly maligned by many. I am glad the Tirisgarde does not fall prey to petty rumors!', 27980), -- An Urgent Situation
(46247, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fine victory, $ct.$b$bBut do not grow complacent! Fight back against the Legion wherever they strike.', 27980), -- Defending Broken Isles
(46182, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our efforts today have prevailed over the Legion\'s presence, though let us not be remiss - our journey has only just begun.', 27980), -- Battle for Highmountain
(45572, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must remember our allies who have fallen on this day and in their honor, continue our fight.$B$BThe time is upon us, $n. Our riders are ready. Let us show the Burning Legion the true strength of Highmountain.', 27980), -- Holding Our Ground
(45840, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My apologies, $n. I hope Aviash and I did not offend you. One cannot be too careful during times like these.', 27980), -- Assault on Highmountain
(50797, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re arrival is most timely. We could use your help!', 27980), -- A Turtle's Invitation
(50956, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<A small advance from Leo, against my share of the loot.>', 27980), -- Walking-Around Money
(50742, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Plundered McGee\'s treasure? Who\'s the pirate now!', 27980), -- All Laid Out For Us
(50803, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m going to be a rich man! You\'re not holding out on me are ya?', 27980), -- I Want It All Now
(50955, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never liked his cat.', 27980), -- We're Not Friends
(52132, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was hard, but it had to be done.', 27980), -- The Proof of Piracy
(50793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s the Irontide! They\'ve found treasure in the caves below us!', 27980), -- Cave Commotion
(50774, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saved Earl-E! I am forever grateful $r.', 27980), -- No Bot Left Behind
(50733, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve filled them in on most of the details already. The Storm\'s Wake will be an invaluable ally if we\'re to reunite Kul Tiras.', 27980), -- A New Dawn
(52800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most of those hostages have seen better days, but they will recover quickly. With Tol Dagor out of the way, Ashvane is quickly running out of places to hide.', 27980), -- Tol Dagor: The Ashvane Overseer
(48770, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Franklin rambles almost incoherently, explaining the mechanics of mining storm silver from a seam>$b$b... and that is how you... get the most of mining... Zzz...$b$b<As Franklin drifts to sleep amidst a pungent cloud of alcohol vapors, you think of the advice he provided.$b$bEager to experiment with your new mining technique, you leave the sleeping man laying where he is.>', 27980), -- Three Sheets to the Wind
(51720, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As the key clicks into place and the new core activates, a low hum begins emitting from the shredder. It accelerates into a high pitched whirring as the instrument panels light up all over the cockpit.>', 27980), -- Get Shredded
(51723, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. That\'ll definitely put a damper on things.', 27980), -- Saw Dusted
(51728, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nothing quite like the smell of freshly roasted Orc!', 27980), -- Burn It All Down
(51881, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A flamethrower!? This could be quite useful, but why couldn\'t you find one in better shape?', 27980), -- The Mine Sweeper
(51752, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully his death throws a wrench into their operation.', 27980), -- Grizzled
(51711, 153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sheesh... with all those explosions, I expect there\'s no one even left alive in that mine.', 27980), -- Having a Blast
(51726, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for rescuing us, we\'d have been trapped in here until we all slowly perished.', 27980), -- Get Out of Here
(52065, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Patrick\'s a good person.  If he trusts you, your help is welcome.', 27980), -- Worse Than It Looks
(51217, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One less Horde in Stormsong.', 27980), -- WANTED: Yarsel'ghun
(50909, 21, 396, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'This is a good start.', 27980), -- Never Outgunned
(50910, 21, 396, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Your skills are impressive.  I don\'t think any of us could have taken out those keenblades so easily.', 27980), -- Dangerous Game
(50908, 21, 396, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'With you around, they won\'t try this again.', 27980), -- Smells Like Trouble
(51159, 21, 396, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'This is an unexpected surprise!', 27980), -- Bring out the Big Gun
(49755, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those were some explosions! I\'m just glad they were directed at the Horde and not us.', 27980), -- Heavy Artillery
(49746, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bombs, fire, Horde. Our town will endure it all.', 27980), -- Dousing the Flames
(49745, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Banshee Queen is not like the previous Warchiefs.', 27980), -- You Have Their Orders
(49744, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These look particularly nasty. I\'m glad they aren\'t blowing up in our faces.', 27980), -- Bombs, Away
(51552, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This can\'t be happening...', 27980), -- The Days Are Just Packed
(50825, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I pray we are not too late. The fleet must return home.', 27980), -- Shrine of the Storm: Whispers Below
(50824, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Samuel was a good man, with a true heart. A fool... but our fool.', 27980), -- Storm's End
(51319, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thought this moment would never come.', 27980), -- The Final Ascent
(51320, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can feel the wards\' power waning even now. This is our chance to strike.', 27980), -- Sealed Fate
(51278, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mourn not for the fallen. We do what we must to save our people.', 27980), -- Lost and Forgotten
(50781, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The way is opened at last.', 27980), -- A Bridge Too Far
(50784, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the only way into the Shrine of the Storm.', 27980), -- Eye of the Storm
(50783, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, Lord Stormsong\'s definitely aware of us now.', 27980), -- The Abyssal Council
(50778, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their rituals are growing bolder. Sooner or later they\'re going to summon something they can\'t control.', 27980), -- Twisted Intentions
(50777, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw some of the defectors leaving. I\'m glad we got to them before Lord Stormsong did.', 27980), -- The Storm Awakens
(50780, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see it deemed you worthy. Good.', 27980), -- Oathbound
(50612, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With any luck we will end this matter here.', 27980), -- A House Divided
(50611, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A pivotal step, but our work is far from finished.', 27980), -- Storm's Vengeance
(50610, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now to finish the deed.', 27980), -- Gathering Storm
(50608, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Each death brings this valley one step closer to redemption.', 27980), -- Forbidden Rites
(50609, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was a tight spot you got me out of back there. I owe ya my life.', 27980), -- From the Maw of Madness
(50593, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This tideblood is saturated with dark magic. Thank you for bringing it to me.', 27980), -- A Bloody Mess
(50594, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Abyssal Melody lies unprotected. Now is our chance.', 27980), -- Beneath the Veil
(50595, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re holding out alright thanks to you, but Sam is still missing!', 27980), -- No Quarter
(49998, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must help the others before they are overrun!', 27980), -- Voices Below
(52796, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.  I can rest easy knowing they are safe.', 27980), -- Sometimes Less Is More
(52793, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.  I can rest easy knowing they are safe.', 27980), -- Circle the Wagons
(52795, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No more smelling it\'s breath in the wind.', 27980), -- A Saur Point
(50553, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, we had quite the adventure $p.\n\nLet\'s try not to do that again anytime soon though!', 27980), -- Back to the Lab
(50534, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelous! Slaying their leader ought to put some fear into \'em.', 27980), -- Wendigo Away
(50165, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! Did you see the look of sheer terror on their faces when they saw the bee swarms? \n\nMarvelous!', 27980), -- The Bee Team
(50493, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ancel will be happy to know that Wrex is safe and sound!', 27980), -- Fetching Wrex
(50264, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Encased in honey, just waiting to be eaten. That must have been absolutely terrifying!', 27980), -- Free the Farmhands
(50504, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thought I was a goner for sure!', 27980), -- Honey Glazed Sam
(50162, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hope you didn\'t have any problems with bees. No, of course not... why would you? \n\nThey\'re totally harmless.', 27980), -- Sticky Situation
(50168, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you still have both of your eyes!', 27980), -- Royal Succession
(50161, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, hah! Ancel sent you to find me, huh?\n\nHey, you found my boots too!? Marvelous!', 27980), -- Recovering Raimond
(50064, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The brue, I saw it. He didn\'t make it up!!', 27980), -- Don't Go in the Basement
(50070, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... we checked everywhere.', 27980), -- Detective Mildenhall
(50359, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for getting rid of those things, $n.', 27980), -- Cleanup Duty
(50343, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where did all of these things come from?', 27980), -- Mayhem at Mildenhall Meadery
(51582, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ancel is nearly hysterical.>', 27980), -- Make it Mildenhall
(49997, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never thought Reid would succumb to darkness. Things are worse than I feared.', 27980), -- Storm's Judgment
(49996, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This valley belongs to its people. We must fight to make it whole again!', 27980), -- Rearmament
(50139, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A cipher? Of course! But by the great sea, what\'s it covered in?!', 27980), -- The Missing Link
(49995, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew they\'d still have \'em! If you ever want something gone, $Glad:lass; you\'d best destroy it yourself.', 27980), -- Fabricated Fabrications
(49975, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for aiding me in my solemn task.', 27980), -- Rest in the Depths
(49794, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This does not bode well.', 27980), -- The Rising Tide
(49792, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I owe you one, stranger!', 27980), -- Bound and Oppressed
(49791, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done. We will release them somewhere a bit more peaceful.', 27980), -- Lost, Not Forgotten
(49793, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those initiates were nowhere near ready to wield our sacred implements. They are far better served in our hands.', 27980), -- Means to an End
(51488, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'d rather not stick around to see if he\'s right.', 27980), -- Archived Knowledge
