(45262, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There. I certainly hope Ly\'leth has good news...', 27980), -- A Message From Ly'leth
(44814, 273, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These people owe their lives to your bravery. They will not forget the risks we have taken for them.', 27980), -- Waning Refuge
(44727, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. We had no hope of rescue before you came along.', 27980), -- Smuggled!
(44726, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Let us leave before they call in reinforcements.', 27980), -- In the Business of Souls
(44725, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for taking this risk. Let us put an end to this now!', 27980), -- Hostage Situation
(44723, 1, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully more will follow their example.$b$bThank you for showing them another way to serve the Nightborne.', 27980), -- More Like Me
(44724, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Silgryn stares grimly at the communicator.>', 27980), -- Missing Persons
(44722, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad you could make it.', 27980), -- Disillusioned Defector
(45261, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, now to set our attention to those still suffering within the city.', 27980), -- Continuing the Cure
(44955, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She looked good. The Arcan\'dor truly is a miracle for our people.$b$bShe is a welcome ally in the fight to come. Silgryn will take good care of her.', 27980), -- Visitor in Shal'Aran
(42889, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When you suddenly vanished from our awareness we thought the worst.$b$bI do not know what to make of your adventures... I will need time to process this tragedy.$b$bRegardless, I am glad you are back safe and sound.', 27980), -- The Way Back Home
(38694, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oculeth has anticipated our arrival. Good, one less thing to worry on.', 27980), -- Regroup
(38720, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you managed to find some survivors. Good, that is a weight off my mind.', 27980), -- No Reason to Stay
(38692, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It had to be done.', 27980), -- Answering Aggression
(38695, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Someone must have informed the Grand Magistrix of Vanthir\'s involvement in the rebellion. Such violence is...$b$bElisande... How could you?', 27980), -- Crackdown
(38649, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Something is amiss. I can feel it in my bones.', 27980), -- Silence in the City
(45260, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will ask this of you again, as more fruit is ready.$B$BFor now, we have some disturbing news to discuss.', 27980), -- One Day at a Time
(43314, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Thalyssra clutches the spellstone tightly for a moment.>$b$bHe brought this upon himself.$b$bI cannot linger in the past. Elisande is weaker without him, and we are one step closer to righting the wrongs inflicted upon the shal\'dorei.', 27980), -- Beware the Fury of a Patient Elf
(42491, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! I will study this immediately.', 27980), -- Long Buried Knowledge
(42490, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. It is one thing I no longer need to think about.', 27980), -- Opening the Arcway
(43596, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the dread ship sundered, the souls of the dead will know their judgement. $B$BOdyn will have his champions, and the Tideskorn will have their honor.', 27980), -- Piercing the Mists
(40567, 273, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Praise Elune and all that her light touches... Malfurion is alive.$b$bI thought I would spend the rest of my days alone, dreaming of the choices I did not make.$b$bThank you. Thank you for returning my love to me.', 27980), -- Enter the Nightmare
(43349, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Aegis of Aggramar is secure within the well-defended city of Dalaran.$B$BYour quest to drive back the Legion is one step closer to fruition.', 27980), -- The Aegis of Aggramar
(42454, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Archmage Khadgar has set aside a space here for the Hammer of Khaz\'goroth, as well as the rest of the Pillars of Creation.>', 27980), -- The Hammer of Khaz'goroth
(40072, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the God-King\'s defeat, the Aegis of Aggramar is yours to claim.', 27980), -- Securing the Aegis
(39781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It was a hard fight, but necessary. $p, on behalf of the Rivermane, the Skyhorn, the Stonedark, I thank you for your efforts.$b$bBut where one battle ends, another begins. When you stand against the coming of the Burning Legion, know that the tribes of Highmountain stand with you.', 27980), -- Neltharion's Lair
(41186, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you, $n. I hope you\'re as interested about the tauren here as I am.', 27980), -- History of Highmountain
(48505, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Told you I knew how to find it!', 27980), -- Lovesick and Lost
(48516, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pleasure doin\' business with you.$B$BIn the future I\'ll make sure you get a special discount. Heh.', 27980), -- Toxic Community
(48419, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ugh... Was I... Was I crying?$B$BLet\'s agree to never speak of this again.', 27980), -- Lured and Allured
(48421, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Keelson looks up at you from a pile of siren corpses.>$B$BI need a drink.', 27980), -- Blood in the Tides
(49181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is that?$B$B<Jane takes the locket and opens it tenderly. Tears begin to well up in her eyes as she closes it and tucks it away in her jacket.>$B$BThank you.', 27980), -- Glimmering Locket
(49226, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By quieting their deadly song, you have saved countless lives.', 27980), -- Silencing the Sisters
(49178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I didn\'t think you\'d actually find all this stuff!$B$BWe don\'t have much, but here\'s a little something for your troubles.', 27980), -- My Favorite Things
(49230, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you\'re a lifesaver!$B$BHang on just a sec, I\'ll cook these up in no time!', 27980), -- Local Flavor
(49218, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you must be from the latest wreck. Those damn sirens are getting bolder by the day.', 27980), -- The Castaways
(47489, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You alright, mate? I\'m afraid your ship\'s gone.$B$BSomethin\' tells me you weren\'t really a part o\' that crew anyway, were ya? Har har!', 27980), -- Stow and Go
(53041, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, I\'ll hang onto them for now.$B$BI think I\'ve found our next lead.', 27980), -- Sampling the Goods
(50531, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Flynn pretends not to notice you, but whispers at you.>$B$BOf course it\'s her.', 27980), -- Under Their Noses
(50573, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most folks workin\' for the Ashvane Trading Company don\'t know how rotten they are, or don\'t have any other choice.$B$BThe sooner we take down Priscilla the better.', 27980), -- Message from the Management
(47488, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These kids are gonna have it hard enough without being under Ashvane\'s thumb. Thanks for getting them out.', 27980), -- Small Haulers
(47486, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sounds like they\'re making a ton of this stuff and keeping it under wraps.$B$BThat\'s bad.', 27980), -- Suspicious Shipments
(47487, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nobody likes livin\' under the thumb of company men like that - they ain\'t gonna be missed.', 27980), -- Labor Dispute
(47485, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eh? What do you want?', 27980), -- The Ashvane Trading Company
(52654, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n. Good to see you again.\n\nWe have a job to do.', 27980), -- The War Campaign
(47181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Adds a kick, don\'t it?', 27980), -- The Smoking Gun
(47960, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maybe with your help we can restore the people\'s faith in Proudmoore leadership.', 27980), -- Tiragarde Sound
(47189, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll support you however we can.', 27980), -- A Nation Divided
(47186, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All set?\n\nGood timing. I have your briefing ready.', 27980), -- Sanctum of the Sages
(52128, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are ferry stations all along the interior coastline of the sound. Don\'t forget about them during your travels!', 27980), -- Ferry Pass
(46729, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve never seen Cyrus fired up like this!\n\nSounds like we have work to do.', 27980), -- The Old Knight
(47099, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ready to meet the Harbormaster himself?', 27980), -- Get Your Bearings
(52462, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And just like that, you\'re back in business. All the materials you put into making the item come back to you with the Scrap-O-Matic 1000.$b$bWell, maybe not ALL the materials, but hey, something\'s better than nothing, right?$b$bOh, and keep an eye out for explusom. It\'s what we\'ve discovered as a magical byproduct of the scrapping process.$b$bIt\'s quite potent and only shows up when we scrap really fancy stuff.', 27980), -- A Load of Scrap
(47098, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s hard to believe the Lord Admiral would willingly hand you and her daughter over to Lady Ashvane.\n\nShe must have had her reasons... right?', 27980), -- Out Like Flynn
(51341, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hope you had a nice nap. You\'re gonna need your strength.', 27980), -- Daughter of the Sea
(46728, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Home again, after all this time.', 27980), -- The Nation of Kul Tiras
(46727, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Horde have forced our hand yet again.\n\nThis cannot stand.', 27980), -- Tides of War
(51403, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Wyrmbane listens to your tale.>\n\nThe Heart of Azeroth... a powerful artifact indeed.  Thank the Light you were there to aid Magni.\n\nBut I fear I bear dire news, $n. While you were away, the Horde launched a brazen attack on Stormwind.\n\nI have a message for you from King Anduin. You must meet him at the keep at once.', 27980), -- The Speaker's Imperative
(52428, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was too close, $n! Now ye\'ve seen the true power of the Heart of Azeroth. \n\nBut we\'ve got a long way tae go before the world is healed.', 27980), -- Infusing the Heart
(51211, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Heart of Azeroth... that\'s the key tae healin\' her wounds!', 27980), -- The Heart of Azeroth
(52946, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ye made it. We don\'t have any time tae lose.', 27980), -- A Dying World
(50239, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your wisdom is always appreciated, $n. The choice you make today will strengthen the Alliance.', 27980), -- A Choice of Allies
(49929, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $n. I am pleased you answered the call.', 27980), -- The Call for Allies
(51795, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, good to see you back on your feet, $n. Many others were not so fortunate.\n\n<Halford lowers his head and whispers a prayer.>\n\nKing Anduin has returned to Stormwind Keep. He must plan what our next move will be.', 27980), -- The Battle for Lordaeron
(53370, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Horde will pay for what they\'ve done.', 27980), -- Hour of Reckoning
(43562, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must take drastic measures.', 27980), -- Giving It All We've Got
(44495, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps there is hope for outlanders after all.', 27980), -- Leyline Master
(43587, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you imbue the feed with the mana the structure stirs to life. Your skin tingles as the surrounding air becomes charged with arcane power.>', 27980), -- Leyline Feed: Elor'shan
(40907, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With my adversaries gone, I can claim leadership of Jandvik unopposed.', 27980), -- Removing Obstacles
(43588, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you imbue the feed with the mana the structure stirs to life. Your skin tingles as the surrounding air becomes charged with arcane power.>', 27980), -- Leyline Feed: Kel'balor
(40125, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never imagined I would spend my time in exile studying withered. Through them, I have learned a great deal about my own people, and the nature of our relationship with the Nightwell.', 27980), -- Branch of the Arcan'dor
(43502, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem our tree is quite thirsty.', 27980), -- A Change of Seasons
(43362, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not know how you obtained this, but I know it was not easy. Much stands against us, but you prevailed. Come. Let us restore the arcan\'dor.', 27980), -- The Stuff of Dreams
(44156, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must find a solution. We are running out of time.', 27980), -- Another Arcan'dor Closes...
(43360, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. This place will never recover, but their madness need not harm others.', 27980); -- The Shardmaidens
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(43361, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will study these carefully. If we are fortunate, there will be answers.', 27980), -- Fragments of Disaster
(44152, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must find a way...', 27980), -- A Growing Crisis
(44053, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She certainly is a worthy companion.', 27980), -- Friends With Benefits
(44561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In the changing of seasons, the truth will be revealed.', 27980), -- Seed of Hope
(43318, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We made great strides today. I will not forget this.', 27980), -- Ly'leth's Champion
(43317, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This may not end as cleanly as I would have preferred.', 27980), -- In the Bag
(43813, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The beacon glows as you infuse it with Ancient Mana.>', 27980), -- Sanctum of Order Teleporter Online!
(43313, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The city is buzzing with very interesting gossip, $n. Victory is that much closer.', 27980), -- Rumor Has It
(43315, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seemed as though you had that well in hand. I did not want to... interrupt.$b$bThat is one less power hoarding noble to worry about. Well done, $n.', 27980), -- Death Becomes Him
(44040, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know of Coryn. We will not underestimate his venom, rest assured.$b$bThank you for helping Aurore. She is a dear friend of mine.', 27980), -- Vote of Confidence
(43311, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well. Let us talk strategy.', 27980), -- Or Against Us
(43312, 5, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He is unharmed! I owe you- and Ly\'leth- a great debt.', 27980), -- Thinly Veiled Threats
(43310, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I love Lady Lunastre like a sister, but I am afraid my hands are tied.', 27980), -- Either With Us
(43309, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, $n.$b$bSo good to see you once again. I trust you are ready to assist me with my campaign.', 27980), -- The Perfect Opportunity
(44052, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a relief, if a small one. You have done well - rest for now.', 27980), -- And They Will Tremble
(42792, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They will not so easily dismiss the Dusk Lily now. Well done.', 27980), -- Make Your Mark
(42841, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pleasure doing business with you.', 27980), -- A Big Score
(43352, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re becoming quite the dependable associate.', 27980), -- Asset Security
(42840, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad to know you understand the value of my services, partner.', 27980), -- If Words Don't Work...
(43969, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will help you, but first I need you to do something for me.', 27980), -- Hired Help
(42839, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Steel yourself, $n.$b$bMargaux\'s loss is regrettable, but not likely to be the last in this effort. Far from it, I fear.', 27980), -- Seek the Unsavory
(44084, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Thalyssra is speechless for a moment.>', 27980), -- Vengeance for Margaux
(42838, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Margaux... no!', 27980), -- Reversal
(42836, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Much better. You have my thanks.', 27980), -- Silkwing Sabotage
(42837, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will have these... ah... souvenirs... boxed for you.', 27980), -- Balance to Spare
(42835, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will be certain to have a bottle of your arcwine prepared for you before you leave.', 27980), -- The Old Fashioned Way
(42834, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Simple, no?', 27980), -- Intense Concentration
(42833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, enjoying your tour?', 27980), -- How It's Made: Arcwine
(42832, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You may want to cleanse your palate - we craft some strong flavors here!', 27980), -- The Fruit of Our Efforts
(42829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me show you around, then.', 27980), -- Make an Entrance
(42828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm, yes. It is as I suspected.', 27980), -- Moths to a Flame
(42488, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How lucky we are that it could be recovered... thank you.', 27980), -- Thalyssra's Abode
(42489, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a comfort beyond words.', 27980), -- Thalyssra's Drawers
(41230, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These devices are peculiar. They are like the traps our hunters use, but can magically attract and trap nearby beasts.', 27980), -- Trapping Evolved
(41215, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. They do not respect the hunt, so they must be reminded of their place.', 27980), -- They Become The Hunted
(40617, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r. I will tend to Nighteyes\' wounds. Tell me what happened!', 27980), -- Turn Around, Nighteyes
(42223, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You could not have arrived at a better time, $r.', 27980), -- Scouting the Crimson Thicket
(41915, 574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well well, looks like that old fool finally met his match?$b$bIt looks like the Promenade is in need of a new jeweler, and I think I have learned all I could from my former master.$b$bHere is something for your efforts.', 27980), -- The Master's Legacy
(41146, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lespin shall pay for his crimes!', 27980), -- Elegant Design
(41465, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, see! I told you it would not tarnish. Now there\'s nothing linking me to that fool...$b$bWhat\'s that? A plot to weaken his position? Regardless, the damage has been done. Better safe than sorry.', 27980), -- Estate Jewelry: A Braggart's Brooch
(41466, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the Magistrix, I had forgotten how ugly that thing is. Impeccable workmanship, obviously. Just... ugh. I should melt the whole thing down.', 27980), -- Estate Jewelry: Haute Claw-ture
(43811, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The beacon glows as you infuse it with Ancient Mana.>', 27980), -- Lunastre Estate Teleporter Online!
(41320, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those wretched creatures are a scourge on our beautiful lands. At least they had good taste in their accessories.$b$bOr maybe they just like shiny things.', 27980), -- Pry It From Their Cold, Feral Claws
(41307, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. I shall have these melted down and turned into ingots for my next batch of commissions.', 27980), -- All That Glitters
(42493, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is true, then. Archmage Vargoth has been corrupted by the legion.', 27980), -- Impending Dooooooom!
(42494, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job, $n.', 27980), -- More Than Just A Food Vendor
(42521, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you are able to put Millhouse\'s determination to good use!', 27980), -- The Enemy of My Enemy...
(42508, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll keep them busy outside while you head in.', 27980), -- Not A Toothless Dragon
(42451, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $n.', 27980), -- Kalec's Plan
(42366, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kyrtos, you old fool! You should have known the risks...', 27980), -- The Bigger They Are, The Harder They Fel
(40642, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kyrtos greedily consumes the essence.>$b$bAhh, much better. My senses are focused and ready for research!', 27980), -- Power! Get The Power!
(40919, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can no longer hear their shrieking. Finally, peace and quiet!', 27980), -- Fel Bent for Leather
(40713, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... Within these pages lies the secret to true mastery of this power.', 27980), -- The Black Tome
(40694, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes...$b$bThis power is... different. Brutal, blunt, powerful.$b$bI can control it. I can master it!', 27980), -- One Small Step for Magic
(40657, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. By studying these materials I can better understand how they imbue magic into their machinery and architecture.', 27980), -- The Road to Fel
(40683, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fel magic is... strange. Almost slippery like an oil, and it burns long and hot. Maybe there\'s a connection...', 27980), -- Discovery Requires Experimentation
(40625, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This was all you could find? I suppose it will have to do, although it is a primitive instrument.', 27980), -- A Different Source
(40412, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With Azoran slain, the Legion has been dealt a crippling blow that they will not soon recover from.$b$bYou have my respect, $n.', 27980), -- Azoran Must Die
(41097, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Shard of Vorgos locks into position next to the portal. Swirling fel energy collects around the shard, filling the room with an ominous, dark presence.>', 27980), -- Shard of Vorgos
(41098, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Shard of Kozak locks into position next to the portal. You can feel the dark writhing of fel energy surround you as it collects near the portal.>', 27980), -- Shard of Kozak
(41309, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see a friendly face, I don\'t know how much longer I could have held out on my own!', 27980), -- Mangelrath
(41214, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Angus wipes away a tear as he speaks.>$b$bBrambley, lad... I promise ye\'ll have tha\' best burial money can buy! An\' all the ale ye can drink...', 27980), -- Parts Unknown
(41222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It canna\' be true!$b$bBrambley... my dear ol\' friend! Why did ye have to go an\' die?', 27980), -- Into The Pit!
(41140, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to finally be free from this dreadful cage. As thanks, I will keep my word to you and your grotesquely hairy friend.', 27980), -- Search and Rescue!
(43594, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you imbue the feed with the mana the structure stirs to life. Your skin tingles as the surrounding air becomes charged with arcane power.>', 27980), -- Leyline Feed: Halls of the Eclipse
