(46297, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now for the main weapon.', 27980), -- Overwhelming Power
(48483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A cowled figure... and it did not attack you?$B$BMost curious.', 27980), -- A Stranger's Plea
(47589, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We may yet stand a chance.', 27980), -- Righteous Fury
(46938, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Argus, homeworld of the Burning Legion.', 27980), -- Alone in the Abyss
(49445, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you\'ve no doubt learned, Primal Sargerite is a precious material which yields great power when infused with items. In our fight against the Legion, we need all the power we can get our hands on.$b$bBring me any Primal Sargerite you find and I will trade with you what I can.', 27980), -- The Prime Exchange
(48440, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must act quickly!', 27980), -- Into the Night
(47224, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have waited many years for this day.$B$BBehold the triumph of the draenei, the Vindicaar!', 27980), -- The Vindicaar
(47223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the Light you have arrived.', 27980), -- Light's Exodus
(47222, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May the Light protect us all this day.', 27980), -- Two If By Sea
(48506, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you were among those called for the expedition to Argus. There will be plenty of fighting ahead.', 27980), -- The Hand of Fate
(47330, 603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This warning is an ill omen indeed, $n. It seems the fate of Azeroth is tied to that of Argus, the homeworld of the Legion.$b$bWe must uncover the Dark Titan\'s plan! I believe the Speaker\'s connection to the world soul will prove crucial to our efforts.$b$bStay vigilant, $ct. We must trust in Magni\'s guidance... and Azeroth\'s as well.', 27980), -- Whispers of a Frightened World
(45861, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We hope the increased power to your weapon will prove useful on the Broken Shore and beyond.', 27980), -- A Gift From the Six
(45127, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Levia is safe? That is a relief, though I wish we could have reached her sooner. An imp mother is bad enough - I can\'t imagine what Agatha will be capable of with Levia\'s power. And who knows what secrets Levia shared while under her thrall?\n\nI\'m afraid that this battle may not be over yet.\n\nFor now, we should celebrate whatever victories we can get. Thank you for your assistance, $n.', 27980), -- Fel-Crossed Lovers
(45126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Disgusting! I can\'t believe I let myself fall under the spell of such a creature! \n\nI was such a fool! She made me think she really cared about me. In the end, it seems nothing I thought I knew about Agatha was true!', 27980), -- Unlikely Seduction
(45917, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What... what is going on? $B$BWho are you?', 27980), -- Following the Scent
(45125, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pleasantly surprised, $c. Without your quick thinking, your mage friend would be lost to Agatha.\n\nThe portal is stabilized, and should lead to the mage\'s location.', 27980), -- Dabbling in the Demonic
(45916, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The amount of power this Levia channeled into this portal is impressive, if unnecessary. Unfortunately, if we don\'t get it stable, it\'s likely to collapse and take us with it. $B$BSufficed to say, that would end your mission pretty quick.\n\nI have to concentrate to keep this open, so I\'ll need your help...', 27980), -- The Acolyte Imperiled
(46327, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are lucky that Modera contacted me for assistance. \n\nAgatha is beyond you, $c. She is beyond any of us.', 27980), -- Bargaining with Shadows
(47055, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it seems that Levia has fallen under the spell of a succubus\' seduction. I fear her time alone as an outcast must have left her vulnerable to such tactics. I cannot help but feel some guilt for her turning down this path.\n\nIn any case, Levia is in great danger. She must be found!', 27980), -- Fire: The Folly of Levia Laurence
(45866, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We hope the increased power to your weapon will prove useful on the Broken Shore and beyond.', 27980), -- A Gift From the Six
(45193, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Raest escaped? This is unfortunate. $B$BStill, I will rest easier knowing the Nethersworn cultists will no longer skulk in the streets of Dalaran. I thank you for that.$B$BThe Kirin Tor will set out at once to figure out how we can reach Raest in the Twisting Nether. I will send for you when we find a way to reach him.', 27980), -- One Step Behind
(45192, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re too late, the rift has closed!$B$BWe\'ll have to find another way to get to him.', 27980), -- Runes of Rending
(45190, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My brother is here!', 27980), -- Where it's Thinnest
(45188, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this, a cultist\'s manifesto?  $B$BSo Raest has really gone down a dark path, hasn\'t he?', 27980), -- The Wisdom of the Council
(45187, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, this definitely says... something.', 27980), -- Secrets in the Underbelly
(45185, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A letter? From one of the cultists? $B$BThat could be the lead we need!', 27980), -- Message from the Shadows
(45182, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You come from the Kirin Tor? So you\'ll help me find my brother?', 27980), -- Frost: The Twisted Twin
(45862, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We hope the increased power to your weapon will prove useful on the Broken Shore and beyond.', 27980), -- A Gift From the Six
(46340, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the daughter of Skovald followed in her father\'s footsteps? A pity, but it may have been inevitable. I believe this may be the \"fall\" the scrolls mentioned.\n\nIf this is true, there may still be hope! I will work on a way to get us into the Halls of Valor to pursue this Sigryn. I will be in touch when we find a way.\n\nIn the meantime, you have done a great service to bring her this far. I would not let that go unrewarded.', 27980), -- The Gates Are Closed
(45525, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sigryn has taken the path of Skovald before her. Only, I fear she is more powerful than her father ever was. \n\nI fear that Sigryn\'s thirst for revenge may lead to her undoing. Though truly powerful, she would be no match for Odyn.\n\nShe must be stopped before it is too late.', 27980), -- Unanswered Questions
(45524, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot believe that I find my brother alive, only to see him fall by my own blade. $B$BHow can fate be so cruel?', 27980), -- The Forgotten Heir
(45523, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have the backing of the Dragon-Riders, but a greater rival to the throne still lives in secret.$B$BThe God-King\'s son yet lives. My riders spotted him among the outcasts of Vrekt. He would be the true heir to Skovald\'s throne.  $B$BThe vrykul would never follow you were he to contend your claim!', 27980), -- To Tame the Drekirjar
(45522, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Bonespeakers yield. Our clan will not interfere with Sigryn\'s claim to the throne.$B$BBe careful of this one, $c. I can see the darkness that consumed Skovald dwelling in this girl\'s heart. How she has resisted it this far, I do not know.$B$BYou had best hope she can control it.', 27980), -- To Silence the Bonespeakers
(45486, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you for bringing Sigryn to me, outsider. She truly is the future of our people.$B$BThough you have already done so much, I would ask another favor of you. Please accompany Sigryn in her challenges. She has grown to trust you, and will need guidance through the trials she must face.', 27980), -- The Reluctant Queen
(45482, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, outsider? What business do you have here?', 27980), -- Arcane: Fate of the Tideskorn
(44821, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So what do you say? Up for a challenge?', 27980); -- In Dire Need
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(44782, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t worry, she\'ll be alright.$B$BWhatever demon did this to her didn\'t hang around long enough to finish the job.', 27980), -- Away From Prying Eyes
(47000, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Khadgar gives you a knowing nod.>$B$BI\'m glad you came, $ct.', 27980), -- The Council's Call
(46499, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, look here! You went and got that treasure! Hey... You still got a spider on your shoulder.$B$BLet\'s see what fantastic treasure you brought me... This is it? This is worthless! Here you keep it.$B$BTough break, kid. Keep at it.', 27980), -- Spiders, Huh?
(46245, 603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good on ya, mate! Not that there\'s a bad choice to be made, of course, but it\'s important to keep a positive attitude when surrounded by an infinite number of demons looking to kill ya.$b$bAs you gather additional supplies, come on back and I\'ll see they get assigned to the fortification of your choice.$b$bPhew! That was a mouthful, right? I\'d say it\'s time for a pint.', 27980), -- Begin Construction
(46286, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s what I\'m talkin\' about, mate!$b$bOi! Time to get to work.', 27980), -- Legionfall Supplies
(46765, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This scroll, fascinating... this confirms our concerns about indirect Legion threats. We must return to Dalaran, $n!', 27980), -- The Broken Shore: Investigating the Legion
(46845, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Illidari don\'t waste time on congratulations. There is more to do, and you\'re the one to do it.$B$BGet a move on.', 27980), -- Vengeance Point
(46832, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chambers sent you? He can down a tankard with the best of \'em, I\'ll give him that. But if he says I owe him anything, he\'s a liar!$b$bDon\'t you worry, my drakes and I will hold the point here. But more of this shore will need to be secured before your campaign can find victory.', 27980), -- Aalgen Point
(42483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<A note from the goblins is left behind, along with an old magnifying glass>$B$BI wish I coulda been there to see the look on your face, but Raz and I got bigger fish to fry!$B$BThanks for the trophies and meat. I\'m sure they\'ll fetch a nice sum on the black market, along with all the goodies we got from those stupid tauren! I\'m sure they won\'t be needing them any more!$B$BSo long sucker!', 27980), -- Put It All on Red
(39786, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, well. I half expected to find your statue on the riverbank. You\'re gonna get a nice payout once those tauren get back...$B$BYou haven\'t seen them around, have you?', 27980), -- A Stone Cold Gamble
(39792, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh hey, it\'s... you again! Of course you didn\'t have any trouble with those musken. You\'re a big, tough hero after all!$B$BThe tauren still aren\'t back, though. I\'m a bit worried that they may have gone off and hunted a bit more that they can chew.$B$BOh, I\'ll take those ribs, though. What do you want for em?', 27980), -- A Stack of Racks
(39793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re back? $B$BI mean... hey, you\'re back!$B$BWell, the tauren haven\'t come back yet, but no worries, I\'ll take that stuff off your hands! Let me show you some of my prime trade goods.', 27980), -- Only the Finest
(39787, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you took him out, eh? Those tauren are gonna be so jealous when they get back!  \n\nNaturally, you\'ll have to wait till the tauren get back and pay their wager before I can give you your cut. But in the meantime, I\'ve got another target for you.', 27980), -- Rigging the Wager
(42447, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems that Nithogg wasn\'t interested in the ravenbears\' tribute.$B$BIt\'s probably a good idea to get out of here before he comes back...', 27980), -- Dances With Ravenbears
(42445, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Caw! Caw! $B$B<The ravenbear chieftain flaps his wings excitedly when he sees the reagents you\'ve brought.>', 27980), -- Nithogg's Tribute
(42446, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Blackfeather chieftain bows respectfully to you. $B$BYou have helped ensure the survival of his tribe.', 27980), -- Singed Feathers
(42444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Caw?$B$B<The ravenbear chieftain seems preoccupied with the gathering of reagents for some sort of ritual. Perhaps you could help him?>', 27980), -- Plight of the Blackfeather
(40120, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to know that our warriors remains have been honored.$B$BMay they now celebrate their victories in the halls of Valhallas.', 27980), -- A Murky Fate
(44721, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She has forced my hand...', 27980), -- Helya's Conquest
(40044, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their toil is ended, and fewer kvaldir walk the lands of Stormheim.$B$BBoth are blessings, I would say.', 27980), -- Shadows in the Mists
(43595, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see that these blades are returned where they belong.$B$BThe dead smile upon you, outsider.', 27980), -- To Honor the Fallen
(40046, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Naglfar...$B$BSo Helya\'s kvaldir can navigate the mists?', 27980), -- Scavenging the Shallows
(39984, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The mists of this bay rot not only the wood of the ships, but the very souls of its inhabitants.$B$BBut it seems you have already discovered this.', 27980), -- Remnants of the Past
(44771, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Delicious, thank you.$B$BBefore we act, we must gather more information onto what Helya is planning.', 27980), -- A Threat Rises
(44720, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good of you to come.', 27980), -- A Call to Action
(50814, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re still moving! Emma\'s going to be so happy they are still fresh!', 27980), -- A Horrible Place
(50753, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will make a nice Mud Worm Soup. I wasn\'t liking this box anyway.', 27980), -- Earl-E Bot Gets the Worm
(50741, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Worm meat for the box full of treasures!  You sure you\'re not a Goblin?', 27980), -- Don't Turtle
(45174, 66, 1, 661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The naaru heard my call? Interesting...$B$BVery well, let\'s get to work. We\'ve found Illidan\'s soul - finally - and it\'s not where we expected it to be held.', 27980), -- The Hunt for Illidan Stormrage
(44481, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I wept when I touched your consciousness in the Great Dark, mortal. For I saw his fall, and I saw you, your shadow casting a dark pall over his body. I felt hatred in your heart as it corrupted your mind.$B$BIt was not Light\'s Heart, but you, that needed preparation. Now you know truth. Are you prepared to do what must be done to save your world and all others?$B$BWhen the time is right, I will call upon you to begin the hunt for Illidan\'s soul.$B$BHis rebirth will be the story of your redemption.', 27980), -- Destiny Unfulfilled
(44480, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Illidan sought out the truth and was blinded by what he saw. He was beginning to understand his destiny, but there was one final sacrifice that he had yet to make.', 27980), -- In My Father's House
(44479, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The line between good and evil is thin, and resides in a place where intention means little.$B$BIllidan wondered how those around him could be so blind to the threat of the Burning Legion. Fate is not without a sense of irony.', 27980), -- Ravencrest's Legacy
(44416, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The spirits honor us with a day of glorious combat! You have my well-earned respect, Illidan Stormrage. I will gladly follow you into any battle.', 27980), -- Hunter of Night
(44415, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A wise warrior welcomes all allies. You fight with the strength of an orc.', 27980), -- The Red Axe
(44414, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done it! Without you, I fear I would have eventually succumbed to the onslaught.', 27980), -- Felspawns of Lothros
(44466, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Failure. Rejection. From that day, Illidan would be haunted by both. Ever undaunted, he would continue the search for his destiny. Another path would be found.', 27980), -- An Unclear Path
(44464, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An auspicious start to a life of tragedy. Perhaps one of the few joyous memories Illidan would have in his life. While the years that followed tested the prophesied child, they would never break him. You must remember that, despite what you may see as our journey continues.$B$BThere is much more to be done, but I am not yet ready. I will call for you when it is time.', 27980), -- Awakenings
(46734, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mephistroth is on the run, and we have a foothold here at Deliverance Point.$b$bA good start, I\'d say, though we still have much to do.', 27980), -- Assault on Broken Shore
(46730, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our forces are assembled. We are ready to begin.', 27980), -- Armies of Legionfall
(38950, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your friend certainly has an... interesting appearance.$b$bHe taught you to sew this silk? Hmm. Maybe we should keep him around for a while.', 27980), -- The Wayward Tailor
(38949, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There you have it!$b$bNo, no, don\'t thank me. I\'m just happy to have been of service.', 27980), -- So You Think You Can Sew
(38948, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You, $n, are a person of great skill. I send you out for patterns, and you do so without question. Remarkable!', 27980), -- Hard Times
(38947, 603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Marvelous!', 27980), -- Runic Catgut
(38946, 5, 1, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My my, look at you! Such an attractive young $c, and all bedecked in magical finery and weaponry. To what do I owe the pleasure?$b$bAha! Tailoring! It\'s your lucky day, er...$b$bI\'m sorry, what was your name? $n?$b$bIt\'s your lucky day, $n! I happen to be one of the best tailors in Suramar...', 27980), -- Consult the Locals
(40336, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done it, $n. You have slain the Tidemistress and saved Jandvik from the Sashj\'tar.', 27980), -- Turning the Tidemistress
(41499, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The naga will not be taking any more of my kin!', 27980), -- Squid Out of Water
(41001, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We may have finally overcome this naga threat.', 27980), -- Shatter the Sashj'tar
(41709, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have all the parts that you will need... two in some cases.', 27980), -- Breaking Down the Big Guns
(41426, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must express gratitude for the vrykul you have saved this day.', 27980), -- Against Their Will
(41409, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fjolrik died in honor of Jandvik. We will remember his bravery.', 27980), -- Timing Is Everything
(41425, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Sashj\'tar forces are far greater than I imagined.', 27980), -- Sunken Foes
(40364, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is no glory or honor in being digested.', 27980), -- Bubble Trouble
(41618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I only wish that I had the chance to get to him first.$B$BBah! His body can rot in these waters for all I care.', 27980), -- The Seawarden
(41606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not know who you are, but you are not a sea giant, and that is enough for me.', 27980), -- Finding Brytag
(41410, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Fjolrik looks at you weakly.>$B$BYou made it back in time...', 27980), -- Dry Powder
(40927, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not know who you are, but I must thank you.', 27980), -- Jandvik's Last Hope
(41034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are sea giants in the bay!?$B$BYou must tell Toryl about this grave news right away.', 27980), -- Testing the Waters
(40334, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brandolf mixes the concoction together.>$B$BWell, I never said that it would taste good. Bottom\'s up.', 27980), -- Fisherman's Tonic
(40332, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hail Jarl Throndyr. May your soul find its place in Valhalas.', 27980), -- Beach Bonfire
(40331, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will wear this in honor of Throndyr!', 27980), -- Bite of the Sashj'tar
(40320, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My kin are safe. Let us see to these serpents!', 27980), -- Band of Blood Brothers
(40908, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Throndyr mutters through shallow breaths.>$B$BPoison... runs through... my body.', 27980), -- Jarl Come Back Now
(43179, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The kirin tor thank you.', 27980), -- The Kirin Tor of Dalaran
(42520, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The loss of Archmage Vargoth from our order is terrible to hear, $n. These are indeed dark times.', 27980), -- A Terrible Loss
(42956, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ari found just the book I needed! And she included a ring for you as well.', 27980), -- Ari's Package
(42702, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Your Hall here isn\'t too shabby, $n. I\'m sure there are lots of nifty secrets I can uncover here. I think I\'ll stay! Er, if you don\'t mind, of course.', 27980), -- Champion: Millhouse Manastorm
(42955, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Power in its purest form. It is a lovely color, is it not? A fitting gift for a book of healing. Will you come out old one, now that you are no longer lost and forgotten?', 27980), -- The Proper Way of Things
(43569, 5, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am not hungry any more. I can think- I will live! Oh, Arluin...', 27980), -- Arluin's Request
(43568, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last... we are free.', 27980), -- Arcan'dor, Gift of the Ancient Magi
(43567, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Behold. The redemption of the Nightfallen.', 27980), -- All In
(43565, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. With this, the chances of me teleporting you all to the bottom of the sea are much lower!', 27980), -- Bring Home the Beacon
(43564, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If my map of the arcways is accurate, that should be all of the outlets we need to worry about.', 27980), -- Flow Control
(43563, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do nicely.', 27980), -- Ephemeral Manastorm Projector
(43582, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was quite the spectacle, $n.$b$bSu\'esh will be a valuable ally in the days to come. I will keep an eye on her for the time being.', 27980), -- Shalassic Park
(41231, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw everything from out here. That was... messy.', 27980), -- Apex Predator
(41216, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could hear their cries and see the carnage from here! That will teach the Nightborne to enslave creatures. Have they fallen so far during all those years under the shield?', 27980), -- Survival of the Fittest
(41258, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Victory tastes sweeter than any dish, even one of mine.', 27980), -- Fruit of the Doom
(41256, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Manatrout was completely fished out of our harbors. Since the shield was raised all we have had of the liquor is memories on our palates.', 27980), -- Blast of Spice Fish
(41107, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. This will be enough for my purposes.', 27980), -- Bad Apples
(43994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<She tenderly plucks the crystals from your hand one by one.>', 27980), -- Feed Thalyssra
(39789, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, hey! You must be lookin for them tauren was camped here. They just stepped out for a bit, but Snaggle here and I - we can take care of ya!$B$BYou say they were gonna pay you for killin\' some worgs, huh? No prob, bub!$B$BI ain\'t got a lot of gold, but these goods are pretty valuable. Take your pick!', 27980), -- Eating Into Our Business
(41778, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Success! While their interior decoration sensibilities may differ significantly from those of Dalaran\'s architects, the demon hunters do make an efficient forge.$b$bYou keep the obliterum, $n. I have a feeling you\'ll be needing it eventually.', 27980), -- Fire it Up
(39986, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A magical message in a bottle, slipped right beneath the Legion\'s nose... Clever.', 27980), -- Magic Message
(45727, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. We still have a long road ahead of us to rid this world of the Legion, but this brings us one step closer.', 27980), -- Uniting the Isles
(40991, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done it! With this technique, we should be able to prepare dried mackerel strips much more efficiently.$b$bI am certain that there is much more we can learn. Keep bringing me ingredients, and I will keep the oven on!', 27980), -- Opening the Test Kitchen
(42424, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good news! Your champion found Archmage Vargoth entering the Arcway Vaults in Suramar.', 27980), -- Following In His Footsteps
(44055, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The other demons we will contend with in time. But that pit lord, it was a creature of great evil and beyond our devices to defeat on our own. Your skills were appreciated.', 27980), -- They Have A Pitlord
(41094, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You feel the warmth of Aviana\'s blessing once more. You have earned the ancient\'s respect.>', 27980), -- Hatchlings of the Talon
(44207, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All those years of study are really paying off...\n\nOnce they\'ve sent the shipment through, it will be waiting here for you.', 27980), -- Portal Full of Shiny Things
(39419, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done the Skyhorn a great service, $n.', 27980), -- Hex-a-Gone
(42590, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your kindness will not be forgotten. You are a friend to my family, $n.', 27980); -- Moozy's Reunion
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(51201, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Princess... Talanji, you say? I see.\n\nKing Wrynn will be told about this. This Zandalari princess will learn what it means to make an enemy of the Alliance.', 28153), -- The Troll's Tale
(51308, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Backups from Kul Tiras? Perfect. I was just about to finish another execution.', 28153), -- Zuldazar Foothold
(53109, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot believe all that has gone on in Drustvar!\n\nI am thankful that House Waycrest will return.', 28153), -- House Waycrest
(51445, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Words cannot express the debt I owe you for helping return my daughter to me, but unfortunately the traitor Ashvane has left us no time for celebration.\n\nWe must act.', 28153), -- Thros, the Blighted Lands
(52488, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Remarkable! Yesterday, I believed this place to only exist in tales and legends, and now I stand a footstep away from it...\n\nI just hope that at least some of those tales were exaggerations...', 28153), -- Runic Resistance
(52487, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It looks like the effigy\'s magic is working, but I think there\'s something we\'re missing here.', 28153), -- Into Darkness
(52149, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must continue to set my House in order, but our relations with the rest of Kul Tiras have suffered neglect for too long. I have some additional things to handle here first, but I will go to Boralus soon to set the rest right.\n\nMy deepest thanks for all you have done, $n.', 28153), -- Everburning
(52486, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, this thing is the key to opening the gateway?\n\nYou truly mean to go through with this, then?', 28153), -- Waycrest Manor: Draining the Heartsbane
(50639, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not relish what we\'ve done, but it was necessary for the good of Drustvar.\n\nI only hope the sacrifices we\'ve made will be worthwhile in the end...', 28153), -- Waycrest Manor: The Fallen Mother
(52485, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Korvash\'s skull will make a powerful focus indeed, but the years have drained it of its natural potency.\n\nYou will need to take further steps to prepare it for your ritual.', 28153), -- Hatred's Focus
(52484, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These runestones still throb with the twisted energy of Gorak Tul\'s magic. They will serve you well.', 28153), -- Buried Power
(52483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can practically feel the hatred emanating off these bones. They will do nicely.', 28153), -- Nightmare Catcher
(52482, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Forgive my hesitation, mainlander. It would appear the minions of Thros are no longer confined to their own realm.\n\nI will help you cross the threshold into the Blighted Lands.', 28153), -- The Old Bear
(52481, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe you\'re thinking of intentionally seeking out the Blighted Lands. The legends say it\'s a terrible place that exists for torment and pain.\n\nI\'m not sure any prize is worth treading those grounds.', 28153), -- Of Myth and Fable
(52513, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Blighted Lands? Why... I thought that was only a legend used to frighten children.\n\nMy daughter... What have I done to you?', 28153), -- Lost in Darkness
(52512, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You appeared to leave the island for a brief moment, then reappeared with that creature. Perhaps where it came from is where Jaina has gone.\n\nLady Katherine should be told of this development.', 28153), -- Fate's End
(52511, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'From here we shall be able to reach Fate\'s End. Hopefully in time.', 28153), -- Opening the Way
(52510, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good! Time is of the essence if we are to save Lady Jaina. I have made what preparations I can. Allow me a moment to read through the ritual and then we may begin.', 28153), -- Shrine of the Storm: The Missing Ritual
(52508, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful. These are more than just a costume, they\'re an essential part of our traditions. For the ritual to work, you\'ll need to step into the role as fully as you can.', 28153), -- Ritual Effects
(52509, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. The staff is now imbued with the strength of those elementals. You will need it for what lies ahead.', 28153), -- The Strength of the Storm
(52453, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Jaina Proudmoore was sent to Fate\'s End and her mother wishes to save her?\n\nThen we must act at once if we are to have any hope of saving her life!', 28153), -- A Forlorn Hope
(52449, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fate\'s End! Merciful Tides, I\'d hoped she wouldn\'t have been sent there... But of course she would be.\n\nNo matter. I must forge ahead.', 28153), -- The Mysterious Island
(52445, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, you have your answer. Jaina was sent to Fate\'s End.', 28153), -- Tol Dagor: The Fourth Key
(52311, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m certain the information we need is in this chest. But given the added security, my backup plan of having Taelia bust this thing open isn\'t going to work. Who knows what other security is set up on this chest?\n\nWe need to get that final key.', 28153), -- Sweete's Strongbox
(52253, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Okay, we have the keys. Now we just need to make a run for the chest.', 28153), -- The Keys to Success in Freehold
(52252, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got our ammo and I got our air support.\n\n<Flynn gestures to Taelia and Galeheart with a grin.>\n\nYou see where I\'m going with this.', 28153), -- An Explosive Entrance
(52762, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'d hoped maybe Lady Jaina\'s location was in the fine print but no such luck. I can confirm that Ashvane was doing business with the Irontide. So we\'re off to Freehold. Again.\n\nJoy.', 28153), -- A Local Guide
(52246, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Katherine looks up, resolved.>\n\nWe have little to go on, but I must believe she still lives.', 28153), -- Lost Shipment
(52194, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Katherine looks away for a moment.>\n\nPriscilla- Lady Ashvane convinced me to exile my daughter. I now see she acted in her own self interest, and I do not know if my daughter still lives.', 28153), -- What You May Regret
(50588, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m sorry... this is all a bit too much...\n\nThank you, $c, for protecting me.  I think I\'m going to need a moment...', 28153), -- Storming the Manor
(50586, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This tale... such a tragic fate to befall my home...\n\nWe must make this right, $c!  For the people of Corlain and all of Drustvar!', 28153), -- The Fall of Corlain
(50583, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All here and accounted for?\n\nVery well, we\'ve no time to waste. We must ride to Waycrest Manor!', 28153), -- To the Other Side
(50584, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad we were able to stop those things here, before the coven could unleash them on Drustvar\'s unsuspecting citizens.', 28153), -- Ruinous Rituals
(50585, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The people of Drustvar will sleep more soundly with less witches in the world.', 28153), -- Hexecutioner
(50454, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Captain Goodspeed was a stain on the reputation of the Waycrest Guard.\n\nI hope his end was painful.', 28153), -- A Traitor's Death
(50457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ballaster\'s plan worked! He is certainly a resourceful blacksmith.\n\nCome, Inquisitor. Waycrest Manor is just ahead!', 28153), -- Break On Through
(50453, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite a bit of powder ya got there.\n\nCareful ya don\'t take the whole wall down.', 28153), -- Barrier Buster
(50455, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work!  With any luck, the falcons should head back to roost at Arom\'s Stand.\n\nThough really, I\'d prefer they be anywhere other than in the coven\'s clutches.\n\nYou have my thanks.', 28153), -- Leaving the Nest
(50456, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The charms are broken? That\'s a relief!\n\nWe may just be able to save our flock after all.', 28153), -- Hexed Hatchlings
(51356, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the witch is dead. Good.\n\nHere\'s your reward, as promised. Keep up the good work, Inquisitor.', 28153), -- WANTED: Sister Lilias
(50452, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The coven is vulnerable to onions!?  I remember my nan used to tell stories about them warding off evil, but I never thought to take it literally!\n\nThis is quite the discovery!', 28153), -- Potent Protection
(50960, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lucille reads the orders.>$B$BSo This pirate seeks to destabilize House Waycrest? As if we don\'t have enough problems already!$B$BThank you for bringing this to my attention, $c. It seems that the coven might just be the beginning of Kul Tiras\' troubles...', 28153), -- Sweete's Orders
(50447, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know what to say. That you would risk your life to bring these items to me speaks greatly of your character, mainlander.\n\nI will make sure these keepsakes make it to the friends and families of the fallen, as well as news of their fate. On their behalf, I thank you for your compassion.', 28153), -- Remembering the Fallen
(50763, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... this is the ring Alexander was to give me at our wedding.  I had thought it long lost...\n\nI do not know how you found this, $c, but words cannot say how grateful I am. Alexander was very dear to me, and this ring was a symbol of the strength of our love.\n\nIt is good to feel that again...', 28153), -- One Last Request
(50446, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us hope this sends a message to the coven.  As long as we have weapons to fight them, we will persevere.\n\nSpeaking of weapons, I believe our blacksmith has an idea on how to take down that barrier. You should have a word with him.', 28153), -- Witchrending
(50762, 5, 661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Her mother ordered the assassination!?\n\nI had known that she didn\'t agree with Lucy marrying a merchant, but I would never suspect she would go so far to prevent it!\n\nThank you, $c.', 28153), -- The Lady's Fate
(50761, 273, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! My guards seem to have gained the upper hand, thanks to you.\n\nBut wait... where is Meredith?', 28153), -- Blood in the Chapel
(50760, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is going on here!?', 28153), -- From This Day Forward
(50759, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Splendid! I\'ll just need to take a few moments to go over this and I\'ll be right down.\n\nPlease let Lucy and Alexander know I will be ready shortly.', 28153), -- Running Late
(50758, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, kind $gsir:madam;!\n\nThe ceremony should begin as soon as the good Lord Waycrest arrives.', 28153), -- Painful Memories
(50754, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lucy sent you? I am relieved to hear she yet lives. \n\nMy name is Alexander Treadward. I am... well, I was Lucy\'s fiance.', 28153), -- To Have Loved and Lost
(50450, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That bunch should serve ya well.', 28153), -- An Offensive Harvest
(50451, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That oughtta do it for a spell.\n\nThanks for the help, stranger.', 28153), -- Eating Through the Defenses
(50449, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You don\'t look like you\'re in league with the coven, so what are you doin\' in Corlain?', 28153), -- Reeking Refuge
(50253, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, she\'s a beaut\'! Back in the navy we used te stuff our muskets with scraps when we ran outta bullets. \n\nThis\'ll do the damage ye need, te be sure!', 28153), -- An Improvised Arsenal
(50173, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found some silver? Excellent!\n\nThough it isn\'t much, any quantity of silver should help our efforts against the coven!', 28153), -- Precious Metals
(50174, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saved them!\n\nYou\'re certainly a hero in my book!', 28153), -- All Wrapped Up
(50175, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... killed them!?\n\nOh thank you so much! It\'s been like a living nightmare in here!', 28153), -- An Eight-Legged Curse
(50152, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the coven didn\'t completely clean out the armory? This is good news for us.\n\nEven the most common villager in Drustvar can hold their own in a fight. With these arms we can turn each person we rescue to another soldier on the line.', 28153), -- Digging for Scraps
(50151, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our fortunes are turning up. \n\nHaving a blacksmith at the tower will ensure our Inquisitors stay equipped for battle.', 28153), -- A Steady Ballast
(50149, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to know that there are still some left to save in Corlain. \n\nWe should focus our attention on them until we can devise a plan to bypass that barrier.\n\nI\'ll make sure to get this whistle back to Notley. Thank you, $c.', 28153), -- A Weather Eye
(50003, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well fought, $c.  The tower is ours.\n\nNow, we should set our sights on Corlain proper!', 28153), -- The First Watch
(49926, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you\'ve arrived. \n\nThis tower watches over Corlain and the surrounding lands. Apparently it is of little value to the coven, but to us it would serve as a valuable foothold.', 28153), -- The Road to Corlain
(50965, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are a few of the remaining relics of my kin. I thought them lost. You have my utmost gratitude.', 28153), -- Those Who Remain
(50967, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She said she would head back on her own? At least she is safe.', 28153), -- Lost in the Woods
(50970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The wood remembers, and guides us. This should be enough power to help this farmer.', 28153), -- A Farmer's Fate
(51001, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey thanks! Bit damp but still good.', 28153), -- Every Day I'm Smugglin'
(51240, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nicely done! Here\'s the reward Slagbolt left. When he comes in to port next he\'ll be glad to see that shark gone.', 28153), -- WANTED: Anchorface
(51018, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'She wanted this?$b$b<Kane cracks open the jar slightly. His eyes begin to water immediately.>$b$bT-thanks.$b$b<Coughing, Kane hastily re-seals the jar.>$b$bThat must have cost a lot. Let me pay you back with a tip.', 28153), -- Asking for a Friend
(50978, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! I\'m the Boss of the Cove now and what I say goes.$b$bSince you\'ve been a pal, I\'ll let you stop in whenever you like. Remember to bring gold.', 28153), -- Out With the Old Boss
(51020, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like this port needs a new innkeeper.$b$bA pleasure doin\' business with ya, $n', 28153), -- Cutthroat Business Practices
(51019, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! Did you see her fly out of there? Like the wind!$B$BThank you, $n. You and Cesi can count on my support.', 28153), -- She's Got it Where it Counts
(52049, 36, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Seeing the map, Cinderfuse puts down her weapon.>$b$bI see ye found me map. Guess that means ye be a miner, too?$b$bWell then, if yer lookin\' fer booty, best bet would be ta check yer breeches. However, if ye lookin\' fer work, then I got just the task fer ya.', 28153), -- X Marks the Plat!
(50988, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Right! So. Cards on the table. We\'re smugglers. We\'re not pirates. Everyone wants those red-coated jerks gone.$b$bYou help me become boss of Anyport and I\'ll help you.$b$bTalk to some of the key folks around here. Do some favors for \'em then come back to me, got it?', 28153), -- An Economic Opportunity
(50533, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'The plans for the Grand Rite are ruined and their rutial sites are in shambles. Master Ashton will be safe here in Arom\'s stand and we can finally send reinforcements to Falconhurst by gryphon.$b$bIn all, a job well done! Thank you for your vital help.', 28153), -- Stick It To 'Em!
(50481, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve wounded him or he wouldn\'t have retreated as he did. Our victory won\'t last long unless we do something about his army.', 28153), -- In the Hall of the Drust King
(50530, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! Not only did you save innocents, you denied the witches fuel for their Grand Rite.', 28153), -- Witch Way Out?
(50325, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Damn!. We\'ve slowed them down, but they are still working. To fully stop them we\'ll need to do more.', 28153), -- Stopping the Grand Rite
(50329, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'The potion worked even better than anticipated! It is heartening to know my time spent in the witches\'... care has yielded positive results.\n\nLosing some of their leadership will certainly set them back.', 28153), -- Matrons of the Crimsonwood
(50445, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. I should be able to do some... Interesting things with these.', 28153), -- Controlling the Situation
(50370, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'By my ancestors\' anchors that is a large army! At least it doesn\'t appear to be mobile yet. And the tree... Clearly it is the focus of their efforts.', 28153), -- Deeper into the Woods
(50327, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh! I say!$b\n<Ashton shudders and coughs>$b\nA bit less hearthbloom next time, Marten, but that did just the trick. Well done both of you.', 28153), -- A Little 'Pick Me Up'
(50306, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... Very interesting. And pungent. Perhaps my first order of business will be something to remove the smell.', 28153), -- Odds and Ends
(50265, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'We had a few visitors while you were gone but I took care of them. \n\nAshton\'s back and safe, though it appears he\'s seen some of the horrors here.', 28153), -- Saving Master Ashton
(50266, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. I\'ll cut a path back to Falconhurst. They will pay for what happened to my family!', 28153), -- Bittersweet
(50172, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'The woods are crawling with witches. We\'ll have a fight on our hands if we\'re to save Master Ashton.', 28153), -- Into the Crimsonwood
(51390, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You finally got those damnable outlaws? Well done! My people have enough trouble here without having to deal with brigands. \n\nTake your reward with my thanks.', 28153), -- WANTED: The Crimson Cutthroats
(50063, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'I tried to stop them but I couldn\'t. They\'ve taken Master Ashton into the woods!', 28153), -- Fighting With Fire
(50238, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Yay! Oh. Y-you saw someone? My papa?$B$B<Lynn hugs her toy and sniffs>$b$bI haven\'t seen my Mama in awhile. I hope she\'s okay.', 28153), -- Bramblethorn
(50090, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. We\'ll be better able to protect the town.', 28153), -- Building Defenses
(50036, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Smells a bit strong but I think it will burn those wooden constructs well! Now it\'s time to test it out.', 28153), -- A Weapon of Old
(50092, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah wonderful! The fires are out and your breath smells minty fresh!', 28153), -- Curiously Strong
(50903, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'I appreciate your help in liberating the town! I was becoming quite concerned by these strange monsters.', 28153), -- A Missing Master
(49939, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'We wouldn\'t have been able to hold out much longer. You saved us all.', 28153), -- So Long, Sister
(50177, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'That witch! She must be the one guiding these attacks!', 28153), -- Hold The Barricade!
(50251, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'I shudder to think what they would have used those people for.', 28153), -- Spell Bound
(50001, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. You\'ve thinned their numbers.', 28153), -- Breaking Hag
(49896, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'The town is under siege! No wonder we have not heard from them. We must help them.', 28153), -- To Falconhurst!
(51472, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your help.', 28153), -- Life Preserver
(50953, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'A grim but necessary task. I hope Greenstalker\'s spirit will find peace now.$b$bBe careful, $n. These woods are being twisted by ancient power.', 28153), -- Greenstalker
(51543, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for returning quickly. These are new growth, full of potent life-giving energy and a necessary sacrifice to cleanse corruption.\n\nGive me a moment as I create the charm.', 28153), -- Saplings in the Snow
(48768, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah!  This is fantastic news! I will have someone run these out to the docks right away.$b$bI was starting to fear that they may have gotten you, too.$b$bThat said, you have avenged my people.  In exchange, let me show you the finer points of harvesting storm silver.$b$b<Myra takes the next several minutes to explain what she knows about harvesting storm silver deposits.>', 28153), -- Brined Justice
(48761, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad to see you made it back in one piece. I\'m tempted to ask how it went, but frankly, thinking about it has been causing me quite a bit of anxiety.$b$bIf you don\'t mind, I\'m going to distract myself from the thought with a lesson.$b$bYou\'ve probably noticed that monelite is really maleable, right? You can use that, even before smelting it.$b$bBy using your pick to deform the metal while it\'s still in the vein, you can heat it up and get a bigger haul using the other technique I taught you.', 28153), -- Spiderphobia
(49730, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The death of the matriarch means the next generation of boars will be delayed. Nice work.', 28153), -- WANTED: Thundersnout
(52130, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite the story, eh $Glad:lass;?! Make sure ye tell yer friends!', 28153), -- Deadliest Cache: Carpe Diem
(50418, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mph mph mph. Mph.', 28153), -- Deadliest Cache: Sink and Swim
(50391, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ozumat ain\'t around on account of I shot the blasted beast in its slimy face! Swear on me beard every word is true!', 28153), -- Deadliest Cache: Gun Fishin'
(50376, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t listen to either of \'em. True every word, I tell ya!', 28153), -- Deadliest Cache: Reel Big Fish
(53045, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, just what I needed. A fresh set o\' ears to hear a tale or two!', 28153), -- Surveying the Wharf
(48767, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the Light! I thought I lost it forever!$b$bThis used to belong to my great grandfather.$b$b<Myra clutches the necklace close to her heart for a moment as a tear runs down her cheek. After a moment, she looks around, shaking her head.>$b$bNothing here can remotely repay this. It\'s not much, but I can show you how to get the most out of mining monelite seams.$b$b<Myra spends the next several minutes explaining several techniques to increase the amount of monelite mined from a seam.>', 28153), -- Seams Familiar
(49898, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, marine! We might make a proper soldier out of you yet!$b$bThey\'ll make Colonel Waycrest a Lord for this, I\'m sure. Your bravery will be remembered.', 28153), -- Clear Victory
(49890, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The carvings could have been Drust propaganda stating he lived, but that voice!\n<Cleardawn\'s face becomes grim>\nIt seems we may have all been mistaken about the ultimate fate of Gorak Tul. I shudder to think what he might be planning now.', 28153), -- Drustfall
(48517, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good their spirits returned to their final rest once more. May they never be disturbed again.', 28153), -- Honorable Discharge
(48184, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Gorak Tul\'s death shattered his army! The carvings here all show that, but now I wonder... Did Gorak Tul actually die?', 28153), -- Pieces of History
(48504, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 0, 'Something has disturbed the spirits here.$b$bThe spirits of the departed still fight with constructs and the shambling dead. $b$bOur goal is Falconhurst, but a quick investigation of this area might help us fight our foes better.', 28153), -- Through the Old Roads
(49807, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There, that was nice and official. \n\nNow, I think it\'s time we took the fight back to the Heartsbane. I believe the marshal has a plan.', 28153), -- A New Order
(49806, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found their leader? Excellent work, $c!\n\nThe people of Arom\'s Stand will be safe, now that you\'ve so thoroughly dismantled the coven\'s machinations here.', 28153), -- Hidden Dealings
(49805, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was good thinking to dispose of the witches\' trappings. $B$BI don\'t want to know what would happen if an innocent villager toyed around with such things!', 28153), -- Implements of Ill Intent
(49804, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It worked?! I knew we were on the right track!\n\nIt\'s too bad we don\'t have a stockpile of silver weapons lying around, but I think I know how we can deal with that.', 28153), -- Sharp Thinking
(49803, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is with reluctance that I hand command of these men over to you, but it must be done.\n\nI hope you lead them well.', 28153), -- Changing of the Guard
(49443, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you found it! Excellent.\n\n<Lucille produces a long sewing needle from the kit>\n\n...You look confused. Let me explain.', 28153), -- A Lesson in Witch Hunting
(48986, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you made it, $n. $B$BWe\'ll need to get started right away if we want to use the knowledge in this tome to fight the coven.', 28153), -- Take the High Road
(52033, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So someone has finally managed to track down the Rime Huntress?  Now our traders can continue their routes to Tiragarde without fear of the beast.\n\nTake your reward, and my thanks.', 28153), -- WANTED: The Rime Huntress
(53110, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What do you have here, mainlander? Ah, I see. My students met with much stronger threats than we\'d expected.\n\nThank you for helping them.', 28153), -- The High Thornspeaker
(48946, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You do great honor to my family, $c.  The most noble of Waycrests were once inquisitors of the order.\n\nIt is only fitting that it is you who takes up its mantle now.', 28153), -- The Order of Embers
(48945, 1, 547, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who would\'ve thought that from this stuffy little chamber would rise some of the greatest warriors of House Waycrest\'s history?\n\nAre you prepared to follow in their footsteps?', 28153), -- The Ruins of Gol Var
(48944, 603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found it! I knew that they were more than stories!\n\nCome, let us see what\'s inside.', 28153), -- Unlocking History
(48963, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was close! \n\nI\'m glad to have such a capable $c as my guardian. I would hate to be your enemy.', 28153), -- Diversionary Tactics
(51134, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These markings... this is the language of the Drust!$B$BThe magic of the coven must be disturbing their spirits, drawing them back into our world to fight us once more!$B$BThis is unsettling... but it is another reason we must bring an end to the Heartsbane!', 28153), -- If Bones Could Talk
(48942, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. Keeping the pass clear will ensure a steady stream of supplies to Highroad Gate.\n\nWe will need them in the battles to come.', 28153), -- Yeti to Rumble
(48943, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m impressed. I didn\'t think there would be this much left from his shipment. This will be very helpful to our men at the gate.$B$BBella knows the way, so she should be able to get these to them.  This place is too dangerous to keep her hitched up, anyway.', 28153), -- Salvage Rights
(48941, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you are here.\n\nUnfortunately it looks like we\'re not going to have an easy path to our destination.', 28153), -- A Slight Detour
(48180, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I suppose I\'m not really surprised Arthur didn\'t exactly follow orders. But I don\'t think I can complain with the results.\n\nThanks for making sure he wasn\'t entirely in over his head.', 28153), -- Really Big Problem
(48183, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $n. We can use these to protect the land and the people and creatures living here.', 28153), -- The Hills Are Alive
(48182, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for destroying those cairns. We should be able to dismantle the Drust constructs and risen dead more easily now.', 28153), -- Total Cairnage
(52075, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully those monsters will stay down. You have my thanks.', 28153), -- Boned
(48179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for helping us, Mainlander.', 28153), -- Rescue Rangers
(52074, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rebecca sent you? Bless that girl! You\'ve come just in time.', 28153), -- Deliverance
(48947, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My aunt sent you? Oh, Light bless that woman.', 28153), -- Gol Koval
(48477, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our thanks to you, brave champion. You have freed us from the witch\'s vile influence and stopped her corruption from spreading. Our very souls have been saved by thy actions.$b$bNow we may rest.', 28153), -- Looking For One More
(48476, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why that pustulent boil on a toad\'s rump! Use me as a pawn? Fie! I will see her sent screaming to the foul pit she crawled from!$b$bMy thanks. The witch will pay for her heinous actions!', 28153), -- Split Party
(48475, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A witch has infested this goodly place with her foul power. Stranger, you have proven yourself a friend. Perhaps you will be our salvation!', 28153), -- Seeing Spirits
(49259, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This situation is much worse than I had thought. The coven has taken House Waycrest?! This will not stand!\n\nWait... you mentioned that they were drawing their power from an ancient ruin?\n\nI think I might have an idea.', 28153), -- And Justice For All
(48538, 604, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'What\'s this? A letter from Mayor Pare?\n\n<Constable Framer reads Evelyn\'s letter.>\n\nWell... it appears we were... mistaken.', 28153), -- An Airtight Alibi
(48524, 547, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wait... you\'re telling me it was even worse in the mines?\n\nYou know what? Just don\'t tell me about it. So long as you killed... whatever was in there... I think we\'ll be okay.', 28153), -- Culling the Coven
(48523, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It worked?! Well, I\'ll be a kraken\'s uncle! You really did save our hides!\n\nI\'m not sure how we can repay you, but this should be a good start!', 28153), -- The Murderous Matron
(48522, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem we were mistaken. Miss Waycrest was just in the wrong place at the wrong time.\n\nHowever, this also means that Fletcher\'s Hollow may be in even more danger.', 28153), -- A Revealing Missive
(48521, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were able to control one of their creations?! That\'s amazing!\n\nThis could really turn the tide for us!', 28153), -- Charming the Lifeless
(48520, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They weren\'t willing to talk?  That\'s unfortunate.\n\nAt least with them gone, we may stand a chance to take back the town.', 28153), -- The Three Sisters
(48519, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. Those villagers owe you their lives.\n\nNow that they\'re safe, we can focus on taking back the town.', 28153), -- Hope They Can't Swim
(49295, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. \n\nIt was starting to feel a bit claustrophobic on this hill.', 28153), -- Clear-Cutting
(48518, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $c! Even if we don\'t manage to take the town back, it\'s good to know we were able to save some of our people.\n\nNow we just have to get them out of here...', 28153), -- Save Who We Can
(48171, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re looking to help solve this curse? Well, that\'s good to hear. We can surely use all the help we can get.$B$BI\'m happy to help you get to the bottom of this. First things first, though, we need to save some of our villagers.$B$BCare to lend a hand?', 28153), -- The Curse of Fletcher's Hollow
(48882, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... yeeesss...\n\nMore entrails... more innards... only the best...', 28153), -- I Like Fish Guts and I Cannot Lie
(48904, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... more meat!\n\nI must not... can not... stop!', 28153), -- Take the Bait
(48880, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The gulls are... no more...\n\nNow... I can catch more...\n\nYes... catch more...', 28153), -- Mean Gulls
(48881, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<That looks like the last of Art\'s rods.\n\nYou manage to salvage some of Art\'s bait with your catch. \n\nWaste not, want not>', 28153), -- The Reel Deal
(48198, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That... didn\'t turn out as expected.\n\nIt appears that my absolution may truly be in your hands.', 28153), -- The Burden of Proof
(48165, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. This toxin should have the... desired effect.\n\nGah, I can\'t believe I\'m going to go through with this.', 28153), -- Harmful If Swallowed
(48170, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. $B$BWith this many bloodflies at least one is bound to bite.', 28153), -- Once Bitten, Twice Shy
(48113, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great, you found one! I was worried that there wouldn\'t be much left growing on that farm. \n\nThe people of Drustvar could learn a thing or two from that hardy onion.', 28153), -- A Pungent Solution
(49242, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c.\n\nMaybe in reviving these fields I can bring a bit of Sam\'s goodness back to this accursed land.', 28153), -- Quill or Be Quilled
(48111, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, those are certainly some interesting beliefs. I think it\'s safe to rule out the fire and drowning, don\'t you think?\n\nLooks like that leaves us with three tests...', 28153), -- Trial by Superstition
(48110, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, those traps should alert us in case anything tries to sneak up on us through the woods.\n\nYou have bought us a modicum of safety, $c.', 28153), -- In Case of Ambush
(48109, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not a beast in sight. Good.\n\nThe foes of this land must not find us here in the open.', 28153), -- The Woods Have Eyes
(48283, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Lady Waycrest has asked that you convince me to let her stand trial?\n\nI think she underestimates the danger of this situation...', 28153), -- Standing Accused
(48108, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can\'t you see that we\'re busy here, $c?\n\nI assume you have a reason for interrupting this trial...', 28153), -- The Waycrest Daughter
(44785, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Was that really Abby? Did she bring forth that... thing? We thought her dead not long ago.$b$bWhat could we have done to bring such... such horror upon our village?', 28153), -- Tea Party
(45079, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Annie looks at you, her eyes hollow and empty. Her clothes are stained with blood, though she seems to be mostly unscathed. She stutters, but her words are unintelligible.>', 28153), -- REUSE
(47428, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mrrow?$b$b<You find Smoochums, but Abby is nowhere to be seen.>', 28153), -- Kitty?
(47289, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hooray! Only one more guest left to find.', 28153), -- Teddies and Tea
(51547, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The beast has been slain? You have my thanks, $c.\n\nHere is your reward, as promised.', 28153), -- WANTED: Rindlewoe
(47982, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s... going on? How long have I been standing here?$B$BA curse!? You\'re saying the whole village was just... stuck? I knew there was something terribly wrong with that old crone...$B$BIt seems that Fallhaven owes you a great debt, stranger.', 28153), -- The Final Effigy
(47981, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The magical energies surrounding the effigy have dissipated.>', 28153), -- Cracking the Curse
(47980, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<With the cursed wildlife culled, the villagers of Fallhaven should no longer have to fear the foothills.>', 28153), -- Furious Familiars
(47979, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The crone is defeated, and will no longer pose a threat to the people of Fallhaven.  $B$BHowever, her curse on the village still lingers...>', 28153), -- Witch Hunt
(47978, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why hello there, young $gman:woman;.\n\nWe don\'t get many visitors to Fallhaven. What brings you to my home?', 28153), -- The Wayward Crone
(47968, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The writings you were able to find all have one common thread - an old woman who recently arrived in town.\n\nThis ledger may contain some information to her whereabouts.>', 28153), -- Signs and Portents
(47950, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! The spell is broken and my men are back to normal!$B$BWell... mostly. They\'re alive at least.$B$BNow we can get back to normal around here. If you see Elijah in Fallhaven, tell him he\'ll get his sausages soon.', 28153), -- Cured Ham
(47949, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Removing it didn\'t break the curse? Damn. We\'ll have to try something else.', 28153), -- That's Not My Fetish
(47948, 578, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Poor Roland. He was... very good at his work. One of the finest butchers in Drustvar. It is a true shame his talents were put to such horrible use.', 28153), -- Pork Chop
(47947, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With those monsters gone, no more of my people are going to get killed.', 28153), -- Big Bad Wolves
(47946, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for sending my workers to a safe spot.$b$bHopefully my men won\'t have to remain pigs for long.', 28153), -- Save Their Bacon
(48683, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well I\'ve certainly learned my lesson.\n\nThank you, friend. I will return to Boralus with my parents now.  \n\nHere, take this for your troubles.', 28153), -- Changing Seasons
(48682, 5, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those cultists tried to kill me!\n\nI don\'t know about you, but I\'ve had about enough of this Wicker Man business!', 28153), -- A Simple Sacrifice
(48679, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were the one looking for Edwin, weren\'t you!?\n\nYou must help him!', 28153), -- Mind the Hives
(48678, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your offerings pleased the Wicker Man. \n\nVery well, ask your questions, $c.', 28153), -- Questionable Offerings
(48677, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What brings you to our valley, $c?', 28153), -- Wicker Worship
(48853, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for saving my grandson and his friends.$b$B I\'m sure they will make fine explorers when they\'re adults.$b$bWhich will be about the time they are no longer grounded!', 28153), -- Terminal Degree
(48805, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Isn\'t our stuff neat? We found real relics!$B$BI bet Brann Bronzebeard will be impressed. We\'re gonna write to him once we get back home.', 28153), -- Research Recovery
(48804, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yay! You saved my friends!$B$BI mean, they probably could have escaped on their own, but it was nice you could distract the troggs for \'em.', 28153), -- Mistakes Were Made
(48792, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look like you\'ve been in a fight. Did you introduce those troggs to the business end of your weapon?$b$bThat\'s what I would have done! Give \'em a good right hook! And then a left! Pow! Bam!$b$bI bet they\'re sorry for messing with you!', 28153), -- Menace to Society
(48793, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nigel\'s grandpa is nice and all, but he\'d have slowed us down! Adventure, fortune and fame awaited!$b$bMaybe we should have brought a weapon or something though.', 28153), -- The Adventurer's Society
(48622, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The effigy is protected by powerful magic. \n\nIt seems it will take more than brute force to break this curse.>', 28153), -- The Vanishing Lord
(47961, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve only been to Drustvar once, on a hunting trip. It\'s a rugged land with a dark history and superstitious people. Steel yourself for this one.', 28153), -- Drustvar
(49223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Slow and steady, my friend.', 28153), -- The Long Con
(51889, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I needed this!$b$b<Franklin spends several moments shoveling food into his mouth.>$b$bMmm... Right! If I recall correctly, you were asking about storm silver seams?$b$bLet me tell you my secret technique, not even Myra knows. The metal is prone to stress fractures, but instead of scoring the metal where it meets the rock and breaking it off, just remove the rock.$b$bThe metal naturally forms prisms, and can be easily pulled out of the stone without wasting anything once it is loosened up.', 28153), -- The Wrath of Grapes
(51380, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Myra sent you?$b$bWait... my old business partner?', 28153), -- Back to Franklin
(48764, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a life saver! Well, a livelihood saver!$b$bAs for that trick I had mentioned: Don\'t bother using a pick to separate the rock from the ore when pulling it from a monelite seam.$b$bIf the ore is big enough, once you remove it from the earth, you can peel the metal back and remove the rocks by hand.', 28153), -- Don't Pick a Fight
(52044, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wow! This is really impressive. You managed to get a decently sized shard of platinum in a single piece.$b$bIt looks like you managed to hit the ore in line with it\'s strata... Think of it like chopping wood with the grain, instead of against it.$b$bYou know, I bet if you sacrificed some of the power of your swing to keep the pick in line with the strata, you could probably get chunks this size all the time!', 28153), -- An Exceptional Platinum Shard
(53097, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your mind has rejected madness, and replaced it with determination. For now.', 28153), -- Despondent Ablutions
(50386, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The things are driven back, for a time.', 28153), -- Flush Them Out
(50417, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have answered the letter. Now you are bound to this place.', 28153), -- Ruin Has Come
(50640, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Calvin has briefed me, but I am eager to hear your report.', 28153), -- A Question of Quillpower
(49908, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, roger! I\'ll head back at once!', 28153), -- Back to Brennadam
(50368, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s done! I was afraid you were done for, but you\'ve saved us all!', 28153), -- Terror of the Kraul
(50340, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s not stealing if we\'re stealing them back. Hey! Are those my lucky anchors?', 28153), -- Steal Them Back
(50365, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those supplies you destroyed should set them back. They must have been saving them for a while...', 28153), -- Run For the Hills
(50367, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This stuff smells awful. Maybe Hobbs will know what to do with it. Once we get out of here I\'ll make sure these samples get to him.', 28153), -- Anger in a Bottle
(50363, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will take these and make sure they get to the farms for proper training.', 28153), -- War Pigs
(50353, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was sure they were done for. You have my thanks.', 28153), -- Boaring Company
(50354, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m amazed I made it here. This place is so heavily guarded...', 28153), -- Look Out!
(50622, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad to know the others are safe. But not for long if we don\'t do something about these quilboar!', 28153), -- Deal's Off
(50088, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. They will rest now.', 28153), -- Golden Fields Forever
(50069, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s done. My family is avenged.', 28153), -- Goldfield's War
(50065, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... you found them. I...', 28153), -- A Reason to Stay
(50041, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good! I can keep shooting, and they can\'t get to me! This is really the perfect setup.', 28153), -- A Pocketful of Shells
(50157, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Roz always worries about me. I keep tellin\' her I\'m fine up here, but she never listens...', 28153), -- There's Gold in Them There Fields
(49960, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Jolly good. With him out of the way, the quilboar around here should be less organized and take longer to mobilize.', 28153), -- Sic 'Em!
(51314, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good harvest this year. Our people will eat well.', 28153), -- Grain Drain
(51310, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah, that\'ll teach them to come here with their pooches and steal our grain!', 28153), -- Raiders of the Lost Crop
(49886, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! I bet ol\' Humphrey gave them a good spook!', 28153), -- Follow Your Nose
(50136, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, that\'ll show them! Those quilboar will think twice before invading my farm again!', 28153), -- Farming Stimulator
(50135, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mystics using magic to shape the vines? I don\'t know much about magic, but I\'m glad you stopped them.', 28153), -- Stop Vining!
(50134, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! With these parts I can rebuild my entire workforce. Or make one of them REALLY powerful.', 28153), -- Gadgets and Gizmos Aplenty
(50158, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I stayed behind to see if I could help... Everyone else made it back okay, right?', 28153), -- Checking Out the Collapse
(50111, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good idea! Smashing those will distract their mystics and set back their expansion.', 28153), -- Totems, Totems, Totems!
(51207, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, my grandson could learn a thing or two from you. Come back to visit anytime!', 28153), -- Ettin It Done
(51209, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe it actually worked. I thought for sure we\'d all be squished!', 28153), -- Mighty Grokkfist
(51208, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow! I can\'t believe you were able to carry all of that.', 28153), -- Wheat A Minute
(51504, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cookies, for me!? Thank you!', 28153), -- Cookie Delivery
(51335, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did you think $n, hit the spot, don\'t they?', 28153), -- Cookies and Cream
(51215, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It smells wonderful. This is perfect, thank you $p!', 28153), -- Milking Goats
(51200, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, my sweet Millie! Thank you, $n. I\'m in your debt.', 28153), -- The Black Sheep
(51203, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My flock should be able to rest easier now.', 28153), -- Cry Wolf
(51204, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, I wasn\'t sure if anyone would ever answer my posting. Thank you!', 28153), -- WANTED: Razorclaw Alpha
(51492, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much. I wish Charles was half as studious as you.', 28153), -- Gunpowder Plot
(51214, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much. I wish Charles was half as studious as you.', 28153), -- Be A Dear
(51251, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can all rest easier now that those spiders have been squashed.', 28153), -- Basement Dwellers
(51205, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you so much. I\'ll get rid of these little guys.', 28153), -- Aww, Rats!
(51218, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ohhhh, goodness! You found my lost tea. Thank you dear!', 28153), -- Undelivered Package
(49831, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done it! The naga are defeated and the levee remains intact!', 28153), -- From the Depths
(50706, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work! That should deter the naga for now.', 28153), -- Clearing the Delta
(50705, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, the bubble seems to be gone, but I don\'t like the looks of that whirlpool.', 28153), -- A Snake with Three Heads
(50773, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How did it feel to be a murloc\'s greatest fear?', 28153), -- You're a Shark
(50698, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you run across any other opportune spots, feel free to set up more mines.', 28153), -- Problem Solving with Gunpowder
(50679, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even I can feel how much power this thing contains.', 28153), -- Piercing the Shield
(50672, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work! Let\'s hope these harpoons can fire from our cannons.', 28153), -- Any Ammo Will Do
(50649, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah! How powerful! These will be a great help.', 28153), -- Filching from Thieves
(50645, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s exactly what I\'m looking for. Give me a bit of time to prepare the spell.', 28153); -- Eeling in a Big One
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(50653, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should slow down their progress quite a bit. You have my gratitude.', 28153), -- Reclaiming our Defenses
(50644, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Each one you killed is one less my men have to worry about. Thanks.', 28153), -- Facing the Invaders
(50635, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm.... This is concerning. Very concerning.', 28153), -- The Shifting Tides
(50621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With these numbers, we should be able to hold our own here. Oars and fishing nets make surprisingly effective weapons.', 28153), -- Caught in the Net
(50616, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have no idea what this might be, but I don\'t like the looks of it.', 28153), -- A Bit of a Bind
(50614, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should slow down their progress quite a bit. You have my gratitude.', 28153), -- Freedom for the Sea
(52070, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad to hear Felecia is safe.  We could use your help here though.', 28153), -- Bauer Backup
(49818, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These fishermen are no pushovers themselves. They should be able to hold their own here with a little help.', 28153), -- Trouble at Fort Daelin
(51386, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This victory will be discussed for millennium to come.  The Venture Co. is a resilient foe though, I am sure we will meet them again!', 28153), -- Battle Victorious
(51545, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done us a great service.', 28153), -- Breaker Bad
(51222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. Our plan is coming together nicely.', 28153), -- What's Yours is Mined
(51220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve struck a mighty blow against these Venture Company thugs, and kept Ai\'twen safe.', 28153), -- Deep Sea Venture
(51427, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An excellent offering.  Let us watch now, and see if this will suffice.', 28153), -- I Like Turtles
(51540, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many battles are won by those who take the initiative and exploit an opportunity. You have spotted an excellent opportunity.  \n\nNow you should exploit it!', 28153), -- Explosive Situation
(51221, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve bought us valuable time with your heroic actions.', 28153), -- Response Required
(51371, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An excellent offering.  Let us watch now, and see if this will suffice.', 28153), -- Flavorable Offering
(51353, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your presence here can only mean one thing.  Ai\'twen\'s help is needed.', 28153), -- Cave of Ai'twen
(53369, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n!', 28153), -- Make Loh Go
(53476, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh my! Is that a complete set of the Ruinous Pilgrimage? With a first-generation scroll case to boot?\n\nWhy, I haven\'t seen one of those in decades! Here, here, I have a nice hat I acquired in a trade from a tall fellow some years ago. Said he was from \"up north\".\n\nDid I ever tell you the stories that my father\'s mother\'s father told me about the days of the pilgrimage? It all started with that scoundrel from... hey, where are you going?', 28153), -- The Great Sea Scrolls
(51343, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do nicely.  Just as we are, you shall now be one with the sea.', 28153), -- Swimming Lessons
(51339, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These smallest of victories are the foundation for the Venture Companies defeat.', 28153), -- Cleaning Bills
(51352, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The war has just begun, but it was a great first victory!', 28153); -- Don't Play with Matches
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(29111, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some days we gain quarter, other days we are beaten back behind our walls. Every day, we bury more of our brothers and sisters.$B$B<Kadrak pauses and takes a deep breath.>$B$BNot only have the supplies you brought strengthened our troops, but your heroic deeds have inspired them as well. Thank you, $c. ', 30706), -- Mor'shan Caravan Delivery
(28493, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re the reinforcements? I suppose you\'ll do fine as long you can kill night elves.', 30706), -- Warchief's Command: Ashenvale!
(29112, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, you\'re back! Balgor made it down before you, and he\'s already eaten two bowls of raptor stew. Considering that his appetite hasn\'t suffered, I\'m sure he will be fit to travel in no time.$B$BI\'ll make sure that this artifact is taken care of. You\'ve done us a great service today.', 30706), -- Demon Seed
(29110, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, you came for me!$B$B<Balgor sobs in relief.>', 30706), -- Mor'shan Caravan Rescue
(29109, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is terrible news! $n, at least you arrived safely.', 30706), -- Mor'shan Caravan Pick-Up
(29095, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello $n. I have heard of your deeds from Darsok. You are a valuable $c of the Horde, indeed.', 30706), -- Report to Thork
(29094, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thought you were a goner. Glad to see you\'re still in one piece.', 30706), -- The Short Way Home
(14006, 4, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found it! Wow, it\'s over 600 pages, only 30 of which are intentionally left blank.$B$BLet\'s see. Chapter three: Backsplicing the Reverse Crankshaft Flywheel Pulley? Interesting. Chapter seven: Valve Timing for the High-Pressure Expansion Condenser!? This stuff is great! And I still don\'t even know what this thing does.$B$BHere, have some of my old tools. Let\'s fire this thing up one last time!', 30706), -- Read the Manual
(29015, 5, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at the size of that thing! We\'re going to be rich! Let\'s see, according to the rates I\'ve seen on gems going into Undermine, I should be able to figure out your cut - fifty percent, don\'t worry!$b$bNow let\'s see... I think this should do about right. Pleasure doing business with you, $n.', 30706), -- Miner's Fortune
(14004, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wenikee said what? Copperplug? BOSS Copperplug? Oh no, this might be tricky.', 30706), -- Return to Samophlanger
(29027, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great, you got them!  Now I can get to work...', 30706), -- Nugget Slugs
(29090, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. This old orc will sleep more safely at night.', 30706), -- A Burning Threat
(29089, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saw sludge being dumped straight into the lake? I wouldn\'t be surprised if the Sludge Beast were a product of the Venture Co.\'s carelessness.', 30706), -- Sludge Beast!
(29026, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, what\'s this? A samophlange, you say? What\'s a samophlange??$B$BAh... but look at the way it moves when you handle it.  And there\'s the sound of intricate gears inside. Oh my! I want to fix it and see what it does, don\'t you??', 30706), -- Wenikee Boltbucket
(14003, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sputtervalve scored us a Samophlange? Lemme see that thing!$B$BYeah, we can get this working again, no problem. Hand me that huge mallet...', 30706), -- Samophlange Repair
(29088, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good riddance! Those filthy pests are more trouble than they\'re worth.', 30706), -- Hyena Extermination
(29087, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look around and notice the lake is covered in slick oil. This once beautiful oasis has been ravaged. You feel a deep sense of foreboding.', 30706), -- Sludge Investigation
(29024, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is... er... interesting... yes. A device this complex is best analyzed by a team of skilled engineers in a clean room, painstakingly reverse engineering each component in a controlled environment.$B$BBut who has that kind of time?$B$BLet\'s just fire this thing up and see what it does...', 30706), -- Samophlange
(29086, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for recovering my blueprints. Now my work on the Silver Bullet X-831 can continue.', 30706), -- Competition Schmompetition
(29023, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Turning the key in the lock, the control console unlocks. A red light at the top of the console turns off and all power drains from the terminal.', 30706), -- Samophlange
(29022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The lights indicating the three control valves dim as they are shut off. Green lights slowly fade into yellow, and the switch controlling the apparatus is now moveable, with the valves closed, it can be turned off.', 30706), -- Samophlange
(29021, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A variety of buttons, levers, and blinking lights are somewhat erratically arrayed on the face of the control console. A small gauge indicates that the apparatus is currently operating within optimal levels, and indicates that control valves one through three are currently open. There is a small keyhole set into the lower right side of the control panel.', 30706), -- Samophlange
(26769, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Nozzlepot snatches the bag of gems from you.>$B$BGazlowe calls this 10%? You tell him I\'m going to weigh these!$B$BI suppose he expects me to pay you a delivery fee, as well? Fine, fine. Have some spoils!', 30706), -- Raging River Ride
(14050, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $n!$B$BOh, the Baron tried to stop you, did he? Well, I hope you gave him a pounding.$B$BNow, I promised you a cut of the goods you recovered. Let\'s see... what\'s one percent of a half percent? Ah, here you go.', 30706), -- Gazlowe's Fortune
(14042, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! Beautiful work, $n. Those Alliance cretins will never trace this back to me. Meanwhile, it\'s back to business as usual: smuggling, double-dealing, price-gouging... I\'ve got a lot of work to catch up on.$B$BHere, I\'ll let you in on a cut of my future profits. Enjoy!', 30706), -- Ammo Kerblammo
(14049, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? What is this? I send you out to fetch my treasure and you bring me a big filthy head?', 30706), -- A Most Unusual Map
(14038, 4, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Excellent! I wish I could\'ve seen the look on that Rear Admiral\'s face when his flagship went up like a candle. Let me use my telescope here to take a look at the damage.$B$BWhat - Whhhaaatt!? That thing is still floating? Hartley must\'ve moved the munitions ashore in case his ship was mined.$B$BI underestimated you, Hartley... but for the last time!', 30706), -- Love it or Limpet
(14063, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Tony is running the show there now? Good! We need more pirates like him in these waters. He\'s a real businessman.$B$B<Dizzywig rubs his hands together greedily.>$B$BSpeaking of business, I suppose I owe you a cut. Would you be interested in insuring any of your new loot? You never know what can happen in a town like this... ', 30706), -- Mutiny, Mon!
(14057, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tony unhinges one of the weapons and peers down the barrel.>$B$BOooh, very nice. Shiny. Loud. Now we\'re talkin\'.$B$BNot much left to do but close the deal...', 30706), -- Guns. We Need Guns.
(14056, 21, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at that. We\'re loaded! In mutiny, you gotta make the money first. Then when you get the money, you get the power. Let\'s go get some power, $n...', 30706), -- Glomp is Sitting On It
(14052, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey hey mon, did Dizzywig send you? Good, good. Did you bring the money? No? ...what about the guns?', 30706), -- Take it up with Tony
(14046, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Baron rubs his sore wrists, his face widening into a malevolent grin.>$B$BOh I won\'t be runnin\' off just yet. I\'ll free me mates and murder my way out of here at a time of me choosin\'. As fer you - a deal\'s a deal. Let\'s talk about that treasure...', 30706), -- The Baron's Demands
(14045, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah-har! So ol\' Gazzy ain\'t given up on his goods yet, has he? Well, looks like that ol\' floppy-eared goldgrubbler jes\' gave me somethin\' ta bargain with.', 30706), -- Find Baron Longshore
(14034, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, this is it - this is it right here! So his flagship is named \"The Bellipotent\" eh?$B$BLet\'s see what it\'ll take to send this nuisance to the bottom of the sea. ', 30706), -- Club Foote
(14067, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gazrog opens the lockbox and begins counting up the silver while you relate your story.>$B$BWhat!? Raptors? Just the raptors? Assaulting our caravans and looting them? Perhaps they are as intelligent as the rumors say. As if we didn\'t have enough problems, now we\'ve got to deal with brainy lizards with a lust for coin.$B$BHere, $n - you\'ve earned a share of the rescued silver. Thank you.', 30706), -- The Stolen Silver
(14068, 71, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hooway! You twapped the waptors I was wooking for! Now we will twain them for twolls to wide to swaughter the Awwiance!', 30706), -- Waptor Twapping
(14066, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This Horde caravan was not merely robbed. It was savagely brutalized. Crates of supplies have been ripped apart by sharp claws. The wagon has been demolished. The food has been eaten and the silver is gone, and yet useful supplies have been left behind...', 30706), -- Investigate the Wreckage
(13999, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quiet! Give me those notes. Were you followed here?', 30706), -- Who's Shroomin' Who?
(13991, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was hoping for a squad of grunts... but if you earned Sergra\'s respect, I suppose you\'ll be more than enough. Let me explain what\'s happening here.', 30706), -- The Purloined Payroll
(14073, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, I\'ve heard about your work, $c. Your timing is fortunate - I\'ve got a major offensive in the works.', 30706), -- Deathgate's Reinforcements
(13998, 6, 11, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Explosive spore clouds? You don\'t say ... tell me more. Choking? Stinging? Burning of the eyes? Was there itching? Nausea? Mortification? Delightful, DELIGHTFUL! You\'ve certainly earned your commission, $n.$B$BThat skin rash of yours should pass in a day or two.', 30706), -- In Fungus We Trust
(13988, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 800, 0, 0, 'I am glad Tonga was able to witness the overgrowth firsthand - words can\'t convey the scope of the damage. Did you bring his totem? I will return it to him when I am finished here.', 30706), -- A Growing Problem
(13995, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Aw mon, why you have to go settin\' Gorgal off like that? Still, I can\'t argue with results. We\'ll need to watch these animals closely to see what they do with Kurak outta the way.$B$BMore watchin\' and waitin\'. Gorgal won\'t like that. ', 30706), -- King of Centaur Mountain
(14072, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n. Did you look through these? They\'re barely legible - more like angry graffiti than war plans. Hatred, jealousy, rage, personal conflicts - it\'s a wonder Verog can keep these centaur from killing each other, much less form them into an army.$B$BWe can use this to our advantage.', 30706), -- Flushing Out Verog
(13992, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Oh, ho! That was beautiful. I probably shouldn\'t have stayed to watch. Now that they\'re looking for you, I\'ll slip quietly away in the dust of their aimless gallopin\'.$B$BBe sure to look for my buds at the other pools. Boss has agents at every one.', 30706), -- A Little Diversion
(13975, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s about time we got some supplies through here. It\'s bad enough to be severed from Mulgore, but this city would fall apart if we lost our trade with Orgrimmar.', 30706), -- Crossroads Caravan Delivery
(13971, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'So that was your handiwork, $r? Yes, the missing Kodo arrived just minutes ago. It will take many nights to nurse the poor beast\'s wounds, but thanks to you it\'s alive. And you saved a whole shipment!$B$BPlease, take your pick of the gear that the kodo was carrying.', 30706), -- The Kodo's Return
(13968, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1200, 0, 0, 'Ah, so Tortusk behaved as I expected? Went right for your throat? It is good that he\'s dead.$B$BThe Razormane quilboar have been separated from their leadership in the southern Barrens, no doubt allowing an animal like him to come to power. Perhaps without his influence we can start a dialogue with the survivors... Although hotter heads may prevail. ', 30706), -- The Tortusk Takedown
(13970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Kodo is voracious! You might as well be pouring those sacks of grain into a hole!$B$BAlready the animal is beginning to perk up.', 30706), -- Animal Services
(13969, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This poor battered kodo looks to be on the verge of death, but is still breathing. The Razormane haven\'t even plundered its cargo yet. If it can be revived, you may be able to save the entire shipment.', 30706), -- Grol'dom's Missing Kodo
(13973, 5, 273, 0, 0, 0, 800, 0, 0, 'I see you\'ve left a string of corpses in your wake, $r. I couldn\'t have done better. The livestock may be lost, but the land remains ours - thank you!', 30706), -- The Grol'dom Militia
(13963, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1500, 0, 0, 'Very interesting - our brute here seems both enthralled and terrified of the one they call \"Tortusk.\" A powerful leader can inspire his people to acts of greatness or atrocity... but we orcs would know that more than others.$B$BWe should turn our attention to this Tortusk problem.', 30706), -- By Hook Or By Crook
(13961, 22, 6, 0, 0, 0, 700, 0, 0, 'Oh my. We want to question this quilboar, not tenderize him!', 30706), -- Drag it Out of Them
(31813, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You fight with the determination of one who does not fear defeat, but does not tolerate it, either. You will go far.', 30706), -- Dagra the Fierce
(13949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a sight, $r. That\'s the first caravan to make it through this week!', 30706), -- Crossroads Caravan Pickup
(13878, 4, 2, 0, 0, 50, 300, 0, 0, 'You save the wolves! So brave! Someday, maybe you get a wolf just like that to ride.$B$B<Dorak looks at the burning stables, then at the nearby river.>$B$BWhat should I do now?', 30706), -- Through Fire and Flames
(26642, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fresh recruit from Orgrimmar is it?$B$B<Kargal sizes you up.>$B$BI\'ll take what I can get. Keeping the roads open has been a nightmare.', 30706), -- Preserving the Barrens
(25243, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m sure she deserved it, $n. She should never have betrayed you like that.$B$BIt gives me the shivers to think that she might have kissed that monster, the Trade Prince!', 30706), -- She Loves Me, She Loves Me NOT!
(25203, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s no two ways about it... he got exactly what he deserved.', 30706), -- What Kind of Name is Chip, Anyway?
(14113, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very nicely done, $g sir : ma\'am;. The party appears to have been a smashing success!$B$BEr... what\'s that?', 30706), -- Life of the Party
(14109, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you are going to look so fine, but not as gorgeous as me! You\'re going to replace the Trade Prince any day now at the rate you\'re going!$B$BI can\'t wait to not have to work anymore! You\'re going to buy me everything that I want, right babe?$B$BLet me have all that stuff and I\'ll help you get into it right before the party.', 30706), -- The New You
(26712, 25, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, it\'s you, sir! Sorry, I didn\'t recognize you at first with all of these commoners milling about.$B$BYou people cool your heels! $n is here!$B$BHere are your macaroons, $g sir : ma\'am;. Come back anytime if you need more.', 30706), -- Off to the Bank
(25165, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it!  The scorpid juju Bom\'bay been waitin\' for!  Now we gonna fix you right up, $c.$b$bYou come back to Bom\'bay when you be needin\' a pickup.  Bom\'bay got the spells to fix ya!', 30706), -- Never Trust a Big Barb and a Smile
(31812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, Varzok. Yes, I know him well. He be makin\' no mistake in sendin\' you here.', 30706), -- Zunta, The Pet Tamer
(32673, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t forget to buy your mount while you are here! You can buy one from Kall Worthaton over there.', 30706), -- Learn To Ride
(32009, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You must be $n. Well met. I am Varzok.$B$BI will serve as your contact from here on out.', 30706), -- Varzok
(26807, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Eitrigg examines the reports.>$B$BThe Alliance has grown bolder than we\'d thought! I\'ll talk to the warchief about sending reinforcements right away. Thank you for getting these reports to me so quickly. I hope this coin is enough to cover your travel expenses.', 30706), -- Return to Eitrigg
(26806, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ready to return to Orgrimmar with those reports? I can arrange a flight for you right away.', 30706), -- Reports to Orgrimmar
(26804, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eitrigg sent you? The warchief must be getting anxious to read my reports. I\'d\'ve sent them long ago, but each day we discover more about the Alliance\'s plans for invading Durotar.', 30706), -- Flight to Razor Hill
(29401, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is GREAT! You did it!$b$bThanks, $gmister:miss;!', 30706), -- Blown Away
(26803, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you need to get to Razor Hill in a hurry? That\'s no problem at all. One of my wind riders will get you there very quickly and it only costs a few coins to hire one.', 30706); -- Missing Reports
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(13801, 5, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Woohooo!!$b$bYou\'ve silenced the voices! Thank you, thank you!', 30920), -- Dead Elves Walking
(13798, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you feel it, $n!?$b$bThe raw fel power seething through your being?$b$bThere is nothing else like it!', 30920), -- Rain of Destruction
(13797, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! These should hold a curse long enough for our purposes....', 30920), -- Dirty Deeds
(13751, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this? Who are you!?$b$b<Durak reads Draaka\'s note.>$b$bHrmphh...$b$bDraaka should know better than to be so brazen, but it looks like you\'re up to your eyes in this with as much to lose as anyone.$b$bVery well.', 30920), -- Tell No One!
(26447, 5, 1, 274, 0, 0, 1000, 1000, 0, 'Dreadlords!  They plan to attack us here at Splintertree Post?!$B$BNot while I still draw breath!$B$B<Valusha crumples the demon-scrawled plans in her fist.>$B$BNo.  We will not allow this to happen!  They are a blight upon our world!', 30920), -- Diabolical Plans
(26448, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'That\'s better!  There\'s nothing quite like ridding our world of a demon.  And they make for worthy opponents as well, unlike the weak races of the Alliance.', 30920), -- Destroy the Legion
(13730, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, yes!$b$bThis will teach those elves, just you watch!', 30920), -- Playing With Felfire
(13805, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done?$b$bGood work, $n. That will gradually weaken their forces, as well as their spirit.', 30920), -- Pierce Their Heart!
(13803, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1500, 0, 0, 'Tainting the Forest\'s Heart?$b$bHow ruthless - an utterly vicious blow....$b$bI adore the idea!', 30920), -- Blood of the Weak
(13712, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Gorka\'s death was not in vain, $n.$b$bSplintertree would have certainly fallen if we hadn\'t come when we did.$b$bNow we must get to work shoring up her defenses.$b$bThis isn\'t over....', 30920), -- To the Rescue!
(13653, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gorka...$b$bWe must always be prepared for losses. Her honorable service to the Horde will not be forgotten.$b$bAnd her sacrifice shall not be in vain!', 30920), -- Crisis at Splintertree
(13651, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for the oil, $c. Now prepare yourself!$b$bMy runner has returned with some desperate news....$b$bSplintertree is surrounded!', 30920), -- Needs a Little Lubrication
(13640, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems you\'ve solved one problem only to face another, $c.', 30920), -- Management Material
(13628, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $c. It is good to see that the road to Mor\'shan Ramparts remains clear.', 30920), -- Got Wood?
(13621, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r.$b$bThe elf captain is dead and the soul of one of our beloved brethren can sleep in peace.$b$bI shall pass on word of your deeds to my superiors in Orgrimmar.', 30920), -- Gorat's Vengeance
(13620, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s have a look, $c.', 30920), -- To Dinah, at Once!
(13612, 5, 1, 5, 0, 0, 500, 500, 0, 'Good work, $c!$b$bYour efforts will help keep the enemy on their heels while our forces sweep across the land!', 30920), -- Mor'shan Defense
(13619, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kadrak listens intently as you share Gorat\'s last words.>$b$bIt is as I feared, then. May his rest be peaceful - only not yet!', 30920), -- Final Report
(13613, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r. I shall include your service to the Horde in my report.$b$bI should have these troops fit to fight again in no time!', 30920), -- Rescue the Fallen
(13615, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c.$b$bThis should help get us by until our shipment arrives.', 30920), -- Empty Quivers
(13618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Listen carefully, $r....', 30920); -- Find Gorat!
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(13842, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As I thought, he was a threat after all. Well done, $n', 32028), -- Dread Head Redemption
(13841, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This woman, Draaka, needs to mind her step. She plays with powers she cannot possibly understand.\n\n<Eitrigg studies you for a moment.>\n\nThis Durak, I sense foul things about this one, and my instincts are rarely wrong.', 32028), -- All Apologies
(13962, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well, $n.$b$bYou have succeeded where I could not. You have earned my respect.', 32028), -- Stalemate
(13958, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Thagg listens intently as you recount your assault on Astranaar.>$b$bThis is good news indeed, $r. But right now, we need more than just good news here.$b$bThese triage kits will be put to good use!', 32028), -- Condition Critical!
(13888, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it! The spirits were right after all!$b$bThe power of fire is subdued and the four elements are returned to harmony.$B$BThe rest of Ashenvale is spared this fiery fate. You have the eternal thanks of the Earthen Ring.', 32028), -- Vortex
(13879, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The goblin stares at you and blinks several times before speaking.>$b$bThe spirits whispered that help would soon arrive.$b$bPardon my surprise, but I was hoping the spirits would guide someone a little more... heroic.$b$bThese elementals are trusted allies. Listen to them and do their bidding. If we fail, there will remain nothing in Ashenvale worth fighting for.', 32028), -- Thunder Peak
(13983, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This looks right, $c.$b$bI should have your shredder put together in no time.', 32028), -- Building Your Own Coffin
(13980, 396, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Nice work, friend.$b$bYour skills have bought us the time we needed to prepare the bomb. It\'s almost complete!', 32028), -- They're Out There!
(13977, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jinx examines the powder carefully for a moment.>$b$bHmmm.$b$bIt\'ll take a little time. But yes, we can put this into a bomb....', 32028), -- Mass Production
(13974, 5, 396, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Well, look at this! Little Tweedle has really come through this time. This stuff blew up Astranaar, you say?$b$bAs you can see, we don\'t need any help taking over Silverwind Refuge, but Tweedle\'s ideas are as small as his hands.$b$bIf this stuff\'s really as good as you say, there\'s no limit to what we might do....', 32028), -- Tweedle's Tiny Package
(13947, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your deeds today shall live long in the Horde\'s glorious history.$b$bYour efforts have dealt a devastating blow to the enemy!', 32028), -- Blastranaar!
(13944, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, Tweedle found a way to get those explosives working, eh?$b$bIt\'s about time...', 32028), -- Small Hands, Short Fuse
(13942, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is PERFECT!$b$bOh, just wait \'til you see what I can do with this....', 32028), -- Set Us Up the Bomb
(13943, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r. But there is much that remains to be done here.', 32028), -- Breathing Room
(13936, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me tell ya somethin\' $c!$b$bThe bossman simply doesn\'t appreciate the art and craftsmanship that goes into making fine explosives.', 32028), -- Tweedle's Dumb
(13923, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You come here as a child, $r.$b$bYou shall leave here a battle-hardened $c of the Horde!$b$bThat, or a corpse....', 32028), -- To Hellscream's Watch
(13901, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!$b$bLet the naga retreat back into the seas where they belong!', 32028), -- Deep Despair
(26890, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! These will do nicely. Here\'s a reward for your hard work.', 32028), -- The Essence of Aku'Mai
(13920, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These venison should make our soldiers\' spirits rise for the coming battles. Here\'s something for your troubles.', 32028), -- Before You Go...
(31814, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You do not understand. I have not been defeated, merely set back.', 32028), -- Analynn
(13890, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $r!$b$bNo more ships will run aground, thanks to you.', 32028), -- Keep the Fires Burning
(13883, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $r.$b$bI\'ll show them how an armored ship should be built!', 32028), -- Lousy Pieces of Ship
(13848, 5, 396, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, '<Commander Grimfang\'s brow wrinkles as he reads the report.>$b$bThis is grim news, indeed.$b$bMay the spirits preserve them until we can fight our way to Splintertree....', 32028), -- Bad News Bear-er
(13967, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Good work, $r.$b$bThis should keep them licking their wounds for a time.', 32028), -- Thinning the... Herd?
(28532, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re to deploy to Stonetalon? Good, we\'ll need your abilities to defeat the Alliance there.', 32028), -- Warchief's Command: Stonetalon Mountains!
(13806, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $r.$b$bOne less thing we have to worry about!', 32028), -- Demon Duty
(26449, 5, 2, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Never again will the Burning Legion make slaves of the orcs, or any other race of the Horde!$B$BBravely fought, $c!  You have the true heart of the Horde beating inside of you!  You give us much honor!', 32028), -- Never Again!
(13875, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Recognizing at once the nature of the gift, Draaka begins to weep.>$b$bOh, $n. Thank you for this gift! It means more than you could know.$b$bHe hasn\'t forgotten...', 32028), -- Gurtar's Request
(13873, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gurtar listens as you inform him of Sheelah\'s passing.>$b$bI\'ll deliver this to Hellscream personally, $r.$b$bIn the meantime, there\'s something I need you to do for me....', 32028), -- Sheelah's Last Wish
(13871, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c.$b$bOne last request - it would probably be best if none of my laborers knew this assassin ever existed.', 32028), -- Security!
(13870, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gorthak sighs disappointedly.>$b$bIf only you\'d arrived an hour ago....$b$bThe diplomat suffered mortal wounds at the hands of an elf assassin.$b$bHow the enemy was able to infiltrate the camp undetected remains a mystery.', 32028), -- As Good as it Gets
(13865, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Well done, $c.$b$bThey\'re in complete disarray. Just look at them!', 32028), -- Wet Work
(13815, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $n.$b$bYou\'ve demoralized the enemy and harvested resources for the Horde.$b$bLet\'s hope the rest of the mission goes as well.', 32028), -- Making Stumps
(13808, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have your work cut out for you here, friend.$b$bLet\'s hope that you\'re up to the task,,,,', 32028); -- Mission Improbable
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(26115, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now you truly know what it means to be a member of the Horde, $n. ', 32144), -- To Be Horde...
(26101, 1, 273, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The traitorous tauren will now stand by as we destroy his precious grove and burn his village to the ground!', 32144), -- Might Makes Right
(26100, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WHAT? My General has been killed by the tauren? This is treason! HIGH TREASON! They will pay for this grievous error.', 32144), -- The General is Dead
(26099, 1, 5, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saw with your own eyes, $n. General Grebo attacked us!$B$B<Masha cries.>$B$BNow what will we do? Surely the Warchief will have us all executed for treason.', 32144), -- Is This Justice?
(26098, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<High Chieftain Cliffwalker takes the insignia from you.>$B$B<High Chieftain Cliffwalker cries out in anger.>', 32144), -- Betrayal at the Grove
(26097, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Orthus is dead. He is clutching something in his hand.', 32144), -- Proof of Lies
(26082, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You possess quite a talent for destruction, $n. Whatever Alliance remain after your rampage across Battlescar Valley will be dealt with by the bomb.', 32144), -- To Battlescar!
(26077, 5, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chieftain Cliffwalker and his tauren seek to commit treason against the Horde! They claim that the ancient tree at the heart of Battlescar Valley is merely a school for druids. They are blind to the fact that desperate measures are taken during war time. My scouts have assured me that the night elves hide a weapon of great power within that tree. We\'re going to end this now!', 32144), -- Final Delivery
(26076, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And they called me crazy. I knew this place was crawling with spies. Poop too.', 32144), -- Spy Infestation
(26075, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sure hope you didn\'t miss any. I don\'t think I can take much more of this!', 32144), -- The Turd Problem
(26074, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Krom\'gar has sent his champion! Well you haven\'t a thing to worry about, Champion. We\'ll get the balloon all fueled up in no time. How about you lend a hand around here while you wait?', 32144), -- Beginning of the End
(26073, 15, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar ogar! You are the embodiment of what it means to be a Horde soldier, $n. If only we had more like you, this war would be over and Kalimdor would belong to the Horde - UNCONTESTED!$B$BRise now as a champion of Krom\'gar!', 32144), -- All's Quiet on the Southern Front
(26063, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Darn still not very happy, but Darn will reward you for what you have done.', 32144), -- The Queen and Her Court
(26134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Furien groans.>\n', 32144); -- Nothing Left for You Here
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(25362, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Traitors to the Horde and traitors to their own people...$B$BI guess they\'re not all bad. They\'ll make fine drinking flasks.', 32185), -- A Grim Discovery
(25391, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'As promised, you have your choice, $n. The muisek of the creatures has been forever sealed into the power of these weapons.$B$BYou may now wield their energy as your own. Use it well.', 32185), -- Weapons of Spirit
(25346, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just imagine the possibilities of what we now possess, $n. Along with the materials that you have collected, I will be able to forever trap the muisek of these creatures into whatever I wish.', 32185), -- Mountain Giant Muisek
(25361, 11, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful, $c! These will do nicely. There are enough here to make a cloak for Korrin, and possibly even more! Thank you.$B$BI hope the trip wasn\'t too dangerous? The area of Feralas is not known for being forgiving, but you\'ve obviously done well enough.$B$BThank you again, $c.', 32185), -- A New Cloak's Sheen
(25345, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. Now the spiritual powers of the faerie dragon will be available to us.$B$BI hope you willing to perform another task for me.', 32185), -- Faerie Dragon Muisek
(25365, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Examining the map reveals it to be the battle plans that Hadoken Swiftstrider wants.  Numerous arrows that perhaps represent troop movements are drawn on the map, though most seem to be headed toward the south rather than to the north where Camp Mojache lies.$B$BAnother section of the map has a picture of what you think is a large insect of some kind, with various tick marks under it.  From the looks of the gnolls, it perhaps represents their losses against the unknown bugs...', 32185), -- Woodpaw Investigation
(25338, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. This is my first time working with treant muisek...', 32185), -- Treant Muisek
(25349, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $n, but the tale of your hunt troubles me. There should not be so many.$B$BThe sickness is still spreading...', 32185), -- Twisted Sisters
(25373, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $n, but there is more work to be done to keep the camp safe. Listen further.', 32185), -- The Hilltop Threat
(25363, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is proof of a good start, $n.  Your skills as a soldier are to be commended.$B$BYou are not the only one I ask that task of.  Many before you have fought them, and in times past, our efforts have kept them at bay.  Recently though, their attempts to push northward into our area of influence have increased dramatically.  Their attacks have also become more savage... almost as if they were desperate.$B$BI have a plan though, $n, that might settle things once and for all against them...', 32185), -- War on the Woodpaw
(25645, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am a fool...I was misled. This is nothing more than a rusted trinket, and my visions have no doubt been fulfilled.$B$BForgive me, $n. But should you meet this demoness again, I pray you will triumph over her as you did Verinias.', 32185), -- Return to Sage Palerunner
(25368, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m free...finally! Oh, it feels so good to be free...$B$BOh, you saw, didn\'t you?', 32185), -- Verinias the Twisted
(25423, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You can feel their anguish, can\'t you?$B$BMy poor friends. At least we can use you to fix things...', 32185), -- Ancient Suffering
(25422, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you! Thank you...$B$BI feel much better. With just a bit more...', 32185), -- The Darkmist Legacy
(25643, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you reach towards the pedestal, you find it empty. A chill fills the room, and you hear a faint voice...>', 32185), -- The Darkmist Ruins
(25387, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am thankful you\'ve come, $c. Our camp is beset by many perils, and yet we must tend to those fleeing the devastation of the cataclysm.$B$BIf there is to be any refuge here, you must help us.', 32185), -- To Camp Mojache
(25641, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done indeed... I\'d expect nothing less from my own daughter. She\'ll make a fine witch doctor someday.', 32185), -- The Flow of Muisek
(25329, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve done it! Cho\'gall himself has been utterly humiliated by you. His minions are dead, the Gordok are scattered, and now all will know the might of the Horde! Lok\'tar, $n. You\'ve more than earned your reward.', 32185), -- Might of the Stonemaul
(25344, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, I can feel the whelp in there. Let\'s get him out and ask him some questions...', 32185), -- Ogre Abduction
(25454, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is an incredible find!  I believe this is the finest yeti hide specimen I have ever seen!$B$BIndeed, this is certainly worthy of an appropriate bounty.  I normally don\'t pay that much for a single hide, but I\'m confident I can make something special from it.  Thanks for thinking of me on this, $n!', 32185), -- Perfect Yeti Hide
(25453, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, excellent!  These are going to work out incredibly well - I can already tell that they\'re going to be much harder when properly cured.$B$BThanks again for your aid, $n.  Here - please take one of my latest creations.', 32185), -- Improved Quality
(25337, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Master always said \"after killing an animal, if we allowed the muisek to escape, it may take the form of an even greater creature.\" This is dangerous stuff. Thanks for helping me with my studies.', 32185), -- Hippogryph Muisek
(28998, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 32185), -- Candy Bucket
(25252, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! Even these fools will soon know that to stand against the Horde means death.', 32185), -- Rulers of Dire Maul
(25342, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'ve you got for me here? You said the Gordunni had this?$B$BDisgusting...', 32185), -- Talk to Swar'jan
(25452, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, excellent!  These hides, when given a special treatment, are as resilient as iron I tell you!  It will take many tries in order to get the right mix down for the tanning, but I am confident they will bring my mark of quality to the next level.$B$BAs for you, $n... your assistance has proven invaluable to me.  Please take your choice from these items I have crafted.', 32185), -- The Mark of Quality
(25336, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 'As my master told me...$B$BUpon a violent death, the muisek of a creature may escape and seek revenge. Shrinking the creatures, as you did, $n, prevents the muisek from escaping. Now we may use it as we please!', 32185), -- Testing the Vessel
(25341, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Let me have a look at this.', 32185), -- The Gordunni Orb
(25209, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have proven yourself to be a trustworthy and dependable ally, $n. ', 32185), -- The Gordunni Threat
(25386, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve been tussling with drakes, eh?$B$BI like it. We need someone who can pull their own weight around here. Are you ready to fight for the Horde?', 32185), -- To Stonemaul Hold
(25250, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The corruption has been stemmed! The forest can begin to heal now.$B$BMay you have the blessing of the Earth Mother wherever you go, friend.', 32185), -- Sealing the Dream
(25241, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The spirits of these guardians will return in time, $n. You\'ve freed them to move on in nature\'s cycle.$B$BNow it falls to us to make sure that cycle is free of corruption and needless suffering.', 32185), -- The Land, Corrupted
(25237, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you once again, $n. I will prepare these for our final task.', 32185), -- Tears of Stone
(25230, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These events disturb me greatly. My study of the antlers while you were gone has revealed little.$B$BWe must find some way to fix this...', 32185), -- More Than Illness
(25340, 2, 0, 0, 0, 400, 0, 0, 0, 'Now I know that Edana is truly dead. This heart, I will keep it in memory of what you did here for me, $n. Thank you.', 32185), -- Dark Heart
(25339, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. You have put an old tauren\'s mind at peace.', 32185), -- Vengeance on the Northspring
(25210, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $n. I will study the horns, but the situation has become even more dire since you left.', 32185), -- Signs of Change
(28510, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is much wrong in Feralas. I am glad to have your help.', 32185), -- Warchief's Command: Feralas!
(29004, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 32185); -- Candy Bucket
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(28521, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $c - I stand guard here as both a speaker for the Timbermaw here in Winterspring and as a defender of the tribe.$B$BOur Winterfall brethren here in this frigid land have fallen under the same corruptive sway as the furbolg of Felwood.  If you\'ve come here offering the Timbermaw furbolgs aid, then we are ready to accept such an offer.', 32305), -- Speak to Salfa
(28366, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r. An action like this will go a long way towards proving yourself as an ally of the Timbermaw.', 32305), -- Disarming Bears
(28338, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sense that you have achieved victory.  Victory... such a hollow word considering what had to be done.  Regardless, you\'ve proven yourself to be worthy of our trust.$B$BIt may take some time before the Timbermaw welcome you without hostility within the Hold.  Still, your perseverance will erode any suspicion my brethren may have about you.  So long as you never betray us and raise weapons against us, we will find common ground.', 32305), -- Deadwood of the North
(28364, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, thank you! I\'m getting out of here right away!$B$BAnd if Ferli sent you here... don\'t tell her I was crying!', 32305), -- The Chieftain's Key
(28362, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Help! Please help!', 32305), -- Stupid Drizle!
(28373, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We furbolg are not foolish, $n. We will not yield Timbermaw Hold to any askers.$B$BHowever, we are also in dire need of assistance. If you help us, we will grant you our favor and allow you passage.', 32305), -- Timbermaw Hold
(28368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, my entire operation\'s nearly been ruined. But you came through in the clinch, $n.$B$BIt could\'ve been worse! I gotta hand it to you.', 32305), -- Fire in the Hole!
(28340, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, nice! I\'ll just take those... carefully...$B$BDon\'t go tellin\' the workers I didn\'t have the guts to go down there myself, you hear? Here\'s your pay... and a little somethin\' extra.', 32305), -- A Bomb Deal
(28335, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You turn the largest handle you can find on the Master Control Pump, and the rattling noises in the nearby pipes stop.$B$BThis gives you a few moments to hear the sound of flames outside before a familiar voice cuts in through a tinny, crackling speaker.', 32305), -- Turn It Off! Turn It Off!
(28380, 20, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a disaster down here! The pump\'s thrown, all my men in there are gone...$B$BYou gotta help!', 32305), -- Pikwik in Peril
(28339, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness the oil is safe! Well done, $n.', 32305), -- Is Your Oil Running?
(28336, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s not working! We\'re going to have to shut it off at the source.$B$BGo talk to the Deputy outside, he\'ll walk you through it!', 32305), -- Slap and Cap
(28370, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pretty little things, aren\'t they? I wonder if we can figure out how to make more of them.', 32305), -- Wisp-napping
(28357, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s hope we put down enough of them to get the message across.', 32305), -- Take it to the Tree
(28334, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mangy curs think they can just waltz in here and ruin my finely-tuned operation. Hah!$B$BI told you not to look directly at the flares, right? Oops.', 32305), -- A Flare Fight
(28333, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Efficiency in the workforce! Wonderful.$B$BMaybe I should check on the goblins inside those shredders later.', 32305), -- It's Time to Oil Up
(28372, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fez sent you, hmm? At least he\'s good for something.', 32305), -- Back to Business
(28374, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s hard work, but it\'s so rewarding when you see them growing up big and strong.$B$BWhen they\'re not covered with demonic thorns, that is!', 32305), -- Weeding the Lawn
(28361, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aren\'t they just adorable?$B$BIt\'s those little victories that keep me going. We\'ll save this forest one squirrel at a time.', 32305), -- Squirrely Clean
(28360, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. They won\'t spread the corruption any further, and they won\'t be in pain either.', 32305), -- Running Their Course
(28994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 32305), -- Candy Bucket
(28306, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kelnir? Hahaha...$B$BSometimes I wonder if her chatter drove all the other dryads away. But I\'m glad she is safe.$B$BWelcome to Whisperwind Grove, $c. Hold peace in your heart, and you will find a home here.', 32305), -- Whisperwind Grove
(28152, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, just what I was expecting. With these herbs, our preparations for Jaedenar are nearly ready.', 32305), -- Jaedenar Awaits
(28288, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see... their eyes are open$B$B<Delaris smiles with bemusement.>$B$BMaybe I\'ll keep Impsy around after all. He\'s got a lot to teach me...', 32305), -- Open Their Eyes
(28102, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A few of the remaining satyr have fled into the deeper woods, but they have taken heavy losses. Good job, $n.', 32305), -- Fight the Power
(28113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See what can get done with a little cooperation?$B$BI\'ll make sure the claw is given to people responsible enough to contain such things... assuming it can\'t be destroyed.', 32305), -- Break the Unbreakable
(28542, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome. My brothers and I are dedicated to the redemption and rejuvenation of this once-sacred forest.', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Felwood!
(28615, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May the Winterfall never threaten the Timbermaw again. Thank you, $n.', 32305), -- Turning the Earth
(28614, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions prove yourself a mighty warrior to me and all the Timbermaw!$B$BLet us hope the Winterfall will be defeated for good now...', 32305), -- Bearzerker
(28545, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps you can help me make sense of my discoveries about the source of the Winterfall furbolgs\' strength.', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Winterspring!
(28748, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe we defeated him, $n! That was the toughest fight yet, but there are still hundreds of crazed zombies roaming around Hillsbrad. We\'ll need to stay alert.', 32305), -- Lawn of the Dead
(28747, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'D... Do you hear that rumblin\'? I think Stillwater is comin\'! HOLY MOLY LOOK OUT!', 32305), -- Someone Setup the Pumpkin Bomb
(28744, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think that made Stillwater angry. He\'s sending the heavy-hitters after us now. No time to lose, friend, let\'s go!', 32305), -- Ghouls Hate My Grains
(28617, 5, 430, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think that was just the start of it, $g bud:lady;! MORE INCOMING!', 32305), -- Flower Power
(28733, 1, 273, 5, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'PHEW! That was close! You\'re a real natural with these plants, $c. You know, I brought the seeds here with me from Lost Isles. I figure once I get them all figured out I\'ll make a fortune in the deadly flower business!$B$BWha... LOOK! MORE ARE COMING!', 32305), -- Basic Botany
(28616, 1, 273, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the fingers destroyed and the hand shattered, the Stormpike will have no choice but to scurry back to their cave in Alterac Valley.$B$B<Cromush spits.>$B$BWarchief Hellscream will hear about your bravery, $n.$B$BAnd rest assured that he will know of the Frostwolf clan\'s treason!', 32305), -- Stormpike Apocalypse
(28605, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the Stormpike forces maimed, the time has come for detonation!', 32305), -- Domination
(28556, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once Melisara is through with you we will detonate the explosives!', 32305), -- Breaking the Hand
(28604, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They won\'t die immediately, but they WILL die! When they finally piece together who was responsible for the deaths of their soldiers, you will be long gone - a phantom of death!', 32305), -- Deception and Trickery
(28603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Melisara\'s voice pervades your thoughts.>$B$BPerfectly handled. You could easily be a Deathstalker. And what could they have even done to you? You acted in self defense!$B$BNow to deal with the final finger.', 32305), -- Infiltration
(28566, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Melisara\'s voice pervades your thoughts.>$B$BThey will see the bloodshed and they will hesitate. Hesitation will make them think twice about ever attacking us again.', 32305), -- Decimation
(28538, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Melisara\'s voice pervades your thoughts.>$B$BThe humans will serve us in life and in death. I will be in contact with you shortly.', 32305), -- Cry of the Banshee
(28506, 273, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The time to act is now. The Stormpike must be crushed!', 32305), -- March of the Stormpike
(28600, 5, 274, 16, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<High Warlord Cromush\'s face turns white.>$B$BTHEY HAVE FORSAKEN US? THEY HAVE FORSAKEN THE HORDE? This cannot be!$B$BI...$B$B<Cromush falls to one knee.>$B$BI... I WILL BE FINE. We will do this without their aid. To hell with the Frostwolf!', 32305), -- Matters of Loyalty
(28587, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You come from Tarren Mill? You reek of death...', 32305), -- Aid of the Frostwolf
(28400, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<High Warlord Cromush salutes.>$B$BHe will be honored as a hero of the Horde, just as he always hoped. What you and Orkus did will save hundreds of lives and ensure that our foothold in Hillsbrad is not lost.', 32305), -- Heroes of the Horde!
(28397, 25, 5, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look upon the carnage, $n. You and I make quite the team!$B$BNow to find those plans and deal with their leaders.', 32305), -- They Will Never Expect This...
(28375, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This place is dark... foreboding. It smells of piss and fur. There are definitely worgen here and very likely dwarves.', 32305), -- The Road to Purgation
(28354, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This mushroom is toxic to living things, but provides a restorative boost to the undead. Let us see how Kasha reacts.', 32305), -- Kasha Will Fly Again
(28355, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though you have taken a sizeable chunk out of the current gnoll populace of Hillsbrad, more will take their place. For now you may sit comfortably knowing that you did your part.', 32305), -- Terrible Little Creatures
(28330, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps with Chet vanquished, the lethality levels of this place will decrease a tad faster. A job well done, $n!', 32305), -- Trail of Filth
(28329, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All signs indicate to a breeding pool being inside the ruined town hall. You\'ll need to investigate!', 32305), -- Angry Scrubbing Bubbles
(28348, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will have my vengeance, but first we must heal Kasha.', 32305), -- Stormpike Rendezvous
(28345, 1, 274, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orkus\' face turns as red as his armor.>$B$BI... uh... the human must have cast some type of mind-altering spell on Orkus. Orkus will explain.', 32305), -- *Gurgle* HELP! *Gurgle*
(28251, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The worgen situation hasn\'t gotten any better and Helcular is really creeping me out.', 32305), -- Trouble at Southshore
(28154, 6, 274, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Muckgill you say? Never heard of him. What is this anyway? Some kind of fin or something?', 32305), -- Muckgill's Flipper or Something...
(27746, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'News of your conquest in Silverpine emboldens us, $n. We are prepared to fight at your command and beat back the last remaining vestiges of humanity in Hillsbrad.', 32305), -- Empire of Dirt
(28571, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was wondering when reinforcements would show up. Suit up, $n. It\'s time to dispense some justice!', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Hillsbrad Foothills!
(27297, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Krog listens to your report.>$B$BI\'m impressed, $n. I would\'ve thought that the Grimtotem criminals would\'ve been more difficult to locate. The Alliance are truly incompetent.$B$BIn truth, I just sought to answer the death of one of my men, but this situation has been more fortunate than expected. If the Grimtotem choose to retaliate, it will likely be against the Alliance. Perhaps we will soon have the manpower to drive the scum from these shores once and for all.', 32305), -- Justice Dispensed
(27296, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Grimtotems should have no trouble understanding our latest message.$B$BAs for you, your contact at Brackenwall Village will want to know of your success. If I know him, he\'ll appreciate the taste of vengeance.', 32305), -- Raze Direhorn Post!
(27295, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tabetha smiles slightly.>$B$BKrog wishes me to scry for the Grimtotems, eh? Well, I have no need of magic in this case.$B$BIt seems we have a mutual enemy. The Grimtotems have built an outpost nearby and are a constant thorn in the side of me and my students.', 32305), -- Seek Out Tabetha
(27293, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Krog reads over the battle plan.>$B$BThere\'s no doubt in my mind that the Grimtotems are moving against the humans. What I don\'t understand is what their intentions are toward us. We knew nothing of these plans and we lost a good man because of it. I don\'t trust that we\'re not next on their list.', 32305), -- The Grimtotem Plot
(27294, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Krog inspects the weapons and armor you\'ve brought from Blackhoof Village.>$B$BThis is unmistakably the work of Mosarn. Questioning him further may draw too much attention, but we have a bit more freedom in dealing with the Grimtotems.', 32305), -- More than Coincidence
(27292, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He actually said that the Grimtotems are his biggest customers? Mosarn gave us more help than he knows. With this much pointing toward the Grimtotems, I think we just found our first suspects.', 32305), -- Return to Krog
(27258, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, you are certainly correct. This is a shield that I made.$b$bI\'m afraid there\'s not much more I can tell you though, $n. I craft so many different shields and sets of armor, I can\'t keep track of them all.', 32305), -- The Black Shield
(27418, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That cowardly fat mass Mok\'Morokk fled like a scared child. You have done a great service, $n.$b$bNow my people can appoint a new leader, one who will help us reclaim our old home once and for all.', 32305), -- Challenge Overlord Mok'Morokk
(27415, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Splendid! It will be sometime before Onyxia can produce more eggs.$b$bOn behalf of my people, I thank you, $n.$b$bI have asked much of you so far. Perhaps you can do the Stonemaul Clan one last service.$b$bMok\'Morokk is not fit to lead us. Tharg would make an excellent leader but is hindered by his injuries and age. Drive Mok\'Morokk from this place by force. Only then can we appoint a new leader to return us to our proper home in the south.', 32305), -- The Brood of Onyxia
(27417, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That lazy coward!$b$bMok\'Morokk displayed strength when Rexxar was our leader. But soon after Rexxar\'s departure Mok\'Morokk fell prey to temptations of power. Rather than lead, he demanded. He does not serve his people but rather expects us to serve him.$b$bSomething must be done.', 32305), -- The Brood of Onyxia
(27416, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why you tell me \'bout dragons? Me no like dragons. Me like it here. No dragons here.', 32305), -- The Brood of Onyxia
(27414, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '\'Twas a perilous affair, no doubt, collecting all of these hearts and tongues. I shall delve into the depths of the arcane to trace the origin of the black menace which has descended upon our former home.', 32305), -- Identifying the Brood
(27424, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You good $r. Me miss things very much. Me like you now.', 32305), -- Overlord Mok'Morokk's Concern
(27348, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow! You certainly found a lot more than I expected would be out there. I\'m not sure how much Drazzit thought we were going to find out here, but he\'s going to have to be happy with this for now.', 32305), -- Secure the Cargo!
(27347, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it does look a little cleaner out there...$B$BI suppose it\'s time to get down to the business of salvaging this wreckage.', 32305), -- Corrosion Prevention
(27346, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So those hermit mages sent you? How can I be sure that I can trust you?$B$BI suppose I can use the help. There\'s not much here a mage would be interested in, anyway.', 32305), -- The Zeppelin Crash
(27339, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Apprentice Garion inspects the venom.>$B$BThis is absolutely perfect! He\'ll never know the difference.', 32305), -- The Reagent Thief
(27336, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The apprentice listens as you describe your experiment.>$B$BA haze and some lightning? That\'s it? There\'s got to be more to the totem than just that! The Grimtotems aren\'t likely to bring something like this to the battlefield unless it has some kind of utility.', 32305), -- The Grimtotem Weapon
(27340, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Apprentice Morlann nods.>$B$BGood. Can\'t say I\'ll miss the company, if you can call it that. You\'d think at least in the middle of the swamp you\'d get some privacy, you know?', 32305), -- Direhorn Raiders
(27253, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The inspector regards you with what can only be disdain and distrust.>$B$BLeave this place be, errand boy, or I\'ll be sure to bring a contingent of guard with me next time to sink the lesson home.', 32305), -- Inspecting the Ruins
(25051, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a great relief, $c. Thank you.', 32305), -- Darkmist Extermination
(27229, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By Grom, I\'m glad that\'s over with. If you read that sign you may have some idea how desperate I got after trying to communicate to these lumbering oafs.', 32305), -- SMASH BROODQUEEN
(27257, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mosarn? Sounds familiar... I can\'t put my finger on it. Maybe it\'ll come to me later.$b$bIt probably isn\'t important. A shield can come from anywhere and not mean anything...', 32305), -- The Black Shield
(27261, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmph. It is good that Reethe will no longer be lurking around the swamp, but it is a shame that humans are built so frail that he could not recover from a little arrow wound.$b$bIt seems that this thread of the mystery has led nowhere, and we must look elsewhere.', 32305), -- Questioning Reethe
(26682, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. We\'ll be able to focus on greater threats here now.', 32305), -- A Shambling Threat
(27244, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n.  Our agent, Marg Nighteye, was stationed outside Theramore.  He was charged to spy on the city.  $B$BThis is his latest report, and it may be his last -- from your testimony, I fear that Marg met his end in the swamp...', 32305), -- The Lost Report
(27256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t like spiders that are so big I can\'t sit on them and squish them.$b$bThanks for getting them, $n. Now I rip them open and pour them onto the shield...', 32305), -- The Black Shield
(27306, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ogron? Yeah, that me.$B$BShh. Keep voice down. Crocs hear you.', 32305), -- Talk to Ogron
(27186, 1, 36, 4, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'That\'s a good blade.  It has a good swing.  It\'s a good swing blade.  Thank you.  Thank you, thank you, thank you!!!  Now I want to try it....  $B$BLater.  I\'ll try it later.  But like I was saying... thanks.', 32305), -- Jarl Needs a Blade
(27191, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonder what it\'s like to be an ogre. Big people have to eat more.$B$BOgres must be even hungrier than me. That doesn\'t sound very fun.', 32305), -- Hungry as an Ogre!
(27184, 4, 1, 3, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 'You got the eyes!  You got the eyes!  Tasty, tasty spider eyes!$B$BSome eyes... when you stare at them they stare back. Eat those last.  They keep you company... out in the swamp.$B$BHello, little spider eyes.  Hello!  You taste like chicken.  Gooey, salty chicken!$B$BMmmh.', 32305), -- Jarl Needs Eyes
(27190, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It worked?$B$B<Mordant clears his throat.>$B$BI mean... it worked! Jarl and I are in your debt, $n. Now the only remaining problem is my friend\'s taste in furniture, and I\'m afraid that won\'t be solved as easily.', 32305), -- Cleansing Witch Hill
(27189, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mordant accepts the bunch of herbs from you.>$B$BThese match the description exactly! I prepared the torch while you were out. All that remains is to fasten the herbs to the end here.', 32305), -- The Witch's Bane
(27188, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mordant produces a small sheet of paper and a pen, beginning to scribble down notes on your findings.>$B$BFrom your findings, the spirits in this place must amount to everyone who ever lived on this land, not just the previous occupants.$B$BSomething has been corrupting and killing them. Those who follow don\'t learn the truth until it\'s too late. We have to put an end to this, $n!', 32305), -- What's Haunting Witch Hill?
(27183, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, that\'s the spice!  Now here\'s some swampy good stew.', 32305), -- Marsh Frog Legs
(27182, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have you come here to spy on me? No?$B$BPerhaps you have an appreciation for fine cuisine, then? Good, you can help!', 32305), -- The Hermit of Witch Hill
(25292, 6, 5, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Alto clenches the bullet in his palm as you tell your story.>$B$BGann? Dead? I ... I should\'ve known. His temper... his recklessness. I knew someday it would get the better of him.$B$BBut it sounds as though you\'ve already gifted him with vengeance. Thank you, $n!$B$BTurn your attention now to Dustwallow. If the Alliance finishes their cursed road through here, all your victories in the Barrens may have been for nothing. ', 32305), -- Next of Kin
(27255, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is good shield. Very strong, heavy, good. But Do\'gol don\'t need it. I make shields, not buy them, $n.$b$bYou should know that.', 32305), -- The Black Shield
(27254, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I grant that humans have strange decorating tastes, but would they use a plain iron shield to adorn their fireplace? Perhaps this shield was placed there by the ones who burned the inn.$b$bA warning? A threat?', 32305), -- The Black Shield
(27260, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... now this is interesting.', 32305), -- Lieutenant Paval Reethe
(27259, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hoofprints... It could have been the quilboar, I suppose. Or maybe even the centaur. Their presence in the Barrens is not insignificant, and I would not think it a stretch to commit such an act.$b$bDid I tell you? It wasn\'t just that the inn was burned down... The owner\'s woman and pup were killed. Bad business, that.$b$bNonetheless, I will send Kagoro to find where the tracks lead.', 32305), -- Suspicious Hoofprints
(28554, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If we can get things straightened out here, we have a chance to strike at the Alliance while most of their forces are busy in the Barrens.', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Dustwallow Marsh!
(27411, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brogg listens as you recount your experience at the entrance to Onyxia\'s lair.>$B$BBrogg know Onyxia dead. Brogg know her brood still there. Brogg not let them forget the Stonemaul.$B$BBrogg is grateful for your help, $n, and he will never forget what you have done for him. Brogg will never give up his quest to bring Stonemaul back where they belong.', 32305), -- Challenge to the Black Flight
(27410, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brogg thanks you for your help, although he knows Overlord Mok\'Morokk never will. At least surviving Stonemaul can finally focus on problems with the living and leave dead where they belong. Only one thing remains for Brogg to do.', 32305), -- Spirits of Stonemaul Hold
(27409, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have Brogg\'s thanks, $n. Once Brogg adds their magic to the totem, it will be able to redeem the spirits of Brogg\'s fallen friends.', 32305), -- The Essence of Enmity
(27408, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have Brogg\'s thanks, $n. Brogg has big plans for clan banner.', 32305), -- Banner of the Stonemaul
(27407, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Brogg accepts the feathers.>$B$BBrogg pleased with these feathers. Very strong magic. Brogg not know what raptors do to give feathers power, but raptor feathers always best for ritual.', 32305), -- Bloodfen Feathers
(27412, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness someone\'s finally taken me up on that offer. I was just thinking that I might need to triple the reward to get that stupid raptor killed, and our budget couldn\'t afford that!', 32305), -- WANTED: Goreclaw the Ravenous
(27413, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you! This will help keep our guys going out in the field until Moxie returns with the rest of the supplies from the zeppelin crash.', 32305), -- Catch a Dragon by the Tail
(28504, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Horde forces in Thousand Needles desperately need your help.', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Thousand Needles!
(26696, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah?  What can I do for ya?', 32305), -- The Call of Kalimdor
(26703, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n!  You\'re awake!  We found you bobbing in the harbor, shortly after the remaining attackers had turned tail.  We were worried about you for a while there...$b$bI\'ve been meaning to thank you, $n.  Not only did you provide us with the intelligence to prepare for this attack, but you helped fight off the Bloodsail AND the Brashtide.  Your name will always be remembered here in Booty Bay.$b$bWe here in Booty Bay pride ourselves on our booty.  Care to take first pick?', 32305), -- Bloodsail's End
(26697, 11, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope those mongrels know how to doggy paddle!$b$bActually, I take that back.', 32305), -- The Final Voyage of the Brashtide
(26699, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We need to keep moving, $n.  Booty Bay won\'t hold out for much longer.', 32305), -- Turning the Brashtide
(26700, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Attacking your former crewmen...$b$bYou really have grown into a real pirate, $n!', 32305), -- The Damsel's (Bad) Luck
(26695, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You brought them!  I\'m beginning to think the tide is turning in our favor, $n.', 32305), -- Prepare for Takeoff
(26698, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I should have known these Brashtide were alive and up to no good.  I\'d written them off years ago.', 32305), -- Seeking Seahorn
(26679, 7, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Baron quickly empties his cup.>$b$bAH!  Much better, $n.  Now, let\'s get down to business.  I believe that you and I have a town to save.', 32305), -- Return to Revilgaz
(26678, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This must be the doublerum.  You pour a glass for Revilgaz, then consider pouring one for yourself...', 32305), -- Doublerum
(26665, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Brashtide!?  I thought they were dead and gone YEARS ago!$b$b<Revilgaz listens intently as you relay the information you gathered.>$b$bNo, that absolutely makes sense.  And it\'s not good news either.  The Brashtide are formidable foes, and if their numbers are anywhere near what they were before they disappeared, we\'re in for a nasty battle.', 32305), -- Call of Booty
(26664, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fewer Bloodsail Buccaneers that Booty Bay has to fight, the better.  However, it might be best to stop slaughtering your supposed allies before you draw suspicion to yourself.', 32305), -- Making Mutiny
(26662, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Brashtide Crew aren\'t just pirates... they\'re worgen pirates!  And they\'re joining in on the attack!$b$bRevilgaz is definitely going to want to know about this.', 32305), -- The Brashtide Crew
(26663, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve set the pirates back several days\' work.  Hopefully this will delay their attack.', 32305), -- Sinking From Within
(26650, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You see a set of plans unrolled on the table.  They explain everything!$b$bThese are the details of the impending attack on Booty Bay.  Battle formations, plans of attack, and something about a group called the \"Brashtide Crew\".', 32305), -- The Damsel's Luck
(26649, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahahaha!  Blasted \'em clear off their rigging!  I\'ll drink to that!$b$bYou\'ve got a bright future, kid.', 32305), -- Drive-By Piracy
(26648, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n.  The eternal battle wages on, but we\'ve tipped the scales in favor of the pirates today.  Firallon will be happy to hear the news.', 32305), -- Our Mortal Enemies
(26647, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I like the cut of your gib, $n.', 32305), -- Ol' Blasty
(26644, 396, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So ye be the one that did ol\' Seahorn?  Yancey sent word, but I wanted to make sure he hadn\'t been telling his tall tales again.$b$bI\'ll make it brief.  Ye did well on Keelhaul\'s crew, but I expect ye to do even better on mine.  I\'ve got an entire fleet to attend to, so you\'ll be helpin\' to run the day-to-day of me ship.$b$bWelcome aboard the Crimson Veil, sailor.', 32305), -- Attracting Attention
(26634, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll distribute these right away, $r.  And I\'ll see what I can do to put in the good word for you.', 32305), -- The Bane of Many A Pirate
(26633, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I heard the most furious mopping sounds from down here, $g mate: wench;.  That\'s EXACTLY what your Captain likes to hear.', 32305), -- Swabbing Duty
(26635, 4, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks, $n.  I\'d been hearing whispers about \"Pretty Boy\" and a \"boo-box\".  I don\'t think I want to go in the boo-box.', 32305), -- Cannonball Swim
(26631, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... yes... I see... well, everything appears to be in order.$b$bSlayer of the great Seahorn, eh?  That doesn\'t matter on MY ship.  Only thing you\'re gonna be slaying is deck stains.  Grab a mop.', 32305), -- Your First Day as a Pirate
(26629, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well blow me down!  Now there\'s something ya don\'t see too often.$b$b<Yancey reaches out and shakes your hand.>$b$bWelcome aboard, $n.  Plunder and booty await ye.', 32305), -- Seeing Where Your Loyalties Lie
(26630, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should fool that Bloodsail dimwit.$b$bThis was fun, $n.', 32305), -- Looks Like a Tauren Pirate to Me
(26595, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great!  I can get a good price for these, especially for what\'s inside Maury\'s foot!  Thanks much, $n!$B$BI hope those three learned their lesson: don\'t bet something you can\'t afford to lose.$B$BAnd maybe it\'s too late for them, but...they should be careful of who they gamble with.', 32305), -- Kill-Collect
(25591, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fantastic. I might challenge you to a duel myself someday.', 32305), -- Thunderdrome: Grudge Match!
(25107, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is truly incredible. The hieroglyphs are undoubtedly titan, but the markings below it...$B$BSome of these characters resemble ancient Kaldorei writings. And you say the antechamber was covered in hieroglyphs?$B$BYou\'ve made a find more monumental than any riches, $n. Please, take whatever reward you prefer.', 32305), -- The Grand Tablet
(25068, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Marvelous. To think the shapers of our world crafted these...', 32305), -- The Crumbling Past
(25070, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The chest now grinds open again, the rest of the antechamber fallen silent.', 32305), -- What Lies Within
(25069, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This chest lies undisturbed, sealed for thousands of years.', 32305), -- The Secrets of Uldum
(25017, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. We would be hard pressed to face such enemies without your assistance.', 32305), -- Ancient Obstacles
(25019, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. The less interference from the Alliance, the better.', 32305), -- Laying Claim
(25020, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. With that dealt with, we can focus our attentions fully on exploring the gateway.', 32305), -- Fragments of Language
(25018, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of all the...you found this in an ogre den? Unthinkable. I\'m amazed they didn\'t try to smash it to pieces.$B$BWith any luck, $c, we\'ll be able to obtain even more fascinating antiquities here...if you\'re willing to help.', 32305), -- Andoren Will Know
(25014, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found that in the ogre den? That\'s...$B$B...nothing to get excited about, I\'m sure! I\'m sure it\'s just...a perfectly benign trinket...that I\'m going to give you precisely detailed instructions on exactly how to handle.$B$B<Megs drops her voice to a whisper.>$B$BKeep your voice down and don\'t wave that thing around.', 32305), -- Sandscraper's Treasure
(25001, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And that\'s a wrap! Nothing left here for us but sand. Good job, babe.$B$BWell, maybe I shouldn\'t be so hasty. Did you find anything in that ogre den?', 32305), -- Sandscraper
(24963, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job, you\'ve taught half the ogres here to fear and respect anything vaguely $r-shaped.$B$BIt\'s amazing what a little reward will do to keep people under your thumb, isn\'t it? Here\'s your payment, by the way.$B$B...what\'s with that look?', 32305), -- Maul 'Em With Kindness
(24957, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ugh! This entire camp is like a sampler course of awful smells.$B$BLet\'s not handle these things any longer than we have to.', 32305), -- Get The Centipaarty Started
(24955, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, nice work! I\'m amazed you even got them to hold a pen without eating it.$B$BYou can uh, just throw the suit over there. Away from me. In the fire.', 32305), -- Un-Chartered
(24905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve got a great one for you this time, $n. We\'re gonna initiate these ogres into the Horde...working directly under us.', 32305), -- Returning a Favor
(25103, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re with Megs, huh? Word is she\'s been pretty hell-bent on making nice with Noggenfogger.$B$BNot like I care. Are you ready to kill some bugs?', 32305), -- Bootlegger Outpost
(24950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sea giants? You think he was training them towards Gadgetzan on purpose?$B$BWhatever, he\'s splitsville now. And Gadgetzan owes us big time! I can\'t wait to see the look on Marin\'s face.$B$BHere\'s your cut, babe. You\'re moving up in the world.', 32305), -- Captain Dreadbeard
(25541, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice!  Remember, gold is gold, no matter who\'s mouth, nose, or otherwise it\'s been in.$B$BIt\'s all perfectly sanitary after being melted down anyway. Or at least wiped off.', 32305), -- Filling Our Pockets
(25534, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, kid. Any close calls? Did you get grazed?$B$BNo? Good, because we\'ve got more fish to fry here.', 32305), -- Going Off-Task
(24949, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful! And to think these idiots were just sitting on it.$B$BHere\'s a bit up front, we\'ll talk about profit-sharing bonuses later.', 32305), -- Booty Duty
(24928, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful job. Have you ever thought about becoming a full-time arsonist? I know a few people, it\'s a nice gig.$B$BWell, we\'ll chit-chat about that one later. More to do here!', 32305), -- To The Ground!
(24927, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pleased to report that our brand recognition in this area has skyrocketed now that you\'ve killed most of the people who didn\'t want us here.', 32305), -- Dead Man's Chest
(24947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good thing you\'re here! I\'m gonna need a lot of help if we want to beat these gnomes to the punch.', 32305), -- Momentum
(24910, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Isn\'t it nice when you can do a good deed, and see enormous future financial gains from it? It warms my little goblin heart. And my big goblin wallet.$B$BYou did great, kid. Gadgetzan\'s gonna be ours soon. Here\'s a little token of my appreciation.', 32305), -- Rocket Rescue
(24907, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Property values have already gone up since you left. People like seafront views that don\'t include briny, gnarled giants stomping around.$B$BHere\'s your cut, $n.', 32305), -- Puddle Stomping
(24906, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm, mostly usable. This is good stuff. I\'ve already got buyers lined up, of course.$B$BHere\'s your advance for the rest of the work you\'re gonna do for me and the Bilgewater Cartel...partner.', 32305), -- Seaside Salvage
(25095, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rather impressive. Few can bear to see a silithid reaver face to face, let alone defeat it.', 32305), -- Thunderdrome: Sarinexx!
(25094, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad. You\'ve got a ways to go, however.', 32305), -- Thunderdrome: Zumonga!
(25067, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An impressive start. Be prepared for more.', 32305), -- Thunderdrome: The Ginormus!
(28509, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could use your help, $c. That blasted gnome is trying to persuade the Steemwheedle Cartel to favor her side!', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Tanaris!
(27447, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well hello there, $c. Welcome to Tanaris!', 32305), -- Tanaris is Calling
(32674, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, good to see you. You look like you are ready to take to the skies!\n\nRemember, you can buy a flying mount from Drakma, just behind me.', 32305), -- I Believe You Can Fly
(24591, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve just learned a little something about the inner workings of Horde high command.$B$BWarlord Bloodhilt is in charge of Desolation Hold now. He may have more for you to do in the courtyard below. ', 32305), -- Changing of the Gar'dul
(29005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 32305), -- Candy Bucket
(27601, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lady Sylvanas Windrunner grimaces in pain.>$B$BThis... is not over. Godfrey and his traitorous allies will pay for what they have done as will the remaining Alliance forces occupying Lordaeron.$B$BOur work has only just begun.', 32305), -- Cities in Dust
(27594, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done it! Finally, everything is in place. Should Crowley not accept our terms, his daughter will be turned.', 32305), -- On Her Majesty's Secret Service
(27575, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 4000, 0, 0, 'Now let\'s see if I can do this.$B$B<Godfrey starts mumbling under his breath.>$B$B...leg bone connects to the thigh bone...$B$B...arm bone to torso...$B$B...sprinkle on a little Forsaken necromancy...$B$BTA-DA!', 32305), -- From the Belly of the Beast
(27574, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know that face, $n. This head belongs to a former Gilnean known as Sean Dempsey. He was imprisoned with Crowley before the great outbreak.$B$B<Godfrey pauses to think for a moment.>$B$BI wonder if it would be possible to put him back together. The rest of him must be in the belly of these crocolisks.', 32305), -- I Never Forget a Face
(27580, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The rest of the Alliance fleet will arrive shortly, only to find their base camp decimated. Now for the second and most important part of our battle plan.', 32305), -- Sowing Discord
(27577, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Walden flips through the battle plan.>$B$BIt looks like the reinforcements from the ships in Gilneas are marching soon. Crowley and Bloodfang have set up an encampment to the southeast for the Gilneas Liberation front.\n', 32305), -- 7th Legion Battle Plans
(27548, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I suspect we\'ll see fewer humans at the Battlefront. The risk for these cowards is too great.', 32305), -- Lessons in Fear
(27547, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What happened here today is between us. Say a word to anyone and you will find yourself in a corpse pit next to these poor fools.', 32305), -- Of No Consequence
(27550, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The part of me that was Gilnean died at Tempest\'s Reach. Only vengeance remains, $n. To that end, we have work to do. Spare me your pointless queries.', 32305), -- Pyrewood's Fall
(27542, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The hour of victory approaches, $n. Godfrey has devised a plan to decimate our enemies. I am sending you into the field with him and his men to bring the rebel insurgents to their knees and seal the fate of the Alliance filth encroaching upon our lands.$B$BOur final march begins when you are ready.', 32305), -- Taking the Battlefront
(27518, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Had I not witnessed what you did with my own eyes I would not have believed it, $n. Now, with the Ambermill magi on our side, there is but one thing left to do before we retake Gilneas and send those Alliance dogs running for Stormwind.', 32305), -- Transdimensional Warfare: Chapter III
(27510, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I only hope that we don\'t end up getting beat down by inconspicuous birds, cats and trees next... or seals. Could you imagine it?', 32305), -- A Wolf in Bear's Clothing
(27513, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Banshee Queen\'s voice invades your thoughts.>$B$BExcellent work, $n. Now to eject them into our waiting hands!', 32305), -- Transdimensional Warfare: Chapter II
(27512, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Banshee Queen\'s voice invades your thoughts.>$B$BYes, this is it. Now run the ring along the runes of the portal and you should become attuned for transdimensional travel.', 32305), -- Transdimensional Warfare: Chapter I
(27484, 6, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only one may enter? I know just the person for this mission.$B$B<Sylvanas nods at you.>$B$BI will prepare our forces and have them at the ready.', 32305), -- Only One May Enter
(27483, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thought for sure that with the death of a dozen of my most hated enemies I would feel a great burden lifted from my shoulders. Sadly, I do not feel a thing. Perhaps I am a psychopath.', 32305), -- Practical Vengeance
(27478, 21, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. I hope this wasn\'t too much trouble to come by, $n. Relios was a pupil of mine back when I was a mortal man thereby making him a competent and formidable adversary. I suppose I could have warned you ahead of time.$B$BNow, let us see the ring.$B$B<Dalar trails the ring across the spine of the codex.>$B$BThere we are...', 32305), -- Relios the Relic Keeper
(27476, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Dark Lady requires my expertise? Well of course! Give it here, $g boy:girl;.', 32305), -- Dalar Dawnweaver
(27474, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Clever mages. The codex is sealed by a magical ward.$B$BPity that they weren\'t clever enough to realize that former archmages of Dalaran are now Forsaken.', 32305), -- Breaking the Barrier
(27475, 457, 457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. The praise the Banshee Queen lavishes upon you is apparently not unfounded.', 32305), -- Unyielding Servitors
(27322, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That towering behemoth has killed hundreds of Forsaken soldiers. You\'ve done a great thing, $n.', 32305), -- Korok the Colossus
(26305, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it!  You freed Yenniku from the will of Zanzil and the tyranny of the Skullsplitter, and completed the mission I had thought was so hopeless.  Zanzil still looms a threat in the Cape of Stranglethorn, but for now, I at least know that the soul of my chief\'s son is free.$B$BOur tribe will remember your name in songs, $n, and we will etch your tale in stone so that it will live forever.', 32305), -- Saving Yenniku
(26386, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You explain to Surkhan what has happened up to this point.>$b$bIt would seem that Jin\'do has survived, and he is rallying his brothers to once again summon Hakkar into this world.  It was good of you to come to speak with me.$b$bThere is not much we can do now but to wait, and watch.  Jin\'do is weak, and prime for striking, but I must wait for word from Rastakhan before issuing orders.  Until then, you and your raptor will have to wait.', 32305), -- Surkhan
(26362, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a shame, yes.$b$bThis is what the spirits wanted, yes.$b$bMaybe when you are stronger, you will go into Zul\'Gurub and take back your $n\'aka from Mandokir, yes.$b$bFor now, Priestess give you this.', 32305), -- Be Raptor
(26405, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As promised, your reward.  You do the troll nation proud.', 32305), -- Zul'Mamwe Mambo
(26360, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hold on, next part is tough, yes.$b$bLots of chances to fail, yes.$b$bBut $n and $n\'aka going to be reunited... yes they will.', 32305), -- Mind Control
(26304, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My mother\'s spirit rests well tonight, $n.$b$bAs will I.', 32305), -- Nighttime in the Jungle
(26403, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great!  Wonderful!  I can get a bundle for these!!$B$BThat Venture Company sure picked the wrong jungle to mine in, didn\'t they?  We\'d all be in better shape if they moved out of here.', 32305), -- Venture Company Mining
(26400, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The goblin peers inside.>$b$bWhaaaaaa?!?$b$bI\'m... I\'m going to have to send this to... to Flem... in the south.  He\'ll know what to do with it.', 32305), -- The Universal Key
(26352, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fuel regulator?  This seems important.  At least, I hope it is.$b$bWe may not have ended the Venture Company\'s operations, but we at least slowed them down.  Thank you, $n.', 32305), -- Cozzle's Plan
(26359, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did Priestess tell you?$b$bThe raptor is daughter of Ohgan, heir to Mandokir\'s seat.$b$bHah!', 32305), -- See Raptor
(26351, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You bring feathers, yes.$b$bYou can follow directions, yes.', 32305), -- Mind Vision
(26399, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Skeezy struggles fruitlessly to open the box.>$b$bThose ogres really know how to close a treasure chest, I\'ll tell you what.  A box is useless to me, $g hero: my dear;.  We\'re going to need to find a way into this crate.', 32305), -- The Mosh'Ogg Bounty
(26303, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You retrieved the eye!  Your might is the stuff of legends, $n!$B$BAnd in getting the Eye, you must have defeated Mai\'Zoth and sent him to the Nether.  That is why the spirits would not mention him before.$B$BIt is good that he is gone from the world of flesh and bone, but now that he is in the realm of spirits...I fear he will begin a new reign.$B$BBut that is a worry for another time.', 32305), -- The Mind's Eye
(26350, 94, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mandokir is alive, yes.$b$bYou are responsible, yes.$b$bYou may be able to stop him still, yes.', 32305), -- Priestess Hu'rala
(26302, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zanzil the Outcast??$B$BIf Yenniku is held by that troll, a vile and powerful witchdoctor, then I fear that only a faint hope remains.  Faint.  And tiny as the smallest insect.$B$BFortunately, I have some suspicions of my own.  Suspicions which may lead to Yenniku\'s salvation.', 32305), -- Chasing Yenniku's Fate
(26301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes.  These will serve me well.  When my spirit is freed, I will enter the Nether with some fine servants indeed!$B$BYou are a credit to your $r clan, and you have appeased me.', 32305), -- Speaking with Nezzliok
(26334, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad to see you\'ve come to your senses.$b$bCome and visit us in Zul\'Gurub sometime, $r.  I\'ll be watching...', 32305), -- Bloodlord Mandokir
(26332, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You throw the mojo into the pot.>$b$bExcellent work, $r.  You and your raptor have done a great thing.  Hakkar would be most pleased...', 32305), -- Skullsplitter Mojo
(26345, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! Thanks to your help I\'ll have this order filled and sent off to Director Riddlevox on the next boat to Undermine. Ahead of schedule, even!$b$bFor all your hard work, here, I made some extras, so take a pair. It\'s on Drizzlik.$b$bAnd remember, there\'s no boot so fine as one of Drizzlik\'s Excelsior line!', 32305), -- Excelsior
(26344, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My boots... they\'re like sausages, $n. Look great, taste great. I tell you they\'re filled with nothing but the finest ingredients and meats, and you eat it, and you love it.$b$bIt\'s safer--and more enjoyable--if you just trust me, and don\'t ask too carefully what\'s really inside.', 32305), -- Some Assembly Required
(26269, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve certainly saved me a heap of trouble, $n!  I can\'t thank you enough.  It shouldn\'t be long now until we see Master Nesingwary\'s book in libraries throughout the world!$B$BI\'ll leave a copy of the book right here, if you ever want to take a peek at the finished product.  Thanks again, $n!', 32305), -- The Green Hills of Stranglethorn
(26343, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These skins should do. Their quality isn\'t too important, given that they\'ll make up the inside layer of the boots, but it\'s still important that they\'re comfortable.$b$bIf they\'re a bit too rigid, I\'ll use some tiger blood to soften it up. Tricks o\' the trade, you know?', 32305), -- Supply and Demand
(26340, 34, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm?  Barnil\'s the name.  And you are...?', 32305), -- The Hunt
(26338, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Balance is restored - for now.  We may call on you again in the future, $n.', 32305), -- Population Con-Troll
(26330, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $r.  Only one more step remains before I may return.', 32305), -- Who's a Big Troll?
(26300, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You place the head of Nezzliok within the cauldron...', 32305), -- Nezzliok Will Know
(26299, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  I will inspect these heads to ensure poor Yenniku was spared the headhunter\'s axe.', 32305), -- Headhunting
(26325, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You drop the fetishes into the pot.>$b$bYes... yesss...$b$bMy spirit is strong again, $r, and I am ready to return to the world.  Now I need a body.', 32305), -- A Nose for This Sort of Thing
(26281, 113, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, '<Aggro\'gosh salutes you.>$b$bThe Horde thanks you, $n.  Grom\'gol is protected, if only for today.', 32305), -- The Defense of Grom'gol: Trollish Thievery
(26323, 71, 153, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What do we have here?  A young raptor, and her pet $r.  Hah!$b$bMore importantly, what is that skull you have there?  This was no ordinary troll.  He was big...$b$b<Nimboya raps on the headcase.>$b$b... and strong, too.  Let\'s see what we can do with this one.$b$bDon\'t go anywhere.', 32305), -- Favored Skull
(26298, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are good tusks, $n.  You prove that you have the strength to hunt the Bloodscalps.$B$BAnd that is good, because you are not done hunting them.', 32305), -- Hunt for Yenniku
(26407, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Far Seer makes sure to hold the item by the string, carefully avoiding the dead ogre\'s fist.>$b$bStrange indeed.  I will pass this on to my contacts in the east, near the Mosh\'Ogg\'s main camp.  I have a feeling that they\'ll be interested in these strange scars.$b$bYou have my thanks, $r.', 32305), -- Mosh'Ogg Handiwork
(26321, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She looks bigger already!  You can see, these raptors grow quickly.  You are lucky to have found such a strong companion.$b$bKeep her by your side as long as you can, $n.  I\'m sure she will prove to be an asset in the future.', 32305), -- I Think She's Hungry
(26280, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. Hopefully the raids will stop for now.$b$bI have one more task for you, $n.', 32305), -- The Defense of Grom'gol: Murloc Menace
(26279, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you are good for more than simple egg-smashing duty.  Good.  The Horde can use a capable $r like you.', 32305), -- The Defense of Grom'gol: Ogre Oppression
(26317, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, the little one seems to have taken a liking to you.  I suppose that one raptor alone and raised among orcs is much less deadly than a whole pack of them.  Keep her, $n... she may come in handy.$b$bIn fact...', 32305), -- A Lashtail Hatchling
(26278, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep up the good work, $c.  Hellscream\'s eyes are upon you.', 32305), -- The Defense of Grom'gol: Raptor Risk
(28688, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last, the Warchief\'s reinforcements have arrived.', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Northern Stranglethorn Vale!
(26416, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah!  That Cromula cracks me up.$b$bOh, right, Stranglethorn.  You\'re really going?', 32305), -- Well, Come to the Jungle
(26594, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Heh heh, well done!  And when you showed Shaky those giblets, how hard did he shake?$B$BHah!  He\'s so easy to read, when I play cards with him I can\'t help but win!$B$BThanks for your help, $n.  Now it\'s your turn to get paid...', 32305), -- Return to MacKinley
(26593, 430, 430, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ack!  Where\'d you get these?  No, don\'t tell me. I don\'t want to know!$B$BWho sent you?  Sea Wolf?', 32305), -- Scaring Shaky
(26435, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating!$b$bI\'ll need some time to study this.  Why don\'t you have a look around Booty Bay and come back later?', 32305), -- I'm A Huge Liar and a Fraud
(25476, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, YOU\'RE the great savior of OOX-22/FE!  I cannot even begin to express my thanks for your assistance!  My homing robot series needs more development, but your recovery has saved me countless hours of extra rebuilding time, as well as many gold pieces in manufacture costs!$B$BPlease, take your choice of any of these items I have.  Thank you again for your generous assistance $n, my robots and I are in your debt!', 32305), -- Rescue OOX-22/FE!
(26535, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is fascinating!  Just think of all the applications!$b$bJust so we\'re clear, I\'m not thinking about using this to make an army of slaves or anything like that.  No, no... I\'m much more interested in the ogre explosions!', 32305), -- Recipe for Disaster
(26555, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I ask you to slay Zanzil the Outcast, a lowly, hermetic exile of the Gurubashi, and what do you do?  You dash headfirst into the Gurubashi capital and eliminate one of their High Priests!  Very nearly two!  Only one word suffices to explain such a rash and foolhardy endeavor:$b$bHeroism.$b$bJin\'do the Hexxer still walks within Zul\'Gurub\'s walls, but he lost one of his legs when you crushed Jeklik.  Today\'s battle is ours.', 32305), -- High Priest Venoxis
(26554, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You find yourself deeper within Zul\'Gurub.  The snake statues indicate that you have reached the terrace of High Priest Venoxis - follower of Hethiss, the snake god.', 32305), -- Plunging Into Zul'Gurub
(26553, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have succeeded in preventing Zanzil from resurrecting High Priestess Jeklik.  Without one of his priests, Jin\'do will certainly have a difficult time summoning Hakkar.', 32305), -- High Priestess Jeklik
(26552, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have arrived safely within Zul\'Gurub, the ruined capital of the once-mighty Gurubashi Empire.', 32305), -- Through the Troll Hole
(26551, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You appear to be too late.  Zanzil has left Aboraz.', 32305), -- Eliminate the Outcast
(26534, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You don\'t say!  Well, that certainly is interesting.  In that case...$b$bForget understanding how the stuff works!  I gotta get my hands on that recipe!', 32305), -- Let's See What You've Got, Zanzil
(26550, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is as I suspected.  Zanzil is too haughty to interfere with the squabbles between the Bloodscalps and the Skullsplitters.  No, he is playing a part in a grander scheme... Jin\'do the Hexxer is using him to help bring Hakkar back to Zul\'Gurub.$b$bIt\'s good that we found this out now, because it offers us a simple solution.', 32305), -- Backdoor Dealings
(26533, 463, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jasper carefully analyzes the strange compound.>$b$bThis mixture is... I don\'t understand it.  Perhaps we need to run some clinical trials.', 32305), -- Zanzil's Secret
(26494, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll file these away for now.  Maybe we can experiment later.$b$b<Jasper looks over at you.>$b$bYeah, you\'ll do.', 32305), -- Mixmaster Jasper
(26495, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The troll looks into the package.>$b$bYou have my thanks.$b$bI have been waiting for you to approach me, $r.  I have identified you as the most promising $r here in this strange town.  I have a task for you, if you would be willing to take it.', 32305), -- Chabal
(26592, 273, 432, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Flem weighs the gems in his hands and nods in approval.>$b$bYes, these will do.  Now to perform the analysis...$b$b<The goblin clacks the gems together for a while, then looks up at you.>$b$bOh, you\'re still here?  You don\'t think I\'m a fraud or something, do you?', 32305), -- Diffractory Chromascope
(26434, 273, 463, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Flem feels the hides and smiles to himself.>$b$bExcellent work, $n!  These reagents will serve perfectly.$b$b<You detect a hint of shame in Flem\'s eyes, almost as if there\'s something he\'s not telling you.>', 32305), -- Primal Reagents of Power
(26493, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great!  These look... disgusting.  But probably pretty valuable.  Let\'s get to splitting these up.  Some for me, some for Jasper, some for Chabal...', 32305), -- There's Somebody Out There Who Wants It
(26433, 7, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, '<The goblin downs the water in one gulp.>$b$bAhh... do you know how hard it is to get fresh water in Stranglethorn?  It\'s no wonder that the nagas guard their shrine so ferociously!$b$bOh, right... your artifact, and clarity.  Clarity...$b$bI\'ve got it!', 32305), -- The Holy Water of Clarity
(26487, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey hey!  Not bad, not bad at all!  You may have a future in resource acquisition.  Or hotel management.', 32305), -- Akiris by the Bundle
(26450, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $n.  Now I\'ve just got to decide what to do with all of these...', 32305), -- If They're Just Going to Leave Them Lying Around...
(28704, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Hardwrench Hideaway!', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: The Cape of Stranglethorn!
(26404, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Skeezy sent you to the right place.  Welcome to Hardwrench Hideaway!', 32305); -- Above My Pay Grade
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(24695, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have proven to be both wise and agile, young $n.  You have my blessing to take your newfound knowledge and spread it as you continue on your journey.', 32305), -- Ever Watching From Above
(24694, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have been watching you, $n.  Your arrival was not unforeseen.$b$bIn fact, your arrival here has been predetermined for some time now.', 32305), -- The Shaper's Terrace
(24723, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A pylon in the west?  And a relationship between titans and dinosaurs?  This is a lot to take in, $n.', 32305), -- The Western Pylon
(24709, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew it!  Durrin HAS been digging around here.  And he\'s been excavating what could be the archaeological find of the century!  Now I just have to find out where he\'s stashing the bones...$b$bThanks $n.  You\'ve been a great help.', 32305), -- A Tale of Two Shovels
(24707, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The day is saved!  Huzzah!  Today we learned that while armor can be replaced, valor has no price.$b$bBecause of your key involvement in this task, I hereby graduate you from squire to fledgling knight.  No longer do the chains of servitude bind you to me; you are free to serve other masters.$b$bGo with honor, young hero!  For chivalry, the Light, and the beauty of Doloria!', 32305), -- The Ballad of Maximillian
(24708, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What an interesting femur you\'ve brought here, but why\'s it all sharp and curvy?$b$b...$b$bWait a minute, that thing\'s a TALON?  A dinosaur with a talon that size would\'ve been... well, really big, that\'s for sure.  Is this the only fossil that you found there?', 32305), -- The Fossil-Finder 3000
(24706, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Might I ask you a question?  What act have you committed to make the spirits so angry at you?  I\'m impressed that you had the patience to sit so still while they pummeled you so violently.$b$bNow we may proceed.  The teeth and scales of Un\'Goro\'s greatest dragon await us.', 32305), -- The Spirits of Golakka Hot Springs
(24730, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, these should do the trick.  And now, if you\'ll permit me, in case anyone\'s listening...$B$BTHANKS FOR DIGGING ALL OF THESE BONES OUT OF THE GROUND FOR US AND NOT HURTING THE NATIVE BEASTS IN ANY WAY.$B$BWhether you really did or didn\'t, I don\'t want to know.  Let\'s keep it that way, shall we?  Here - maybe this will keep your lips shut on the whole thing.  Anything to get out of here alive, I say!', 32305), -- Roll the Bones
(24704, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '...and that makes 15 of them.$b$bJustice had a name today... and that name was Maximillian of Northshire.  For Doloria!', 32305), -- The Evil Dragons of Un'Goro Crater
(24705, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our duty is fulfilled.  Even so, it troubles me that today\'s damsels were less than gracious... only the fair-haired one by the lake managed to show us any gratitude for our chivalry.  Perhaps tomorrow\'s damsels will have thankfulness to match their beauty.$b$bNow we must ride.  More adventures await!', 32305), -- Damsels Were Made to be Saved
(24703, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You please me, $n.  From this day forward, you are no longer a simple beggar, but a squire loyal to Maximillian of Northshire.  Prepare yourself for our first sally, good squire, for together we shall plunge our fists elbow-deep into what they call adventure!', 32305), -- An Important Lesson
(24698, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good ol\' Nolen.  How is he doing?  Hopefully better than I am...', 32305), -- Adventures in Archaeology
(24722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You think this may be related to the attacks on Marshal\'s Refuge, $n?', 32305), -- The Northern Pylon
(24718, 4, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, look at this one!  Not just the color, but the size of it... you could cover a tauren with this.$b$bHere you go, $n.  You\'ve earned this.  Stick around, I\'m sure we can find something else for you to do.', 32305), -- The Mighty U'cha
(24717, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, 2 of each color!  You\'re certainly an overachiever, $n.  My companions and I could use a $r like you around here.  Ever consider a career in profiteering?', 32305), -- The Apes of Un'Goro
(24699, 21, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this tar is just the stuff...$B$BHey, wait a minute, my hands... I can\'t seem to get them apart...$B$BMaybe this wasn\'t such a good idea. Oh, but wait! Super sticky tar remover! That\'s where the real money is!', 32305), -- Gormashh the Glutinous
(24926, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She decided to stay?  Fascinating... I\'ll have to look over this data and find out why.$B$BThank you again, $n. I really appreciate it.', 32305), -- Serving A-Me 01
(24715, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You pour the coconut milk into what appears to be A-Me 01\'s oil reservoir.  You hear the sound of gears whirring and actuators firing.', 32305), -- Repairing A-Me 01
(24714, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A-Me lies motionless before you.  No power seems to be running through her components.', 32305), -- Chasing A-Me 01
(24701, 275, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a bunch of junk, but it\'s a bunch of FREE junk, and that\'s all that matters to me.$b$bWell, mostly free.  Here\'s your share.  Thanks!', 32305), -- Marshal's Refuse
(24700, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, there they are.  Great work, $g handsome: sweetheart;!  Here\'s some gold.  You\'ve earned it.', 32305), -- Hard to Harvest
(24737, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, this tar is pretty sticky, I guess.  I mean, it\'s sticky, but it\'s not \"make fistfuls of money\" sticky.  I guess I\'ll have to keep thinking.', 32305), -- Super Sticky
(24736, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, these scales are perfect. I should be able to get this flyer off the ground with these scales for sure!$B$BThanks!', 32305), -- Shizzle's Flyer
(24693, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well, if Quixxil recommended you, then I suppose you\'re alright.  In all our years working together, Quixxil\'s never steered me wrong.', 32305), -- Mossy Pile
(24692, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve completed a remarkable task, $n.  You are truly worthy of commendation.  Thank you, and congratulations!', 32305), -- The Fledgling Colossus
(24691, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant!  We\'re on the cusp of something big here, $n.  Here\'s your share of the inevitably huge profits.$b$bNow, on to other matters...', 32305), -- Peculiar Delicacies
(24690, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last, Blazerunner is dispatched.  Thanks, $n... he was driving me batty.', 32305), -- Blazerunner
(24735, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ringo\'s not in the best shape, $n, but I am glad to have him back in one piece!$B$BThank you for finding him.', 32305), -- A Little Help From My Friends
(24734, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You find what appears to be Ringo\'s belongings.  If he left these here, he can\'t have gone far away.  Maybe you should look for him.', 32305), -- Lost!
(24720, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now I will continue my experiments! Thank you, $n.', 32305), -- Crystals of Power
(24740, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope that did the trick.  I\'ll take the ash... this may come in handy sometime down the line.', 32305), -- Volcanic Activity
(24866, 4, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well I\'ll be... that\'s Shizzle\'s old portable dinomometer!  Where did you find this?$b$bI\'m surprised it\'s still functional, even after all these years.  I\'ll have it delivered to Shizzle promptly.', 32305), -- An Abandoned Research Camp
(24794, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What?  Krakle sent you?', 32305), -- Speak With Spraggle
(24742, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These results are astounding!  My boss will be pleased.  Thank you, kind $r!', 32305), -- Finding the Source
(24697, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n.  Now we\'re a bit safer from dinosaur attacks... plus I\'ve got all this fresh meat to serve to my men.', 32305), -- How to Make Meat Fresh Again
(24721, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were right to bring this pylon to my attention, $n.  This is just the sort of thing I\'ve been studying.', 32305), -- The Eastern Pylon
(24865, 14, 22, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh... wow... it\'s some really old food.  Hey Hol\'anyee, take a look at this!  This $r brought us those old rations that we abandoned!$b$bNo, not from Marshal\'s Refuge... from the old base camp!$b$b<Williden turns back toward you.>$b$bI\'m not sure I want to peek inside.  I\'ll just give it to Nolen, I guess... he\'ll know what to do with it.', 32305), -- Is This Stuff Still Good?
(28526, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $c. My scientists and explorers will be glad to have your help.', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Un'Goro Crater!
(24733, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Earth Mother be praised! You\'ve done it! Fair play to you, $n. You have proven to be a great hunter in your own right. Your spirit is strong. Your bravery unmatched. And your strength has been fortified. I bow down to your skills.$B$BOnly the greatest of my ancestors could have accomplished something so incredible. Congratulations.', 32305), -- The Bait for Lar'korwi
(24855, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The scent of bloodpetal pollen hangs about your head, $c.  This is good.$b$bYou\'ve earned your reward.', 32305), -- Aberrant Flora
(24687, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You return victorious.  Good, good... perhaps the crater will now be a bit safer to those who travel through it.', 32305), -- Bouquets of Death
(24689, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh... did Garl send you?  How are his studies coming?  I find that he can be a bit slow at times, but he\'s truly a force to be reckoned with when he takes the form of the bear.$b$bNow, we have more pressing matters to attend to.', 32305), -- Flowing to the North
(24732, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, fine specimens, $n. The two pieces you\'ve found should be perfect for baiting Lar\'korwi into the open. I cannot wait to see the outcome of your fight with the monster. He is a massive thing with claws as sharp as the finest blades. You will look into his eyes and you will know death.', 32305), -- The Scent of Lar'korwi
(24686, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... yes, these seeds will do nicely.  You have the gratitude of the Cenarion Circle, $n.', 32305), -- Carried on the Waves
(24719, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My mentor says that sometimes you have to take away from nature before you can give back.  These raptors... I feel that they died for good cause.$b$bThank you, $n.', 32305), -- Claws of White
(24731, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will do nicely, $n. It seems Lar\'korwi eats well these days. Although, I wonder where he found a threshadon in this area. Odd.$B$BRegardless, I will hold onto this until you are ready for your confrontation with the beast. Do not worry for my safety--I am sure you\'ve angered Lar\'korwi enough that he will not kill me until after he\'s tasted your flesh.', 32305), -- The Fare of Lar'korwi
(28161, 6, 25, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, she\'s evil! But, what does it mean, $n? Is Magatha going to destroy us? Is she in charge of the Twilight\'s Hammer now?$B$BWhatever happens, you\'ve delivered us from our enemies. Please allow me to show you our gratitude.', 32305), -- Spread the Word
(28159, 6, 11, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Surprising... you lived.$B$BI thank you for doing my dirty work, $c. You kept my hands clean while ridding me of some incompetent Grimtotem leaders.$B$BNot only do I have the Rattle of Bones, the Writ of History, and the Drums of War, but I now have the ultimate artifact: the Doomstone!', 32305), -- The Doomstone
(28157, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Magatha gazes at you with naked disdain.>$B$BI\'ll combine them into a suitable form. I\'ll keep its use simple.', 32305), -- Four Twilight Elements
(28158, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A simple task for a simple $g boy : girl;. Let us see if you have what it takes to finish the job.', 32305), -- Unbound
(28142, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It took you long enough. Do you think that we are playing games here?', 32305), -- To the Withering
(28140, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve freed the Elder Crone. Time to follow the path east and meet her at the Twilight Withering.$B$BThe final confrontation with the Twilight\'s Hammer is upon you!', 32305), -- The Elder Crone
(28136, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that those three are dealt with, the combined forces from Freewind Post should be able to handle the rest of the cultists here.', 32305), -- Behind You!
(28139, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Now there\'s only one thing left to do.', 32305), -- Codemaster's Code
(28127, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You give so much of yourself without requiring anything in return.$B$BThe people of Thousand Needles are grateful, as am I.', 32305), -- Break Them Out
(28125, 6, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Lakota looks worried about the condition of the armor, especially the bloodstains.>$B$BYou sure don\'t fool around, do you, $n? Well, it\'ll have to do.', 32305), -- Something to Wear
(28124, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad that you made it.$B$BDon\'t mind my new clothes. It seemed prudent to blend in.', 32305), -- On to the Bulwark
(28098, 11, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The pridelings did what? They must love you deeply for freeing them.$B$BThank you, $n. You\'ve saved Highperch!', 32305), -- The Twilight Skymaster
(28088, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The great Heartrazor is a majestic creature. He has told me of his gratitude and fondness for you, $n.', 32305), -- Release Heartrazor
(28087, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'ll be no more trapping this day!', 32305), -- Death to all Trappers!
(28086, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re precious. One day they\'ll grow strong, but until then, they must be protected.', 32305), -- Free the Pridelings
(28085, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know nothing of the Elder Crone, Magatha. What I do know is that the Twilight\'s Hammer is destroying Highperch.$B$BWill you help me to stop them, $c?', 32305), -- Trouble at Highperch
(27330, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, she\'s been taken prisoner by the Twilight\'s Hammer. I can\'t say that I feel sorry for her, but she might prove even more dangerous in their hands.', 32305), -- Invoking the Serpent
(27358, 2, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is embarrassing to have been kidnapped by Arnak again. I heard the fighting outside. Did you kill him?$B$B<The shaman looks sad for just a moment.>$B$BI am happy to be free once more. Now, how can I help you, $c?', 32305), -- The Captive Bride
(27328, 25, 274, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They all believed that you have been sent by Magatha Grimtotem. There is no arguing that her pet, Arikara, has been lurking about.$B$B<The brave gives you a long look.>$B$BIt does not matter. Arnak is dead. It is only a matter of time before we take back Freewind Post.$B$BPerhaps now we will be able to establish a lasting peace with the Grimtotem?', 32305), -- Grimtotem Chiefs: The Chief of Chiefs
(27324, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The brave gives you an appraising look.>$B$BThere is something special about you, $n. That much is certain.', 32305), -- Grimtotem Chiefs: Grundig Darkcloud
(27319, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was not pleasant. I wonder what he meant by calling you, \"the Chosen\"?', 32305), -- Grimtotem Chiefs: Elder Stormhoof
(25874, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The cliffwatcher was a Grimtotem spy?! No wonder we had no warning!$B$B<Thalia seethes with barely contained rage.>$B$BI don\'t want that damned thing. Throw it into the water and let the Longhorn name never be spoken again!', 32305), -- Horn of the Traitor
(25870, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a good start. Normally, I wouldn\'t wish harm on any of the Earth Mother\'s creatures.$B$BBut attacking us at our most vulnerable moment?! They deserve to die!', 32305), -- Grimtotem in the Post
(27315, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She was more formidable than her reputation suggested. Although we worked well together, we must make certain not to underestimate the other Grimtotem chiefs.', 32305), -- Grimtotem Chiefs: Isha Gloomaxe
(27311, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us see how well they fight without their weapons.', 32305), -- No Weapons For You!
(27313, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While the Earth Mother does not condone such violence, we had no choice. The Grimtotem have ignored Her teachings for too long and are reaping what they have sown.', 32305), -- Darkcloud Grimtotem
(27326, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Surely that was the voice of the Elder Crone!$B$BWe must be very careful, $n. Great danger lies ahead if Magatha Grimtotem has taken notice of you.', 32305), -- The Drums of War
(27321, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is very exciting and also worrisome, $n. What are these artifacts doing here? Are they being used as a weapons against us by the Grimtotem?$B$BThe wind serpent flew northwest to that next bluff. Maybe that\'s where the drums are?', 32305), -- The Writ of History
(27317, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is true then! What is it doing here, though? And if it is here, that must mean that the writ and the drums are also nearby!$B$BPerhaps there is some link between it and the wind serpent that just appeared? I think that I have an idea what that creature is as well.', 32305), -- The Rattle of Bones
(27276, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am honored by your presence, $n. Let us put the fear of the Earth Mother into the Grimtotem.', 32305), -- Together Again
(25872, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for freeing him, $n. Those Grimtotem would have killed him in cold blood.', 32305), -- The Brave and the Bold
(25836, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am honored that you have come to help, $c. It was kind of Pozzik to send you.', 32305), -- Free Freewind Post
(25826, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is oil! You\'re the best, $n!$B$BToo bad I\'m going to have to send you off now.', 32305), -- Deliver the Goods
(25586, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'re still shooting, but not nearly as much! Yeeeeeeeeeaaaaaaaaaaah!', 32305), -- Quiet the Cannons
(25589, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll teach those scurvy dogs! You have my thanks, $n.', 32305), -- A Little Payback
(25814, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well then, let\'s see them get any kind of magical hocus pocus air support now when we take over!', 32305), -- Go Blow that Horn
(25799, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oil! Black gold! Tanaris Tea!$B$BWe\'re rich! We just have to clear out the remaining pesky centaur. I\'m sure with all the money we\'re going to make, we can relocate them to some other bluff.', 32305), -- Defend the Drill
(25797, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll teach them. You\'ve softened the Splithoof up enough that we should be able to govern them now with a minimal guard presence from the Speedbarge.$B$BThat is, once we\'ve dealt with their supposed air elemental leader.', 32305), -- Eminent Domain
(25791, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'THEY WHAT?!', 32305), -- Back to Riznek
(25779, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just put it down on the ground, $r.', 32305), -- Fake Gold for Black Gold
(25762, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did this favor to ingratiate yourself with me, but I will not sing your praises.$B$BI know what is to come. Where the sea failed, the great air spirit will strike you and your people down for your many transgressions against the elements.$B$BBegone from my sight!', 32305), -- The Ancient Brazier
(25775, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Genius! Now, where\'s that gold paint? I know it\'s around here somewhere.', 32305), -- Fool's Gold
(25757, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What?! How\'d they get that much gold to offer?$B$BWe don\'t have that kind of money!', 32305), -- Get Koalbeard!
(25745, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Riznek gets a gleam in his eye.>$B$BI\'ve got Trackmaster Zherin up there talking to one of their chiefs, but now that you\'re here, we\'ll have the rights to pump up their oil in no time!', 32305), -- Negotiations
(25704, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now we gonna bring Tony Two-Tusk back ta life. You both ready, mon?', 32305), -- The Mad Magus
(25672, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, that\'s disgustin\'!$B$BWe almost there, mon. Just need ta do one more ting!', 32305), -- Carcass Collection
(25661, 11, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Ajamon makes a face at the state of the organs.>$B$BThey\'s gonna have ta do. It not be like he had many friends. Ain\'t that right, Two-Tusk?', 32305), -- With a Little Help...
(25660, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What ya be wantin\'? Oh no you don\'t. I can see ya got Tony\'s spirit with ya, and I want nothin\' to do with it!', 32305), -- Haunted
(25628, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, yeah, yeah... I\'m sure that your little adventure into the cave was very interesting.$B$BHow about we talk about it over drinks back on the Speedbarge once you get me out of this cage?', 32305), -- Two-Tusk Takedown
(25610, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yeah! Look at all that booty.$B$BWait a minute... bring it closer!', 32305), -- Sunken Treasure
(25596, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey! Get me out of here!', 32305), -- Where's Synge?
(28048, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outstanding! Nothing can stop us from being the greatest purveyors of ice cream in all of Azeroth!', 32305), -- That Smart One's Gotta Go
(28047, 6, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you hear that, $n? That\'s the sweet hum of the refrigeration kicking in.$B$BWe\'ll be able to store our inventory down there in no time. Thank you!', 32305), -- Freezing the Pipes
(28051, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. They gave their lives for ice cream.', 32305), -- We All Scream for Ice Cream... and then Die!
(28045, 15, 94, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yeah! This is going to be the greatest flavor in the world!$B$BLook out, Tigule and Foror!!!', 32305), -- The Greatest Flavor in the World!
(28042, 4, 25, 6, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Brivelthwerp eyes you up and down, but becomes overjoyed at the sight of the special delivery.>$B$BWelcome, friend, welcome! I\'m going to give you the chance to get involved at the ground level of a once-in-a-lifetime opportuntity.$B$BThe entrepreneurial spirit knows nothing of the differences between the Alliance and the Horde!$B$BTell me... how do you feel about ice cream?', 32305), -- Special Delivery for Brivelthwerp
(25543, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saved my Speedbarge!$B$B<Razzeric $G embraces you in a manly hug : grabs you for a big hug and a kiss;!>$B$BI can\'t begin to tell you how relieved I am, Captain $n!', 32305), -- Circle the Wagons... er, Boats
(25533, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One problem down. Now to deal with the greater threat!', 32305), -- Pirate Accuracy Increasing
(25518, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes! You\'re a real credit to the Horde!$B$BYou know, you can go back in there and do that anytime you feel like it. I highly encourage you to do so!', 32305), -- Bar Fight!
(25516, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a great start!', 32305), -- Down in the Deeps
(25526, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank goodness! Now, just a little shove....', 32305), -- In the Outhouse
(25505, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Heya, $g pal : gal;, mind if I take a look at that list?$B$B<Razzeric nearly spits!>$B$BWhat\'s Pozzik thinking? He knows that I don\'t have even half of that stuff!', 32305), -- Do Me a Favor?
(25489, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Heya, kid, I\'ll be right with ya. Just gotta shut this gnome twerp up first.', 32305), -- Two If By Boat
(25487, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You want a canoe to go out to the salt flats? But, surely the race track has been destroyed?!$B$BNonetheless, for your bravery, you will have the last one!', 32305), -- The Grimtotem are Coming
(25478, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nyse sent you? Good! We need your help, now!', 32305), -- To the Summit
(28527, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Cenarion Hold.', 32305), -- Warchief's Command: Silithus!
(24433, 15, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar ogar, $n! As they discover the bodies of their comrades they will learn that no place is safe from the fury of the horde, and their will to fight will crumble.', 32305), -- Let Them Feast on Fear
(14477, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, let them burn! Let them burn through the night, so that their flaming tower will light the battlefield beneath us as we rain terror upon their heads.$B$BThank you, $n. Stay close: the invasion is about to begin...', 32305), -- Push the Button!
(14476, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sweet. Let\'s torch this banana stand!', 32305), -- Rigged to Blow
(14475, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Reinforcements, at last!', 32305), -- Grounded!
(24434, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Images of a great and distant tree flood your mind. Your stomach lurches as you reorient the stone, briefly filling your senses with visions of a fiery portal, a towering mountain, a frigid wasteland, and a terrible scar across the earth.$B$BAfter a moment, the magical energies of the stone calm, and you feel you are but a step away from Valormok. Andorel\'s invasion can begin...', 32305), -- Commando Drop
(14464, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m impressed by the cleverness of our new goblin allies, but I\'m even more impressed by you, $n. Look at the gaze of terror frozen onto the Captain\'s face! He never saw your attack coming. Imagine the fear this will cause in Northwatch when they see what happened to one of their precious officers in night elf lands.$B$BWell done, $c. Our assault proceeds... ', 32305), -- Lightning Strike Assassination
(14462, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re just in time, $c. I\'m about to launch a lightning-strike precision assassination. Let\'s see...$B$BExplosives? Check.$BPneumatic grapplestabber? Check.$BPortable parachute? Check.$BCrippling nerve toxin?$B$B<Sharpshiv licks one of her blades.>$B$BCheck. Let\'s do this thing.', 32305), -- Where's My Head?
(24497, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s past time that these night elf scum be purged from Azshara. Glad to have an able body like you to sink the point home.$B$BReady to get to work?', 32305), -- Airborne Again
(14392, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey there... again.$B$BLook, I gave you my hat. It was a gift. I thought you\'d make some use of it. More specifically though, I thought you\'d get it the heck away from me.$B$BCan you imagine my surprise when Xylem comes by himself to give it back to me? \"Want to be more like my other apprentices, Sorata? Give your hat another try.\"  Not one of my proudest moments.$B$BSo what... you just tossed it aside for him to find? No. I don\'t think so. You\'re going to take this hat and you\'re going to like it. Really.', 32305), -- Farewell, Minnow
(14297, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks there, pal. Here\'s your commission.$B$BIf you\'ll excuse me, I\'ve gotta get these slackers back to work.', 32305), -- Pro-liberation
(14261, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? So you didn\'t bring any of the drake pieces back? Disappointing.$B$BI knew I should have made you sign a contract before I sent you out...', 32305), -- Ice Cold
(24467, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You truly amaze me, mortal. It\'s rare to meet someone so dedicated and resourceful.$B$BAzuregos and I are likely to depart Azshara and remain discrete for a while. I do hope that we meet again someday though. Perhaps to put an end to Deathwing himself.$B$BFarewell, $n. Stay safe.', 32305), -- Fade to Black
(14391, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great to see you again! Thank you for finding Azuregos and sending him to me.$B$BI do feel I owe you an apology - I may have undersold how difficult it would be to accomplish the task I gave you. You performed quite admirably, $n.', 32305), -- Turning the Tables
(14390, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Azuregos has agreed to rendezvous with Kalecgos. Success!', 32305), -- Easy is Boring
(14389, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Azuregos! At last you\'ve found him!', 32305), -- Wasn't It Obvious?
(14299, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome! You seem to have survived the trials relatively unscathed. Good for you, love.$B$BYou look to have come with a purpose in mind as well. A question. Your thoughts are very loud, it\'s hard for me to not hear them.$B$BGo ahead then, hon. Ask away.', 32305), -- Xylem's Asylum
(24478, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliant. You certainly don\'t let cold feet stop you. Or cold any part for that matter!$B$BNo? ...too soon?', 32305), -- The Trial of Frost
(14300, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Woo! Good for you! That trial really put a fire under your bottom.', 32305), -- The Trial of Fire
(24479, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I like the way you move, apprentice.$B$BDon\'t you worry about where I got all the souls from. They were obtained in a perfectly humane manner, I assure you.', 32305), -- The Trial of Shadow
(14296, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is in this moment that most of my apprentices wonder if there was a logical purpose to storing the energy for my portal in those conduits so that it has to be collected in such a fashion.$B$BOf course there\'s a purpose! I wish to study your behavior... your strategies, your mistakes, your frustrations, your triumphs. Those are the entire point of these trials.$B$BNow, more. More trials! Doesn\'t that sound exciting?! Of course it does.', 32305), -- Watch Your Step
(14413, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here so soon! Lovely trip I hope. Not too nauseous or anything?$B$BThere will be much running and much jumping, so a settled stomach is of great practicality.', 32305), -- The Pinnacle of Learning
(14230, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Peachy. Back to work then.$B$BThanks, snookums.', 32305), -- Manual Labor
(14226, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Archmage Xylem appears to be doing some kind of dance as he turns to you.>$B$BDo not fret, and better yet, do not forget, to do not let the bug juice set or you will regret... well, you\'ll regret the smell of your boots really! It won\'t smell good today and it won\'t smell good even more tomorrow!', 32305), -- Trouble Under Foot
(14435, 5, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Victory! The Blackmaw won\'t know who to trust anymore.$B$BWith that delicate bit of business complete, I can orchestrate a full-on assault against those beasts without worrying about them siding with the Alliance.$B$BYou do good work, $n. Perhaps we should place you in the Horde diplomatic corps? Hah-har!', 32305), -- The Blackmaw Doublecross
(14433, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work! Let me see those documents. Hmm. Now we know exactly when and where the final negotiations will happen. Don\'t worry if those robes don\'t fit you - I\'ve got it all worked out.', 32305), -- Diplomacy by Another Means
(14432, 432, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah good, that\'s plenty. We\'ll boil this stuff up and you can bask in the fumes for a while - you\'ll be speaking like a furbolg in no time. Our plan is beginning to take shape...', 32305), -- A Pale Brew
(14431, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see... This definitely looks like a working draft of some sort of treaty. That\'s a worst-case scenario for us, $n: Night elves coordinating attacks with entrenched furbolg allies.$B$BMy initial instinct - a full-out frontal assault - would only drive them into the arms of the Alliance. We will have to take a different approach...', 32305), -- The Blackmaw Scar
(14430, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Haha! Hah - HA! Night elf \"mages\" fleeing their own arcane creation. Your actions have made my month, $n. That\'s why we blood elves don\'t use arcane constructs anymore - they\'ve been outlawed for, oh, 1500 years. It\'s amusing to me to watch our foes repeat the mistakes of the past. \"Mages.\" Indeed. ', 32305), -- Hacking the Construct
(14250, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. This should keep us for another few hours before we have to go back for more.$B$BHe doesn\'t seem to be the brightest of giants. I expect we\'ll be able to keep doing this for a while before he catches on.', 32305), -- Renewable Resource
(14249, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha ha! Perfect! Let me toss this together really fast. The Archmage is sure to be taken in by my style!', 32305), -- Shear Will
(14263, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. It\'s quite interesting how useful the most random things end up being to incantations of this sort.$B$BSo much more to learn!', 32305), -- Waste of Thyme
(14429, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work getting those runestones. To be honest, I only needed one, but the thought of so many night elves slain for such useless baubles fills me with a dark, giddy joy.$B$BPlease hold one of those runes up to the scrying stone to let me see. Hmmm. As I suspected, an amateur effort at best.', 32305), -- Arcane De-Construction
(14428, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Amberwind was making use of an Arcane Construct? Hah! How delightfully inexperienced. It\'s like watching children play with firearms.$B$BLet\'s take a look at that journal, $n. Hold it up to the scrying stone... keep it still ...$B$B<A green beam of light scans across the text of the book as you hold it against the orb.>', 32305), -- Amberwind's Journal
(14340, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well look at you, aren\'t you just a marvel of modern Magery! Quite a fancy hat, I must say.$B$BApprentices. Apprentici? I do think that I might have quite a few already, but I suppose one can never have too many appren..tici.', 32305), -- Dressed to Impress
(14345, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look buddy, I was in your shoes not a week ago. Big powerful Archmage actually takes on apprentices! Who could pass up an opportunity like that?!$B$BSometimes, things really are just too good to be true.', 32305), -- Wash Out
(14324, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Convenient, no? Who needs hot springs anyway. This is perfect.', 32305), -- Full of Hot Water
(14132, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Too mean? Naw, not too mean. They deserved it.$B$BI don\'t gum up their plants. Not ever.', 32305), -- That's Just Rude!
(14131, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful beans! They smell absolutely delicious, don\'t they?', 32305), -- A Little Pick-me-up
(14323, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve collected all of the simmering water droplets that Ergll requested. Now it\'s just a matter of summoning the \"jumbo\" elemental.', 32305), -- Absorbent
(14130, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello there! A new friend! So glad to meet you. My name is Ergll. The g is silent.', 32305), -- Friends Come In All Colors
(24449, 5, 1, 1, 0, 0, 60, 60, 0, 'And you come with the artifact! The operation was a success then. Mergers and Acquisitions can definitely handle themselves. This thing will fetch quite a pretty penny.$B$BAnd you - I heard you did some impressive work down there. You may well have cut-down expenses by 10% single-handedly. That\'s the kind of smarty businessman I want in my army!$B$BHere are your wages, as promised. And a little something extra too - I hope you like it.', 32305), -- Shore Leave
(14486, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Here\'s your cut.$B$BGood doing business with you.', 32305), -- Handling the Goods
(14485, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The hope is that that cuts off a major source of their magic. The truth is, we don\'t really have a clue. Who can pass up an opportunity to blow some stuff up though.', 32305), -- Ticker Required
(14484, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad you\'re on our side, soldier.', 32305), -- Head of the Snake
(14480, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your name\'s getting around... nearly Gob Squad status some would say. You\'re a vicious one.', 32305), -- Extermination
(14487, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hahah! It\'s HUGE!$B$BWe\'ll have you take it back to Uncle Bedlam as soon as everything\'s cleaned up here and you\'re ready to go.', 32305), -- Still Beating Heart
(24448, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n! You made it in one piece, good.$B$BWe\'ve got a lot of work for you to handle for us inside the ruins, but we\'re sending you in with the best to take care of it. You\'re working with GAMA Force now, Goblin Army: Mergers and Acquisitions. Molotov says you can handle it - that\'s all I need to hear.', 32305), -- Field Promotion
(24437, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah hah! Brilliant. Right fine job there, $G boy:gal;.', 32305), -- First Come, First Served
(24435, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good clean fun.', 32305), -- Mop Up
(24436, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine job there, $G bud:gal;. We\'ll have this beach cleaned up in no time.', 32305), -- Halo Drops
(14479, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bumpy ride?', 32305), -- There Are Many Like It
(14407, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for coming. I apologize for the discretion, but it\'s extremely important that I not be seen by certain individuals.$B$BI\'m in quite a bind and I\'ve taken notice of some of your recent deeds. Hear me out, help me, and I\'ll see to it that you\'re rewarded in kind.', 32305), -- Azshara Blues
(24455, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice to meet you soldier. Commander Molotov speaks highly of you.', 32305), -- Rapid Deployment
(24458, 71, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh! This is it! It\'s the big one!$B$B<Fizzlefuse calls out to his workers.>$B$BWe\'re in business boys!', 32305), -- A Hello to Arms
(14478, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back to duty soldier. Good to have you back.', 32305), -- Operation Fishgut
(14295, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now THAT is how we used to handle serpents back in Durotar - we crushed them under our boots! You have done the Horde proud, $n. As soon as my reinforcements arrive we\'ll mop up the rest of those vermin and claim this peninsula once and for all.', 32305), -- Sisters of the Sea
(14271, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An energy barrier, you say? This explains a great deal! I\'ve seen firsthand how Naga leaders have been able to turn aside the blades of some of my best warriors.$B$BNow we know the source of their power, $n. Let\'s finish this!', 32305), -- Report to Twocrush
(14262, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Torg scans the horizon.> And still they come! They are like a plague, $n. But with strength like yours, we will crush them. Someday.', 32305), -- To Gut a Fish
(14270, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The keystone shard slides into place and previously invisible runes suddenly erupt onto the surface of the stone, shimmering in blue and violet hues. Your knees buckle as powerful arcane currents suddenly race into your body...', 32305), -- The Keystone Shard
(14267, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The stone in the center of this shrine emits a faint glow and roars with the power of the angry sea.', 32305), -- Investigating the Sea Shrine
(14388, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So scaring him didn\'t work, either? Double-nertz! I\'ll have to break the news to Grapplehammer: Azsharite\'s going to remain the rarest substance on the planet. We\'ll have to use it sparingly.', 32305), -- Azsharite Experiment Number Two
(14258, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sweet! Beautiful! Brilliant! Who loves you?$B$BWith my mortars re-supplied, I can help you as you assault the Naga east of here. Use these markers to call in an artillery strike anywhere on the cliffs, and I\'ll splatter the whole area with fiery hurt. Oh delicious, merciless, random destruction! I hope you\'re well-armored...', 32305), -- Mortar the Point
(14422, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Exemplary work, $n! As you have no doubt surmised, my objective with regard to this rocket is to utilize it as a sort of astral cradle, an ark if you will, allowing my newly-forged race to slip the surly bonds of this ravaged planet and colonize a world to our own liking. You have been instrumental to our cause. Please accept this currency as I will be minting my own monetary units upon arrival. Farewell, $n!', 32305), -- Raptor Raptor Rocket
(14408, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The raptor snatches the paperwork in her prehensile claws and holds the schematics up to her face, clucking her pointed teeth dismissively.>$B$BThese are like the scrawling of children. Common sense precludes the routing of control hydraulics so near to the secondary stage burners! Still, this is salvageable.$B$BDo you know how to refactor fuel matrixes for pressure variations at a fixed acceleration? No? Very well, perhaps you can do something else for me while I reconfigure the rocket...', 32305), -- Nine's Plan
(14322, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the world is safe for science again? Excellent! Next time I\'ll try heated needles or something.', 32305), -- Bad Science! Bad!
(14424, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is Clubnik talking about? Haunted construction equipment? Does it look like I have time for ghost stories?$B$BI\'ve got a laboratory in the middle of a meltdown, fires burning, animals mutated, and worst of all - projects falling behind schedule. Help!', 32305), -- Need More Science
(14216, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A Sarcen stone? That\'s the stuff of legend - let me see that!$B$B$n, Sarcen stones are used to redirect the ley lines of magical energy. You realize what this means? The mages of Mennar weren\'t staying behind out of misguided loyalty. They sacrificed their lives in order to create this artifact in an attempt to draw energy away from the portal through which the demons were flooding Azeroth. They were buying time for the rest of the world to fight back! History never recorded their deeds. What a discovery!', 32305), -- Mystery of the Sarcen Stone
(14215, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You reel as the spirit\'s vision fades, relieved to once again feel the earth beneath your feet and the comforting rhythm of your own quickened heart.', 32305), -- Memories of the Dead
(14423, 6, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? ...What?$B$BMargene! Oh my sweet Margene!!', 32305), -- Dozercism
(14209, 274, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Busted ball bearings! Look at this stuff - ugh, SMELL this stuff - my poor, poor dozer!$B$B$n, I consider myself a goop expert and this here goop ain\'t natural. It\'s supernatural. This is ghost goop. We\'re going to need more than a mechanic...', 32305), -- Gunk in the Trunk
(14201, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Malynea furrows her brow and begins sifting through the artifacts you brought her.>$B$BSo the spirits of the dead still haunt those old stones, hm? Well $n, as it happens, I\'m counting on their help. Let\'s see what the dead have to say...', 32305), -- A Thousand Stories in the Sand
(14202, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Beautiful work! Now that we know the area better, we can tear this lake a new one.', 32305), -- Survey the Lakeshore
(24453, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What?! I got left out of the action completely? Are you serious?$B$BAlright, alright... no shooting the messenger. Thanks for the news, bud. Maybe I\'ll see you back at town.', 32305), -- Private Chat
(49813, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Having made your decision, you can now set off in search of bigger adventures in far-off lands.>', 32305), -- Adventure Calls
(24452, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hahah! Sweet deal. I\'ll get the ball rolling on this. All I need now is to find a buyer and get the go-ahead from Uncle Bedlam.$B$BHere are your wages for your work here. Excellent work, soldier.', 32305), -- Profitability Scouting
(14472, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'BAM! In the face! Nice shot, kid.', 32305), -- In The Face!
(14469, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a light-footed bugger, aren\'t ya? Good work.$B$BHere are a few of the supplies to keep you lively.', 32305), -- Hand-me-downs
(14470, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quick work there, recruit.$B$BShe\'s a beaut, isn\'t she? Assembled her myself. I\'ve got special plans for this baby.', 32305), -- Military Breakthrough
(14471, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can you believe they PAY us to do this?', 32305), -- First Degree Mortar
(14468, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Latest recruit, eh?$B$BI\'ll make this short and sweet. We\'re under contract to keep the naga in the ruins from reaching Gallywix or his property. You handle whatever we ask of you, and I\'ll see to it that you get paid when all of your rounds are complete.$B$BWelcome to the Bilgewater Battalion.', 32305), -- Another Warm Body
(14194, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, good. Now we can get these slackers back to work. You\'ve earned a cut of the profits though - minus the usual company fees. Take your pick!', 32305), -- Refleshification
(14161, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. One less nuisance to worry about.', 32305), -- Basilisk Bashin'
(14197, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! When it comes to iron, always pick quantity over quality.', 32305), -- A Quota to Meet
(14192, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You pop out the lens assembly and slide the crystal into place. The weapon hums ominously.>', 32305), -- Prismbreak
(14190, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zignibble\'s voice squawks over the speakers.>$B$BIs that you, $n? Still alive? You aren\'t trashing my explosive stockpiles are you?$B$BHmmm... you say you found a clear crystal pendant. That makes sense. A perfect prism would refract the gaze of the basilisk. Maybe we can use this to our advantage. Time to drop some science!', 32305), -- The Perfect Prism
(14165, 1, 432, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well well, let\'s take a look at what we got here...$B$B<Horzak examines the shattered remains of the poor petrified miner.>$B$BBah! Crumbly! Useless. Wouldn\'t even make a good countertop. My miners may be mediocre workers, but they make lousy bricks.$B$B<Sigh>. Well, I suppose we should re-fleshify these guys so I can get some return on my investment.', 32305), -- Stone Cold
(14128, 5, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What? Give that here, this instant! Ag\'tor is correct, these are arcane runes. They\'re scouting out magical sites? Experimenting with the arcane arts? This is a marked departure from thousands of years of night elven history.$B$BHmph! The idea that they will achieve any competence in this field - even those who once counted themselves among the highborne - is absurd.$B$B<Malynea puts aside the scroll dismissively, but her face is furrowed with concern.>', 32305), -- Return of the Highborne?
(14162, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re here to help? Excellent! Here, sign this indemnity waiver. And here, this noncompete clause. Let\'s get you started!', 32305), -- Report to Horzak
(14155, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $n! The invaders have pulled back. And they told me I was crazy for installing a grenade launcher on a woodchipper...$B$BGreat work with the shredder. With an impressive showing like that right here on the Warchief\'s doorstep, the Horde can\'t doubt what goblin technology can do for them. I owe you a big thanks!', 32305), -- Arborcide
(14127, 6, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ag\'tor squints at the parchment, turning it in the light.>$B$BNo, I can\'t make sense of it either, but I don\'t like what I see. Are these arcane runes?$B$BI\'ll need you to deliver this to an expert.', 32305), -- Return of the Highborne?
(14117, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. As their scouts fail to report in, Talrendis will feel the terror they\'ve tried in vain to inflict on us.', 32305), -- The Eyes of Ashenvale
(14118, 21, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Meat - and lots of it! Well done. This will keep bellies full as we build our arsenal.', 32305), -- Venison for the Troops
(14146, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice kills, $n - They\'ve never dealt with the likes of you!', 32305), -- Defend the Gates!
(14135, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work, $n! That\'s how we took care of business back on Kezan.', 32305), -- Up a Tree
(14134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! You\'ve loaded the shredder to capacity. You\'re getting pretty handy with that thing...', 32305), -- The Captain's Logs
(14129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Labor Captain Grabbit\'s voice crackles over the radio.>$B$BHey $n! Are you reading this?$B$BPiloting that sucker is easy. Push the pedals for your pedal controls and, ah, move the levers for your lever controls. Got it?', 32305), -- Runaway Shredder!
(25275, 5, 25, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n? The $n?!$B$B<The labor captain eyes you up and down.>$B$BThe rumors are already flying about you. I don\'t know if I should be thankful or frightened that you\'re here. At least we don\'t have any volcanoes in Azshara!$B$BHonestly, I can\'t believe you\'re showing your face here... Trade Prince Gallywix has setup shop atop the mountain!', 32305), -- Report to the Labor Captain
(25648, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you\'re here.  Welcome to Azshara, the stage for the next act of the Horde\'s glorious future.  Now get to work.', 32305); -- Beyond Durotar
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(27480, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Smart $g boy:girl;! I can most definitely use these arcane remnants in my studies. Indeed, Dalaran was built upon a massive ley line. It\'s no wonder, then, that such things exist at the crater.', 32638), -- Ley Energies
(27144, 274, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have nothing against the Knights of the Ebon Blade, but Koltira needs to be reminded who he works for now.  His loyalty must lie with the Horde.$b$bOr, more specifically, the Forsaken.$b$bI wouldn\'t plan on seeing Koltira anytime soon.  Now that I have him... you can rest assured that any bonds he may have had with that Alliance scum will be thoroughly broken.', 32638), -- The Reckoning
(27090, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See?  All it took was a little help from the val\'kyr.  These creatures are turning to be much more helpful than I had first thought.$b$bNow, on to other matters.', 32638), -- Andorhal, Once and For All
(27089, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the body of Lurid, Thassarian\'s trusted knight.  With Thassarian nowhere to be found, it would seem that the Alliance forces have withdrawn.$b$bThe Forsaken have won the battle for Andorhal.', 32638), -- Ace in the Hole
(27087, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You won\'t be taking me anywhere, $n.$b$bWhile Koltira prances about with his playmate, Thassarian, I plan to win this battle.  Then I\'ll make Koltira suffer for his weakness.$b$bDon\'t believe me?  Fine, I\'ll let you in on a little secret...', 32638), -- Lindsay Ravensun, Revealed
(27085, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You fight well, $n.  I wish I had your ability... and your bravery.', 32638), -- Supporting the Troops
(27086, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done.  With them out of the way, I have no more excuses.$b$bSoon, I must battle Thassarian, for honor and for Andorhal.', 32638), -- Ashes to Ashes
(27084, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Merely a dent in their numbers... but the sight of their fellow men falling from the skies surely weakened their resolve.', 32638), -- The Farmers' Militia
(27083, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thassarian and the humans made their move.  I thought I had an agreement with Thassarian... but I suppose this will do.', 32638), -- The Battle Resumes!
(26938, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When Koltira gives his word, I will bring these val\'kyr into Andorhal.  We will win.  And yet another piece of Lordaeron will fall to the might of the Forsaken.', 32638), -- Combat Training
(26937, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am able to communicate with you through the Val\'kyr, $n.  You have done well.$b$bRemain on Felstone Field.  We must now teach these newly-converted Forsaken how to fight.', 32638), -- When Death is Not Enough
(26979, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n.  The Dark Lady watches over you.', 32638), -- Strange New Faces
(26936, 1, 22, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Felstone is cleared and the bombs are set.  I hope you\'re ready.  I recommend covering your ears.$b$b<Derrington looks down and places his finger on an ignition switch.>$b$bEVERYBODY, PREPARE FOR IGNITION!  IN 3...$b$b2....$b$b1...', 32638), -- Lower the Boom
(26930, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Burning bodies?  No survivors?  I guessed correctly.$b$bAll the better!  We\'re better off without the Scarlet taint upon Lordaeron.  They epitomized all the worst things about humans.', 32638), -- After the Crusade
(26926, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Word arrived shortly before you did, $n.  With the Scourge ejected from Andorhal, the Forsaken has cemented its foothold in Lordaeron.', 32638), -- Victory, For Now
(27117, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellently done, $n.', 32638), -- Brute Strength
(26924, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellently done, $n.  And now, with the leader of the Scourge forces eliminated from Andorhal, we bide our time.', 32638), -- Scholomancer
(26925, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Araj dead... this is good.  The Royal Apothecary Society has done its part.  As have you, $n.', 32638), -- Araj the Summoner
(26923, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the behemoths out of the way, our victory against the Scourge is inevitable.$b$bOur current chances against the Alliance aren\'t quite as favorable... but that\'s no concern of yours.  Not yet, anyhow.', 32638), -- War Machines
(26921, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You may not act quickly, but at least you do not fail me.$b$bVery well.  I will have a more important task for you, $n, when the time is right.', 32638), -- Scourge First... Alliance Later
(26922, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These grenades are all explosives, nothing more.  Even as a member of the Royal Apothecary Society, I recognize that some problems are not solved by throwing more plague at them.', 32638), -- The Endless Flow
(28575, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is this all the warchief can spare? Don\'t worry, you\'ll be put to good use.', 32638), -- Warchief's Command: Western Plaguelands!
(27055, 2, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have gone above and beyond, $n.  Not only have we set back the Cult of the Damned in their crusade to re-plague the plaguelands, but you have uncovered another set of dire plans: they continue to re-animate the dead!$b$bYour name will definitely be mentioned when this information is presented to Highlord Fordring, $n.  You have my thanks, and the blessing of the Argent Crusade.', 32638), -- Students of Krastinov
(26955, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the grace of the Earthmother, he\'s done it!  Thank you, $n!$b$bI admit, I had nearly given up hope on Zen\'Kiki.  It is only due to your patience and diligence that he has come into his own as a druid and member of the Cenarion Circle.  And that\'s without even mentioning the good you\'ve done for nature.$b$bYou have my admiration and respect.', 32638), -- Zen'Kiki and the Cultists
(27054, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The orders in Malicia\'s possession incriminate Darkmaster Gandling of the Scholomance, but they also conceal another important bit of information.', 32638), -- Desperate Acts
(27057, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work.  One moment please...$b$b<The draenei takes a moment to compare your sample with a sample he presumably had distilled earlier.>$b$bYes, this appears to be the same corruption that is affecting the wildlife.  With this knowledge, and with your combat expertise, we may have the power to stop this.', 32638), -- Return to the Stead
(27017, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... Gloria used to read from this prayer book every night!  How had I forgotten?  She was so devout, $n.$b$b<Del\'s eyes turn to the finger painting.>$b$bOh...$b$bThis painting... my daughter, Andrea... she loved to... to paint...', 32638), -- Memories from a Lost Past
(27053, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cauldron Lord Soulwrath\'s key disintegrates as it touches the lock on the access panel at the base of the cauldron\'s platform.  A slight clanking noise is heard within, and the access panel swings open to reveal more viscous toxins within the cauldron\'s framework.$B$BThere is a small spigot that the bottle fits well enough under, allowing you to draw a sample for Field Agent Kaartish back at the Menders\' Stead.', 32638), -- Gahrron's Withering Cauldron
(26957, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would appear that I arrived before you, $n.$b$bField Agent Kaartish gave me the details about my old home.  It seems my battles with the Scourge aren\'t quite over yet.', 32638), -- The Long Trip Home
(27155, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m already aware of your actions, $n.  I welcome you into my town, give you my blessing, and what do you do?$b$bYou slay the traitor that we\'ve been hunting down for weeks.  Well done.  Your heroism is budding much earlier than even I had anticipated.', 32638), -- Turning Yourself In
(27154, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I suppose that we can take his aggression as an admission of guilt.  You alright, $n?', 32638), -- Bagging Bisp
(27153, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Did you notice, $n?  Many names were mentioned, but one name was mentioned far more than the others.$b$bBisp.', 32638), -- The Good People of Hearthglen
(27152, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gnolls and necromancy... what a surprise!  And I thought that, here in the Western Plaguelands, we had put these dark days behind us.$b$b<You sense Daria\'s eyes focusing on something on the ground.>$b$bWait... what is THAT?', 32638), -- Unusual Behavior... Even For Gnolls
(27151, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must admit, $n... I have been using my mind vision spell to keep tabs on you.  And I must say... the number of gnolls you found on the trail is truly staggering!', 32638), -- Taelan Fordring's Legacy
(27002, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n.  It is truly a pleasure.$b$bI know you are young, and still training, but I\'ve had my eye on you.  We among the Argent Crusade are always looking for promising new recruits, and you have indeed shown great promise.  I have no immediate tasks for you, but merely wished to meet you in person, and see for myself what type of $r you really were.$b$bFor the time being, the amenities of Hearthglen are yours to enjoy.  I look forward to our next meeting, $n.  You are dismissed.', 32638), -- An Audience with the Highlord
(27157, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work!  In retrospect, I\'m glad that other $r $c never showed up... you\'ve proven to be all the help I need.', 32638), -- Drudges... <Sigh>
(27156, 1, 24, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m just looking over my paperwork here, and it says that we were expecting a $g FEMALE: MALE; $r $c.  You\'re not, umm...$b$b<Lieutenant Myner looks at you awkwardly.>$b$bNever mind.  It would appear that you are not the person that I originally hired, but you did a good job.  So I\'m going to pay you anyhow.', 32638), -- It's About Time!
(27012, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  I\'ll be throwing these in the fire.  We don\'t want those gnolls just sneaking in and stealing them back.', 32638), -- A Gnoll's Resolve
(27011, 396, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll just put this back over in the lumber stores outside.  Nathaniel probably won\'t even notice it was missing.', 32638), -- Redpine Thievery
(27001, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s much more like it!  Now my lumberjacks can get to work again.$b$bNice riding out there, $n.  You cut a pretty impressive silhouette on that mustang.', 32638), -- This Means WAR (Wild Arachnid Roundup)
(27013, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I feel a bit more relieved, $n.  Thank you.', 32638), -- Too Close for Comfort
(27000, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it sounds like they\'re certainly afraid of the mustang, but they\'re not leaving for good.  I can\'t have you running around on a horse forever.  Nor do I think you\'d want to.$b$bFine.  Bloodshed it is.', 32638), -- Learning the Ropes
(26935, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Northridge, $c.', 32638), -- Northridge Lumber Mill
(26954, 1, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now we\'re getting somewhere.  How many birds did Zen\'Kiki end up killing?$b$bNone?  You killed them all yourself?$b$bAlright, I suppose we\'ll have to find another use for him then.  I will let you know when the time is right.', 32638), -- A Different Approach
(26956, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your help, $n.  I know that picking vegetables isn\'t the most heroic task imaginable, but even the humblest tasks have their rewards.', 32638), -- I Ain't Sayin' You a Gourd-Digger...
(26953, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It looks like Zen\'Kiki is still having a little bit of trouble with his shapeshifting.', 32638), -- Zen'Kiki, the Druid
(26999, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will be more than enough, $n.  Now, I will need some time to perform my studies.', 32638), -- A New Era for the Plaguelands
(26952, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $c.  As you can see, our camp is a joint expedition between Argent Crusade members and Cenarion Circle druids, but we welcome all who wish to help heal the land.', 32638), -- The Menders' Stead
(26978, 4, 6, 22, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Dithers practically glimmers with excitement.>$b$bThe drums are placed?  In their positions?$b$bVery well then, I will give the word to the High Executor.  When the time is ready, he will be the one to press the ignition switch.', 32638), -- Who Needs Cauldrons?
(26933, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha ha!  I hope that they come back as zombies.', 32638), -- Foes Before Hoes
(26934, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glorious!  This is the last bit I need.$b$bActually, stick around, $n.  Let me tell you a little bit more about our plan.', 32638), -- Latent Disease
(26931, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a relief to have those hunters out of the way.  We\'re not done killing Alliance, however...', 32638), -- Foxes and Hounds
(26912, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As the eldritch shackles are placed around the Shards, an unhuman wail is heard from far below.  The scream is followed by a roar.$B$BThe Shards of Myzrael no longer invoke feelings of warmth and security as they once did.  Now they pulse with an open menace... as if the thing beneath them holds ill will toward the surface.', 32638), -- The Princess Unleashed
(26911, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know, $n. I should not have sent you.$B$BForgive me... the whispers of the past are sometimes too strong.', 32638), -- Myzrael's Tale
(26429, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The signs of war are upon your garments, and sweat drips from your brow. Good, very good indeed.', 32638), -- Crush the Witherbark
(26108, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As Tor\'gan taught me, I transfer the power and the spirit of the raptors into this orb. It will imbue our warriors with the fiery strength and intelligence of the raptor.$B$BThe guile of the raptor is yours now as well, $c. Take it with pride, for the Horde!', 32638), -- Guile of the Raptor
(26042, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You place the rod in the keystone.  And a shudder is felt beneath you...', 32638), -- Breaking the Keystone
(26041, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Myzrael speaks through the stone.>$B$BYou have done it!  You opened the Stones of Binding!  I can feel the shackles about me loosen, and freedom draws ever closer.$B$BYou are a noble $c, $n.  My rescuer!', 32638), -- Stones of Binding
(26107, 1, 432, 432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The lethargy that overcame me even after the camps fell was so strong, I refused this gift when it was first given to me.$B$BNow, I am proud to do my part in the name of the Horde.', 32638), -- Raising Spirits
(26039, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah!  You activated these shards.  Already I feel more myself!$B$BBut alas, I am still far from free...', 32638), -- The Princess Trapped
(26909, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The shards pulse softly, and a whisper slowly echoes through your head.>$B$BHelp...', 32638), -- The Stone Shards
(26084, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Throm\'ka, $c. If your deeds for the undead are as great as you claim, I am honored to help you serve the Horde.', 32638), -- Hammerfall
(26628, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We survived the attack!$b$bWe could not have done it without you, $n.$b$bWe\'ll be heading out as soon as the tide rises. If you weren\'t such a promising hero I\'d offer you a place on my crew. But I can tell you have bigger fish to fry.$b$bEven if you are a puny $r....', 32638), -- Death From Below
(26052, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So the little gnomes proved their worth after all? I knew we kept those ankle biters around for a reason!', 32638), -- Speak to Shakes
(26051, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most superb, $n! The Captain will be very pleased! And just wait until word gets back to Fleetmaster Seahorn!', 32638), -- Sunken Treasure
(26055, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work out there, $n.$b$bThose scum deserved what they got. While nothin\' will ever bring me ship or me crew back, the death of those naga gives me some solace.', 32638), -- Drowned Sorrows
(26050, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The goggles work perfectly now! Well done, $n.', 32638), -- Goggle Boggle
(26083, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You friends with Goutgut! Him weird ogre. Smell funny.', 32638), -- Hello Lolo
(26081, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The news of your victory satisfies me, $c... a rare sensation. The Dark Lady herself has mused that our conquest of Lordaeron may be the only way the Forsaken can find true satisfaction, and pehaps even relief.$B$BBut it matters not. Our victory is inevitable. For your loyal service to the Forsaken, I award you in the name of Sylvanas.', 32638), -- Alina's Reward
(26033, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Trol\'kalar, my father\'s blade... it seems like it\'s been an eternity since I saw it.', 32638), -- Trol'kalar
(26032, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Valorcall was loyal to me in life. His death will not be something I bear lightly.$B$BBut bear it I must. I am Forsaken. My old existence means nothing.$B$BThe sigils are ours; Trol\'kalar awaits.', 32638), -- Sigil of Arathor
(26031, 1, 432, 432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thoradin was the founder of Arathor. Just as I join these fragments together, he joined the scattered tribes of humans into their first great nation.$B$BBut I\'m sure you\'re not interested in such drivel. Forgive me. Old memories are often hard to bury.', 32638), -- Sigil of Thoradin
(26029, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the fate of all who would stand in our way.', 32638), -- The Real Threat
(26030, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hated the Syndicate in life as much as I do in death. To see the sigil again is a small comfort.$B$BBut we have much more work to do... for Sylvanas.', 32638), -- Sigil of Strom
(26025, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My restless nights will turn to peaceful slumber when I have destroyed this orb. Thank you, $n. It is a chilling reminder of the terrible power the demons held over the orcs before Hellscream released them from their curse.', 32638), -- The Traitor Orc
(26027, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cleared out properly? Good. I doubt we\'ll even bother to lurk in Stromgarde. That ramshackle hole needs to be razed into dust.$B$BThe land would make a decent spot for a new Undercity in its place.', 32638), -- Call to Arms
(26023, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... I was once Prince of the fallen kingdom of Stromgarde. I was cut down by the one seeking Trol\'kalar.$B$BI rue my foolish life now. I serve...only Sylvanas.', 32638), -- The Forsaken Trollbane
(26022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is but a prelude to the slaughter we will visit upon these lands. All will know our name.$B$BYou have done well, $n. Victory for Sylvanas!', 32638), -- First Blood
(26053, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. The march of the Forsaken continues.', 32638), -- Clearing the Highlands
(26428, 1, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You stand before me as a figure of vengeance, and I bow down before you in thanks.$B$BWith that cow\'s death, and knowing that their seed will no longer spread over the face of Azeroth, I can put my energy into something more lucrative. I hope you looted their farmstead after you finished them off.', 32638), -- To Steal From Thieves
(28619, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last, the Warchief\'s reinforcements have arrived. The Dark Lady has plans for you, as she does for us.', 32638), -- Warchief's Command: Arathi Highlands!
(27449, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, you are indeed strong... and I submit to you.$b$bI will join you and your friend, the worgen.  My strength is yours.', 32638), -- Honor and Strength
(27448, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve enjoyed having you ride with us, $n.  Hopefully, once Gidwin and Tarenar join the Argent Crusade, we can continue to travel together.', 32638), -- The Trek Continues
(27555, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fiona has left some of her charms inside the caravan.$b$bAs a trader, she seems to be pretty good with money.  Maybe carrying one of her charms will help out with your finances.', 32638), -- Fiona's Lucky Charm
(27391, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The key fits the lock, and the chest opens...', 32638), -- Hidden Treasures
(27390, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fighting is over!  I heard my daddy whisper to me.  He scared away all the ghosts and he says he\'s coming home!  I\'m so happy!$B$BHe also said I should welcome you if you came to our house, so I made some tea!$B$BI hope you like lots of sugar!', 32638), -- The Battle of Darrowshire
(27389, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n.  Are you certain you haven\'t done this before?', 32638), -- Marauders of Darrowshire
(27388, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have the relics?  Good.  I will get to work on resolving any temporal discontinuities.$b$bDon\'t worry... that\'s not something you have to worry about.  You just gather the reagents.', 32638), -- Heroes of Darrowshire
(27387, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found them!  Well done, $n!  These relics hold within them the memories of the Scourge forces at Darrowshire.  We will need these if we are to save your Joseph Redpath.', 32638), -- Villains of Darrowshire
(27421, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even if the flowers died out shortly after they bloomed, they proved our point to the Scourge: they are losing, and we are winning.$b$bThank you for your assistance.', 32638), -- Amidst Death, Life
(27420, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The sooner those Scourge are pushed out of the Fungal Vale, the sooner we can heal it.$b$bThank you, $n.', 32638), -- Postponing the Inevitable
(27544, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I suppose I had better work on my stealth, if you were able to find me.$b$bAre you interested in helping me heal the Plaguelands?', 32638), -- Cenarion Tenacity
(27382, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course a young $r like you would have no trouble taking care of a few wild animals.  With the roads clear, my journey to the next tower will be much easier.', 32638), -- Rough Roads
(27386, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this?  A warsword?  A butter knife?  I\'m useless when it comes to blades.  Let me see...$B$BAh!  This sword was once in the hand of a great man, but there is much tragedy in that man\'s past.$B$BAre you here to help him?  It\'s far too late for him now... but perhaps we can help him in the past!', 32638), -- A Strange Historian
(27432, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great, you got him!  And I hope you taught his gang a lesson too!', 32638), -- Zaeldarr the Outcast
(27385, 18, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve seen Pamela?  She\'s alive?$B$BShe\'s dead?  No!  Oh, Pamela!  Why does your spirit still suffer in this world?  Why are you perished, while fortune keeps me alive?  In an instant I would switch places with you and wander dead Darrowshire, a ghost and alone!$B$BAh, but this news cannot change fate.  Thank you, $n.  Now my duty, my duty to revenge, burns hot as ever.$b$bSay, what is that sword you have there?', 32638), -- Uncle Carlin
(27392, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s my daddy\'s sword!  How did you find it?  Did you find the bad hunter?', 32638), -- I'm Not Supposed to Tell You This
(27384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found it!  You found my doll!  Oh, thank you!', 32638), -- Pamela's Doll
(27383, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello.  I\'m Pamela, what\'s your name?', 32638), -- Little Pamela
(27381, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Argus Highbeacon... that old guy on the top of the tower?  Great!$b$bA man his age must have been in the Argent Crusade for a long time.  Maybe he can put in the good word for us at Light\'s Hope.', 32638), -- Traveling Companions
(27373, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hope the ride wasn\'t too bumpy for you.$b$bHave a look around the tower while the horses rest.  It\'s no Light\'s Hope Chapel, but I\'m sure you can find some way to keep yourself busy.', 32638), -- Onward, to Light's Hope Chapel
(27556, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gidwin has left several bottles of weapon oil inside the caravan.$b$bHe seems to be quite a fierce combatant up close.  Perhaps his weapon oil will help you out as well.', 32638), -- Gidwin's Weapon Oil
(27372, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why, this is exactly what I needed!  Fine, I\'ll forgive Tarenar for running off.$b$b$n, you\'re welcome to join us anytime.', 32638), -- A Gift For Fiona
(27371, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Five should be good enough.$b$bYikes, look at the time!  I need to head back to camp.', 32638), -- What I Do Best
(27370, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve found them, $r.  The Scourge.  How I\'ve longed for this day.', 32638), -- Tarenar Sunstrike
(27369, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll tear that pint-size paladin to shreds before he... wait a minute are those Banshee\'s Bells?  You brought these for me?$b$bOh, Gidwin asked you to get them for me!  That sweet little guy.  Alright.  He\'s off the hook for now.', 32638), -- Greasing the Wheel
(27368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re back?!  Thank the Light!$b$bBefore you throw that acid on me, I need to ask: Are you the $g guy: girl; who was here before, or are you one of those eight-legged cowards?  I need to know whether or not I should smack you on my way out.', 32638), -- Just Encased
(27367, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$g Tarenar?: Fiona?;  Is that you?$b$bWhoever you are, would you mind helping me out of this thing?', 32638), -- Gidwin Goldbraids
(28577, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps you can help, $c.', 32638); -- Warchief's Command: Eastern Plaguelands!
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(27527, 2, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve been more help than anyone expected of you, $n.  The doors of my caravan are always open to you.$b$bThe boys and I have even put together a little something special for you.  Here, take your pick!', 32722), -- Journey's End
(27533, 70, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see them!  Can you?  The little pig spirits, on their way to the great sty in the sky...', 32722), -- A Fate Worse Than Butchery
(27534, 4, 2, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'There it is!  And oh my!  I forgot how full it was!$B$BThis is a glorious day, $n!  Stupendous!  Insanely good, I say!', 32722), -- Augustus' Receipt Book
(27535, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve come to the right place, $g mister: lady;!  No place better than Terrordale, yes siree, that\'s right!  The jewel of Lordaeron!', 32722), -- Just a Little Touched
(27531, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I love the smell of fresh foot scrapings, don\'t you?$b$bIf we\'re going to find a cure to the plague, we need to get creative with our ingredients.  Now, if you don\'t mind, I\'m going to get back to work.', 32722), -- Counter-Plague Research
(27532, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whew.  Every time Argus comes plodding through that Plaguewood, I fear it to be his last.  It\'s good to see that he\'s wise enough to send a youngblood like you in his stead.', 32722), -- The Plaguewood Tower
(27530, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a true Champion of the Light, $n.  I wish you luck in your future endeavors, wherever they might take you.$b$bIf you need anything in the future, you can always find me here - knee-deep in the corpses of the slain.', 32722), -- The Corpsebeasts
(27526, 5, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have no idea how happy I am to see you two!  You\'re a sight for sore eyes... sore eyes that have been starin\' through a banshee for far too long now.$b$bI\'m sorry for causing so much trouble.  Will you take me back to the caravan?', 32722), -- Gidwin's Fate Revealed
(27539, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May my pile never stop growing.', 32722), -- Add 'em to the Pile
(27529, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to hear you found the tortured souls of my brethren and freed them.  I find my strength renewed, knowing at least some of the defenders of Darrowshire no longer wallow in the vile subservience of the Scourge.', 32722), -- Defenders of Darrowshire
(27528, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A blessed fire cleanses even the most corrupt of flesh.$b$bThey stood no chance in the face of the Light.', 32722), -- Scourged Mass
(27551, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it!  If this missive is to be believed, then he\'s literally right over this hill!$b$bWhat are we waiting for, $n?', 32722), -- The Baroness' Missive
(27525, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve got to keep moving!  We\'re getting so very close!', 32722), -- Guardians of Stratholme
(27524, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I haven\'t found anything but brainless undead, and plenty of them.  I was just about to kill my way into Stratholme when you arrived.$b$bDid you have any more success?', 32722), -- Blind Fury
(27523, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work.  I can now continue my work without the distractions of that great white beast.$b$bI shall fashion this fur into something you can use.\n', 32722), -- Duskwing, Oh How I Hate Thee...
(27522, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It sounds like you were successful.  Hopefully this is enough information to find Gidwin.', 32722), -- Beat it Out of Them
(27521, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not feel sorry for me.  Those were my friends that you saw at Quel\'lithien Lodge, but they were already as good as dead.', 32722), -- Wretched Hive of Scum and Villainy
(27489, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Time is wasting, $n.  Every minute we waste gives the Scourge another chance to kill Gidwin.  If he isn\'t dead already.$b$bNot that I think he is.  Giddy may be a stick-in-the-mud, but when it comes down to it, he can swing the Light like a champion.', 32722), -- Nobody to Blame but Myself
(27488, 6, 20, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You didn\'t see him?  Where could he have gone then?$b$bHis... his prayer book?  Why would he leave that behind?$b$bOh...$b$bBy the Light, what have I done?', 32722), -- Impatience
(27479, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, hallelujah, and praise, praise be to the Light, my $g brother: sister;!', 32722), -- Righteous Indignation
(27487, 22, 5, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I couldn\'t stop him.  While you and Tarenar were out, Giddy ran north all alone!$b$bTarenar, you should have known better!  Gidwin gets so impatient sometimes, and you only egg him on.  If Giddy gets into any trouble, I\'m blaming you for this.', 32722), -- Ix'lar the Underlord
(27477, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep this up and I may have to keep you here at Eastwall, $r.\n', 32722), -- The Corpulent One
(27482, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vex\'tul has passed on into the next realm.  Your job here in Zul\'Mashar is done.$b$bWait, what\'s this?  Vex\'tul must have dropped it on his way into the fire.', 32722), -- Into the Flames
(27481, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My duty is not over yet.  In many ways, this was the easy step.', 32722), -- Out of the Ziggurat
(27457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You brought us a shaman!  From the Earthen Ring, no less!$b$bI have no idea how we\'ll fit him in the caravan, but we\'ll find a way.  Welcome aboard, Rimblat Earthshatter!', 32722), -- An Opportune Alliance
(27466, 3, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, $n!  Glad to see you\'ve rejoined the caravan!$b$bTarenar and Gidwin arrived here before you.  Tarenar\'s just right there, and Gidwin\'s... well... he\'s in a little bit of a mood right now.  I think he\'s in the tower.', 32722), -- Argent Call: Northdale
(27620, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While I can\'t agree with their methods, I can\'t argue with their results.  In many ways, the Scarlet Crusade were well-intentioned, but their zeal grew too strong, and their hate blinded them to reason.$b$bI only hope that the same doesn\'t happen to our Brotherhood of Light.', 32722), -- Like Rats
(27618, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It sounds like Korfax really cleaned house over at the barracks.  It\'s very much like him to show off like that.', 32722), -- Argent Upheaval
(27619, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good.  These barracks are as good as fallen.', 32722), -- The Commander
(27615, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are well on your way to becoming a true champion of the Light, $n.  Well done.', 32722), -- The Wrathcaster
(27616, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One less thing to worry about.  Nice work up there.', 32722), -- The Huntsman
(27614, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.  I will deliver these to Tyrosus when we return.', 32722), -- Scarlet Salvage
(27617, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, the abbey is ours.  I never doubted Eligor\'s ability for a moment.', 32722), -- Befouled No More
(27613, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The death of Rohan eases my spirits a bit.$b$bI once fought beside him, you know.  He was an emissary of the Scarlet Crusade; one of the few that deigned to join us in our battle against Kel\'thuzad, so many years ago.  How quickly things change.', 32722), -- The Assassin
(27612, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The abbey will fall shortly.  We can soon move on, deeper into Tyr\'s Hand.', 32722), -- Victory From Within
(27461, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met, $n.  Can I trust you to assist me in taking this abbey away from these abominations?', 32722), -- To Take the Abbey
(27462, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll be handling things from here, $c.$b$bFine, you want an assignment?  I suppose I can afford to send you in on a mission or two.', 32722), -- To Take the Barracks
(27460, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The flare is fully assembled, and the matches lie unused next to the fuse.$b$bThe fallen Argent centurion got much closer to setting off this flare than you had guessed.', 32722), -- Soft Landing
(27459, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A $c!  Just what we needed.  Your arrival couldn\'t have been more timely.', 32722), -- The Brotherhood of Light
(27467, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our duty for the day is done.$b$bIt is only a matter of time before we defeat the Scourge.  Today, we made progress.', 32722), -- Buried Blades
(27465, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve returned sooner than I expected.  Excellent.$b$bWe will continue our path into the north.  Next, you will be completing a similar task - this time, in Northdale.', 32722), -- Argent Call: The Noxious Glade
(27458, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well well well!  Someone who goes and gets things done!  Here\'s your cut, $g chief: sweetie;.  I\'ll be seein\' you around.', 32722), -- Smokey and the Bandage
(27456, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May the Earthmother watch over you! Bless you, young one.', 32722), -- Gathering Some Grub(s)
(27464, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Remember that your ancestors always watch over you.  As a $g brother: sister; of the Argent Crusade, you will join a family that has a long line of such fallen ancestors.  Their vigil and protection will be your strength as you press forward against the Scourge.$b$bCongratulations Tarenar, Gidwin, and $n.  Welcome to the Argent Crusade.', 32722), -- Argent Call: The Trial of the Crypt
(27463, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Light\'s Hope Chapel.$b$bYou wish to join the Crusade?  Very well.  We have plenty of tasks for new recruits.$b$bBut first, a test.', 32722), -- A Boyhood Dream
(28580, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sure, I can get you to the Badlands, but when you get there, I want you to agree to help my comrades.', 32722), -- Warchief's Command: Badlands!
(27455, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe it.  We\'re literally FEET away from becoming sworn members of the Argent Crusade.$b$bWe\'d be in there already if it weren\'t for Tarenar\'s dallying.  If he doesn\'t quit chatting with the locals soon, I\'m going to head in there myself.', 32722), -- Boys Will Be Boys
(27558, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You see a small doll sitting in the back corner of the caravan.$b$bTarenar tells you that it must belong to Gidwin, and Gidwin says that it\'s probably Tarenar\'s.', 32722), -- Pamela's Doll
(27559, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vex\'tul has left some of his wrappings within the caravan.  Surprisingly, he was courteous enough to keep them folded and separate from everyone else\'s belongings.$b$bVex\'tul values strength over everything else.  Leaning in close, you can sense some of his residual strength emanating from within these armbands.', 32722), -- Vex'tul's Armbands
(27560, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You see a trail-worn journal inside the caravan.  Judging by the Argent Crusade emblem on its spine, it must belong to Argus.$b$bWritten within the journal are several accounts of Argus\' experiences during his tenure in the Crusade.  It should prove to be an interesting read while on the road.', 32722), -- Argus' Journal
(27450, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... they didn\'t survive the trip out of the water as well as I had hoped.$b$bOh well!  Seafood salad for Frederick tonight!', 32722), -- Frederick's Fish Fancy
(27454, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It should take them weeks to get their operation running again.  Thank you, $n.', 32722), -- Just a Drop in the Bucket
(27453, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Uh oh... it looks like we may have gathered a little too much coagulated rot.  Oh well, we\'ll just have to improvise, then!$b$bWhat could possibly go wrong?', 32722), -- Catalysm
(27451, 274, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello!  It\'s me.  Hope you don\'t mind a little home-brewed magic to allow me to communicate with you in the field.  It\'ll save us both some time.$b$bWe\'re going to incorporate that living rot into a mixture that\'ll ruin their next batch of plague.  That\'ll show them!', 32722), -- To Kill With Purpose
(27452, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve got both pieces!  Good.  These will help when trying to sneak into their death camp.', 32722); -- Dark Garb
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(49534, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Death and acts of sacrilege pervert this land.\n\n<Lantinga lets out a drawn-out sigh.>\n\nThankfully, we\'re here to stop it.', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Zul'Drak!
(27916, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ruag reads over the report.>$b$bI see.  Thank you for this information, $n.', 32750), -- Ruag's Report
(27911, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He is gone.$B$BHe is right. I must be strong for him...', 32750), -- With Dying Breath
(27910, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With Duskfang to shroud his body, he will carry the animal\'s spirit with him into the afterlife.$B$BListen to me. An old superstitious fool. I\'m so sorry, Helgrum...', 32750), -- Last Regrets
(27909, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He can only drink so much. The rest might be used for washing his body, after...$B$B<Neeka glares in frustration and shudders, turning her head away.>', 32750), -- The Purespring
(27908, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At least I can soothe him with my own hands while he still breathes. Thank you, $n.', 32750), -- Secrets of the Mire
(27907, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will grind these and try to get him to eat. Thank you.', 32750), -- Prayerblossom
(27906, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope the sight of my sniveling amuses you, $n. It will be the only joy here.', 32750), -- Neeka Bloodscar
(27857, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Alliance is driven out! Stonard will be safe, thanks to your ferocity. Lok\'tar Ogar!', 32750), -- We're Under Attack!
(27856, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You honor both the dead and the living with your courage, $n.', 32750), -- Marking the Fallen
(27855, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With no link to the outside, the Alliance must rely on what they\'ve brought to the swamp. We shall see if they can handle our home environment.', 32750), -- Reinforcements Denied
(27854, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a true champion, $n, to take the lives of so many on the battlefield. I hope it will be enough to save Stonard.', 32750), -- Tides of Darkness
(27853, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No true member of the Horde should find pleasure in killing such terrified weaklings... without challenge, victory has no true thrill.$B$BBut your dirty work has helped stave off the Alliance and protect our homes here. Be proud of your work for the Horde.', 32750), -- Lumbering Oafs
(27852, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will fight to the last orc, $n. I hope you\'ll keep yourself alive long enough to properly destroy these trespassers.', 32750), -- Orcs and Humans
(27871, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have no time to send orcs to the temple, $n. The humans come, and they are many. Stonard must be defended!', 32750), -- To Stonard
(27914, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have performed a great service for me and my kind, $n. Accept this as a symbol of my gratitude, and of your courage.', 32750), -- Blessing of the Green Dragonflight
(27773, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He has escaped! I should have known it would not be so easy.$B$BThe path is clear, $n. It is time to return.', 32750), -- Step Three: Prophet
(27768, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A deserved fate. You will not find the pacifism of the red dragonflight among my kin, $n; we will not suffer the intrusions of mortals.', 32750), -- Step Two: The Bloodletter
(27705, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good riddance. Another source of corruption in this world put to rest.$B$BI thank you for your bravery, $n.', 32750), -- Step One: The Priestess
(27704, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it!$B$BThese are the bones of my kin...', 32750), -- Legends of the Sunken Temple
(27694, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The essence of the green dragonflight wafts from these artifacts; the vestiges of my corrupted kin. In purifying them, I form a bond between us.$B$BStep forward, $n, and receive the Oathstone of Ysera\'s Dragonflight.', 32750), -- Pool of Tears
(27869, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The goblin sent you? She has a cunning eye, that one.$B$BShe speaks the truth. I am here to stem the tide of corruption seeping from this temple. If you would save your people from a wicked fate, $n, I ask for your assistance.', 32750), -- The Dragon and the Temple
(27818, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s have a look then...$B$BMmm, oh dear. That\'s what I thought these were. They might still be usable, but it\'s horrid to have such things in my backyard.', 32750), -- Slithering Signs
(27757, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh my. It sounds like you ran across quite a sinister being. I wonder what one of those was doing all the way out here...', 32750), -- The Darkest Depths
(27691, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have to wonder just what\'s out there. This is the coast of the Forbidding Sea, with nothing beyond its reaches... but all these fishy folk just stomped right out of it.$B$BWhat\'s more, I saw where they\'ve been going...', 32750), -- Marshfin Madness
(27740, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, it\'s so nice to have help dropped in.$B$BModern convenience... I can\'t get enough of it.', 32750), -- Baba Bogbrew
(27600, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My high-grade fuse! My imported blasting powder!$B$BAnd my--hello there! I\'ll just be taking that!$B$BThose are all worth more gold than what you\'re wearing, you know! Thanks for your help!', 32750), -- In With a Bang
(27599, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WOW!$B$BI don\'t know why I said that. I\'m excitable! But man, there was a lot of stuff on these guys, check it out!$B$BHere, you want this?', 32750), -- Can't Take It With Them
(27598, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'ll show those fish-faced freaks! Good work!', 32750), -- Kill Gil
(27597, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Silversnap sent you?! I\'m DOOMED!$B$BOh, he sent you to help me! That\'s different, haha!', 32750), -- Crazy Larry
(27663, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, good, good! Just what I needed.', 32750), -- Tastes Like Strider
(27656, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All taken care of? Good to hear. Takes a load off my mind.$B$BNow I can focus on proper business for the fine folk of Marshtide and Stonard, weary from the war... and all that junk.', 32750), -- Croc-Out
(27536, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did I tell you, eh? Perfectly safe!$B$BI\'ll see about getting some of these over to to your friends, $n. At a discount.', 32750), -- Mostly Harmless
(27587, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can see it now: our own famous Bogpaddle Lobster-Poppers! Made fresh from the sea! Oh, it\'s like this stuff writes itself...$B$BYour help is very much appreciated, my friend. I\'ll start seeing if I can\'t cut your people a favorable arrangement, eh?', 32750), -- Maliciously Delicious
(27592, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our ice-cold, refreshing Silversnap Ice! I can\'t thank you enough, \"dawg\", for this entirely spontaneous act of heroism!$B$BHere, have your very own bottle as a totally sincere gesture of thanks! Be sure to tell ALL YOUR FRIENDS how good it is.', 32750), -- Drinks on the Rocks
(28677, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to beautiful Bogpaddle!', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Swamp of Sorrows!
(49536, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yo! Do I have an explosive proposition for you, pal....', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Storm Peaks!
(29609, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been expecting you! This inn is part of Sunreaver\'s Sanctuary, the Horde\'s enclave in Dalaran.$B$BDon\'t forget to bind your hearthstone here for easy travel to the city and access to the portal to Orgrimmar, out by the fountain.', 32750), -- Friends in Dalaran
(49537, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Warsong Offensive is ready to strike at the heart of the Scourge, $c. Are you up to the challenge?', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Icecrown!
(49535, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad you\'re here, $r. Hemet has not been heard from for quite some time, and I could really use your help finding him.', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Sholazar Basin!
(39203, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What took you so long? Time waits only for Aspects, $r.$B$BWe have much work to do, you and I.', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Dragonblight
(28581, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We, too, are suspicious of the Dark Irons\' recent activities.', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Searing Gorge!
(28456, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You peer inside, and find...', 32750), -- The Spoils of War
(28455, 2, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Eitrigg bows.>$b$bWelcome home, $g boys: you two;.', 32750), -- Glory Amidst Chaos
(28454, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Eitrigg looks over the devastation below.>$b$bOur job is almost done, $n.  It\'s time to deliver the deathblow.', 32750), -- Assault on Dreadmaul Rock
(28453, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n\'s here!  We can get started.$b$bThis is our big moment, $n.  I hope you are prepared.', 32750), -- Locked and Loaded
(28451, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What are these?  Oh, are these imps?$b$bI\'m pretty sure that imps don\'t just fall asleep in boxes!$b$bI\'ll take your word for it, though.  I don\'t understand any of this warlock crap.  Leave them in the corner.', 32750), -- A Delivery for Neeralak
(28450, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well would you look at that!  My favorite soldier comes through in the clutch!$b$bI\'ll make sure to get this distributed among the ogres.$b$bI\'ll see you in Redridge, soldier.  For the glory of the Blackrock!', 32750), -- A Delivery for Thorg'izog
(28452, 1, 6, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pff!  You\'re late!  Do you know how long I\'ve been waiting for Ner\'gosh to deliver this orb?$b$b<Xi\'lun looks down at the orb, then up at you.>$b$bThere\'s something strange about this orb... it\'s too...$b$b<Xi\'lun trails off.>$b$bNever mind, it must be my nerves talking.  Thank you for the delivery.  For blood and honor!', 32750), -- A Delivery for Xi'lun
(28449, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you\'re back.$b$bI hope you\'ve still got that disguise.  You\'re going back undercover, $n.', 32750), -- Placing the Pawns
(28448, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, the whelplings.  I will take care of them.$b$bAs for the agreement I made with your father earlier, tell him that I will hold up my end of the bargain.  You will have your dragon for the battle against the orcs.$b$bWe share your grudge against the Blackrock clan.', 32750), -- A Deal With a Dragon
(28447, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your kill count is adding up, $n.  We\'re chipping away at them.$b$bAnd we are going to win.', 32750), -- Draconic Vanguard
(28446, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ariok is covered in blood and sweat.>$b$bThat was exactly what I needed.', 32750), -- Blood Tour
(28491, 5, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work!  More pets for Kibler!', 32750), -- Not Fireflies, Flameflies
(28445, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This meat looks good... but I think it needs a little \"seasoning\".  I\'ll make sure that gets taken care of.$b$bThank you, $n.', 32750), -- A Heap of Delicious Worg
(28444, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To the untrained eye, these will look exactly like imps.$b$bWe just need to get them to that untrained eye.  I\'ll work on preparing them for delivery.', 32750), -- Latent Demons of the Land
(28443, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, these will do.  I will get this packed up for you.', 32750), -- Blackened Ashes
(28442, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh.  Visitors?', 32750), -- Flame Crest
(28441, 6, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you alright?$b$bGood.  You were strong out there, $n.  Strong, and wise.$b$bNow pack up your things.  We\'re moving out of here.', 32750), -- Enough Damage For One Day
(28439, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have a feeling we\'ll be hearing about you and your exploits for a long time, soldier.  I look forward to fighting by your side in Redridge.$b$bYou are dismissed.', 32750), -- I Am the Law and I Am the Lash
(28440, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Without those sergeants, Thorg\'izog will be hard-pressed getting his troops ready for battle.$b$bAlready the dominoes are beginning to fall, $n.', 32750), -- Abuse of Power
(28438, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had a feeling you\'d be the one returning to me.  I like your style, soldier.', 32750), -- Trial by Magma
(28437, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More outsiders?  What do you want?', 32750), -- General Thorg'izog
(28436, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'True, an attack on Redridge is an attack against the Alliance... but it is also an attack against innocents.$b$bI won\'t stand for that.  Not as a Crusader.  Not as an orc.$b$bIt\'s time we taught the Blackrock clan - my old clan - that their raiding days are over.', 32750), -- Taking the Horn For Ourselves
(28435, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your job is complete.  You take a look at the horn that they gave you, and decide to hang onto it for a while longer.', 32750), -- The Kodocaller's Horn
(28433, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmph.  Good work, grunt.', 32750), -- Grunt Work
(28434, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not only did you pull off the executions, you managed to make them all look like accidents.$b$bYou were the right $r for this undercover work.  Good job, soldier.', 32750), -- Strategic Cuts
(28432, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where have you been, grunt?  You\'re late!  Give me one reason why I shouldn\'t kill you on the spot!', 32750), -- Into the Black Tooth Hovel
(28227, 4, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yer a lifesaver, $n.  With golems like these, we won\'t have to worry about Dark Irons, Blackrock orcs... maybe even dragons!$b$bIf ye ever need anything from the Thorium Brotherhood, don\'t hesitate to ask.  That goes for yer friends, too.', 32750), -- Golem Training
(28226, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is exactly what we needed.  I\'ll get the boys workin\' on the next batch of golems right away.', 32750), -- Scrapped Golems
(28225, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s what I like to see!  Yer alright, $r.', 32750), -- Prove Yer Allegiance
(28430, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s it?  That\'s your disguise?  I\'m feeling less confident about our chances.$b$bBut still confident.', 32750), -- A Perfect Costume
(28427, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You need a disguise?  Well, you came to the right place, $g honey: sister;.$b$bLet me take a look... mm-hmm.  I know exactly what we\'ll do.', 32750), -- A Needle in a Hellhole
(28426, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ll have to excuse me, but we\'re not taking visitors right now.  I\'ll ask you to leave Chiselgrip out the same door you came in.$b$bOh, Ariok... is that you?', 32750), -- Chiselgrip, the Heart of the Steppes
(28425, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ariok looks through the crate.>$b$bGood, good, good.  We can move on.  Our war takes us east, away from Blackrock Mountain... for now.', 32750), -- Return to Ariok
(28424, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Knowing the way those orcs operate, there\'ll be another one to take his place soon.  I\'ll see if I can\'t sneak back into the altar before that happens.$b$bThanks, $g buddy: my dear;.', 32750), -- Shadow Boxing
(28423, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope that\'s what Ariok was looking for.  It\'s not doing me much good right now, anyhow.', 32750), -- Warlocks Have the Neatest Stuff
(28422, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gah!  Who are you?$b$bOh, so Ariok sent you?  Good.  Would ya mind sticking around for a while?  It\'s nothing big... I just need you to kill some warlocks for me.', 32750), -- The Sand, the Cider, and the Orb
(28421, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is exactly what we need.$b$bDon\'t worry, $n... the killing will come soon enough.', 32750), -- Mud Hunter
(28420, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Believe me, $n... I\'m just as anxious to get to the killing as you are.  We\'ve got to keep to the plan.  The armageddon will come soon enough.$b$bI\'ll keep these hides here.', 32750), -- A Future Project
(28419, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those scorpids are easy to underestimate.  You\'re lucky you didn\'t end up on the end of one of these barbs.  Or maybe you\'re just good.$b$bI\'ll add these to the stockpile.  We\'re not done yet, $r.', 32750), -- Stocking Up
(28417, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see to it that these dragons are taken care of.', 32750), -- Done Nothing Wrong
(28418, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re in, then?$b$bGood.', 32750), -- Burning Vengeance
(28515, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, Oilfist sent you?  Hah!$b$bDid he ever tell you how he got the name Oilfist?  You\'ll have to ask him about that one sometime.', 32750), -- Mouton Flamestar
(28667, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must stop the Blackrock orcs before they can expand their influence.', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Burning Steppes!
(49846, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Having made your decision, you can now set off in search of bigger adventures in far-off lands.>', 32750), -- Wars on Two Fronts
(28711, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Warsong Offensive could use more like you, $c.', 32750), -- Warchief's Command: Northrend!
(25771, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just a shard?  Pfuh!  This gets me nothing!  Take your reward and get out of my sight.$B$BSounds familiar?  It should, because I say it a thousand times per day.$B$BOh how I loathe this world.\n', 32750), -- One Draenei's Junk...
(25720, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully, with this druid out of the picture, we can get back to our digging.  The world is full of powerful artifacts, $n.  You just need to be willing to do what it takes to get to them.$b$bFeel free to take one of these.  The Reliquary is always happy to share some of its trove with fellow members of the Horde.', 32750), -- The Downfall of Marl Wormthorn
(25719, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brilliantly done, $n.  We have what we need to break the worgen\'s trance.', 32750), -- Demoniac Vessel
(25718, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rohan\'s sending YOU to slay his druid?  Very well.$b$bYou should know: Marl Wormthorn is as much demon as he is druid.  Even a druid of his power doesn\'t have a chance against the demonic energies that run so deeply through this land.  That does not, however, make him any less of an obstacle.', 32750), -- How Best to Proceed
(25717, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.$b$bI should be a bit more up-front with you.  The demons were a nuisance, but they are not the real problem.  That worgen druid is our problem.', 32750), -- The Demons and the Druid
(25696, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, traveler.  Thank you for responding to my summons.', 32750), -- The Sunveil Excursion
(25707, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Rockpool tadpoles float off into the distance, thankful and safe.', 32750), -- The Future of the Rockpool
(25706, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The last Rockpool may be taken hostage today and killed tomorrow, landwalker... but they will pass into the underworld knowing that a brave $r avenged their death.  Thank you.', 32750), -- Neptool's Revenge
(25705, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You make an old murloc proud, $r.$b$bThank you, and may the waves ever lap at your feet.', 32750), -- False Idols
(25703, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, brave $c.  I am pleased... but I am not yet satisfied.', 32750), -- Atrocities
(25702, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The murloc spirit looks upon you sadly.>$b$bSalt-Flop did not shame himself by running away.  Look behind me, and see for yourself.$b$bThe Rockpool had no hope against the naga\'s attack.', 32750), -- Home... Gone... Naga...
(25701, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see.  So this was Loramus\' plan all along.$b$bI suspected correctly, but I suppose I refused to believe it.  And now, his final instruction for me makes much more sense:$b$bHe asked me to let you choose from one of these.', 32750), -- You Are Rakh'likh, Demon
(25700, 397, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that we are prepared to face our demon, $n.  We have the amulet\'s blessing, we have the stone knife, and I alone know the demon\'s true name: Rakh\'likh.  Together, this may be enough to defeat the Defiler.', 32750), -- Loramus Thalipedes Awaits
(25699, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lynnore clutches the third amulet.>$b$bHe was a powerful warrior, this one.  I will keep the amulet until Loramus is ready to proceed.', 32750), -- The Amulet of Grol
(25698, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lynnore hefts the amulet.>$b$bA warlock... and a powerful one at that.  I will hold onto this until the time is right.', 32750), -- The Amulet of Sevine
(25697, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lynnore examines the amulet.>$b$bHe was an archmage, I can feel it.  I will hold the amulet for you while you collect the rest.', 32750), -- The Amulet of Allistarj
(25693, 396, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is sufficient.  If you see Wazzik again, you may tell him that he performed satisfactorily.  I will get the bloodmages to work on fashioning the stone knife of sealing.  There is no need for questions now.  All will be revealed in time.$b$bWhile they work, I have another task for you to complete.  Actually, make that three tasks.', 32750), -- Enhancing the Stone
(25695, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re certain nobody saw you?  Good.$b$b<Dar\'toon listens to your recount of the information you saw.>$b$bHmph... fairly harmless stuff.  Either the Alliance are foolish enough to NOT be planning something against us... or they\'re hiding their information better than I expected.  Either way, well done, soldier.', 32750), -- Watching Our Back
(25692, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s no doubt about it, you found demon blood.$b$bLoramus\' requests aside, I\'m sure Dar\'toon is thankful for your efforts.  They\'ve been struggling to deal with these demon distractions for some time now.', 32750), -- The Vile Blood of Demons
(25691, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope this is what he needs.  We probably don\'t have time for you to return and mine any more.', 32750), -- The Charred Granite of the Dark Portal
(25694, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your work is appreciated, soldier.$b$b<The warlord leans in close, and whispers:>$b$b$R... if you\'re still interested, I have one more small task for you...', 32750), -- Protecting Our Rear
(25689, 5, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What?  LORAMUS?!$b$bOh blast, keep it down, would ya?  If my boss gets word that I worked for Loramus, do you know how quickly I\'d be on my rear end?!$b$b<Wazzik takes the rune from you, presses it to his chest, closes his eyes, and nods.>$b$bWell, you weren\'t lying.  Let\'s get to work.', 32750), -- Time is Short
(25772, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Simply amazing.  I had doubted that anyone could find another sphere, yet here it is, pulsating in my hands.$B$BWell done, $n!$B$BShould you find anymore--and I believe this to be an impossibility--return them to me and I shall reward you again.', 32750), -- Kum'isha's Endeavors
(25688, 53, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... you fool!  What have you done?', 32750), -- The Altar of Storms
(25687, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see... yes, we can work with this.$b$b<Lynnore looks at the night elf\'s head.>$b$bLoramus Thalipedes, demon hunter.  I look forward to meeting you.', 32750), -- Not Just Any Body
(25686, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The blood ritual was a success; I can clearly see where Loramus is right now.  That is, I can see where the pieces of his body lie...', 32750), -- Blood Ritual
(25690, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfect, $n.  Lynnore and I will eat well for the next several days.', 32750), -- A Bloodmage's Gotta Eat Too
(25685, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lynnore eyes the blood hungrily.>$b$bMore than enough, and still warm!  Now, let\'s get this ritual started, shall we?', 32750), -- The First Step
(25675, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well today, $n.  Not only have you purchased more time before the next ogre attack, but I think you scared some of the captives into working harder.', 32750), -- Ogre Combat
(25684, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  Now that that\'s out of the way...', 32750), -- Attune the Bloodstone
(25683, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Okrilla sent you?  Okrilla the killa\'?$b$b<Lynnore listens to your tale.>$b$bLoramus was his name?  I\'m sorry to say that we have not seen your demon hunter... but we have ways of finding him.', 32750), -- The Dreadmaul Furnace
(25682, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Okrilla glances over the report.>$b$bImpressive, $n.  I wouldn\'t have hidden in that box, but otherwise, you have performed bravely and admirably.  The battle we won today may not win us any immediate spoils, but the damage you\'ve done to the Alliance will last for a long time.', 32750), -- Mission Complete
(25681, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, mon!  Without Hondo, these guys are helpless.  Dis mine\'ll be ours soon enough!', 32750), -- Some People Just Need Killing
(25680, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So it was a demon?  Those miners never seen a demon before?  We\'re in the Blasted Lands, mon!  Demons are everywhere!$b$b<Tak\'arili sighs.>$b$bAh well... let\'s get on to da good stuff, shall we?', 32750), -- That's Not Us
(25679, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you here already.  Stick around for a bit, little $r.  We gonna mess with the Alliance.$b$bI love my job, mon.', 32750), -- Into the Mountain
(25678, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, friend.  I like the way you do business.', 32750), -- Pick Your Fate
(25677, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s nothing quite like a big fat kick in the wallet, is there, you Alliance lunkheads?!', 32750), -- It's All Mine
(25676, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally... another operative shows up.  I hope you\'re loosened up... it\'s time to tango, partner.', 32750), -- Heartstrike
(25674, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r.  You\'ve proven that you can take down an ogre... no small feat.  Now let\'s see if you can take down an Alliance iron mine...', 32750), -- Futile Pride
(28865, 11, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Silithus, such a worthless piece of land. It is a wonder that the great cataclysm did not sunder it fully!', 32750), -- Call of the Warmatron
(27715, 274, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can\'t believe those guys would interrupt me like that.  My story was going so well, too...$b$bAnyhow, thanks for sticking around so long.  It\'s nice to have someone new to share tall tales with.  I\'m sure Lucien and Theldurin feel the same way.$b$bYou have any you\'d like to share with us?', 32750), -- The Day that Deathwing Came: What Really Happened
(27714, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The end!  No moral.', 32750), -- The Day that Deathwing Came: The Real Story
(27713, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some story, huh?  Now you know why Deathwing hasn\'t come back here since.', 32750), -- The Day that Deathwing Came
(27927, 11, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They sent you to check up on us?  Pshh... I\'ve been around this desert longer than any of those chumps.  We\'re just soaking in some of the scenery and telling stories about old times.$b$bYou like telling stories?', 32750), -- Down to the Scar
(27879, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I imagine those ogres weren\'t too much trouble for you.  Here - some coin for your troubles.', 32750), -- Survival of the Fattest
(27880, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve got the hint of a hero in you, $r.$b$bNow get out of my battlefield.', 32750), -- Half-Ton Holdouts
(27859, 25, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You were not the only mortal that Rheastrasza confided in.  I too earned the dragon\'s trust.$b$bI have already moved the real purified egg on to a safer location, away from the Badlands.  It will continue to grow, out of Deathwing\'s sight.$b$bThe red dragonflight is as benevolent as it is powerful.  It was Rheastrasza\'s final wish that I give this to you.', 32750), -- The Egg Lives On
(27930, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Heroes:$b$bIf you are reading this, then my suspicions were correct.  Deathwing has found us.  The egg is destroyed, as am I.$b$bThis was, actually, the plan from the beginning.  You see... the egg that Deathwing destroyed was not the egg he sought.$b$bIt was mine.', 32750), -- Devastation
(27898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thankfully, you have avoided Deathwing\'s notice.  Rhea and the black dragon egg, however, may not have been so lucky...', 32750), -- Rheastrasza's Gift
(27897, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The egg must always be moving.  We are not safe anywhere.$b$bDeathwing, even in his madness, knows all the hidden places in this world.  The egg must not rest.', 32750), -- The Hidden Clutch
(27896, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just think... Nyxondra may end up being the mother of the new black dragonflight.  In death, she has given a gift to the future generations of Azeroth.', 32750), -- The Sorrow and the Fury
(27895, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Two more dangerous black dragons have been removed from this egg hunt.  Your greatest task, however, still awaits.', 32750), -- Their Hunt Continues
(27894, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One less dragon to worry about, one step closer to redemption.  Onward, my soldiers!', 32750), -- The Wrath of a Dragonflight
(27893, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See?  No need to worry when Gargal is around.  Just let me know, and I\'ll protect you from the monsters.', 32750), -- Gargal, the Behemoth
(27891, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m looking forward to fighting with you.', 32750), -- Amakkar, Jack of All Trades
(27892, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I think you\'re ready, $n.  You\'re getting the hang of this.', 32750), -- Jurrix the Striker
(27890, 1, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re the $r we\'ve been waiting for?  It\'s about time you got here.  My legs could use a stretch.$b$bCome on boys!  Let\'s go kill us some black dragons!', 32750), -- The Bad Dogs
(27889, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ll take that egg out of your hands now.  We need to get this egg incubated... and hidden, quickly.  There are lots of angry dragons looking for this.$b$bIt\'s good to see you again, by the way.', 32750), -- New Kargath
(27888, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just one tiny little device?$b$bI never did understand those titans.$b$bVery well!  Let\'s see what this peeper can do.', 32750), -- Return to Blam
(27913, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You peer into the chest...', 32750), -- The Titans' Trove
(27887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With your inspection complete, the statues return to their original positions.  Something seems different in the room, however...', 32750), -- Ancient Protectors
(27885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The jade statue becomes one again, and you place it in your pocket.  You hear a shifting noise in the tomb\'s central chamber.', 32750), -- The Warden's Game
(27883, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The statue clicks into place on the large stone slab.>', 32750), -- The Warden's Pawn
(27886, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The red statue falls over, and you place it back in your bags.  You hear a rumbling noise in the tomb\'s central chamber.>', 32750), -- The Sentinel's Game
(27884, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The statue slides into place on the cold marble slab.>', 32750), -- The Sentinel's Pawn
(27877, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent!  We\'ll bury these immediately.  Those Explorers\' League dimwits will never suspect us!', 32750), -- The Morons' League
(27878, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew it!  The High Examiner will be pleased to see this.$b$bNice work, $r.', 32750), -- Forcible Acquisition
(27882, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chalice... worthless.$b$bVase... counterfeit.$b$bHieroglyph... interesting, but rather common.$b$bWhat\'s this?  I\'ve never seen trogg craftsmanship of this caliber!  You\'ve stumbled upon something rare indeed, $n.$b$bWe must not be so hasty as to overlook the troggs.  They may be simple, but they know things about the deep, hidden places of this world.$b$bYou\'ve performed well enough.  Let\'s talk titans, shall we?', 32750), -- It's Not About History, It's About Power
(27881, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Titans?  You come to me, asking about titans?$b$bYou\'ve come to the right place, as we\'re on the brink of discovering something big.  You will, however, need to earn your keep first.', 32750), -- Bloodwatcher Point
(27763, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Fuselight!', 32750), -- To Fuselight Proper
(27762, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice landing!', 32750); -- Fuselight; Ho!
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(49817, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A brisk wind greets you as you approach the frigid northern shore. It smells of salt, death, and adventure.$b$bWelcome to Northrend.', 33941), -- To Northrend!
(39206, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who are you?$B$BTell me why I shouldn\'t split you in two where you stand!', 33941), -- Warchief's Command: Grizzly Hills
(49533, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n, you have arrived!$B$BLet\'s get to work.', 33941); -- Warchief's Command: Howling Fjord!
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(27721, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We knew the Horde would send help and not a moment too soon!', 34601), -- Warchief's Command: Mount Hyjal!
(49851, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n. Thank you for responding to my request.', 34601); -- Cataclysm First Responder
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(25439, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to have a real warrior at my side. Too often, my shaman brethren can\'t seem to stomach the work.', 35435), -- Vengeful Heart
(25441, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Too often, we are mistaken for druidic types. Perhaps that\'s true for some shaman, but do not let yourself be plagued by the ignorant belief that we are always peaceful.$B$BNothing about what I do is harmonious. I command the elements to my will. There is nothing offered in return. I would have it no other way.', 35435), -- Vortex
(25359, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I remember you. You were there when they attacked us back in the cave.$B$BGood to have you with me, $c. Ready for a little vengeance?', 35435), -- Toshe's Vengeance
(25456, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sam\'s in one piece then? And his poor assistant Felice? Good to hear.$B$BI hope that one day he\'ll learn to respect the elements as more than just a tool.', 35435), -- Back in One Piece
(25217, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another sample. Brilliant! The rocky riches of the sea shall soon be mine!', 35435), -- Totem Modification
(25360, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Does everything down here only come in jumbo size? Oooh! That\'s a thought. Maybe there are some hunky sea goblins around here somewhere.$B$BThanks, by the way.', 35435), -- Crabby Patrons
(25218, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya know, I should have given you a weight belt so that you wouldn\'t just float away, air balloon and all. Lucky for me you came down here with armor and all! Hah!', 35435), -- Undersea Inflation
(25216, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another fan of the Great Sambino! Come all this way for an autograph perhaps? I\'m far too busy to be signing anything... move along now.', 35435), -- The Great Sambino
(25219, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. Seriously. If I would have had to endure another shipwreckee laughing at me, I swear I would have gored someone.$B$BI\'ll let you know if I come up with anything.', 35435), -- Don't be Shellfish
(25220, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. There are still much bigger predators we\'ll have to keep an eye out for, but this will at least give us a bit of peace of mind around the cave.', 35435), -- Slippery Threat
(25215, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It shouldn\'t take long to cleanse the water. Thank you for your help.', 35435), -- A Distracting Scent
(25222, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A friendly face! Welcome!$B$BVery kind of you to come check on us. We\'re fine. A naga scouting force did find us, but I\'m pretty sure none escaped. We should be safe for now.', 35435), -- Silver Tide Hollow
(25221, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Swift work. Very impressive.$B$BThat Fathom-Lord got away... I don\'t see him anywhere. He\'s most certainly the key to finding our captured friends.$B$BI will hunt him down. He cannot stay hidden for long.', 35435), -- Rundown
(25164, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you were here, mon.$B$BToshe be lookin\' like he wants to chase dem down. You should go help\'em.', 35435), -- Backed Into a Corner
(25334, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'d all suspected da naga, but I knew nothin\' of the Twilight Cult bein\' beneath the waves. Somehow dey are corruptin\' and pervertin\' the elements, makin\' demselves into dese horrors.$B$BWe goin\' ta have to be fightin\' both of dese threats to stand a chance of bringin\' peace ta Vashj\'ir. We don\'t have da men ta do that yet.$B$BCome, $c, we got much ta do.', 35435), -- The Looming Threat
(25471, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ello, mon! You look a bit more capable then most of dem coming through here.$B$BCome rest a bit. Make yaself at home.', 35435), -- Across the Great Divide
(27708, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that this operation has been undone.$b$bSoon, I must move on...', 35435), -- The Warden's Time
(26008, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us hope for the safety of those released prisoners.$b$bIn return for your noble efforts, please accept this gift.', 35435), -- Decompression
(26040, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes. This is the stuff.$b$bMaybe I can wean off of it and avoid the side-effect.$b$bThank you, $n.', 35435), -- What? What? In My Gut...?
(25883, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re confident that your assault on the naga armaments has made an impact on their effectiveness.', 35435), -- How Disarming
(25884, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The waters surrounding the Holding Pens are red with the blood of the naga.$b$bRendel would be proud!', 35435), -- Come Hell or High Water
(25887, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is as it should be.$b$bNow the way is clear to deal these naga a crippling blow.', 35435), -- Wake of Destruction
(26007, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s not encouraging, but it\'s something...', 35435), -- Debriefing
(25503, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This item was highly prized by the local gilblin population - even coveted by King Gurboggle, himself!', 35435), -- Blackfin's Booty
(25467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The satisfying sound of a chest unlocking is followed by the sight of once-hidden treasure.', 35435), -- Kliklak's Craw
(25419, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This treasure was obviously crafted by the local water-goblins for a female they regarded highly.', 35435), -- Lady La-La's Medallion
(25377, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve discovered lost treasure!$b$bYour mind reels at the thought of what else might be hidden in the depths of the sea.', 35435), -- The Horde's Hoard
(25946, 5, 5, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Blood and Thunder!$b$bThis changes everything, $c!', 35435), -- Helm's Deep
(25944, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $r.$b$bOur chances of survival are increasing.', 35435), -- Girding Our Loins
(25943, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good grub.$b$bSoon we\'ll be back to fighting strength.', 35435), -- Traveling on Our Stomachs
(25942, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us hope that your work has bought us the time we need...', 35435), -- Buy Us Some Time
(25941, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hear you, $r.$b$bI understand the urgency, but these men are in no condition to fight.', 35435), -- Rest For the Weary
(25936, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While you were away, I was able to revive some of the fallen warriors.$b$bWe\'ll need every hand if we are to survive here.', 35435), -- Pay It Forward
(25929, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here you are, $c. With this you should find maneuvering in the sea to be nearly effortless. $b$bNow we must get to work. There is much to be done in little time.', 35435), -- Sea Legs
(25924, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not exactly the battle you had anticipated, I\'ll wager. But a battle nonetheless, as you shall soon see....', 35435), -- Call of Duty
(27718, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar, $g brother:sister;! You have arrived just in time.', 35435), -- Warchief's Command: Vashj'ir!
(27399, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your aid is most timely, $n.', 35435), -- The Battle Is Won, The War Goes On
(27722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our world is in danger, $n! We need the help of great heroes, like you, to save it!', 35435), -- Warchief's Command: Deepholm!
(28805, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that your eyes have seen the truth, where will you choose to serve?', 35435); -- The Eye of the Storm
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(27059, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! Excellent work, $g my boy : young lady;. You found out what the Twilight\'s Hammer were up to and you stopped them dead in their tracks!$B$B<Examiner Rowe pats you on the back with his bony hand.>$B$BNow I\'m certain that I have something around here for you.$B$B<He begins rummaging around for your reward.>', 35662), -- The Wrong Sequence
(27043, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'An excellent display of $c prowess.$B$B<The Reliquary eyes you up and down.>$B$BI believe that a reward is in order. Something appropriate for a $g powerful man : lovely lady; such as yourself.', 35662), -- Fight Fire and Water and Air with...
(27041, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah ha! So, that\'s it! They\'re planning on invading Uldum.$B$BWhat\'s worse is that the pyramid inside the Maker\'s Rise at Uldum can be reconfigured to become a weapon. A weapon that is capable of destroying all life on Azeroth!', 35662), -- Decryption Made Easy
(27008, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A waygate?! They unearthed a Titan waygate.$B$BThis is very interesting and potentially very bad.', 35662), -- Fly Over
(27005, 5, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<The examiner takes a look at the plans that you hand to him.>$B$BThis is just gibberish!$B$BWhat does this even say? What language is that?', 35662); -- The Twilight Plot
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(28973, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 36322), -- Candy Bucket
(27690, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Narkrall sizes you up.>$B$BAnother mewling Horde whelp? Zaela saps our strength by diluting our forces with the weak. Very well, $c. Prove yourself to me, and show me what your Horde is made of. ', 36322), -- Narkrall, the Drake-Tamer
(27611, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good. Let them reap what they sow!', 36322), -- Blood on the Sand
(27610, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $c. Now you know the lay of the land.$B$BIf you\'re ever having difficulty fighting here on the Twilight Shores, remember that capturing and holding the Beach Head will give all Horde forces here a combat advantage!', 36322), -- Scouting the Shore
(27607, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good timing, $c. We were just about to unleash a counter-attack.', 36322), -- The Southern Flank
(27606, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Boom baby, boom!$B$BWhat? You killed the Fathom-Lord already?$B$BI suppose we should stop shelling his corpse, then.', 36322), -- Blast Him!
(27586, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh yeah. YEAH! These are DEFINITELY going to kill somebody.$B$BProbably naga.', 36322), -- Shells on the Sea Shore
(27584, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gralok sizes you up.>$B$BYou\'re a true fighter, $n. I liked watching you work. Perhaps the Dragonmaw really DO belong in your Horde. ', 36322), -- Blood in the Surf
(27583, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Warlord Zaela sent you? Good.$B$BIf you Horde are as strong as your Warchief promised, I expect to see some bloodshed on these shores.', 36322), -- The Northern Flank
(28975, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 36322), -- Candy Bucket
(28992, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 36322), -- Candy Bucket
(60887, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many choices, so little time!$b$bGood luck out there, $n... but I don\'t think you\'ll need it.', 36322), -- -Unknown-
(26709, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You returned. This is good. The Stone Lords have been asking after you.', 36322), -- The Stone Throne
(26971, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maruut said when all dis started dat he would gladly give his life ta see our task done. He would be proud of dis success... of dis death.$B$BDa rift be closed on dis side. Deepholm should calm down a bit. It\'ll be takin\' time for Thrall to mend da wound in Azeroth, and we\'ll be needin\' to remain until he finishes.$B$BThank you for all ya\'ve done. I don\'t tink we could have been accomplishin\' dis so soon without you.', 36322), -- The Binding
(26875, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Twilight forces continue to stream in, but it looks like the Earthen Ring defenders can handle them.', 36322), -- Undying Twilight
(26833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gorsik has arrived. All of the pieces of the World Pillar are here, thanks to you.$B$BWhat you have done for us is immeasurable.  These final moments shall be the most crucial.  I hesitate to ask more of you, but I\'d like you to stay with us and see this through.$B$BThe Twilight\'s Hammer was devastated by your attacks, but not destroyed.  It\'s no stretch to assume they will try to stop us from completing our ritual.\n', 36322), -- Word In Stone
(26832, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You let Lorthuna escape? I warned you of this.$B$BStill, their forces are shattered and their resources cut off. There is little they can do to me or my allies.', 36322), -- Therazane's Mercy
(26829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their blood upon the earth is a sweet thing. I shall cherish every moment, slowly extinguishing the stragglers from my realm.', 36322), -- The Stone March
(26831, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you were here. I find my size to be inhibiting when it comes to dragon riding, strangely.', 36322), -- The Twilight Flight
(26828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And so you arrive, fleshling.  As promised.', 36322), -- Our Part of the Bargain
(26827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done what I thought not possible. Quite impressive, $c.', 36322), -- Rallying the Earthen Ring
(26752, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya\'ve done well, $Gbrotha:sista;. Da Stonemother be listenin\' and da World Pillar is not far from our reach.', 36322), -- Audience with the Stonemother
(26750, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'ve come.$B$BFleshlings just like you killed my daughter... my only daughter. With no provocation.$B$BNot sated at stripping me of my family, more of you flocked to Deathwing to serve him in ravaging my home.$B$BYou\'re quite arrogant to come before me asking for MY help. I\'m tempted to crush you where you stand.', 36322), -- At the Stonemother's Call
(26585, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So your words prove true. You have my gratitude, $r.', 36322), -- Corruption Destruction
(26584, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done fleshling. Your presence complemented my brothers well.', 36322), -- Shaken and Stirred
(26583, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $r.$B$BGorsik shall hear of your deed. Therazane shall hear of your deed.$B$BYou are quite vicious for one so small... and so soft.', 36322), -- Wrath of the Fungalmancer
(26582, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The stone troggs? And I am to trust you at your word?$B$BI have no love for the Verlok anyway. Suspicion is more than enough reason to lay waste to them. We shall see if your word is true.', 36322), -- Unnatural Causes
(26581, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You let the mist touch your skin? I hope there weren\'t any adverse affects.', 36322), -- A Head Full of Wind
(26579, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You carry with you a certain degree of potency. I can find some respect for such strength, especially in your kind.$B$BMy concerns are not yet abated. Not for the source of the overgrowth, and not for you.', 36322), -- Gone Soft
(26578, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have appealed to Diamant. He is patient. Trusting. Perhaps too much so. You have much to prove if you wish my favor, $r.$B$BStill, this is a start.', 36322), -- Doomshrooms
(26580, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see you again, $g brother:sister;. I see that your efforts go well. The Stone Lords appear to be showing you some degree of trust.$B$BWe\'ve come to help. We might be of some aid in tracking down the source of this sudden growth. I highly suspect your giant friend\'s aggressions are focused in the wrong direction.', 36322), -- Familiar Intruders
(26577, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are Diamant\'s chosen.$B$BSo small. So fragile.$B$BDo you realize that your actions shall be the basis by which your entire, \"Earthen Ring\" is judged? You truly think you can stand for so many?$B$BYou are a fool. A confident fool. We shall see if you are a capable fool as well.', 36322), -- Rocky Upheaval
(26427, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All right, help me get tied to the wheel.$B$B<Moody sips from the bottle.>', 36322), -- Without a Captain or Crew
(29019, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 36322); -- Candy Bucket
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(27627, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you obliterated the final scarab, you noticed an ancient piece of ornamental jewelry on the ground...', 36372), -- Just a Fancy Cockroach
(28633, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course! I had a hunch this is what we\'d find.$b$bHad no idea about the organic transformations, though, I must admit.$b$bThere\'s more to this old relic than I\'d dared to hope.', 36372), -- The Coffer of Promise
(28622, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $glad:lass;.$b$bLooks as tho everything made the trip in one piece.$b$bI\'m beginnin\' ta see why junior keeps ye around.', 36372), -- Three if by Air
(28621, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course I have a plan for moving the coffer.$b$bSomeday, maybe the old coot will learn to trust me.', 36372), -- Put That Baby in the Cradle!
(28612, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lucky fer you, this ol\' dwarf\'s still got a few tricks up his sleeve!$b$bHeehee! ...shoulda seen tha look on yer faces!', 36372), -- Harrison Jones and the Temple of Uldum
(27748, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you\'re still in one piece, $n.', 36372), -- Fortune and Glory
(28613, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So far, so good...', 36372), -- See You on the Other Side!
(28497, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n.$b$bNow let\'s see if we can make our way up there before they\'re able to recover.', 36372), -- Fire From the Sky
(28482, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Glad you could make it, $n!', 36372), -- Sullah's Gift
(28404, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should do it.$b$bStand back!', 36372), -- I'll Do It By Hand
(28403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Okay, $n.$b$bI think I can do this manually, but I\'ll need your help.', 36372), -- Bad Datas
(28402, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright, $n.$b$bI think everything is in order. Let\'s do this!', 36372), -- Schnottz So Fast
(28367, 153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah!$b$bI heard it from here! I wish I could\'ve been there to see it!', 36372), -- Shroud of the Makers
(28363, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You know, I believe I have just the thing!', 36372), -- Stirred the Hornet's Nest
(28272, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Harrison quickly skims through the scrolls.>$b$bYes... yes... perfect!$b$bI\'ll need some time to make sense of these, but the information is there.$b$bGood work, $n!', 36372), -- Missing Pieces
(28271, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job with Schnottz\'s men.$b$bSounds like you gave them something to think about.$b$bHopefully it bought us the time we need.', 36372), -- Reduced Productivity
(28353, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Alright, kid.$b$bMy research is complete. We\'re about ready to activate the final obelisk.', 36372), -- Jonesy Sent For You
(28351, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Splendid!$b$bThis is shaping up to be better than I had dared to dream!', 36372), -- Unlimited Potential
(28352, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it!$b$bI now have camels to spare. Perhaps one day we shall take our show on the road!', 36372), -- Camel Tow
(28350, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work, $gmy boy: little lady;!$b$bYou\'ll master this trapping skill in no time.', 36372), -- Master Trapper
(28274, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Here we are, $n!$b$bGreat things will happen here... magical things!', 36372), -- Two Tents
(28273, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome $c!$b$bYou and I are going to be good friends! I can tell already.', 36372), -- Friend of a Friend
(28269, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, glad you could make it.$b$bI could use a hand here.', 36372), -- Meet Me In Vir'sar
(29016, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 36372), -- Candy Bucket
(28267, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, this Schnottz character is working with Deathwing!?$b$bThis is even more distressing than you think...', 36372), -- Firing Squad
(28194, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfect, $c.$b$bWish us luck!', 36372), -- The Great Escape
(28195, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good, $r...', 36372), -- Sending a Message
(28193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zhey know nozhink, you say?$b$bVery vell, zhen. Zhe search goes on...', 36372), -- Lockdown!
(28187, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is times like zhese, zhat one learns who his friends really are...', 36372), -- Missed Me By Zhat Much!
(27990, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Auch!$b$bIf I vere an inch or two taller, I\'d be dead!', 36372), -- Battlezone
(28002, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm, still a bit frazzled, are they?$b$bWell, you know what they say. Time heals all wounds.$b$bExcept for those of the ambassador, of course...', 36372), -- Crisis Management
(27969, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vell done, $c.$b$bZhere may be hope for you yet.', 36372), -- Make Yourself Useful
(27950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was probably not the transformation Schnottz was hoping for...', 36372), -- Gobbles!
(27942, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zhese look to be of sufficient quality.$b$bVizh zhese, ve are vone shtep closah to zhe cleansink ritual. ', 36372), -- Idolatry
(27943, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very goot!$b$bYou have earned yourself a place at zhe ritual.$b$bYou shall be among zhe first to velcome Gobbles back to his... original form.', 36372), -- Angered Spirits
(27941, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Most efficient work, $c.$b$bYou should rise rapidly through the ranks.', 36372), -- Fashionism
(27939, 396, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it!$b$bPerhaps I can trust you vizh more serious matters, hmm?', 36372), -- The Desert Fox
(27928, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, these are exquisite!$b$bThe commander will be able to make a winter uniform with these.', 36372), -- A Favor for the Furrier
(27926, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust that you had no troubles fitting in with our guests, hmm?', 36372), -- Eastern Hospitality
(28132, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh look, it\'s one of little Schnottz\'s pamphlets.$b$bI\'ll just be taking that from you, if you don\'t mind.', 36372), -- Efficient Excavations
(28520, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done.  We have defeated the Neferset inside their own city.$B$BI wish I could say that there is peace for my people at last, but I only foresee more bloodshed.', 36372), -- The Fall of Neferset City
(28486, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $n!  Excellent!', 36372), -- Salhet's Gambit
(28483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $n.  Our troops will hear of your deeds.', 36372), -- Bleeding the Enemy
(28480, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a valuable ally, $n.  We are one step closer to defeating the enemy.', 36372), -- Lieutenants of Darkness
(28623, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve arrived just in time, $n.  ', 36372), -- The Push Westward
(27755, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They couldn\'t be saved, $n.  The ancient curse that fell upon them is irrevocable.', 36372), -- The Curse of the Tombs
(27779, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done, user $n.  I thank you for your assistance with this unfortunate task.', 36372), -- Gnomebliteration
(27778, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am in control, user $n.  But I cannot keep the core temperature stable indefinitely.', 36372), -- Hacking the Wibson
(27761, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.  The expedition has already doomed itself.$B$BThere is no need for it to endanger the rest of the world as well.', 36372), -- A Disarming Distraction
(27777, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, user $n.  We must obtain access to the fusion core now.', 36372), -- Core Access Codes
(27760, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Scanning subject...$B$BCerebral cortex diagnostics indicate the absence of \"tomb curse\" phenomenon.$B$BDiagnostics did reveal frequent head trauma.  The user would do well to exercise more caution around blunt objects in the future.', 36372), -- Artificial Intelligence
(28501, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it, $n!  We held Nahom.', 36372), -- The Defense of Nahom
(28500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is true then?  It does exist!', 36372), -- The Cypher of Keset
(28498, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent.  Let\'s see if we can find anything of importance.', 36372), -- The Secret of Nahom
(28499, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps you are as powerful as I\'ve heard afterall.$B$BYou have our gratitude.', 36372), -- Punish the Trespassers
(28561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n!  It\'s you!  My regiment was ambushed on our way here.$B$BOur captain was slain, leaving me in command... until you got here, that is... sir!', 36372), -- Nahom Must Hold
(27905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work back there, $n.$b$bLooks like we\'ve lost them, for now at least.', 36372), -- Tailgunner!
(27903, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'According to Harrison\'s notes, placing the lens upon this dais should re-activate this obelisk.$b$bExactly what that means remains to be seen...', 36372), -- Ignition
(27901, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s it!$b$bGood work, $n!', 36372), -- They Don't Know What They've Got Here
(27900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a relief. Thanks, $n.$b$bTurns out I\'ve got my hands full here.', 36372), -- I've Got This Guy
(27899, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that I\'m not the only one interested in these obelisks...', 36372), -- That Gleam in his Eye
(28533, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Two pieces of news have reached me today, $c.$B$BThe High Council has reached a decision about war and my brother has been slain by Neferset scum.$B$BI no longer need to wait for the former to lead my people into battle.  We move against the Neferset as soon as my people are ready.', 36372), -- The High Council's Decision
(28291, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Salhet?  A tactician, you say?$B$BHah!  Very well, if you\'ll vouch for him, we might be able to arrange something.', 36372), -- Return to Camp
(27839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is quite timely.  I will distribute these armaments to my best men and to the laborers that you recruited.$B$BI\'ve a feeling they\'ll show as much courage as my best trained captains.', 36372), -- Ancient Weapons
(27738, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you for what you\'ve done, $n.  You can count on my vote when High Council convenes.', 36372), -- The Pit of Scales
(28277, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad, huh?  Maybe you can put a word in with the high commander.$B$BMaybe he\'ll put us in charge of our own squad!', 36372), -- Salhet the Tactician
(28276, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Aren\'t they beautiful?', 36372), -- Salhet's Secret
(28210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well... that wasn\'t all that great, was it?', 36372), -- Shaping Up
(27707, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If the prisoner\'s information is true, Tahet is in great danger.', 36372), -- Neferset Prison
(27632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve obtained a map of the Vir\'Naal river delta.', 36372), -- Tanotep's Son
(27629, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What manner of creature are you?  You will leave the king\'s lands before...$B$BWait!  You are that $n I\'ve heard so much about.$B$BYou must pardon my lack of hospitality.  We have seen all manner of hostile intruders since the barrier around Uldum failed.', 36372), -- The Vizier's Vote
(28200, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent job, $n.  You might not think this adds up to much, but this might very well be the difference between life and death to one of our soldiers.', 36372), -- The Element of Supplies
(28201, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a born leader, $n.  It\'ll be good to have you by our side when war comes to these lands.', 36372), -- Ploughshares to Swords
(28198, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a great honor to meet you, $n!  I\'ve heard much about you.', 36372), -- The Weakest Link
(27631, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No need to fill me in on the events in Orsis, $n.$B$BI\'ve heard about them already.  And about you.  Any enemy of Al\'Akir is a friend of mine.', 36372), -- The High Commander's Vote
(27838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes.  The waters are clearing up.$B$BI am certain I will be visited by a vision before the High Council meets.$B$BBe warned, $r.  My vote will only be swayed by what I see.$B$BYou might have helped us greatly here today, but if the vision sways me to make a case against war then that is the way my vote will be cast.', 36372), -- The Root of the Corruption
(28611, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The waters of the river are nearly cleansed.  Our prophetic visions will soon return.', 36372), -- The Defilers' Ritual
(27837, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, $n.  I can feel the disruption in the river fading.$B$BYet, I feel the source of this taint still lingers.', 36372), -- Trespassers in the Water
(27836, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $n.  This will make our prophetic visions that much clearer.', 36372), -- Stopping the Spread
(27630, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'War, you say.$B$BDivinations for war are always difficult.  Some wars must never be fought, even if victory was assured.  Some wars have to be waged even if defeat is certain.', 36372), -- The High Priest's Vote
(27628, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is just the beginning, $n.  If Deathwing\'s minions can bury entire cities, we have little chance of defeating them through conventional means.', 36372), -- Send Word to Phaoris
(27706, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So... this is what Al\'Akir wanted all along.', 36372), -- The Scepter of Orsis
(27623, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You place the two gems inside the sockets in the wall.', 36372), -- Colossal Guardians
(27602, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though the chest is locked, there is a plaque bearing interesting hieroglyphs above it.', 36372), -- The Prophet's Dying Words
(27519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $n.  Orsis was punished for not joining the forces of Deathwing.$B$BPrince Nadun has offered my people refuge in his city.  I must go there and tend the survivors.', 36372), -- Under the Choking Sands
(27520, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You continue to prove to be a valuable ally, $n.  ', 36372), -- Minions of Al'Akir
(27595, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who... who are you?  Sent here... to rescue my people and fight our enemies.', 36372), -- The Prophet Hadassi
(28135, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you see what Deathwing\'s minions have done?  Great Orsis is now all but buried in the sand!', 36372), -- Al'Akir's Vengeance
(28134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Orsis!  Of course!$B$BHow could I not have seen this?', 36372), -- Impending Retribution
(28250, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You showed those thieving little scoundrels!  Great job.', 36372), -- Thieving Little Pluckers
(27669, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, now. Would ya look at that!$b$bAs amazing as this is, I am confident that there\'s more to our discovery than meets the eye...$b$bMuch more.', 36372), -- Do the Honors
(27624, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work, $n.$b$b<Harrison studies the tablets.>$b$bIt looks as though our work here is nearly complete.', 36372), -- After the Fall
(27431, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Talk about bringing the house down...', 36372), -- Tipping the Balance
(27549, 396, 5, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Well, kid, it looks like you\'ve done it again.$b$b<Harrison points to an image on the tablets.>$b$bThis starlight is exactly what we were missing.$b$bNow we can get to work!', 36372), -- By the Light of the Stars
(27541, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Odd...$b$bIt looks as if someone used gemstones as lenses.$b$bI should be able to fix them without too much trouble.', 36372), -- Lessons From the Past
(27517, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, rope! Thanks, kid.$b$bSomething tells me I\'m going to need this.', 36372), -- Be Prepared
(27511, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your exploration of the Chamber of the Stars has yielded more questions than answers...', 36372), -- The Thrill of Discovery
(27196, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Would you get a load of this place!', 36372), -- On to Something
(27176, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Doctor Jones puts on his spectacles.>$b$bLet\'s have a look at this. Shall we?', 36372), -- Just the Tip
(27179, 396, 5, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'These tablets are covered with titan writings. There\'s never-before seen information here, $n!$b$bMissing pieces to an ancient puzzle...$b$bGood work!', 36372), -- Field Work
(27187, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The world is a better place because of your deeds here today.', 36372), -- Do the World a Favor
(27141, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shake it off, kid.$b$bHappens to me all the time...', 36372), -- Premature Explosionation
(27993, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see ya, kid.$b$bWould\'ve been even better if you\'d have been here to help me take care of these little savages...', 36372), -- Take it to 'Em!
(28502, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you, $n.  These savages must be punished for what they\'ve done here.', 36372), -- The Bandit Warlord
(28145, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.  We might yet save Iset.', 36372), -- Venomblood Antidote
(28141, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.  The rumors I\'d heard about you are proving true after all.', 36372), -- Relics of the Sun King
(29017, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 36372), -- Candy Bucket
(49538, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar ogar, $n. You\'ve arrived not a moment too soon....', 36372), -- Warchief's Command: Jade Forest!
(28293, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Uldum? What about Uldum? Speak quickly!', 36372), -- That's No Pyramid!
(28976, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 36372), -- Candy Bucket
(27788, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $n! You beat that damned gronn and sent Cho\'gall packing into the Twilight Bastion.$B$BDon\'t you worry. With your help and that of your friends, we\'ll get in there and we\'ll kill Cho\'gall once and for all!', 36372), -- Skullcrusher the Mountain
(27786, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Hammer of Twilight floats in the middle of the altar, unprotected....', 36372), -- The Hammer of Twilight
(27783, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you\'re back. It\'s about time. We know where Cho\'gall\'s ultimate weapon is located!', 36372), -- Garona Needs You
(27745, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We survived and all of the portals are now shutdown!$B$BYou don\'t think Magmatooth is going to hold a grudge, do you?', 36372), -- A Fiery Reunion
(27744, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'That\'ll teach \'em to move in on our territory!$B$BWhat\'s that over across the way?', 36372), -- Rune Ruination
(27743, 14, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They had it coming to them.', 36372), -- While We're Here
(27742, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Goldmine slyly looks at the pile of Elementium shards.>$B$BHmm, I don\'t think that stuff\'s going to sell for much. I better give you your cut right now so you don\'t feel ripped off.', 36372), -- A Little on the Side
(28885, 5, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh no! My weapons and totems!$B$BThey\'re destroyed!!!', 36372), -- Mr. Goldmine's Wild Ride
(27659, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The last portal is deep within the mine here, but we\'ll deal with that in a bit.', 36372), -- Portal Overload
(27798, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Hammer of Twilight? And you say you got this information out of a drowned Wildhammer dwarf?$B$BYou\'re kidding, right?', 36372), -- Water of Life
(27661, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am pleased. Lord Cannon was always an unworthy adversary.$B$BVery well, $r, I will help you gain the information which you seek.', 36372), -- Fire the Cannon
(27703, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good thing that you and Warlord Krogg made friends with the red dragons.', 36372), -- Coup de Grace
(28974, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Candy buckets like this are located in inns throughout the realms. Go ahead... take some!', 36372), -- Candy Bucket
(28038, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, you\'re one $gbig strong heap of:lovely killing machine,; $c. Can you handle the crucible? We got bookies standing by!', 36372), -- Blood in the Highlands
(28170, 4, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You see! De dead be nothing to be scared of. You brought de light to de darkness, mon, and never flinched.$B$BWe can use dis cave now as a base of operations in de northern Highlands. You\'re de best, $n!', 36372), -- Night Terrors
(28166, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, dis be it, mon.$B$B<The lens glows brightly in Buunu\'s hands, casting unearthly rays of light across the shadowy cave mouth.>$B$BWe be ready to bring dem spirits out de shadows now.', 36372), -- Thog's Nightlight
(28151, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! I\'m sure Twilight\'s Hammer wanted to number those ogres among their ranks. Now they\'ll probably have to fight them off instead.$B$BThis is good, $n. With one well-placed $c we managed to do the work of a small army. I\'ll let Warlord Krogg know of your work here!', 36372), -- Dressed to Kill
(28149, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat\'s de stuff, mon!$B$BNow can you hear dem? De spirits, dey be talkin\', but dey say nothing nice.$B$BLet us bring dem to de light.', 36372), -- Whispers in the Wind
(28147, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did you manage to get? I suppose we can piece something together from this.$B$BAfter all, you\'re not joining the cult. We just need to fool a few ogres.', 36372), -- Purple is Your Color
(28133, 1, 273, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once free of the chain, Torth died rather than submit again. I admire the creature. I will have his hide fashioned into a set of armor.$B$BThis much is clear to me now: The Dragonmaw cannot stand alone if the Alliance backs the Wildhammer. Narkrall proved that. And you have proven the might of the Horde, again and again.$B$BI will rebuild our drake wings and take up position outside the Bastion of Twilight. You should continue to help out here in the Gullet and elsewhere in the Highlands.', 36372), -- Fury Unbound
(28123, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Zaela takes the gore-spattered length of chain and wraps it around her hand and wrist.>$B$BIf the stories are true, $n, it was on this length of chain that Deathwing had once fastened the Demon Soul, forged in his bid to control the other dragonflights. The Demon Soul has long been destroyed but perhaps this hunk of elementium holds some residual power...$B$BYou\'ve done a great thing today.', 36372), -- The Demon Chain
(28043, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was an impressive aerial display, $n, but I wish it had come at a better time.$B$BNarkrall is a great warrior, but he\'s also an impatient fool. He\'s about to get himself killed ... and we\'re about to lose one of our most important weapons in the battle for the Highlands!', 36372), -- How to Maim Your Dragon
(27576, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got the dragons in the game! Good on you.$B$BWe\'d already laid out plans for our ambush by the time the dragons contacted us. They\'re helping by cutting off their retreat.$B$BIt\'s not too late for you to join in on the fun though. We saved some for you.', 36372), -- Patchwork Command
(27508, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know if you did this for me or the young inside these eggs, but it doesn\'t really matter, either way it\'s clear that you want to be an ally of our flight. I appreciate that.$B$BI cannot forgive the attacks by your allies against my brood, but for now, it seems you have chosen the right side.', 36372), -- Far from the Nest
(27509, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Thank you, $r.$B$BI will not be so foolish as to let such an oversight happen again.', 36372), -- Breach in the Defenses
(27507, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have a talent for killing I see. In times like these, that has its place.', 36372), -- Encroaching Twilight
(27564, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you\'re as tough as your gear suggests. The Twilight\'s Hammer have made their way within the redoubt somehow and I need someone to hunt them down.', 36372), -- In Defense of the Redoubt
(27506, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In this, we deny Deathwing the destruction that he so passionately seeks. In this, life continues.', 36372), -- Life from Death
(27505, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will take Grim Batol back from the Twilight\'s Hammer and their allies. It may take time, but this is one charge that we cannot forsake.', 36372), -- Draconic Mending
(27504, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Calen has become very trusting. It is not often that strangers are permitted within the redoubt.', 36372), -- Even Dragons Bleed
(27486, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad Lira didn\'t scare you off. I won\'t say her concerns aren\'t warranted, but we have a common enemy. She is perhaps a bit overzealous.', 36372), -- Warm Welcome
(27380, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saved many of my closest allies today, $n. I can only imagine what horrors you witnessed within Iso\'rath, but you have the thanks of all of the Earthen Ring.', 36372), -- Nightmare
(27379, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'United with the Earthen Ring, we can survive the horrors of Iso\'rath. Now it is time to turn our vengeance upon him!', 36372), -- The Terrors of Iso'rath
(27378, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re awake! Thank the elements. I\'d almost lost all hope.', 36372), -- The Worldbreaker
(27377, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve brought you back from the brink of death, hero!$B$BDeathwing is upon us! We need your help.', 36372), -- Devoured
(27376, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The tentacles swept us off of our gryphons as well! They were far more nimble than we anticipated.$B$BNo matter. We were prepared for this possibility. I can summon the elemental from here if you can keep me safe.', 36372), -- The Maw of Iso'rath
(27300, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Revenge is bittersweet, but I\'m glad we be havin\' someone as powerful as you do see dis done.', 36372), -- Pushing Back
(27303, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. You are quite capable. I\'m extremely grateful that you\'ve chosen to aid us.', 36372), -- Mercy for the Bound
(27302, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that\'s what I\'m talkin\' about! Can you think of all the uses for this stuff? I definitely can\'t. But I can think of a lot, and I\'m liking the possibilities.', 36372), -- Simple Solutions
(27301, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the elements that you\'ve come. Did my brothers send you?', 36372), -- Unbroken
(27299, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tank ya, $c. A bit of breathin\' room helps a lot.', 36372), -- Torn Ground
(27375, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $Gbrotha:sista;. You\'ve chosen a harsh time to be joinin\' us, but that is to our fortune. We could use ya help.', 36372), -- The Weeping Wound
(27955, 6, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve gone pale, $c. What did the Eye show you?$B$BYou saw Cho\'gall? Wait - Cho\'gall saw you? He\'s watching us? He\'s watching us right now!?$B$BDamn this stupid dark magic! I\'m going to have to infiltrate Cho\'gall\'s stronghold myself.', 36372), -- Eye Spy
(27945, 1, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mallia removes her eyepatch and holds the black diamond before her empty eye socket.>$B$BWhat have we, what have we - breaches, the breaches number three. Two heads, one wholly given to its master. I see the future. A hammer united. A mountain shattered. Oh - OH!$B$B<Mallia drops the diamond to the floor, covering her face with her hands.>', 36372), -- Paint it Black
(27954, 6, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found one? I\'ve been searching everywhere. Give it here!$B$BSome of these eyes are won over with riddles or verse. Others require magic. What did this one demand? Ah, it\'s no matter. What matters is that it\'s ours. ', 36372), -- The Eyes Have It
(28041, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You gather up the fresh carcass.>', 36372), -- Bait and Throttle
(27951, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Eye glimmers darkly, colors swirling about its dusky surface.>$B$BAh, the succulent thrill of life extinguished. Do you feel it, $c? Do you relish it as I do?$B$BNo, I see not. You fight to protect the lives of others. Pity.', 36372), -- We All Must Sacrifice
(27947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Eye sits before you, humming ominously with dark energies.>$B$B<Without warning, the orb rotates, as if to look at you. You sense a malevolent presence, as though the orb is alive.>', 36372), -- A Vision of Twilight
(27750, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Griff greedily snatches the heap of food, enough to feed dozens of men.>$B$BGreat! Did you get any for yourself?', 36372), -- War Forage
(27929, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You look a little battered. Those dwarves didn\'t give you any challenge, did they?$B$BStill, that was an impressive show.', 36372), -- Drag 'em Down
(27751, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Narkrall clenches the insignias in his weathered hand.>$B$BSo, $c. There\'s more to you than meets the eye.$B$BMaybe your Horde can stand with the best of my warriors. Let\'s try you out...', 36372), -- Crushing the Wildhammer
(27747, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes. Burn them out, as you would flush groundhogs from their holes...$B$BWell done, $n.', 36372); -- Total War
